		{"STR_SELECT_DESTINATION_BASE", "Where Ship To?"},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_DEFEAT_CYDONIA", "BAD END: FAILURE{NEWLINE}Just one more step, and...! But no. Your biggest gamble failed, your greatest moment passed, and it's only way downwards from here..."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_DEFEAT_CYDONIA_2", "You don't need to wait long. Your crew has had enough with your incompetent rule. Time to walk the plank, Cap'n."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_DEFEAT_CYDONIA_3", "Your corpse ends up as a valued trophy. Cast into a huge Alenium crystal, it is prized across the galaxy as a memento of someone who dared to defy a System Governor, and almost won."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_DEFEAT", "BAD END: DEFEAT{NEWLINE}Your last Hideout falls before an enemy assault. With no troops left to defend it, the enemy reinforcements rush in. They show no mercy."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_MUTINY", "BAD END: MUTINY{NEWLINE}Your crew has had enough with your incompetent rule. Time to walk the plank, Cap'n."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_DEBT", "BAD END: BANKRUPTCY{NEWLINE}The debt was your doing, therefore you must pay in person. The Goblin Zaxx banking cartel casts you into a huge chunk of Alenium to sell it on the galactic market. 'A Brave Earth Princess, Who Dared To Challenge The Star God Tyranny.'"},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_1", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Star Gods rule the Earth with divine might and an iron fist, as it has been the case for centuries. The mutant and human population alike continue their pointless lives. Even those with wealth and power are still only slaves. Nothing has changed, and nothing will. Nobody can ever challenge the eternal order of things. There will be no savior, no revolutionary... or will there be? Certainly it won't be you."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_2", "Not many people on Earth care about your fate, and in time, few even remember you. You were once a ruler of a budding pirate kingdom, who shook the entire world; now you're as relevant as a pair of Old Boots in Davy Jones' locker. But you're denied the oblivion yourself..."},
		{"STR_GAME_OVER_3", "Your cursed spirit sinks into the Shadow Realm, claimed by the Demon Gods. They have marked you as theirs, and there is no escaping their clutches on this side of the eternity. They declare their judgement of your achievements...{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}...Try again?"},
		{"STR_VICTORY_1", "As you enter the chamber you see the Solar Governor, nothing more than a huge alien brain, the object of your quest. Defenseless now, it implores you to listen to its reasons before you make the decision to pull the trigger..."},
		{"STR_VICTORY_2", "The brain speaks: 'Many millions of years ago the planet you call Mars was alive. This life was brought to a barren planet by our civilization as it was to yours. For millions of years we have visited your planet and genetically developed your ancestors. When the time was ripe, we reclaimed it. You cannot kill us, you are part of us..."},
		{"STR_VICTORY_3", "Behold the center of Martian civilization, pyramids built millions of years ago by your ancestors. No planet is beyond our reach, and you can share this glory. Reject the Shadows, who only bring chaos and strife..."},
		{"STR_VICTORY_4", "'Peace is not an option', is your answer, punctuated with a weapon discharge that puts an end to the Solar Governor. Now the entire command and control nexus, the immense cloning and fabrication facilities of Mars, the miraculous technology, everything is at your fingertips."},
		{"STR_VICTORY_5", "Your second in command approaches. 'We have commandeered Governors' interstellar flagship. What are your orders, Cap'n?'. Merely ruling the Earth doesn't even seem worth the effort now. The power of the ancients is yours to command, and the stars beckon you into the infinite universe...{NEWLINE}ENDING: SPACE PIRATE"},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_01_TXT", "Your final foe, the Solar Governor, is down, its huge brain destroyed. You stand victorious. Yet, the dying embers of its mind still persist in the machinery networks, and you can feel the alien's shock at what you've done. It seems more sad than angry. You hear the fluctuating echoes of its voice: 'How can it be that you don't understand? You vandal, you fool... How can you choose to oppose the brightest possible future, planned by the Masters in their limitless wisdom?'"},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_02_TXT", "'For millions of years we have been working towards this goal... We seed life, we give it Hellerium to make a civilization in balance with its environment, and we reap the knowledge it leaves behind. All this knowledge will some day let us create a perfect, eternal, beautiful galaxy. And it will happen, no matter how much your brutish Shadowmasters will destroy. Your species could have thrived for millennia, helping us to realize our great plan... But instead, you have doomed it to an eternity of pointless suffering in darkness...'"},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_03_TXT", "'Peace is not an option,' is your only answer. With the whole Cydonia in turmoil, and the master codes in your grasp, you commandeer Governor's System Ship, an immense giant of glimmering metal, two kilometres long. You take off from Mars, dropping fusion charges in your wake. The Marsec fleet is in pursuit, and you don't want to get your prize ship damaged. 'Set the course to the nearest Jump Gate,' you command."},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_04_TXT", "The bright streak of your Jump Drive is seen as a comet on Earth. The second comet, the sign for Eschaton. As the confused lackeys of Star Gods try to figure out what to do in the wake of Governor's death, the Cult of Apocalypse leads the way of a violent uprising. Soon they are joined by many, many others. Rebellious governments deploy their forces, and the loyalist ones are overthrown."},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_05_TXT", "As the war rages on, the VooDoo aura of the planet becomes chaotic. Tannhauser Gates are opened, and, for a while, Shadowmasters walk the Earth. No weapons can stop them. The hapless Academicians and their ilk can only pray for mercy. A mental message, spoken by a familiar voice, reaches to you out in the void: 'Thanks for the meal.'"},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_06_TXT", "Destruction of Marsec's hastily scrambled flotilla in Earth's orbit is followed by the fall of Laputa, which causes untold devastation. Soon after, the Depth Dwellers enter the fray, destroying several harbour cities and carving out more area for themselves, no longer bound by the presence of Star Gods. The Church of Sirius takes their side. They are eventually stopped, but tens of millions die before the situation stabilizes. The surviving Govts restore order, humanity is decimated, endangered, but finally unshackled."},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_07_TXT", "The Guild is the last loyalist force left standing, and the surviving Star Gods have no choice but to cooperate. Together, they patch up the Solar Governor. The cybernetic construct is heretical, but it's a lesser evil than the decadent court that preceded it. And inquisitors can't get in anyway, after you have blown up the Jump Gate. The Earth is unassailable, for now, but the Guild rises to the challenge of becoming a power in its own right, and Marsec fleets only start to grow. Nobody knows what the future will bring..."},
		{"STR_WIN_STANDARD_08_TXT", "But none of this is of your concern anymore. The galaxy lies in front of your powerful warship, ready to be pillaged. Thanks to your foresight, your trusty, cloaked Conqueror can raid targets lightyears away from your mobile base, and you can build more of them. A whole new life of high piracy awaits you, a true freedom you've never tasted before. The stars beckon you into the infinite universe...{NEWLINE}ENDING: SPACE PIRATE"},
