		{"STR_NEPOTISM_UFOPEDIA", "To 'Nep' someone is to give them undue privilege. Which costs money, but improves the readiness of the chosen officer (rank Mistress or higher).{NEWLINE}People will naturally not acknowledge having already been Nepped, but they will not get any extra benefit from repeated Neppings.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+15 Freshness"},
		{"STR_PERSONAL_ATTENTION_UFOPEDIA", "'In just 6 days, I will make you a Man!'{NEWLINE}Your personal involvement with the crew, while potentially dangerous, can make them fight harder! Whether it's through rigorous disciplining, wise lessons, special equipment, or your bed, whatever is your technique, you're able to push your crewmembers to become just a little better.{NEWLINE}This training requires CULTURAL facility and 6 Glamour. It puts the warrior on a 6-day vacation.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness"},
		{"STR_BRIDE_UFOPEDIA", "This person is a member of your personal harem, by the means of being permanently wed to a Harem Collar. It increases their fanaticism, but isn't that good for their clarity of mind. Your own sanity is helped, however, because they stop coming to receive more Neppings.{NEWLINE}Requires Nepping and Personal Attention first. Costs $3M for harem-related expenses. Requires Cultural facility.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+6 TU, +6 STA, +6 FRS{NEWLINE}+1 Morale and Stun regen{NEWLINE}-6 VSKL"},
		{"STR_CONDEMNED_UFOPEDIA", "This is likely the first award a Gal gets. She starts to be recognizable to our enemies, thus cementing her fall to the Pirate lifestyle. No way back now!{NEWLINE}Bonuses like this one can be earned through Condemnations and special training. They count on top of Gal's normal stats, and do not interfere with stat maximums. You can see them by clicking small button in the upper-right area of Gal's file in the 'Hands on Deck' menu.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ORIGINAL8_UFOPEDIA", "The original crew, hailing from various Uber zones, have escaped the captivity of a weird, experimental Academy's camp, where they spent most of their lives. In their commandeered Airbus, knowing no better, they followed a mysterious dream and found refuge in some underground tunnels, which turned out to be much more than just some tunnels...{NEWLINE}They had little more than rags they called clothes, a few weapons they managed to construct or scavenge, and not much knowledge of the world at large, but they're amongst the finest Uber specimens out there.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 to All Stats"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SERVICE_TIME_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded every six months, counting from the time of joining our ranks. Yes, the time passes so quickly, we have birthdays twice a year!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Health per level{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness or Reactions alternatively per level{NEWLINE}-1.33 Stamina per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_IMMORTAL_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded to a gal that has survived 6 years of pirating career, which, in this path of life, is almost equal to being immortal. But the age shows. It will be awarded yearly until the 10th anniversary, then bi-yearly. Maybe it is time to finish the campaign, one way or another?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 Health per level{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness & -2 Stamina per level{NEWLINE}-1 Energy Regen per level{NEWLINE}-1 Reactions every odd level{NEWLINE}-1 TUs every third level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_STATGAIN_UFOPEDIA", "Marks those who have grown past limits and boundaries into truly beautiful beings. 125 points of stat gains minimum, and every next level of this Condemnation requires 25 more (33 on higher tiers).{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 to a different stat each level:{NEWLINE}STA, HP, STR, THR{NEWLINE}TU, FRS, MEL{NEWLINE}VPWR, REA, ACC"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_SCORE_UFOPEDIA", "You're known and feared across the globe (or at least in some parts of it, or some taverns). This is awarded for participating in high-scoring missions. All the points are then given to each participant and tallied up. Now she must bear the weight of fame...{NEWLINE}5000 Infamy minimum. 20,000 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions per level.{NEWLINE}+1 HP every 5th level.{NEWLINE}+1 Melee, VPWR or TU alternatively per level.{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_MISSIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for amassing a large grand total of missions in the course of a piratin' career. Only victorious missions count. Your battle experience makes you tougher and calmer.{NEWLINE}5 Missions minimum. 20 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Health and Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_MISSIONS2_UFOPEDIA", "This person had survived an impossible number of victorious missions. How comes that they're still alive?{NEWLINE}250 Missions minimum. 500 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 Armor per level, in sequence: side, front, back, bottom."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_NIGHTOPS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for participating in many Night missions. This trains a keen eye, but results in totally confused sleep schedules.{NEWLINE}4 Missions minimum. 15 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Night Vision range every other level{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BASE_DEFENSE_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for defending one's Hideout, duh.{NEWLINE}One Level awarded for each Hideout Defense.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Health per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BULWARK_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for participating in an ungodly amount of Hideout Defenses.{NEWLINE}12 minimum. 18 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Front Armor, FRS or HP per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ALIEN_BASE_ASSAULT_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for raiding Secret Bases and Hideouts (only medium and large bases count, outposts don't).{NEWLINE}One Level awarded for each successful raid.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 TU per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_INFILTRATION_MISSIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for victories in missions where you need to get out of your combat duds, and the weapon selection is limited. Such missions train patience and endurance, as well as confidence in your own body.{NEWLINE}2 Missions Minimum. 8 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Health, Morale Regen or Reactions alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness each other level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNDERSEA_MISSIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for participating in undersea missions. It is good for your physical health... if you can survive the dangers of the abyss!{NEWLINE}2 Missions Minimum. 8 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Energy Regen, Stun Regen or Health (not regen) alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina each other level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNDERGROUND_MISSIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for participating in underground missions where Big People cannot go. It teaches you to step lightly and makes you tough like the bones of the Earth.{NEWLINE}2 Missions Minimum. 8 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Strength, Armor or Night Vision alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 TU each other level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_0G_MISSIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Fights in zero-G are fast and brutal. Those who survive, learn to shoot accurately and react quickly. They also lose a few marbles in the process.{NEWLINE}1 Mission Minimum. 10 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions, Firing or TU alternatively per level;{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at level 4;{NEWLINE}+1 VPWR and VSKL at level 7 and 10;{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SHADOWREALMS_MISSIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for conquest of the weird, oneiric and mysterious Shadowrealms. Contact with these other worlds fills you with dark power.{NEWLINE}1 Mission Minimum. 10 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power, TU or Health alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+2 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CAMPAIGN_RIBBON_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for participating in many missions in a Region. Successful, failed or complicated.{NEWLINE}20 Missions minimum. 40 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MURDERER_UFOPEDIA", "This Gal has the blood of fellow human-like beings on her hands. Was it really necessary?{NEWLINE}12 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Awards 'Condemned'"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_KILLS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for slaying an impressive number of beings throughout their whole career. Civilian and Friendly casualties count.{NEWLINE}50 Kills minimum. 150 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_CAPTURES_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for knocking out lots of enemies.{NEWLINE}10 Stuns minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_RACE_KILLS_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for taking out a lot of enemies belonging to a single faction. Still, you can't ever kill everyone!{NEWLINE}30 Neutralizations minimum. 75 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness, TU or VooDoo Power alternatively per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WEAPON_PROFICIENCY_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for taking out a lot of enemies with a single type of weapon. You need to be a very boring person to reach a high rank.{NEWLINE}20 Neutralizations minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing, Melee or Firing alternatively per level.{NEWLINE}+3 to all three instead at max level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FIREKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Killing It with Fire.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 30 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness and TU per level{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery on level 8 {NEWLINE}Increased Freshness drain each level (0.08)"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CHEMKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for deviously melting enemies with acid and anti-E511 chemicals. Your knowledge of biochemistry improved your metabolism, while your mind grows cold and detached.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina per level.{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power each 5th level.{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at level 9."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_LASERKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for spreading enlightenment and debunking superstition by the means of laser weapons.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_POISONKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for the gentle art of poisoning and choking enemies to death. You have become very enduring, but somewhat twitchy.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Health per level{NEWLINE}Health recovery when HPs are low (maximum recovery 3HP/turn){NEWLINE}-1 TU or REA alternatively per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ELECTROKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for inviting enemies to their last dance by the means of Electricity and EMP. You've become quite a good dancer yourself, too.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WARPKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for turning your enemies into horrifying works of abstract art with the use of Warp damage. You're changing into an implacable engine of destruction, but madness is the price you pay.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 TU Recovery per level (relevant only at low Freshness){NEWLINE}+1 Energy Regen every other level{NEWLINE}+1 Night Vision every 3rd level{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power and TU at level 10{NEWLINE}-1 Morale Regen every 3rd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MAGICKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills effected by a curse, causing Mind damage. The Warlock is of strong mind, but feeble body.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Voodoo Skill, VooDoo Power or Freshness alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina ever other level{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power extra at level 7{NEWLINE}+2 VooDoo Skill extra at level 10{NEWLINE}-1 Strength or Melee every level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ARCHER_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with bows, throwing weapons and spears of all kinds.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing per level{NEWLINE}+1 TU or Throwing extra alternatively per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PRIMAL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with stone age weapons.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina per level{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing or Strength alternatively per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PIRATE_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with pirate-themed weapons. Cosplay, or poverty? The crippling alcohol addiction is real in either case.{NEWLINE}20 Kills minimum. 75 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 alternatively per level: STA, STR, HP, FRS, Armor.{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level.{NEWLINE}+1 extra Frontal Armor every 3rd level.{NEWLINE}-1 Energy Regen every odd level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_NINJA_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with NINJA weapons?! Both traditional and Sky Ninja weapons count. You become fast like a Ninja but suffer from self-doubt.{NEWLINE}20 Kills minimum. 75 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 alternatively per level: TU, REA, THR, MEL, Nightvision.{NEWLINE}In addition, +1 TU or REA every 2nd level.{NEWLINE}-1 Morale Regen every odd level.{NEWLINE}-1 HP every 3rd level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MEDIEVAL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with medieval-like armaments, like swords, axes, maces and certain kinds of arrows and throwables. You adapt to handling hard times and heavy armor better.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 alternatively per level: Side Armor, STR, Energy Regen, STA."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_HIGHNOON_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with Frontier-era weapons, like ol' revolvers, ol' shotguns or ol' carbines. Perfect timing in duels and arcades is what you gain, by challenging the Time itself (you need higher Freshness levels to keep your edge).{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 alternatively per level: REA, ACC or TU{NEWLINE}-1 Time Regen every level except 5th and 10th"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SHELLSHOCKED_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with weapons similar to these used in trench warfare during the Old Earth era of great wars. You're becoming an indifferent killing machine, at the price of narcolepsy.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 alternatively per level: HP, STA, REA.{NEWLINE}In addition, +1 Morale Regen or FRS every 2nd level.{NEWLINE}-1 Stun Regen every odd level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PROFESIONAL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with all these sleek and futuristic looking firearms (and a few other things, like martial arts). You might just become like a cyborg yourself.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina each 2nd level{NEWLINE}+1 Strength each 3rd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_IDIOT_UFOPEDIA", "They said this weapon is no good for Killing, but you just wouldn't listen!{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 STR, ACC or HP per level{NEWLINE}+10 BRA at level 6{NEWLINE}+1 extra HP or STR alternatively each level from 7th{NEWLINE}-1 VSKL per level{NEWLINE}-1 REA every 2nd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_NUCLEAR_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with atomic weapons. The future is so bright, you gotta wear shades!{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 NV every 3rd level and +10 BRA every 5th level.{NEWLINE}+1 Health on all other levels.{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_TECHNOBARBARIAN_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with primitive weapons created with advanced technology, and experimental weapons.{NEWLINE}25 Kills minimum. 100 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina every level{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness every 2nd level{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions every 3rd level{NEWLINE}+1 extra Stamina every 4th level{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery on 10th level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PROXYKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with traps (like Landmines). Improving this skill makes you extremely patient, but the constant vigilance affects your physical health.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 30 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 TU Recovery per level (at low Fresh){NEWLINE}+1 Morale recovery each odd level{NEWLINE}-1 Health per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SLAVEKILLS_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made by units under your psionic control. It improves your VooDoo, but paranoia sets in.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 30 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Voodoo Skill per level{NEWLINE}-1 Morale Regen each odd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_HAMMERER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing enemies, using various industrial, mining and otherwise unlikely equipment like hammers, pickaxes and crowbars, to name a few.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina per level{NEWLINE}+1 Strength every 2nd level{NEWLINE}+1 Energy regeneration every 3rd level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_GUNSLINGER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using firearms. (Only Piercing and Laser damage counts).{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Firing per level{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness each odd level{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions every 3rd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_EXECUTIONER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using ranged Slashing weapons.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina or Strength alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing each odd level{NEWLINE}+1 Energy Regen every 3rd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_THORNY_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using ranged Stabbing weapons, like pikes, bows or javelins.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina per level, except for Reactions every 5th level{NEWLINE}+1 TU each odd level{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing every 3rd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BOMBER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using explosives (bombs, rockets, grenades etc.). It makes you resistant to concussions but also deaf.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing every odd level{NEWLINE}+1 Bottom armor every 3rd level{NEWLINE}+1 Stun regeneration at 5th level{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at 10th level{NEWLINE}-1 Reactions per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MELEEKILL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for Kills made with melee weapons.{NEWLINE}10 Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Melee per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SLASHER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using Slashing, Laser or Plasma melee weapons.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Melee and TU per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_STABBER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using Stabbing melee weapons.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Melee and Reactions per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SAMURAI_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 8 in a single mission, using melee weapons.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Melee and Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MONSTER_UFOPEDIA", "This gal is rippling with power. In fact, she's so strong she has managed to kill people using Daze melee weapons.{NEWLINE}2 Kills minimum. 15 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Health per level{NEWLINE}+1 Strength every odd level{NEWLINE}-1 Reactions every third level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_TANK_KILLER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for killing enemy war machines.{NEWLINE}1 minimum. 5 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Firing and TU per level{NEWLINE}+1 Strength every odd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MONSTER_HUNTER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for bravely killing monsters with melee weapons. Good job, you sexy beast!{NEWLINE}3 minimum. 12 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 HP or STA alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 Armor (except bottom) every other level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ASSAULTER_UFOPEDIA", "Marks a very experienced street punk. Awarded for kills with knives, swords, as well as with pistols, one-handed SMGs and instant-thrown explosives, incendiaries etc.{NEWLINE}5 minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Firing and Reactions per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PSYCHOKILL_UFOPEDIA", "Given only to true psychopaths, when it comes to weapon choices. Awarded for Kills with things like claws, gauntlets, machetes, cleavers, maces, axes, barbaric weapons, as well as chainsaws, shotguns, flamethrowers and a couple other weapons.{NEWLINE}5 minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 TU and Stamina per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SMGKILL_UFOPEDIA", "Spray them with a rain of hot lead from close range, then drive away. This Condemnation is given for using 2-handed SMGs.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina and Firing each odd level{NEWLINE}+1 TU and Reactions each other level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_RIFLEKILL_UFOPEDIA", "Fancy weapons are not for you. The ubiquitousness and dependability of assault rifles is what you respect. Experience in that area gives you accuracy and endurance.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Firing per level{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness or Health alternatively per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CANNONEER_UFOPEDIA", "This Gal likes them in any shape: grenade launchers, cannons, bazookas. The bigger the weapon, the better.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Strength per level{NEWLINE}+1 Firing or HP alternatively each level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SNIPER_UFOPEDIA", "Kill enemies elegantly - with single-fire rifles, carbines and similar weapons.{NEWLINE}5 minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 Firing per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MAXDAKKA_UFOPEDIA", "There is nothing quite like ripping your opposition apart with a hail of bullets. This Condemnation is dispensed for killing enemies with heavy automatic weapons. However, using vehicle-mounted weapons will not grant you this Condemnation.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Firing and Strength per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_JOKER_UFOPEDIA", "Some weapons are considered a joke. This Gal made the joke a killing. Which weapons are these? If you're reading this, you might already have some clues!?{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Throwing and Reactions each odd level{NEWLINE}+1 TU and Stamina each other level{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power each 3rd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BATTLEMAGE_UFOPEDIA", "This Condemnation is awarded for Kills made with Magitech weapons which don't belong to any standard category.{NEWLINE}5 Kills minimum. 35 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Skill per level{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina or Freshness alternatively each level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_DBLKILL_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for 2 Kills in a single turn.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 TU per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_QUADKILL_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for 4 Kills in a single turn.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_7V7KILL_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for 7 Kills in a single turn.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MISSION_KILLS_5_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 5 in a single mission.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina and Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MISSION_KILLS_11_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 11 in a single mission.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 HP and Stamina per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MISSION_KILLS_23_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for Killing 23 in a single mission.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WRESTLER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded to those who subdue enemies up close and personal, using unarmed techniques.{NEWLINE}10 Stuns/Kills minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Strength or Health alternatively each level{NEWLINE}+2 STA on 2nd level, +2 REA on 4th, +2 MEL on 6th, +2 TU on 8th{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at 10th level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SPECIALSTUN_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for neutralizing enemies using Charm, Choking or improvisation.{NEWLINE}10 Stuns minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina or Freshness alternatively per level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_IDOL_UFOPEDIA", "This is awarded for capturing 3 enemies in a single turn.{NEWLINE}Repeating it 8 times is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 VooDoo Power every 2nd level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SUCCUBUS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded to those who capture many enemies using Charm damage.{NEWLINE}10 Stuns minimum. 50 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina, VooDoo Skill or Health Regen alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 Stun Regen every 2nd level{NEWLINE}+6 Extra Stamina at 5th level{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at 10th level{NEWLINE}Increased Freshness drain each level (0.36)"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_VOIDKILL_UFOPEDIA", "People just tend to die around you for seemingly accidental reasons. How do you do it? Are you even really involved? Only you may know. In any case, you wield, or are wielded by, the allure of the Void.{NEWLINE}3 Kills minimum. 21 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Freshness, Reactions or VooDoo Power alternatively per level.{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at level 7 instead."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_VIPHUNTER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for capturing high-ranking enemies.{NEWLINE}7 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Strength per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BANDITCHATCHER_UFOPEDIA", "You've been capturing a lot of Bandits alive. What are you going to do, give them a due process or what? Madness!{NEWLINE}The Black Dragon is displeased.{NEWLINE}Mistress of the Nine Moons is pleased.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}10 minimum. 40 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 VSKL and REA per level{NEWLINE}-1 Strength and HP per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ATTITUDE_PROBLEM_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for hushing down 7 of these bossy Guild Team Managers and Reps for good.{NEWLINE}One-Time award.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+3 Morale Regen"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_DOTS_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for punishing the worst enemies of real science, the Academy Provosts, Counsellors and Scientists. 3 Kills required.{NEWLINE}One-Time award.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery, +10 Freshness"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ROOMSERVICE_UFOPEDIA", "Maids, maids, maids! You simply can't get enough of maids! And having this much roomservice surely helps! This Condemnation is awarded for capturing 10 Shrine Maidens or Warmaidens.{NEWLINE}One-Time award.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+6 Freshness"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNMAGICA_UFOPEDIA", "Earned for turning Magical Girls into dead girls. Purple Bloom hopes you regret your excess feistyness. Do you?{NEWLINE}She can't do a heck about it anyway!{NEWLINE}Awarded once per Kill.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No Bonus"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REACTIONFIRE_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for total Kills with Reaction Fire.{NEWLINE}2 Kills minimum. 11 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_LUCKYSHOT_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for hitting targets despite lousy odds.{NEWLINE}5 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Firing per level, except +1 HP every third level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNDERFIRE_UFOPEDIA", "You were targeted by lots and lots of attacks during a single mission. Hopefully they were unsuccessful. This is an unnerving situation to be in, and mental scars remain.{NEWLINE}10 attack attempts minimum. 40 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 Reactions every third level{NEWLINE}+3 Stamina at level 10"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MULTIPLEHITS_UFOPEDIA", "You've received many hits that failed to cause any damage during a single mission. You became arrogant.{NEWLINE}4 hits minimum. 8 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Energy Recovery or Stamina alternatively per level{NEWLINE}+1 armor (all facings) every 3rd level{NEWLINE}-1 Reactions per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PURPLE_HEART_UFOPEDIA", "This testifies the number of battle scars you've earned. This makes you tougher but the pain becomes your old friend. Each mission you've been wounded counts as 1, regardless of the number of Wounds.{NEWLINE}7 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 HP per level{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNCONSCIOUS_UFOPEDIA", "This notes the dubious achievement of frequently passing out during a battle.{NEWLINE}8 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No Bonus"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CRIMSON_HEART_UFOPEDIA", "Medical documentation on how many days you've uselessly spent in your bunk, feeling miserable. You have developed pain resistance... and drug reliance. The Doctor looks at you disapprovingly.{NEWLINE}15 days minimum. 100 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-1 Freshness per level{NEWLINE}+1 Stun recovery every 3rd level{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery at level 10"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_HEALER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for healing many wounds.{NEWLINE}5 Heals minimum. 10 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No Bonus"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REVIVE_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for raising unconscious people, regardless of reason.{NEWLINE}10 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No Bonus"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FRIENDLYFIRE_UFOPEDIA", "Slapped onto those who often get hit by their comrades in combat. Hopefully you've made up for this!{NEWLINE}15 for Third Judas Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Awards 'Condemned'"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_LONESURVIVOR_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for one who was a lone survivor of a mission. Whether they lost all their comrades to enemy action, accident, or simply killed them all to claim the laurel, they're equally survive-y. However, this leaves them less than sane...{NEWLINE}8 Survivals for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 TU per level{NEWLINE}-10 Bravery every third level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SAVEDALL_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for saving all friendly peasants from evildoers, or otherwise gaining great fame amongst the masses.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1.5 Freshness per level (rounded down).{NEWLINE}+3 TU on 5th level{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery on 10th level."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_GLOBETROTTER_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded for seeing all countries of the world.{NEWLINE}Awarded once.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+5 TU"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CIV_KILLS_UFOPEDIA", "Either by accident or by design, this pirate killed those who were supposed to be protected. It makes it harder to sleep at night.{NEWLINE}Killing 8 is required for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-2 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CIV_STUNS_UFOPEDIA", "You have knocked out many neutral or friendly units. It was the only logical choice to achieve the greater good, you're sure of it!{NEWLINE}2 Minimum. 12 for Third Iron Skull.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-1 Melee per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BETRAYER_UFOPEDIA", "This supremely shameful title belongs to those who hamper our cause by killing their comrades or committing suicide.{NEWLINE}Awarded once for each Kill.{NEWLINE}-1 Morale Regen per level{NEWLINE}+1 Voodoo Skill every other level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_VALKYRIE_UFOPEDIA", "Pay respects to this Gal. Everyone agrees that, at the moment of her death, she was the greatest pirate in your crew. Now the voice of legend made her even greater.{NEWLINE}Awarded once to the best pirate lost during a mission.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 to all stats except VSKL, Freshness and Bravery."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_POSTMORTEM_KILL_UFOPEDIA", "Awarded posthumously to those, who manage to slay enemies even in death.{NEWLINE}Decoration level depends on the number of kills.{NEWLINE}One-time award.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+10 Bravery, +3 Reactions and VooDoo Power"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FALLEN_UFOPEDIA", "This gal has been killed and is now likely haunting some remote and uninteresting region of Hell. Let's keep living while we can.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-4 Freshness"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FALLEN2_UFOPEDIA", "This gal has returned from Hell, only to be killed again. And possibly again. Will that stubborn wench ever learn?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-2 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REVOLVINGDOOR_UFOPEDIA", "This gal has been killed so many times that they're likely keeping a special oven just for her in Hell.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}-2 Freshness per level"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MIA_UFOPEDIA", "Denotes that the gal in question isn't currently in our ranks due to being missing.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No Bonus"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ORIGINAL8_DESCRIPTION", "This pirate is a member of the original crew of 6 misfits that found the abandoned base where your Hideout is located now."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SERVICE_TIME_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded every six months, counting from the time of joining our ranks. Yes, we have birthdays twice a year!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_IMMORTAL_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded to a gal that has survived 6 years of pirating career, which, in this path of life, is almost equal to being immortal. It will be awarded yearly until the 10th anniversary, then bi-yearly. Maybe it is time to finish the campaign, one way or another?"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_STATGAIN_DESCRIPTION", "Marks those who have grown past limits and boundaries into truly beautiful beings (by increasing their stats compared to what they started with)."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_SCORE_DESCRIPTION", "You're known and feared across the globe (or at least in some parts of it, or some taverns). This is awarded for participating in many high-scoring missions."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_MISSIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for amassing a large grand total of missions in the course of a piratin' career. Only victorious missions count."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_MISSIONS2_DESCRIPTION", "This person had survived an impossible number of victorious missions. How comes that they're still alive?"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_NIGHTOPS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for participating in many Night missions."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BASE_DEFENSE_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for defending one's Hideout, duh."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BULWARK_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for participating in an ungodly amount of Hideout Defenses."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ALIEN_BASE_ASSAULT_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for raiding Secret Bases and Hideouts (only medium and large bases count, outposts don't)."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_INFILTRATION_MISSIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for victories in missions where you need to get out of your combat duds, and the weapon selection is limited."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNDERSEA_MISSIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for participating in undersea missions. It is good for your physical health... if you can survive the dangers of the abyss!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNDERGROUND_MISSIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for participating in underground missions where Big People cannot go."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_0G_MISSIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Fights in zero-G are fast and brutal. Those who survive, learn to shoot accurately and react quickly. They also lose a few marbles in the process."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SHADOWREALMS_MISSIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for conquest of the weird, oneiric and mysterious Shadowrealms."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CAMPAIGN_RIBBON_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for participating in many missions in a Region. Successful, failed or complicated."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MURDERER_DESCRIPTION", "This Gal has the blood of fellow human-like beings on her hands. Was it really necessary?"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_KILLS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for slaying an impressive number of beings throughout their whole career. Civilian and Friendly casualties count."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CARREER_CAPTURES_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for knocking out lots of enemies."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_RACE_KILLS_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for taking out a lot of enemies belonging to a single faction. Still, you can't ever kill everyone!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WEAPON_PROFICIENCY_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for taking out a lot of enemies with a single type of weapon. You need to be a very boring person to reach a high rank."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FIREKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Killing It with Fire."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CHEMKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for deviously melting enemies with acid and anti-E511 chemicals."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_LASERKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for spreading enlightenment and debunking superstition by the means of laser weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_POISONKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for the gentle art of poisoning and choking enemies to death."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ELECTROKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for inviting enemies to their last dance by the means of Electricity and EMP."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WARPKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for turning your enemies into horrifying works of abstract art with the use of Warp damage."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MAGICKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills effected by a curse, causing Mind damage."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_VOIDKILL_DESCRIPTION:", "People just tend to die around you for seemingly accidental reasons. How do you do it? Are you even really involved? Only you may know."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ARCHER_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with bows, throwing weapons and spears of all kinds."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PRIMAL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with stone age weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PIRATE_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with pirate-themed weapons. Cosplay, or poverty? The crippling alcohol addiction is real in either case."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_NINJA_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with NINJA weapons?! Both traditional and Sky Ninja weapons count. You become fast like a Ninja but suffer from self-doubt."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MEDIEVAL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with medieval-like armaments, like swords, axes, maces and certain kinds of arrows and throwables. You adapt to handling hard times and heavy armor better."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_HIGHNOON_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with Frontier-era weapons. Perfect timing in duels and arcades is what you gain, by challenging the Time itself (you need higher Freshness levels to keep your edge)."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SHELLSHOCKED_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with weapons similar to these used in trench warfare during the Old Earth era of great wars. You're becoming an indifferent killing machine, at the price of narcolepsy."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PROFESIONAL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with all these sleek and futuristic looking firearms (and a few other things, like martial arts). You might just become like a cyborg yourself."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_IDIOT_DESCRIPTION", "They said this weapon is no good for Killing, but you just wouldn't listen!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_NUCLEAR_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with atomic weapons. The future is so bright, you gotta wear shades!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_TECHNOBARBARIAN_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with primitive weapons created with advanced technology, and experimental weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PROXYKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with traps (like Landmines). Improving this skill makes you extremely patient, but the constant vigilance affects your physical health."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SLAVEKILLS_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made by units under your psionic control."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_HAMMERER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing enemies, using various industrial, mining and otherwise unlikely equipment like hammers, pickaxes and crowbars, to name a few."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_GUNSLINGER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using firearms. (Only Piercing and Laser damage counts)."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_EXECUTIONER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using ranged Slashing weapons, like thrown axes."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_THORNY_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using ranged Stabbing weapons, like pikes, bows or javelins."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BOMBER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using explosives (bombs, rockets, grenades etc.). It makes you resistant to concussions damage but also deaf."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MELEEKILL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for Kills made with melee weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SLASHER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using Slashing, Laser or Plasma melee weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_STABBER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 3 in a single turn, using Stabbing melee weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SAMURAI_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 8 in a single mission, using melee weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MONSTER_DESCRIPTION", "This gal is rippling with power to such extent that she managed to kill several people using only Daze damage."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_TANK_KILLER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for killing enemy war machines."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MONSTER_HUNTER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for bravely killing monsters with melee weapons. Good job, you sexy beast!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ASSAULTER_DESCRIPTION", "Marks a very experienced street punk. Awarded for kills with knives, swords, as well as with pistols, one-handed SMGs and instant-thrown explosives, incendiaries etc."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PSYCHOKILL_DESCRIPTION", "Given only to true psychopaths, when it comes to weapon choices. Awarded for Kills with things like claws, gauntlets, machetes, cleavers, maces, axes, barbaric weapons, as well as chainsaws, shotguns, flamethrowers and a couple other weapons."},
