		{"STR_MEDAL_CANNONEER_DESCRIPTION", "This Gal likes them in any shape: grenade launchers, cannons, bazookas. The bigger the weapon, the better."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SNIPER_DESCRIPTION", "Kill enemies elegantly - with single-fire rifles, carbines and similar weapons."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MAXDAKKA_DESCRIPTION", "There is nothing quite like ripping your opposition apart with a hail of bullets. This Condemnation is dispensed for killing enemies with heavy automatic weapons. However, using vehicle-mounted weapons will not grant you this Condemnation."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_JOKER_DESCRIPTION", "Some weapons are considered a joke. This Gal made the joke a killing. Which weapons are these? If you're reading this, you might already have some clues!?"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BATTLEMAGE_DESCRIPTION", "This Condemnation is awarded for Kills made with Magitech weapons which don't belong to any standard category."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_DBLKILL_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for 2 Kills in a single turn."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_QUADKILL_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for 4 Kills in a single turn."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_7V7KILL_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for 7 Kills in a single turn."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MISSION_KILLS_5_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 5 in a single mission."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MISSION_KILLS_11_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 11 in a single mission."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MISSION_KILLS_23_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Killing 23 in a single mission."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SPECIALSTUN_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for neutralizing enemies using Charm, Choking or improvisation."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WRESTLER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded to those who subdue enemies up close and personal, using unarmed techniques."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_IDOL_DESCRIPTION", "This is awarded for capturing 3 enemies in a single turn."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SUCCUBUS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded to those who capture many enemies using Charm damage."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_VIPHUNTER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for capturing high-ranking enemies."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BANDITCHATCHER_DESCRIPTION", "You've been capturing a lot of Bandits alive."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ATTITUDE_PROBLEM_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for hushing down these bossy Guild Team Managers and Reps for good.{NEWLINE}Awarded once."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_DOTS_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for punishing the worst enemies of real science, the Academy Provosts.{NEWLINE}Awarded once."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_ROOMSERVICE_DESCRIPTION", "Maids, maids, maids! You simply can't get enough of maids! And having this much roomservice surely helps! This Condemnation is awarded for capturing 10 Shrine Maidens or Warmaidens.{NEWLINE}Awarded once."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNMAGICA_DESCRIPTION", "Earned for turning Magical Girls into dead girls. Purple Bloom hopes you regret your excess feistyness. Do you?{NEWLINE}She can't do a heck about it anyway!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REACTIONFIRE_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for Kills with Reaction Fire."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_LUCKYSHOT_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for hitting targets despite lousy odds."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNDERFIRE_DESCRIPTION", "You were targeted by lots and lots of attacks during a single mission. Hopefully they were unsuccessful. This is an unnerving situation to be in, and mental scars remain."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MULTIPLEHITS_DESCRIPTION", "You've received many hits during a single mission. You became arrogant."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_PURPLE_HEART_DESCRIPTION", "This testifies the number of battle scars you've earned. Each mission you've been wounded counts as 1, regardless of the number of Wounds."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_UNCONSCIOUS_DESCRIPTION", "This notes the dubious achievement of frequently passing out during a battle."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CRIMSON_HEART_DESCRIPTION", "Medical documentation on how many days you've uselessly spent in your bunk, feeling miserable. The Doctor looks at you disapprovingly."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_HEALER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for healing many wounds."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REVIVE_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for raising unconscious people, regardless of reason."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FRIENDLYFIRE_DESCRIPTION", "Slapped onto those who often get hit by their comrades in combat. Hopefully you've made up for this!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_LONESURVIVOR_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for one who was a lone survivor of a mission. Whether they lost all their comrades to enemy action, accident, or simply killed them all to claim the laurel, they're equally survive-y. However, this leaves them less than sane..."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_SAVEDALL_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for saving all friendly peasants from evildoers, or otherwise gaining great fame amongst the masses."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_GLOBETROTTER_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded for seeing all countries of the world.{NEWLINE}Awarded once."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CIV_STUNS_DESCRIPTION", "You have knocked out many neutral or friendly units. It was the only logical choice to achieve the greater good, you're sure of it!"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_CIV_KILLS_DESCRIPTION", "Either by accident or by design, this pirate killed those who were supposed to be protected."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BETRAYER_DESCRIPTION", "This supremely shameful title belongs to those who hamper our cause by killing their comrades or committing suicide."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_VALKYRIE_DESCRIPTION", "Pay respects to this Gal. Everyone agrees that, at the moment of her demise, she was the greatest pirate in your crew.{NEWLINE}Awarded once to the best pirate lost during a mission."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_POSTMORTEM_KILL_DESCRIPTION", "Awarded posthumously to those, who manage to slay enemies even in death.{NEWLINE}Decoration level depends on the number of kills."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FALLEN_DESCRIPTION", "This gal has been killed and is now likely haunting some remote and uninteresting region of Hell. Let's keep living while we can."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_FALLEN2_DESCRIPTION", "This gal has returned from Hell, only to be killed again. And possibly again. Will that stubborn wench ever learn?"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REVOLVINGDOOR_DESCRIPTION", "This gal has been killed so many times that they're likely keeping a special oven just for her in Hell."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_MIA_DESCRIPTION", "Denotes that the gal in question isn't currently in our ranks due to being missing."},
		{"STR_ART_OF_TROUNCING", "Art of Trouncing"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_OUTLAW", "Outlaw"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_OUTLAW_BONUS", "Hardened Outlaw"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_OUTLAW_DESCRIPTION", "This Catgirl is on the wanted list on the planets of the Stellar Empire as a dangerous criminal."},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_OUTLAW_UFOPEDIA", "Many Catgirls are on the wanted list on the planets of the Stellar Empire as a dangerous criminals. Some of them even manage to be caught and imprisoned (for how long is another question).{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A life full of dangers, fights and chases strengthens the body:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+6 TU, STA, HP, REA, STR, MEL{NEWLINE}+4 Stress (unruly)."},
		{"STR_HERBALIST_TRAINING", "The Path of Herbs"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_HERBALIST", "Herbalist"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_HERBALIST_BONUS", "Herbalist"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_HERBALIST_DESCRIPTION", "This Catgirl studied the physiology of earthlings and became a specialist in traditional medicine."},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_HERBALIST_UFOPEDIA", "Catgirls are very interested in the Earth's flora (and especially Valeriana Officinalis). If we channel this curiosity in the right direction, then we can get a specialist in the field of traditional medicine: herbs, decoctions and tinctures in some cases may be more useful and effective than synthetic pills. Also, Catgirl will need to know the physiology of earthlings perfectly well, so it will take a lot of time to learn. The presence of medical establishments in the Hideout will speed up the process, and the Library is indispensable.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 VSKILL;{NEWLINE}+30 Freshness."},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_WARRIOR", "Nekomimi Warrior"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_WARRIOR_BONUS", "Nekomimi Warrior"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_WARRIOR_DESCRIPTION", "This Catgirl is a Nekomimi regular army soldier."},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_WARRIOR_UFOPEDIA", "This Catgirl is a Nekomimi regular army soldier. She is better equipped and trained than ordinary adventuring Catgirls.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+10 TU, Firing, Throwing & Stamina;{NEWLINE}+5 Strength and Melee."},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_ACE", "Flight Ace"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_ACE_BONUS", "Flight Ace"},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_ACE_DESCRIPTION", "This Catgirl was trained to operate Nekomimi military machines and shown excellent results in piloting fighters."},
		{"STR_NEKO_CLASS_ACE_UFOPEDIA", "This Catgirl was trained to operate Nekomimi military machines and showed excellent results in piloting fighters.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+20 Firing.{NEWLINE}+20 Bravery.{NEWLINE}+15 Reactions."},
		{"STR_SWIFTPAW_TRAINING", "Swiftpaws training"},
		{"STR_NEKO_SWIFTPAW", "Swiftpaw"},
		{"STR_NEKO_SWIFTPAW_UFOPEDIA", "The next step in the growth of Catgirls' gladiatorial talents. To access this training, one need to become the Black Widow, the level 3 Fencer and the Murderer with 1st Silver Skull. But remember: choosing the path of improving dexterity, you will have to give up strength trainings.{NEWLINE}Side effect: mild psychopathy.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+5 TU & Stamina.{NEWLINE}+15 Melee.{NEWLINE}-3 Morale Regen."},
		{"STR_NEKO_BODYBUILDER_TRAINING", "Workout for Catgirls"},
		{"STR_NEKO_BODYBUILDER", "Bodybuilder"},
		{"STR_NEKO_BODYBUILDER_UFOPEDIA", "Neko Outlaws, already exceptional individuals, can become absolute beasts with further gladiatorial fights. However, this will have detrimental effect on their minds.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+8 HP & STR{NEWLINE}+1 Armor & Stun Recovery{NEWLINE}+3 Stress{NEWLINE}-5 VPWR, -10 FRS"},
		{"STR_HONORED_WARRIOR_TRAINING", "Glory to the catty warrior!"},
		{"STR_HONORED_WARRIOR", "Honored Warrior"},
		{"STR_HONORED_WARRIOR_TRAINING_UFOPEDIA", "Any Catgirl who reached the rank of Space Hero or higher can undergo this training to formalize her rank. After going through many battles, she becomes strong in both body and spirit.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 STA & STR.{NEWLINE}+3 HP.{NEWLINE}+2 Morale Recovery.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_ANNA_PUMA", "Hero: Anna Puma"},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_ANNA_PUMA_BONUS", "Hero: Anna Puma"},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_ANNA_PUMA_DESCRIPTION", "Anna is more calm and judicious than Uni. Although in general she is still more reckless than the usual Catgirls."},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_ANNA_PUMA_UFOPEDIA", "Anna is the 'brain' of the Puma Sisters duo: she is more calm and judicious than Uni. Although in general she is still more reckless than the usual Catgirls.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+1 Stamina & Stun regen;{NEWLINE}+2 Morale regen;{NEWLINE}+5 VSKILL."},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_UNI_PUMA", "Hero: Uni Puma"},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_UNI_PUMA_BONUS", "Hero: Uni Puma"},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_UNI_PUMA_DESCRIPTION", "Uni sees in the dark and handles ranged weapons better than other Catgirls. In addition, she has an increased pain threshold, due to which she loses less HP from fatal wounds."},
		{"STR_NEKO_HERO_UNI_PUMA_UFOPEDIA", "Uni is the 'muscles' of the Puma Sisters duo: she sees in the dark and handles ranged weapons better than other Catgirls. In addition, she has a increased pain threshold, due to which she loses less HP from fatal wounds.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+5 Firing & Reactions;{NEWLINE}+3 NV."},
		{"STR_READ_OR_DIE", "Read Or Die"},
		{"STR_READ_OR_DIE_DESCRIPTION", "You recall one of the lessons Dr. X gave you: 'No war has ever been won by illiterates, even though they were often used as cannon fodder'. To avoid behaving like an idiot, knowing your Bootypedia thoroughly is of paramount importance. Consult it often. You can R-click on a topic to mark it as 'unread' (white) again, if you want to be able to easily find it in the future."},
		{"STR_JACKS_WARNING", "Jack's Warning"},
		{"STR_JACKS_WARNING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Mercenaries! The Sky Ninjas are on the move. I know they're preparing to launch a Mobile Fortress, which means they're in the business of building Hideouts. This will have major consequences to our cause. They will steal a lot of your Infamy, however you're too weak yet to deal with them directly. Bide your time and watch out for their air patrols. May the Demon Gods give you victory."},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_INTRODUCTION", "Resource Wars"},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_INTRODUCTION_DESCRIPTION", "From: Colonel Clemborg{NEWLINE}We meet again... Captain. You might not remember, but I was there when you signed up for this whole... 'Protection' thing. I act as an envoy. I will let you on a secret they 'forgot' to tell you... Governments stealing resources from each other, Guild and Academy stealing from governments... We feed you real-time global information about unwanted activity, and resource wars generate big spikes... Check your Charts. All you really need is to scare them off. Small ships, they land twice."},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_ESCALATION", "Escalation"},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_ESCALATION_DESCRIPTION", "From: Colonel Clemborg{NEWLINE}Another meeting, Captain... And another secret for you. You... survived up to this point, so the... forces I represent... certain parts of Provincial Govts, want you to become more active... You will be fed more data about global activity, which will increase your... burden. Don't expect this to be temporary. It will only get worse and worse, as it is natural with all things in life... I would be... disappointed, if yours reaches its conclusion too soon..."},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_ON_NINJAS", "Govts And Ninjas"},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_ON_NINJAS_DESCRIPTION", "From: Colonel Clemborg{NEWLINE}So, it seems you have... seriously inconvenienced the Sky Ninjas... You see, Captain... the Govts are divided on whether they should back you or them.... Now the Ninjas will be more actively trying to gain... more influence, especially in the areas outside your sight. And, also... it's only a question of time before they'll go for those Govt people who lean to your side... A word of advice... Don't even try to fight them unless you're confident in victory. Just try to keep... important friends... safe, and ignore the rest of damage..."},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_SABBAH", "Message Incoming..."},
		{"STR_CLEMBORG_SABBAH_DESCRIPTION", "From: Colonel Clemborg{NEWLINE}A word of advice... Captain. Not all Sabbahs... are faithful to the Star Gods. But to Star Gods... they're allies... Not... slaves, like the Big Factions."},
		{"STR_BOUNTY_HUNTS_LATE", "A Most Brilliant Idea"},
		{"STR_BOUNTY_HUNTS_LATE_DESCRIPTION", "When thinking how to improve finances and Infamy ratings (which also improve finances), you remembered hearsay from Jackstown that many mercenary bands can rise to fame especially quickly by engaging in Bounty Hunts, and that these missions seem easy to do, considering the quality of your crew. How comes you're not digging that gold vein yet!{NEWLINE}[Having regrets: -25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_PERSONAL_LABS_LATE", "Research Issues"},
		{"STR_PERSONAL_LABS_LATE_DESCRIPTION", "Ma Capitaine, the issue I want to discuss is passive information spread. Even if we keep low profile, we cannot avoid becoming more known as the time passes. And thus, we're going to face more and more challenges. Lack of funds might be lethal short term, but lack of research will surely kill us long term. I estimate that without 16 Brainers working full time within next couple of months, our chances of surviving to 2603 are below 50%. Yet we don't even have Personal Labs yet.{NEWLINE}[Brainer Morale decreases: -25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_PERSONAL_LABS_THANK_YOU", "Personal Labs"},
		{"STR_PERSONAL_LABS_THANK_YOU_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Merci, Ma Capitaine, our new Personal Labs are just perfect, finally we don't have to work elbow-to-elbow! I don't know about you, but I just hate it when someone watches my hands while I work. By the way, while moving my things, I found these... you might find them useful.{NEWLINE}[+3 Gothic Raygun clips]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_GREAT", "Captain's Log #1"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_GREAT_DESCRIPTION", "You feel relaxed today. Your life has really gotten better, and you start to wake up to a completely alien concept - free time; something unheard of under Academy's boot.{NEWLINE}Speaking of the time... You feel that you managed to make a very good use of it - so much done within three months!{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy, +35 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_GOOD", "Captain's Log #1"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "You feel relaxed today. Your life has really gotten better, and you start to wake up to a completely alien concept - free time; something unheard of under Academy's boot.{NEWLINE}Speaking of the time... You feel that you used your time well, it took you under half a year to get to this point.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy, +20 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_OK", "Captain's Log #1"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_OK_DESCRIPTION", "You feel relaxed today. Your life has really gotten better, and you start to wake up to a completely alien concept - free time; something unheard of under Academy's boot.{NEWLINE}Speaking of the time... You feel that your progress could have been faster, it took you over half a year to get here...{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +10 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_POOR", "Captain's Log #1"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_POOR_DESCRIPTION", "You feel relaxed today. Your life has really gotten better, and you start to wake up to a completely alien concept - free time; something unheard of under Academy's boot.{NEWLINE}Speaking of the time... It's been a long, slow march to get here. You can only hope it wasn't too slow."},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_AWFUL", "Captain's Log #1"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_1_AWFUL_DESCRIPTION", "You feel relaxed today. Your life has really gotten better, and you start to wake up to a completely alien concept - free time; something unheard of under Academy's boot.{NEWLINE}Speaking of the time... You look at the calendar and your face gets pale. It's been over a year already?! Are you doomed? Your good mood evaporates in an instant.{NEWLINE}[-75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_GREAT", "Captain's Log #2"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_GREAT_DESCRIPTION", "The cultural advancement of your band of pirates is mirrored by your personal growth. You have become sophisticated, cultured, persuasive. It feels like an eternity since you were just a patient at Academy's asylum...{NEWLINE}But it was, in reality, very recently! You're amazed at your impossibly fast progress!{NEWLINE}[+1500 Infamy, +100 Glamour, +50 Culture]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_GOOD", "Captain's Log #2"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "The cultural advancement of your band of pirates is mirrored by your personal growth. You have become sophisticated, cultured, persuasive. It feels like an eternity since you were just a patient at Academy's asylum...{NEWLINE}Yet only less than a year has passed. You're faring better than anyone could expect!{NEWLINE}[+1250 Infamy, +60 Glamour, +50 Culture]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_OK", "Captain's Log #2"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_OK_DESCRIPTION", "The cultural advancement of your band of pirates is mirrored by your personal growth. You have become sophisticated, cultured, persuasive. It feels like an eternity since you were just a patient at Academy's asylum...{NEWLINE}And sure enough, it was over a year since that time. Yet you have grown so much.{NEWLINE}[+1000 Infamy, +25 Glamour, +50 Culture]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_POOR", "Captain's Log #2"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_POOR_DESCRIPTION", "The cultural advancement of your band of pirates is mirrored by your personal growth. You have become sophisticated, cultured, persuasive. It feels like an eternity since you were just a patient at Academy's asylum...{NEWLINE}Almost two years since then. What if it was too long?{NEWLINE}[+500 Infamy, +50 Culture]"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_AWFUL", "Captain's Log #2"},
		{"STR_CAP_LOG_2_AWFUL_DESCRIPTION", "The cultural advancement of your band of pirates is mirrored by your personal growth. You have become sophisticated, cultured, persuasive. It feels like an eternity since you were just a patient at Academy's asylum...{NEWLINE}And it was indeed over two years ago. You've wasted so much time! You feel an intense sense of forebodding.{NEWLINE}[-500 Infamy, +25 Culture]"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_1", "TERROR HACK"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_1_DESCRIPTION", "We have so much money we can't really protect it well. Our networks were hacked, and a huge amount of funds went missing. We suspect the Sky Ninjas.{NEWLINE}[-$1.25M]"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_2", "TERROR HACK"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_2_DESCRIPTION", "We have so much money we can't really protect it well. Our networks were hacked, and a huge amount of funds went missing. We suspect the Sky Ninjas.{NEWLINE}[-$10M]"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_3", "TERROR HACK"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_3_DESCRIPTION", "We have so much money we can't really protect it well. Our networks were hacked, and a huge amount of funds went missing. We suspect the Sky Ninjas.{NEWLINE}[-$50M]"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_4", "TERROR HACK"},
		{"STR_TERROR_HACK_4_DESCRIPTION", "We have so much money we can't really protect it well. Our networks were hacked, and a huge amount of funds went missing. We suspect the Sky Ninjas.{NEWLINE}[-$250M]"},
		{"STR_CURSE_OF_DOLLAR", "Curse of Dolaro"},
		{"STR_CURSE_OF_DOLLAR_DESCRIPTION", "Our money reserves have mysteriously shrunk by $1M! Nobody knows the real reason, but old Black Market merchants are saying that we have angered Dollar the Almighty by hoarding it."},
		{"STR_GOLD_TRADE", "Gold Trade"},
		{"STR_GOLD_TRADE_DESCRIPTION", "You have spotted an opportunity to buy gold at a discount. Considering your overall financial situation, you decided to go for it - after all, it's the only sure way to keep your wealth safe!{NEWLINE}[-$3M, +100 Gold Bars]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_HEROIC", "Heroic Speech"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_HEROIC_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You're an unquestioned hero of the Revolution. The revolutionary passion of your followers is now unbreakable, and your enemies shake in fear.{NEWLINE}[+3 Recruits, +500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_GOOD", "Great Speech"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You gave a great speech, filling your followers with revolutionary fervour! They are willing to fight to the death!{NEWLINE}[+1 Recruit, +200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_NORMAL", "Revolutionary Speech"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_NORMAL_DESCRIPTION", "You gave a speech in which you explained to your followers why the revolution is necessary and how its victory is inevitable.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_THEBES", "Diplomatic Speech"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_THEBES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your revolutionary speech has convinced the Theban Hive to send you three Assault Clones as reinfocements. This has caused some diplomatic tensions with other Govts.{NEWLINE}[-150 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_DONATIONS", "Fundraising Speech"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_DONATIONS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Revolution can't go on faith alone! You've appealed to your followers for donations to aid political prisoners. Especially you, you're basically a prisoner yourself, a prisoner of love to people's cause!{NEWLINE}[+$200k]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_DIFFERENCES", "People's Speech"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_SPEECH_DIFFERENCES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today's speech was a free discussion. It was a disaster, since everyone had a different idea on what the whole Revolution is really about. Now everyone is angry at each other, and most of all, at you, for your attempts to moderate the event.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_REINFORCEMENTS", "Revolutionary Reinforcements"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_REINFORCEMENTS_2", "Revolutionary Reinforcements"},
		{"STR_REVOLUTIONARY_REINFORCEMENTS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}New volunteers for our glorious cause have arrived!"},
		{"STR_RED_REV_EVENT", "Red Or Not"},
		{"STR_RED_REV_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Revolution supports OUR revolution, even though they don't have much idea what it is about! In any case, due to our Hideout's presence there, we've managed to get them to transfer some of their political prisoners to us."},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_HOARD", "Dragon's Hoard"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_FEAR", "Dragon Fear"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_SLAVES", "Dragon Hypnosis"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_NAGGING_FEELING", "Dragon Paranoia"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_HOARD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You feel irresistible compulsion to compliment the Lizardman Statue with other valuables. It just looks so much better when surrounded by a pile of gold and jewels. Whatever the price.{NEWLINE}[-$400k, +12 Jewelry]"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_FEAR_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Lizardman Statue displayed in your Hideout emits an aura of evil power. This makes yourself perceived as powerful, too.{NEWLINE}[+150 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_SLAVES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Some of the people who visit your Hideout feel compelled to approach the Lizard Statue and just stand there, transfixed by its mesmerizing aura. In this state, they did not resist at all when you nicely asked them to stip naked and sell their souls. You're feeling no regrets, they should've learned to say 'no'.{NEWLINE}[Slaves and Credit Chips gained]"},
		{"STR_LIZARDMAN_STATUE_EVENT_NAGGING_FEELING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You've got a nagging feeling that keeping the Lizardman Statue in your possession might be turning away some of those who'd otherwise help you..."},
		{"STR_POLYMAKH_SHAPKA_EVENT_RECRUIT", "The Allure of Polymakh's Cap"},
		{"STR_POLYMAKH_SHAPKA_EVENT_FAME", "The Allure of Polymakh's Cap"},
		{"STR_POLYMAKH_SHAPKA_EVENT_GOLD", "The Allure of Polymakh's Cap"},
		{"STR_POLYMAKH_SHAPKA_EVENT_RECRUIT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The legendary power of the Cap seduced some lunatic to join our cause."},
		{"STR_POLYMAKH_SHAPKA_EVENT_FAME_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The tales of the Cap being in our possession spread awe amongst those in the know.{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_POLYMAKH_SHAPKA_EVENT_GOLD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In recognition of our rule, local leaders have paid us taxes.{NEWLINE}[+10 Gold Bars]"},
		{"STR_MUTANT_COMPLAINT_REMINDER", "Capitatory Tax"},
		{"STR_MUTANT_COMPLAINT_REMINDER_DESCRIPTION", "From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Be reminded that no matter whom you think you are, it's the Alliance's support what makes your operations possible. Therefore, any greviances about your activities that hurt the mutant community must be settled with us. Financially."},
		{"STR_ABSENCE_OF_APPLES", "Absence of Apples"},
		{"STR_ABSENCE_OF_APPLES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}For someone, it would be a name of a punk band. For you, it is a great longing that cannot be slaked, a hole in your soul that cannot be filled. But the suffering supposedly enriches your soul.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy, +3 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_RAGS_FOR_FREAKS", "Rags For Freaks"},
		{"STR_RAGS_FOR_FREAKS_DESCRIPTION", "Honestly, how hard it is to find some DIRTY RAGS? With considerable effort, you've managed to convince a Freak Gal you hold in the prison that your old coat is dirty enough for her tastes.{NEWLINE}[+5 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SHADOW_OF_THE_COMET", "Shadow Of The Comet"},
		{"STR_SHADOW_OF_THE_COMET_DESCRIPTION", "A comet was sighted in the sky, rousing anxiety about what the upcoming year 2602 will bring. Many believe a major change is coming. Some influential figures see you as an agent of that change, and they decided to back you up, just in case.{NEWLINE}[+400 Infamy, +$200k]"},
		{"STR_A_LEAFLET", "Dusty Letter"},
		{"STR_A_LEAFLET_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}A mysterious letter has arrived at our Hideout. It contains some sort of a leaflet."},
		{"STR_SLAVE_CAUGHT_EVENT", "Travelling Maiden"},
		{"STR_SLAVE_CAUGHT_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You spotted a beautiful, wealthy and completely clueless maiden travelling near your hideout. Time to give her a private lesson about piracy!{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +$15,000]"},
		{"STR_WANTED_POSTER", "Wanted!"},
		{"STR_WANTED_POSTER_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}One crewmember brought you a poster she found hanging on some fence outside. The writings on it do not make much sense to you, but the woman depicted there reminds you of yourself! (At least if you squint hard enough.) You're famous! And this surely must be work of someone who is looking for you!{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_INTREPID_BRAINERS", "Intrepid Brainers"},
		{"STR_INTREPID_BRAINERS_DESCRIPTION", "Communication is always a two-way street. The techniques developed for inducting Castaways into Brainers have also made Brainers less shut-in. They've recently mounted an exploratory expedition into some old ruins and brought several valuable findings home."},
		{"STR_LAB_ACCIDENT", "Lab Accident"},
		{"STR_LAB_ACCIDENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}There was an explosion at your lab, which destroyed a lot of valuable equipment. But it wasn't completely in vain! Progress Before Safety!{NEWLINE}[-$250k, Random Item Gained]"},
		{"STR_TERROR_VACCUI", "Terror Vaccui"},
		{"STR_TERROR_VACCUI_DESCRIPTION", "You use your Astrosensorium to look into the Abyss... and it stares back. Existential fear spreads amongst the crew.{NEWLINE}[-333 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_OUTBREAK", "Fungus Outbreak"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_OUTBREAK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout has been infested by fungus! We must either burn it to the ground, which will cost us lots of money ($500k), or learn to live with it and only stop it from spreading too much ($25k monthly). I believe a Genius like you will find some use of it, Cap'n!"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_OUTBREAK_NORED", "Fungus Outbreak"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_OUTBREAK_NORED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout has been infested by fungus! We must either burn it to the ground, which will cost us lots of money ($500k), or learn to live with it and only stop it from spreading too much ($25k monthly). You might not be the tidiest person around, but it was surely not your fault, Cap'n!"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_OUTBREAK_GROWTH", "Fungus Growth"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_OUTBREAK_GROWTH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Fungus grows bigger!"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_HARVEST", "Fungus Harvest"},
		{"STR_FUNGUS_HARVEST_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Some of the fungi that infest our Hideout can be useful for something. We have harvested them."},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_30K", "Taxman Visit"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_30K_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy bonus income last month exceeded $10M, which prompted the Govts to incur a tax to the tune of $3M. However, there are indirect advantages of being a taxpayer...{NEWLINE}[Gained a Minor Land Deed and 10 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_45K", "Taxman Visit"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_45K_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy bonus income last month exceeded $15M, which prompted the Govts to incur a tax to the tune of $5M. However, there are indirect advantages of being a taxpayer...{NEWLINE}[Gained a Minor Land Deed and 15 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_60K", "Taxman Visit"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_60K_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy bonus income last month exceeded $20M, which prompted the Govts to incur a tax to the tune of $8M. However, there are indirect advantages of being a taxpayer...{NEWLINE}[Gained a Minor Land Deed and 20 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_75K", "Taxman Visit"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_75K_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy bonus income last month exceeded $25M, which prompted the Govts to incur a tax to the tune of $12M. However, there are indirect advantages of being a taxpayer...{NEWLINE}[Gained a Minor Land Deed and 25 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_90K", "Taxman Visit"},
		{"STR_TAXMAN_90K_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy bonus income last month exceeded $30M, which prompted the Govts to incur a tax to the tune of $17.5M. However, there are indirect advantages of being a taxpayer...{NEWLINE}[Gained a Minor Land Deed and 30 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_UNBELIEVEABLE_SCORE", "The Price of Success"},
		{"STR_UNBELIEVEABLE_SCORE2", "The Price of Success"},
		{"STR_UNBELIEVEABLE_SCORE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy gains last month were so great it beggars belief. The Govts become very suspicious... Expect them to be much less forthcoming with support the next month."},
		{"STR_SUPERIOR_BEINGS", "Superior Beings"},
		{"STR_SUPERIOR_BEINGS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We, as Gals, are proud of our perfection and its every aspect. Some people revere us as demigods, as they should. But most are upset about what they see as our supreme arrogance.{NEWLINE}[-250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CULT_STATUS", "Cult Status"},
		{"STR_CULT_STATUS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We, as Gals, are proud of our perfection and its every aspect. Some people revere us as demigods, as they should, and pay us due tribute.{NEWLINE}[+100,000$]"},
		{"STR_LOOSE_LIPS", "Loose Lips Sink Ships"},
		{"STR_LOOSE_LIPS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We stand by our decision to allows males into our ranks on a regular basis, but we must face the facts: gender mixing leads to Gals spending more time on romancing and they're less focused on their work. We already had some minor accidents and cases of major negligence.{NEWLINE}[-$100,000, +3 Zines]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Some fool infiltrated the Hideout in an attempt on your life. Your gals, however, are never unarmed and they scrubbed the floor with that bitch. And there went your new carpet. And the walls need to be fixed, too...{NEWLINE}Predictably, the corpse has nothing to say about who sent her. We only got her tools.{NEWLINE}[-$5000]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_NINJA", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_NINJA_DESCRIPTION", "A Sky Ninja infiltrated the Hideout in an attempt on your life. Your gals, however, are always ready for trouble and they managed to find that bitch and knock her out cold, before she could carry out her odious task.{NEWLINE}[Got a Ninja Warrior]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_PRO", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_PRO_DESCRIPTION", "You were targeted by a professional assassin! Luckily, she wasn't able to complete her odious task and bailed, but if you were less lucky... You don't dare to think about it.{NEWLINE}[-300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_BOMB", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_BOMB_DESCRIPTION", "Somebody planted a bomb to kill you! However, you were late in your daily schedule and the bomb exploded before you arrived. It only caused some damage to the Hideout...{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy, -$100k]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_POISON", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_POISON_DESCRIPTION", "You were poisoned! This sucks... At least some of this chocolate is still edible, hmmm...{NEWLINE}[-200 Infamy, +3 Chocolate (possibly poisoned)]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_SNIPER", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_SNIPER_DESCRIPTION", "You were taking a stroll outside the Hideout, when a bullet whizzed past your head! Maybe it's better to always stay indoors...?{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_NUKE", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_NUKE_DESCRIPTION", "Somebody set us up a bomb! What? It was a nuclear bomb, and it would take you out alongside a good chunk of the Hideout, if not for the vigilant Runts and their Geiger counters!{NEWLINE}[Gained Barrel of Nuke]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_HITMAN", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_HITMAN_DESCRIPTION", "You were targeted by a hitman, however your crew managed to apprehend him before he could approach you. Turns out he carried a strange weapon, custom-built for this mission."},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_DUEL", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_DUEL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You were challenged to a duel by one of your Gals! It was the dumbest one, apparently, so you only gave her some spanking. That was good exercise!{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_DRONE", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_DRONE_DESCRIPTION", "When you were strolling around your Hideout, a sudden explosion threw you on the ground, and rocks started to fall from the ceiling. Later investigation has show that someone used a drone strike against you, but, luckily, they underestimated the thickness of your roof.{NEWLINE}[-$50k damages]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_OMINOUS", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_OMINOUS_DESCRIPTION", "Your Gals reported a suspicious individual hiding in the wilderness near your base for the past few days. They failed to catch him, but you are convinced he was looking to assassinate you. But what for?!{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_SOREASS", "Assassination Attempt!"},
		{"STR_ASSASSINATION_ATTEMPT_SOREASS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}There was a plot to assassinate you, but, being a Headstrong Captain, you're constantly on guard and the attempt was foiled.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_RITSUKO_DRINKING_DEFAULT", "Drinking Night"},
		{"STR_RITSUKO_DRINKING_DEFAULT_DESCRIPTION", "You were drinking hard with your Favorite Best Brainer (FBB), exchanging your various woes, comments on the sourness of life, and philosophical opinions. You feel like your burdens were lessened a bit, and you developed a better understanding of each other. You also feel like your head is going to explode. Damn, she can drink a lot...{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SAYA_VS_GDX", "Saya Disses Gudrun"},
		{"STR_SAYA_VS_GDX_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Saya was visibly angry and emotional today. She confronted you and forced you to listen to her:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'I cannot believe my own eyes, on how you're... you're... cozying up to that bitch! She's an elitist and authoritarian, who has caused much suffering to the mutantkind! Associating yourself with such a criminal does not paint you in a good light. I'd get rid of her if I were you.'{NEWLINE}[-200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SAYA_VS_GDX_LADY", "Saya Doubts Gudrun"},
		{"STR_SAYA_VS_GDX_LADY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Your marriage with Dr. X is now a fact, and Saya can't do anything about it. Still, she has her misgivings.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'I understand it was a political decision. I hope your dream of building bridges between Purebloods and Mutants has any chance of succeeding, but I remain unconvinced. The Alliance doesn't trust her either.'{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DATING_RITSUKO", "Dating FBB"},
		{"STR_DATING_RITSUKO_DESCRIPTION", "While drinking with the FBB, you started discussing gravity physics. As the gravity pulled you close, you moved on to temperature increase with pressure and friction, and a long time later, ended with the heat death of the universe...{NEWLINE}[+70 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DATING_RITSUKO_UFOPEDIA", "It kind of happened..."},
		{"STR_DATING_SAYA", "Dating Saya"},
		{"STR_DATING_SAYA_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You have taken Saya to an exotic location, where you busied yourselves with the usual stuff two adult women of your stature would do for fun: sightseeing, physical exercise, shopping, eating ice cream, brawling, lazing about with a glass of alcohol in hand, to finally talk the evening away in a luxurious sleeping room - in a hotel, on a boat, on a plane. Naturally, all bills are on you. It's not like you lack funds!{NEWLINE}[-$30,000]"},
		{"STR_DATING_SAYA_UFOPEDIA", "Your continuously successful work for the Mutant Alliance has made Saya more and more begrudged - until she unexpectedly accepted your invitation into hot springs. There she presented you her secret martial arts - she literally made a believable illusion of a dragon appear out of water vapour. Then she said: 'I think I didn't treat you fairly. Despite how much you have helped the Alliance... I was biased. You see, I used to be a Sky Ninja. This is their secret technique. Then... I lost my whole clan and decided to join the Alliance... Maybe to repent for what I have done as a Sky Ninja. They might support the Alliance, but they don't really care about the weakest of us. Let's meet again sometime, I might have a rant or two about them...'"},
		{"STR_WASTELAND_SORCERESS", "Wasteland Sorceress"},
		{"STR_WASTELAND_SORCERESS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}The gals have caught a travelling woman, wearing some very fancy looking robes. Realizing she is cornered, she willingly gave up her possessions. She only asked to keep her magical diadem, a conduit to her powers, and offered to tell you the future in exchange. And thus, now she is awaiting in your chambers..."},
		{"STR_WASTELAND_SORCERESS_UFOPEDIA", "Once you were alone, the sorceress fixed her gaze on you, and you found yourself paralyzed by some implacable force. 'I know your destiny,' she was saying, moving closer and closer. 'There are four princesses looking for you, but only one of them really knows who you are. The other three are The Mage, The Witch and The Doll. One of the three will see you as a Bounty Hunter in the Magic Shoppe; another as a Demon Slayer, but only if you visit the Cellar of Rats first. The last one, unless she grows up, will see you as a threat to the metal kingdom she was created to protect. You're an accursed creature... darling'. By the time you woke up, the sorceress was nowhere to be found. Her loot, though, should be secure... [-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ARCH_WITCHES_COVEN", "The Coven of Arch-Witches"},
		{"STR_ARCH_WITCHES_COVEN_UFOPEDIA", "They are the secret masters of the 5 Elemental Magics and they became interested in you. What they plan for you? Would anyone trust a mage?"},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES", "2 Girls 1 Panties"},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES_CONTINUED", "She-Devil"},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES_GRAY", "Call She-Devil Back!"},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES_UFOPEDIA", "There is a strange pattern appearing across many of the best erotic stories of Zany Zines; a couple of mysterious women who look very much like some sort of V.I.Ps. Who are they exactly, and why would people of high standing behave... in such ways? We were unable to determine that yet, but we will keep trying. Indeed we will!{NEWLINE}[+1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES_CONTINUED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Everything goes red, as an image of a demonic woman forms in your mind. She smiles queerily and speaks:{NEWLINE}'...Confused? I'm used to that. You did well, finding the trails which me and my... friend have left for you in all this erotica. 2 girls 1 panties? That was fun. You are progressing as the Shadowmasters have foreseen, and we, the Witches of the Coven, can help you along the way. If you have what it takes. Keep growing, little one... I will be watching you...'{NEWLINE}[+1 Zine, +10 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES_CONTINUED_UFOPEDIA", "While you have seen her across erotic Zines in many forms and shapes, that face and queer smile always belonged to the pantless, self-described Witch who invaded your mind. Her usual, pink-haired companion must then be a Witch too. Both powerful enough to do as they please and remain elusive. Perhaps we can find out more if we socialize with the right kind of people..."},
		{"STR_2_GIRLS_1_PANTIES_GRAY_UFOPEDIA", "'You again? Seriously, a telepathic call? Gods, those Devious Queens are always so inquisitive. Couldn't you be a Red Queen and happily chopping off some heads? No, it's questions, suggestions! You want me to get mad or what? If you want to be in total control, create your own freaking world, you know? OK, will you fuck off if I give you clues to Phantom Bolts? No, OF COURSE not. But I'm tied by the rules too. You're a Devious Queen so I'm obliged to answer some questions. Yes, yes, you want to talk, let's talk. Next thing I know, you'll be stalking me on social media... At least grab me a pack of cigs while you're at it, you dummy...'"},
		{"STR_POPULAR_HERO", "Hero of the Masses"},
		{"STR_POPULAR_HERO_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}People at the taverns all over the world are drinking to you! You've gained sudden popularity amongst the masses!{NEWLINE}[+400 Infamy, +25 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_KOKORO_VISIT", "Love Crusader"},
		{"STR_KOKORO_VISIT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The mysterious Meymey, the lesbian Knight of Love, barged into your Hideout, looking for any princesses to save. In the string of events that followed, you misplaced her armor somewhere, but she said 'Don't worry dear, I happen to find these quite often' and continued on her merry way.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_EARTHQUAKE", "Earthquake!"},
		{"STR_EARTHQUAKE_DESCRIPTION", "The ground shook mightily today, Cap'n! Our facilities sustained $175,000 in damages, and piles of rocks are laying everywhere! I am sure, however, that such a Genius as you can turn this catastrophe into a blessing!"},
		{"STR_EARTHQUAKE_SOREASS", "Earthquake!"},
		{"STR_EARTHQUAKE_SOREASS_DESCRIPTION", "The ground shook mightily today, Cap'n! Piles of rocks are laying everywhere. Our facilities, however, sustained only $50,000 in damages, thanks to your preparations as a Headstrong Captain."},
		{"STR_COUGH_COUGH", "Cough, Cough"},
		{"STR_COUGH_COUGH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Bad news, Cap'n. Our crew is plagued by a disease. Improving our medical knowledge will make such issues less frequent in the future.{NEWLINE}[-150 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_COUGH_COUGH_GREEN", "Cough, Cough"},
		{"STR_COUGH_COUGH_GREEN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout has been plagued by an epidemic. However, due to our knowledge of Green Codex ways, this was merely an inconvenience. We even managed to produce some medicines from all the phlegm.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy, +9 Medical Supplies]"},
		{"STR_SUPREME_BEING", "Supreme Being"},
		{"STR_SUPREME_BEING_DESCRIPTION", "Your computer network was attacked by a very vicious virus, calling itself some sort of 'supreme something'. We didn't know what to do, so before we finally managed to delete it, it caused an awful lot of damage.{NEWLINE}[-$75,000]"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_ON_FIRE", "Hideout On Fire!"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_ON_FIRE_DESCRIPTION", "A fire of unknown origin has erupted in our Hideout! We managed to defeat it, but not before about $125k of stuff was turned to so much ashes. Could this be an enemy attack? Sabotage? Simple negligence? Only a Veteran like you could know, Cap'n!"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_ON_FIRE_NORED", "Hideout On Fire!"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_ON_FIRE_NORED_DESCRIPTION", "A fire of unknown origin has erupted in our Hideout! We managed to defeat it, but not before about $125k of stuff was turned to so much ashes. Could this be an enemy attack? Sabotage? Simple negligence? It surely couldn't be that you were playing with fire, Capt'n!"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_ON_FIRE_SOREASS", "Hideout On Fire!"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_ON_FIRE_SOREASS_DESCRIPTION", "A fire of unknown origin has erupted in our Hideout! However, a Headstrong Captain like you is prepared for any emergency, and the damage was limited to $50k."},
		{"STR_ROBOTIC_SPIDERS", "Robotic Spiders"},
		{"STR_ROBOTIC_SPIDERS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}They came out of nowhere, or straight from a nightmare! By the time our squad got there, they were gone. Several locals went missing, and our power lines were cut. Valuable materiel of all sorts was stolen. Wild panic is spreading. Only Jack Sparrow himself could have predicted such a calamity, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[-$200k, -400 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ROBOTIC_SPIDERS_UFOPEDIA", "These mechanical horrors can literally appear from the ground to perform whatever task their unknown masters desire them to, usually sabotage or kidnappings. Since Robo Spiders only attack defenseless targets and work really fast, hunting them down seems hopeless. Really, no one can feel safe with such things around."},
		{"STR_CREW_GRUBBY", "Angry Noises"},
		{"STR_CREW_GRUBBY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The crew have been feeling rather grubby today, they rant about your performance not being optimal enough since you've ended the last month with 'too large cash surplus'. You needed to shell out $150k for various 'optimizations', yet they still remain unsatisfied.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_REASON_ATAC", "Attack of Common Sense"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_REASON_ATAC_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today you said something wise and reasonable. The crew was very surprised; some are even worried about you due to this unusual event.{NEWLINE}[+20 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_2_DUMB_2_DIE", "Too Dumb To Die"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_2_DUMB_2_DIE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your last month's Infamy was in the negative, but you have issues fearing such abstract things. It's not like a Chupacabra attacked you in your toilet... The crew is somehow very impressed with your calmness.{NEWLINE}[+80 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_REFORMS", "No-Sugar-Month"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_REFORMS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In the light of the dire financial situation at the end of last month, you've decided to start spending less money on luxuries until the situation improves.{NEWLINE}[+$80,000]"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_FAUX_PASS", "Faux Pas"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_FAUX_PASS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy is pretty high and you got invited to a diplomatic meeting with some Government people. It was a big mistake on their part to ask you what you think, because you've honestly told them what you think.{NEWLINE}[-200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_STUPIDITY", "Stupidity"},
		{"STR_SLOWPOKE_STUPIDITY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Someone called you stupid. Being pig-headed as you are, you don't care.{NEWLINE}[+10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_MOPPING", "Hardworking Captain"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_MOPPING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}To promote hygiene and personal discipline, you decide to lead by example and clean all Hideout corridors with a mop. Gals are mostly indifferent, but Runts seem to really appreciate the gesture and are happy to focus on other things.{NEWLINE}[$250, +10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_PAPERWORK", "Hardworking Captain"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_PAPERWORK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}There is a lot of paperwork waiting, so you sit down and do your paperwork. It's not fun, but has to be done, and isn't even so bad once you get into it. You manage to finish before morning, seriously impressing those who know how much there was.{NEWLINE}[+$30,000, +10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_BEST_BARGAIN", "Best Bargain"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_BEST_BARGAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Visiting Jackstown, you decide to try and haggle with shopkeepers a little harder than usual. After a few hours, they pool their resources and pay you $5,000 to 'please, please go somewhere else', as their overall sales suffer greatly from your constant nagging."},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_COLLECT_AND_RECYCLE", "Collect & Recycle"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_COLLECT_AND_RECYCLE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}As a firm enemy of wastage, you order your crew to collect any useless pieces of metal for recycling. The gals complain a lot, but they still do what must be done.{NEWLINE}[-10 Infamy, +25 Scrap Metal]"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_HOP_AND_MOP", "Hop & Mop"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_HOP_AND_MOP_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}As Cap'n who always wants her crew in top condition, you order them to mop up the entire Hideout, generously spurring them into action with your booming voice. This will teach them to never relax!{NEWLINE}[-20 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_FINE_PRINT", "Fine Print"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_FINE_PRINT_DESCRIPTION", "While poring over your agreements with the Local Govts, you notice a clause which makes you eligible for some investment returns. You file a formal request to send you some dough to cover your operational costs in their area. The Govt in question seems a little annoyed, but accepts your claims as valid.{NEWLINE}[+$50k, -5 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_AIRHEAD_STUPIDITY", "Stupidity"},
		{"STR_AIRHEAD_STUPIDITY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In a quarrel, you've come one witty riposte too short. Now everyone must be thinking you're stupid!!! You cannot get over it.{NEWLINE}[-40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_GRACEFUL_STEAMROLL", "Know When to Hold 'Em"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_GRACEFUL_STEAMROLL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your crew invited you over for a game of cards. You eagerly agreed, and thoroughly trashed them with your superior intellect, bravery and luck. Now they look up to you even more!{NEWLINE}[+$10,000, +10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_STARGAZING", "Stargazing"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_STARGAZING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You wake up in the middle of the night, leave your room and the Hideout, and climb atop nearest hill to watch the stars. The sight fills you with intense yearning to experience and conquer it all.{NEWLINE}[+40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_BATTLE_OF_WITS", "Battle of Wits"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_BATTLE_OF_WITS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}One smartass from your crew asked you a trick question to make fun of you, but your uncanny response made her look like a tool. Much laugh was had.{NEWLINE}[+10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_LEWD_MOOD_THERAPY", "Lewd Mood"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_LEWD_MOOD_THERAPY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Overcome with erotic fantasies, you cannot focus today, so you decide to ask your FBB for help. She tells you to lie down on the couch and starts asking you rather intimate questions regarding your sexuality, fantasies and experiences. Once satisfied, she produces a Ball Bat from behind the couch and socks you right in the head! A few bonks later, she declares you 'not horny' and sends you over to the Sick Bay.{NEWLINE}[-15 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_LEWD_MOOD_COUNSELING", "Lewd Mood"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_LEWD_MOOD_COUNSELING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Overcome with erotic fantasies, you cannot focus today, so you decide to ask your FBB for help. She tells you to lie down on the couch and starts asking you rather intimate questions regarding your sexuality, fantasies and experiences. Stuff that neither of you is supposed to discuss with other people ensues.{NEWLINE}[+65 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_LEWD_MOOD_CREATIVE", "Lewd Mood"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_LEWD_MOOD_CREATIVE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Overcome with erotic fantasies, you are desperate to give them a creative outlet! After a few hours of work, you are ready to present your opus to the ever-hungry public around the Hideout. You are giddy with anticipation: what will their reactions be? Will there be... stuff happening...?{NEWLINE}[+10 Infamy, +2 Zines]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_SWEET_DREAMS", "Sweet Dreams"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_SWEET_DREAMS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You've been having particularly nice dreams lately, vivid and complex, with interesting characters and engaging stories. Every morning you feel not only rejuvenated, but also inspired! Your crew is impressed with your positive disposition and unusually profound insight.{NEWLINE}[+$5,000, +30 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_BEST_BARGAIN", "Best Bargain"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_BEST_BARGAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Visiting Jackstown, you decide to try and haggle with the shopkeeper a little harder than usual. However, you meet your match and spend the next several hours arguing about the goods' quality. In the end you manage to lower the price only a little, but the shopkeeper gives you a free drink for your company. What a lonely, yet kind person!{NEWLINE}[+$500, +10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_MAN_OF_THE_CLOTH", "Man Of The Cloth"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_OF_THE_CLOTH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you encounter a wandering priest of Eris. He seems kinda shifty to you, so, following the advice of your inner Inquisitor, you tie him up and interrogate him. Turns out he was only pretending to be a priest to con gullible people. Real cultists, who hate competition, seem pretty happy with your actions. Yet another sign of your total intellectual superiority!{NEWLINE}[+75 Infamy, +1 Jewelry, +1 Heroes' Blessings]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_ALL_IS_ONE", "All Is One"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_ALL_IS_ONE_DESCRIPTION", "You dream of a puzzle box, made of rotating parts which interconnect and bind to one another in complex ways. You are absolutely sure that the puzzle box is directly linked to the Universe, and you can almost discern some galaxy clusters within it... The inside being outside and the idea of potential total control over reality overwhelm you completely. You wake up confused and exhilarated, but you also gain a new perspective that you must share with the crew...{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, +5 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_AT_SEANS_RABID_FANS", "At Sean's"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_AT_SEANS_RABID_FANS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your usual trips to your favorite pub, you bumped into an avid fan of yours, who was so entranced with your personality that they refused to leave your side, no matter what. Being so agreeable, you offered to take them with you. The crew however has doubts about the sincerity of this unusual companion."},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN", "Hardworking Captain"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Anxious for some productive activity, you head down to the workshops to give your Runts a hand. After you press some button - clearly mislabeled! - the machine you work on starts whirring and smoking, and a small explosion follows. Runts don't even show any remorse and actually have the nerve to blame you! That's it, you will never offer your help again! Never, ever!{NEWLINE}[-$25,000, -50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_CARING_CAPTAIN", "Caring Captain"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_CARING_CAPTAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Feeling generous, you decide to help out in the infirmary. You spend the day tending to your beautiful, brave, cute and at the moment endearingly harmless crew members. You work hard to cheer them up with your sexy figure and tend to all their needs with your high-level body expertise. You think you'll have very interesting dreams after this...{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, +1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_EROTIC_ADVENTURE", "Erotic Adventure"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_EROTIC_ADVENTURE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today in the cafeteria, you lewded the chief Runt a little, leaving her confused and flustered. Everyone in the Hideout liked that.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_MOVIE_NIGHT", "Movie Night!"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_MOVIE_NIGHT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}There's no better way to relax than chill with your friends over a decent movie, so you organize a movie marathon in the mess hall. For the main course, you choose the classic 'Steel Mountain of Fire' trilogy (director's cut). It takes a whole night and then some to finish this, and Gals fall asleep one after another, but you aren't sleepy at all. How could you sleep through such splendid entertainment?! Best movie night ever!{NEWLINE}[+40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_MUSIC_NIGHT", "Music Night!"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_MUSIC_NIGHT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In order to raise morale, you hire a friendly music band to give a concert in the hangars. The event is a spectacular success, and nothing bad happens!{NEWLINE}[-$10,000, +100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_SEDUCTION", "Seduction"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_SEDUCTION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You were acting very sexy today, yet nobody bothered to seduce you! What a disappointing band of lazy bastards!{NEWLINE}[-30 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_SEDUCTION_RITSUKO", "Seduction"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_SEDUCTION_RITSUKO_DESCRIPTION", "Being lewd as you are, you've inevitably ended in one bed with your FBB. The experience was very good, the subsequent awkwardness less so.{NEWLINE}[+60 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_LOVE_IS_STRONGER", "Love Is Stronger Than Death"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_LOVE_IS_STRONGER_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You dream of your lost comrades, cheering for you from beyond the veil. You wake up wistful, but also energized.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, +5 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_SEDUCTION", "Seduction"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_SEDUCTION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You've succeeded at yet another romantic conquest! Your charm is irresistible!{NEWLINE}[+3 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_PAINT_MY_WORLD", "Paint My World"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_PAINT_MY_WORLD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Feeling a sudden spark of inspiration, you grab some cans of paint and cover a wall in your Hideout with kickass graffiti! Gals appreciate the rich colors and your rebel spirit, which is good for morale (and your ego).{NEWLINE}[+40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_NAKED_PARTY", "Know When to Hold 'Em"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_NAKED_PARTY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a card game, you managed to take everything off your opponents' hands. And yes, that means everything... The ensuing party got so wild that nobody even complained.{NEWLINE}[+$15,000, +2 Zines]"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_LEWD_MOOD_HURTY", "Lewd Mood"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_LEWD_MOOD_HURTY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Overcome with erotic fantasies, you try to molest some Gals in the mess hall. Now your face is all hurty.{NEWLINE}[-20 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_YOURS_TO_COMMAND", "Yours to Command"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_YOURS_TO_COMMAND_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You dream of sitting on a gigantic throne in some alien place called the Galactic Nexus. From its impossible height, you overlook your eternal domain, and the power of the Ancients is within your arm's reach. You are completely naked, and everyone in the Galaxy is looking right at you... You wake up embarrassed, ecstatic and pretty horny all at once.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, +5 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_AIRHEAD_ART", "Art Inspiration!"},
		{"STR_AIRHEAD_ART_DESCRIPTION", "You've written your own book! You have no idea what it is about, but you're an artist, not a critic!"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_BLESSINGS", "Popularity!"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_BLESSINGS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You seem to be loved by the mutant masess, although you're not sure why. They're dedicating prayers to Purple Bloom in your intention!{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +9 Heroes' Blessings]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_PIRATEZ", "No Clothes Day!"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_PIRATEZ_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Arr, Lewd Captain!{NEWLINE}As your faithful Lewd Pirates, we came up with an idea to have No Clothes Day! You are of course required to participate!{NEWLINE}[Crew Bonding: +90 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_DONATION", "No Donation, No Salvation!"},
		{"STR_DUMBLAZY_DONATION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Understanding the needs of religious capitalism, you donate a sizeable sum of $20k to the Cult of Eris.{NEWLINE}[+1 Glamour, +1 Heroes' Blessings]"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_PIRATEZ", "Literature Club!"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_PIRATEZ_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Arr, Smart Captain!{NEWLINE}As your faithful Smart Pirates, we came up with an idea to organize a Literature Club! You are of course required to participate!{NEWLINE}[+1 Grrrl Guide, +5 Zines, +5 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_PIRATEZ", "Fireworks!"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_PIRATEZ_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Arr, Scary Captain!{NEWLINE}As your faithful Scary Pirates, we came up with an idea to scare the locals by organizing festivities in honor of The Destroyer! And that means launching fireworks and shooting our guns in the air all night long!!!{NEWLINE}[-$25k, +220 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_PIRATEZ", "Adventuring!"},
		{"STR_JACKDUMB_PIRATEZ_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Arr, Adventurous Captain!{NEWLINE}As your faithful Adventurous Pirates, we came up with an idea to organize a search party and check out our surroundings for any treasure!{NEWLINE}[-$10k, +1 Journey Notes, Random Treasure]"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_PIRATEZ", "Dare To Dream!"},
		{"STR_JACKLAZY_PIRATEZ_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Arr, Progressive Captain!{NEWLINE}As your faithful Progressive Pirates, we decided to brainstorm on how to be even more progressive! No dream is too small or too big to pursue it!{NEWLINE}(Yes, it ended in a quarrel.){NEWLINE}[+1 Mad Scribblings, +3 Glamour, +3 Zines, -70 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_PIRATEZ", "Tax Collected!"},
		{"STR_SOREDUMB_PIRATEZ_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Arr, Hard Captain!{NEWLINE}As your faithful Hard Pirates, we came up with an idea to collect some taxes from the local peasants! Surprisingly, they didn't even protest!{NEWLINE}[+$70k]"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_GUN_RESEARCH", "Weapon Lore"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_GUN_RESEARCH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}While reading some books, as you often do, you learned about a new type of weapon...{NEWLINE}[+10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_WELCOME_TO_HELL", "Welcome To Hell"},
		{"STR_WELCOME_TO_HELL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You feel the reality bend, as a vision appears before your eyes. A woman on a dark throne speaks to you in a hollow, monotone voice."},
		{"STR_WELCOME_TO_HELL_UFOPEDIA", "'I am the Black Dragon, the guardian of the Dark Utopia, the wielder of Assured Doom. Challenger! You choose, or have been chosen, to follow the path of Jack Sparrow. The laws of Universe work differently in this reality. All the odds are stacked against you. Enjoy your forlorn struggle, the fire, the blood, the steel. Your first trial will come with Summer, the season of madness, when I lay down in death. Pray that I will judge you worthy when I return next year. Or begone from this world, while you still can.'{NEWLINE}[-666 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME", "It Was Your Choice"},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME_DESCRIPTION", "The whole Hideout is in turmoil. When you enter the bridge, you learn why. Queen-Bee Cleopatra of Thebes herself is calling you. She seems amused... dangerously amused.{NEWLINE}'Look at you, little one. You have opted to seek one of the most hostile timelines, yet you dare to settle in Egypt, on my bosom, to receive my help? Don't you know that being my friend can be fatal?' She chuckles. 'Or maybe you simply like dangerous games? Let's play a game, then,' she says, then she smiles, but her eyes are as cold as a snake's."},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME_EASY", "It Was Your Choice"},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME_EASY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}The whole Hideout is in turmoil. When you enter the bridge, you learn why. Queen-Bee Cleopatra of Thebes herself is calling you. She seems amused... dangerously amused.{NEWLINE}'Did getting the Assault Clones feel like too good to be true? Well, that's because it was. There is a catch.' She chuckles. 'I hope you like dangerous games... because we will be playing one,' she says, then she smiles, but her eyes are as cold as a snake's."},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME_UFOPEDIA", "You have put yourself in Queen Cleopatra's power, and she forced you to play the game of 'red lilly, blue lilly'. To make matters worse, you have apparently picked the red one already by your previous actions. Where does this rabbit hole go? The rules of the game remain a mystery."},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME2", "The Red Lilly Game"},
		{"STR_CLEO_LETS_PLAY_A_GAME2_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Cleopatra calls again.{NEWLINE}'Yes, the unannounced visit you had last month wasn't random. By associating yourself with me, you've become a target to my enemies. You've become the Red Lilly. A bait. While I'm the Blue Lilly, letting them infiltrate my defenses and watching as they expose their spies and secret identities. Good hunting,' She smiles."},
		{"STR_TURAN_THIEVERY", "Turanian Hospitality"},
		{"STR_TURAN_THIEVERY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The weird woman from the vision was not lying! Bad luck is upon you! Your accounts have been drained, and there's that smug message: 'You've been robbed by Turanians. Feel honored'. They surely had some help on the inside...{NEWLINE}[-$500,000]"},
		{"STR_THREAD_OF_PROPHECY", "Threads of Prophecy Severed"},
		{"STR_THREAD_OF_PROPHECY_DESCRIPTION", "As months pass by, you begin to slowly realize that something is not right with the world. Everything seems easier and brighter than you feared it to be. Nobody else seems to be sharing that feeling with you. Is this only a good dream? What dark secrets remain forever hidden from your eye? You decide you're better off not knowing. In time, it even makes you feel better.{NEWLINE}[Cap'n Kid Limits. +50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_ENJOYING_THE_DREAM", "Enjoying the Dream?"},
		{"STR_ENJOYING_THE_DREAM_DESCRIPTION", "Cap'n Kidd, dear Cap'n Kidd... I see you're still living in your never-never-land? I would be the last to criticize, but... While you still can defeat the Solar Governor and became a Space Pirate here, while pounding weak enemies into the ground, the reality is so much more exciting! Unlike myself, not even the Shadows can find you here, and there is so much you won't ever learn. Let's meet there, when you're ready to face the Threads of Prophecy. Me, the Night Witch, I'm your secret fan, you know?{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BLESSINGS", "Blessings"},
		{"STR_BLESSINGS_DESCRIPTION", "A passing Wasteland Priestess offered you her blessings. It is a good omen.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BLESSINGS_2_DESCRIPTION", "The Wasteland Priestess has returned, and she is smiling at you sagely. Looks like she has new things to tell you."},
		{"STR_SIVALINGA_RESURRECTION_EVENT", "Blessings"},
		{"STR_SIVALINGA_RESURRECTION_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "The Wasteland Priestess has returned. 'Looks like you have grown a lot since we've last met. You have learned VooDoo, and you have won more favors of the Bloom Lady. Now you will understand how to use a certain gift of Hers, and I will teach you how...'"},
		{"STR_STARDOM_GIG_GOOD", "The Price of Stardom"},
		{"STR_STARDOM_GIG_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "Your latest gig on stage grossed 5,000,000 dolaros of pure profit. However, many people think you're selling yourself out...{NEWLINE}[-1000 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CHARMY", "Charms"},
		{"STR_CHARMY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You have performed a successful charm offensive against the Govts' representatives, convincing their masters to allocate an extra $150k funding to your cause."},
		{"STR_MORALE_BUSTING_SPEECH", "Morale Busting Speech"},
		{"STR_MORALE_BUSTING_SPEECH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You got so drunk that you started to challenge every Gal, waving your gun around and giving them some incomprehensible speeches in drunkard's drawl. The crew is rather worried about you, and some even speak of it being an ill omen...{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_MORALE_BOOSTING_SPEECH", "Morale Boosting Speech"},
		{"STR_MORALE_BOOSTING_SPEECH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You gave your hearty crew a mighty speech, in which you filled them with fiery fighting spirit and love for plunderin'! Long live the Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_VOLLEYBALL_MATCH", "Volleyball!"},
		{"STR_VOLLEYBALL_MATCH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today, Brainers faced off against Runts in a volleyball game underneath one of our Hangars! Everyone was covered in sludge! Now that's a game where everyone wins, most of all the spectators!{NEWLINE}[+125 Infamy, +3 Zines & Glamour]"},
		{"STR_SNEAKY_NINJAS", "Sneaky Ninjas"},
		{"STR_SNEAKY_NINJAS_DESCRIPTION", "The Sky Ninjas are turning our strength against us! It is difficult to handle as much fame and influence as we have, and they sneakily managed to belittle the value of some of the great achievements we accomplished last month, and have taken credit for some others. They have no shame, nor a honorable bone in their bodies!!!{NEWLINE}[-1000 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NINJA_JETBIKES_SIGHTED", "Ninja Jetbikes"},
		{"STR_NINJA_JETBIKES_SIGHTED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}There were sightings of something called 'Ninja Jetbikes' in the vicinity of our Hideout. They seem to be sending a message to us...{NEWLINE}[-150 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NINJA_OVERFLIGHTS", "Ninja Air Patrols"},
		{"STR_NINJA_OVERFLIGHTS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We intercepted Ninja communications. They are going to launch their jetfighters to hunt down our craft around the planet. The reason appears to be our capability of intercepting their communications.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NARLOCK_PHOTOOP", "Mysterious Photographer"},
		{"STR_NARLOCK_PHOTOOP_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We have sighted a mysterious person, taking photographs of our Hideout... However we didn't manage to catch them.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NARLOCK_PHOTOOP_LEWD", "Mysterious Photographer"},
		{"STR_NARLOCK_PHOTOOP_LEWD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We have sighted a mysterious person, taking photographs of our Hideout... You hurried outside, totally not to flaunt, but you can't be sure if she caught you in the picture properly!{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NARLOCK_PHOTOOP_SOREASS", "Mysterious Photographer"},
		{"STR_NARLOCK_PHOTOOP_SOREASS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We have sighted a mysterious person, taking photographs of our Hideout... You fired some rounds in their general direction, and you think they ran away.{NEWLINE}[-$100]"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_001", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_002", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_003", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_004", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_005", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_006", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_007", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_008", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_009", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_010", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_011", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_012", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_001_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Another large ship went down in flames, this time in the vicinity of {0}. Most of the crew actually survived the crash, but by the time help arrived, not a living soul was found at the site. Everyone has been murdered or kidnapped, the ship and corpses stripped bare of anything valuable. Apparently the Three Factions do not control Earth's airspace like they claim they do, and if so, what is their protection even worth?"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_002_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The world discusses yesterday's incident in the vicinity of {0}, where a Guild base was eradicated by a massive blast. Radiological survey suggests that what was claimed as 'warehouse accident' by the Guild, was, indeed, a nuclear explosion, caused by agents unknown. Of course, nuclear weapons no longer exist, but I'd still advise Guild personnel to never go to work in Eurasian Autonomy without wearing a lot of sunblock lotion."},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_003_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A most horrible sight was witnessed by the citizens of {0} today. Apparently one of the high ranking and very aged Academicians overdosed her Longevity Serum. She, or rather, what was left of her, crawled up to the window and fell down on the street. Academy's mop up teams weren't fast enough to hide the display from the public. Why, indeed, rely on such disgusting therapies if you can instead let yourself be embraced by the Shadow?"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_004_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In a quite drastic development that shook {0}, a huge detonation occurred at its government engineering facility. The crew took heavy casualties, and some witnesses blabbered about 'killer robots falling from the sky right after the blast'. Said robots immediately lived up to their name, exterminating many of the survivors with highly precise plasma fire. I'm not pointing any fingers, but that Technocracy is not to be triffled with!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_005_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Last morning, several bodies were recovered from a garbage dump in {0}, each having been recently deposited with two large-bore rounds to the head. The cadavers have been all identified as having had dealings with top echelons of the Eurosyndicate in the past. The local Military Police suspects foul play, however, a Megapol official stated that a suicide pact cannot be ruled out."},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_006_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In the small morning hours, a violent laser battle erupted on the streets of {0}, temporarily changing the city's downtowno into a literalo disco inferno, and leaving dozens of charred bodies and smoldering vehicles in its wake. Suspects have not been identified so far, and remain at large."},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_007_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Rolling power blackouts continue unabated in {0}. This begs the question, how can we have power blackouts in the era of limitless Hellerium energy? Since the Guild owns most of the generators, we will ask a Guild representative to answer it...{NEWLINE}(Muffled female screams in the background){NEWLINE}...It seems the mystery is not easy to solve, but the Shadow Channel will investigate it thoroughly!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_008_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our investigations into Academy-run charity girl orphanages in {0} revealed that last year, less than 5% of their funds were spent on the needs of the children, while the remaining 95% plus were allocated towards salaries and bonuses for the staff. With such kind of charities, who needs taxes?"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_009_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Major incidents of racial motivated violence occured in {0}. Local Beastmen population became divided over the issue of which ones of them are Mutants and which are Purebloods, resulting in (mostly unarmed) clashes, in which already hundreds of Beastmen have been killed by other Beastmen. Both Mutants and Purebloods for the most part agree that these events are 'quite entertaining'."},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_010_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A new disease is sweeping across {0}. According to the Academy, it causes Purebloods to turn into Mutants. Many former-Purebloods have been already evicted. Curiously enough, the disease seems to be market-conscious - its biggest concentration correlates with the area where a new Academy hospital is planned to be built. What a golden opportunity with land price suddenly falling like that!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_011_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A new subculture is gaining traction in {0}, to the horror of Pureblood educators and parents. Their teenage children join gangs which wear scary masks and other paraphenalia, identifying themselves as Mutants. We here at the Shadow Channel are sure that Eris is smiling on this refreshingly unexpected development!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_NEWS_012_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A citizen of {0} has left his aircar at a local service shop. When he returned the next day, he found neither his aircar nor the service shop. Almost like the Shadow swallowed it, ha, ha!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_001", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_002", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_003", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_004", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_005", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_001_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Over the past 3 years, the number of officially recognized Pureblood medical afflictions increased by nearly 200. According to our sources, a vast majority of these afflictions is not actually detrimental, but a result of mutant genetic heritage. This, of course, is a big no-no for the Purebloods. We should point out that many Academicians profit from this, since all the new diseases need to be named, described, evaluated, processed... So everyone is happy!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_002_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today's topic: the mythical Ubers! Literal supermutants, whose Hellerium diet gives them uncanny abilities and the instinctual understanding of ship technology. These 'Zone Raiders' attack and rob anything that flies, before hiding back in their inaccessible Zones. However, lately two new Uber organizations have began to gain even higher notoriety: Ninjas and Pirates. Question is, who's behind such a meteoric rise? Wink-wink."},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_003_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today, in the Iron Tribe capital of Spectral, an unusual even took place: a competition between Bens to determine which one was the biggest. The title was successfully defended by the last year's champion, the Big Ben."},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_004_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Recent polls show that only 20% of the population follows the cause of Sirius, while almost thrice as much follow various denominations of the Eris cult, like the reverence of the Demon Gods. Remember kids - Eris doesn't want your prayers or wallets, she only wants more discord!{NEWLINE}All Hail Eris! All Hail Discordia!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_ONETIME_005_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A farmer was arrested in Thebes for using refugees as cheap labour. The liberated workers have been sent to a state-run orphanage. Where is that orphanage? Where is the farmer now? The Shadow obscures all."},
		{"STR_SC_34_SPECIAL_1", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_SPECIAL_1_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Merry Horus Day 2601! As a present, you'll get a pinup of mine, so you'll better like it, or be annihilated, understood, meatsack?! Now...! Back to news! 2602 predictions! Whispers in the shadows tell us, that Megapol plans to significantly improve their armaments. Meanwhile, as the existence of Isolated Valleys became known, Technocracy's murderbots are scouting for them, drawn by the unique Shelter technologies...{NEWLINE}Eris bless you all!"},
		{"STR_SC_34_PINUP_1", "LOLA Mk.669 Examination"},
		{"STR_SC_34_PINUP_1_UFOPEDIA", "Type: Shadowsyn, 669th gen.{NEWLINE}Subtype: Tactical Node lvl. 3{NEWLINE}Complexion/Hair: Zortrium Purple{NEWLINE}Power: 5.3 MW at peak{NEWLINE}Origin: Black Pearl Forgeworld{NEWLINE}Hivemind uplink: false{NEWLINE}Sex: true{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Operational Status: 91%{NEWLINE}Chaoticity: 49%{NEWLINE}Morality: 11%{NEWLINE}Integrity: 52%{NEWLINE}Spirituality: 24%{NEWLINE}Intelligence: 9631%{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Note: visible Chaos mutation - eyes glow red when aggressive."},
		{"STR_SC_34_SPECIAL_2", "Shadow News"},
		{"STR_SC_34_SPECIAL_2_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Following up on the story of the unusually large Bandit army, yesterday they have left the vicinity of Jackstown after camping there for the last week. Exclusively for you, we have invited Mr. Jack himself to comment on that! Mr Jack, by what trick of diplomacy you've avoided a battle? <None. The bandits just took several days to count all of our machineguns. They are kind of slow, but they did reach the correct conclusions in the end.> "},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_EXPECTATIONS", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_EXPECTATIONS_DESCRIPTION", "Due to the last month of piratin' going great, everyone has overblown expectations for the current one. They will be hard to please...{NEWLINE}[-2500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_STRIKE", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_STRIKE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going great, the Brainers decided they were not compensated well enough for their efforts. Worse still, they cajouled the Runts to strike as well. You had no choice but to cough up extra $500k."},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_VACATION", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_VACATION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going great, you decided to take a well-deserved vacation. Predictably, things went awry with you away, but you managed to refresh yourself and meet some interesting people.{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy, -$50k, +20 Glam, +5 P.Data]"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_LAZY", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_LAZY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going great, the Gals are getting lazy and capricious. The overall morale is good, but our budget suffers.{NEWLINE}[+250 Infamy, -$20k]"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_CAT", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_CAT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going great, or maybe for no reason at all, a stray cat took shelter in you Hideout. The Gals think this is a good omen.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_PARTY", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_PARTY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going great, the Gals have thrown a big party! Morale soars.{NEWLINE}[+500 Infamy, -$5k]"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_SUPPLIES", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_SUPPLIES_DESCRIPTION", "Due to the last month of piratin' going great, the Govts have sent us an additional $750k bonus in supplies."},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_TOURNAMENT", "High Times"},
		{"STR_GOODSCORE_TOURNAMENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going great, a few members of your crew got invited to a grand fighting tournament. Your gals did great, and their controversial fighting style is being discussed by everyone!{NEWLINE}[+750 Infamy, +$250k]"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_TOY", "Gangsta Style"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_TOY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our successes last month have made the crew boisterous! You are pleased with this situation, and you have bought an expensive toy to congratulate yourself. What's that toy, though? Please tell me, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[-$75,000]"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_DRUNK", "Gangsta Style"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_DRUNK_DESCRIPTION", "Our successes last month have made the crew boisterous! Your Favorite Brainer was especially enthusiastic, and she convinced you to have a few drinks in public. You don't remember much after the first hour of drinking, and what little you do remember, you'd rather not.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_BOX", "Gangsta Style"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_BOX_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our successes last month have made the crew boisterous! You could trust them enough to leave for a much-needed few days off. You spent it in the blissful solitude of wastelands. While exploring some old ruins, you have found an interesting crate."},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_IMPROVEMENTS", "Gangsta Style"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_IMPROVEMENTS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our successes last month have made the crew boisterous! The Runts came up with various efficiency improvements on their own, which effectively refunded $100k from the last month's running costs."},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_BRAWL", "Gangsta Style"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_BRAWL_DESCRIPTION", "Our successes last month have made the crew boisterous! They organized a grand brawl at the hangar. Fists were flying everywhere, and it was glorious!{NEWLINE}[+300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_EXPLOSION", "Gangsta Style"},
		{"STR_OKSCORE_EXPLOSION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our successes last month have made the crew boisterous! Which probably contributed to an explosion that rocked our Hideout today. Repairs after this accident (if it was an accident?) have eaten up no less than 200,000 Dolaros."},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_TIPS", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_TIPS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. Your Favorite Brainer took upon herself to improve the situation, and she came up with some tips.{NEWLINE}[Random Pinup Unlocked, +25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_SPEECH", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_SPEECH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. You decided to gather these freaks 'round and give them one more great speech to rouse their morale. It worked.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_STAGNATION", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_STAGNATION_DESCRIPTION", "The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. They're starting to believe nothing ever really gets done here, and no good things will ever come to them. For every step forward, we're making a step back. No real achievements, just eternal drudge. Life is sour, and every success turns to ashes. Etc, etc... They can speak like that for hours.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_ROBBERY", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_ROBBERY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. Frustrated, they turned to smalltime robbery. This helped with our funds, but the locals trust us less.{NEWLINE}[+$25k, -50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_DRINKING", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_DRINKING_DESCRIPTION", "The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. Their alcohol intake skyrocketed, and their moral standards, including the sense of duty, sunk very low.{NEWLINE}[-$50k, +1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_JUNK_PILES", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_JUNK_PILES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. The discouraged runts started to wander around the Hideout, instead of working. We took some financial losses, but they brought 5 huge bags of previously-undiscovered Hideout junk.{NEWLINE}[-$10k, +5 Junk Pile]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_BRAWL", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_BRAWL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. An unusually violent fight broke out, and you had to throw the offenders into prison. This did little to help the morale.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_PILL", "Thug Life"},
		{"STR_NORMALSCORE_PILL_DESCRIPTION", "The piratin' business last month was rather slow, and the crew is grumpy. You got so depressed, you took some drugs, advertised as 'self-rape pills'. It seemed like a fine idea back then. When you woke up, you were sore all over, in a prison cell, and completely naked. The first passerby let you out, but nobody wants to talk what happened, supposedly on your own order. However, the depression vanished, you feel inspired to write! Looks like the pills worked as intended?{NEWLINE}[-250 Infamy, +3 Zines]"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_GOODENDO", "Mutiny!"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_GOODENDO_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going poorly, the crew turned rebellious! Thankfully, you were able to forcibly re-assert your authority.{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_OKENDO", "Mutiny!"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_OKENDO_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going poorly, the crew turned rebellious! Thankfully they calmed down after you managed to charm the Govts into supplying you with extra funds...{NEWLINE}[+$50k]"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_AVERTED", "Mutiny!"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_AVERTED_DESCRIPTION", "Due to the last month of piratin' going poorly, the crew turned rebellious! You gave them $100k to fuck off. It seems to be working."},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_MEHENDO", "Mutiny!"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_MEHENDO_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going poorly, the crew turned rebellious! They did not confront you openly yet, but mass paranoia is slowly setting in...{NEWLINE}[-200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_BADENDO", "Mutiny!"},
		{"STR_LOWSCORE_BADENDO_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Due to the last month of piratin' going poorly, the crew turned rebellious! They have stripped you down, chained you up and threw you into a pit of sludge. It was just a warning; the next time they might remove you permanently.{NEWLINE}[-500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_BULLY_GOOD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_BULLY_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They picked up a fight with a bunch of Academy Nurses in a nearby village and dragged one back to your prison, where they bullied her some more.{NEWLINE}[+150 Infamy, +1 Nurse, +1 Stun Baton]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_BULLY_BAD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_BULLY_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They took their anger out on some aggressive local mutants.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +5 Capitatory Tax]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SCHOOL_GOOD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SCHOOL_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They decided to become more like Brainers and started to study.{NEWLINE}[A Pinup Unlocked, +1 Database]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SCHOOL_BAD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SCHOOL_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They went to the Brainers for help, and a Brainer gave them a mildly successful lecture on how the progress will turn the things around eventually.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_PARTY_GOOD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_PARTY_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They have thrown a great party, like the world was ending... nevermind the expenses.{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy, -$5k, +5 Cleaning Bills]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_PARTY_BAD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_PARTY_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They decided to throw a party, which quickly degraded into an orgy of desperate debauchery. There was a lot of awkwardness the next day, but the morale improved a little bit.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy, +10 Cleaning Bills]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_HOBO_GOOD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_HOBO_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They started to clean the Hideout till it was sparkling, and sold some unused stuff at the Black Market. This improved both the mood and the finances.{NEWLINE}[+125 Infamy, +$5k, +1 Junk Pile]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_HOBO_BAD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_HOBO_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}The mood has fallen so low that Gals stopped to care too much about wearing clothes or bathing regularly. This new low of expectations gave them some relief, but the Hideout got more messy.{NEWLINE}[+75 Infamy, +5 Cleaning Bills]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SPORTS_GOOD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SPORTS_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They decided to focus on improving their physical fitness, and their new look boosted their morale and our sponsors' confidence.{NEWLINE}[+175 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SPORTS_BAD", "Delinquency"},
		{"STR_DELINQUENT_SPORTS_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The pirating adventure last month was less glamorous than you promised, and the Gals are taking things into their own hands.{NEWLINE}They decided to focus on improving their physical fitness, but found out that sport events also give different... opportunities. They traded their pictures to some local perverts, and you get a cut.{NEWLINE}[+$1000, random items]"},
		{"STR_STREET_FIGHTING", "Street Fighting"},
		{"STR_STREET_FIGHTING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A pair of our Gals got so drunk that they decided to have a nude brawl in front of one of Jackstown's bars. If that wasn't enough, the event immediately became very popular with the locals. The gals did indeed give them a memorable show of Mutant Martial Arts. Jack has sent us our share of bet money.{NEWLINE}[+$5000, +75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_POLTERGEIST", "A POLTERGEIST !!!"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_POLTERGEIST_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Arr, Cap'n! Something strange is going on. We are beset with severe, inexplicable power outages and blowing-up monitors. There have been also ghost sightings. Brainers say that some force is behind it, and that force possesses a mind of its own. All efforts to catch this creature have been in vain so far."},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SDD", "DEVICE OF DOOM !!!"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SDD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Arr, Cap'n! We have found something really sinister in our storage. It appears to be some kind of extremely powerful bomb (according to Brainers), which talks in a robotic voice. It threatens to destroy our Hideout if we touch it. We have no idea what this thing is, nor how it got here."},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_JIM", "WHO IS JIM !?"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_JIM_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Arr, Cap'n! We have found a strange interloper in our crew quarters, apparently at least a little interested in our state of unclothing! He won't leave, and won't apologize! He wants to be called Jim. He claims he came out of that strange flask one Gal brought here the other day. We don't know yet how to dislodge him without blowing up our Hideout. Who knows, he might be even useful?"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SLIME_INFESTATION", "INFESTATION !!!"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SLIME_INFESTATION_DESCRIPTION", "Arr, Cap'n! A crazy slime creature has been spotted in our Hideout's sewers! All conventional efforts to kill it have failed, and the monster has grown into the storage areas, and it is bothering our Runts as we speak!"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SLIME_MOLESTATION", "Slime Molestation"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SLIME_MOLESTATION_DESCRIPTION", "The slime infesting our Hideout was molesting the Runts again! Runts, Cap'n! They lack expertise in Xenology to engage into close encounters of the fifth kind without Brainer supervision! Or they should leave this kind of thing to us completely!{NEWLINE}[+5 Hideout Cleaning Bills]"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SLIME_RESEARCH", "Slime Research"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_SLIME_RESEARCH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Thanks to our knowledge of Xenology, we were able to conduct very... involved... research on the Slime Infestation, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +5 Zines]"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_JIM_MOLESTATION", "Jim's Corruption"},
		{"STR_PLAGUE_JIM_MOLESTATION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Jim has focused recently on coercing one of our Gals to do lewd things. Apparently she enjoyed that a lot. I'm not sure which of these two things is more disturbing. Anyway, we've got some... material. A lot, actually. Okay, it's just absurd how much.{NEWLINE}[+12 Zines]"},
		{"STR_EXTREME_WEATHER_EVIL", "Extreme Weather"},
		{"STR_EXTREME_WEATHER_EVIL_DESCRIPTION", "Our area was hit by extreme weather. The local population was in dire need of fuel, so we could sell some of ours for five times the price. Now that must have been the best deal in history of deals!{NEWLINE}[-15 Infamy, +$20,000]"},
		{"STR_EXTREME_WEATHER_GOOD", "Extreme Weather"},
		{"STR_EXTREME_WEATHER_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "Our area was hit by extreme weather. The local population was in dire need of fuel, so we gave them some barrels. Now they're praising us as saviours.{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy, -$5,000]"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_WIN", "Gambling Night"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_LOSE", "Gambling Night"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_CHEAT", "Gambling Night"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_WIN_DUMBASS", "Gambling Night"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_LOSE_DUMBASS", "Gambling Night"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_FAVOR", "Gambler!"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_WIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You went to town gambling and managed to liberate a rich lady from all her possessions!"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_LOSE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You went to town gambling and lost everything, including your clothes. Next time, you'll show them!... Wait a minute...{NEWLINE}[-$100k]"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_CHEAT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You went to town gambling and, as it befits an Insidious Queen, cheated hard!{NEWLINE}[+100 Blue Chips]"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_DUMBASS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE} Dumbass that you are, you decided to gamble again!"},
		{"STR_GAMBLING_NIGHT_FAVOR_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your addiction to gambling amuses Jack. You're also accumulating a lot of useless stuff."},
		{"STR_LORD_TAURON_CUTS_CABLES", "Lord Tauron Cuts Cables"},
		{"STR_LORD_TAURON_CUTS_CABLES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Enraged by our excess Hideout electricity sales, Lord Tauron, the Traders Guild's Energetics Overseer, has sent engineer teams to cut suspect power lines. Many settlements have been bereft of electricity, we had to buy materials to restore their (and ours) grid security.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy, -$200,000]"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_FLATTERING_SONG", "Brazen Bard"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_FLATTERING_SONG_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A popular bard has been performing a song about our deeds. It was flattering.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_UNFLATTERING_SONG", "Brazen Bard"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_UNFLATTERING_SONG_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A popular bard has been performing a song about our deeds. It was unflattering.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_FORGETTABLE_SONG", "Brazen Bard"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_FORGETTABLE_SONG_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A popular bard has been performing a song about our deeds. It didn't get any traction, though."},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_COPYRIGHTED_SONG", "Brazen Bard"},
		{"STR_BRAZEN_BARD_COPYRIGHTED_SONG_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A popular bard has been performing a song about our deeds, then he sued us over a copyright infringement. The poor bastard didn't get what 'Pirates' are, so the Gals taught him a lesson in assault & robbery.{NEWLINE}[-1 Infamy, +$500]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_SOREASS", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_SOREASS_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. However, they were greeted by VISITORS NOT WELCOME signs, which you, being a Headstrong Captain, ordered to put up. To make sure they get the message, you also fired several rounds in their general direction.{NEWLINE}[+15 Infamy, -$50]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_MYSTERIOUS_STALKER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_MYSTERIOUS_STALKER_DESCRIPTION", "Somebody knocked on the door to your Hideout but when you checked, nobody was there anymore. You only heard (or imagined?) sounds of heavy breathing. Is someone stalking you? You feel uneasy.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ATTACKED_IN_BED", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ATTACKED_IN_BED_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a damsel of exceptional cuteness whom you lost no time in dragging to your bedchamber. Only to almost get assassinated with a dagger she held in her sleeve. After that failed, you were able to overpower her, but your crew questions your sanity for insisting to keep the assailant alive and mostly unharmed.{NEWLINE}[-125 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_APOSTATE_OF_APOCALYPSE", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_APOSTATE_OF_APOCALYPSE_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be some religious wacko with weirdly glowing eyes, grinning all the time. But the uncanny way he moves indicates he can be a powerful recruit."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ZONE_STALKER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ZONE_STALKER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a mysterious tough guy looking for an employer. For the time being, we have put him in a cell, and his weapons in the vaults."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WILD_GIRL", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WILD_GIRL_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a naked girl armed with a bow and spear. For the time being, we have put her in a cell, and her weapons in the vaults."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WASTELAND_GIRL", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WASTELAND_GIRL_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a female drifter, possibly useable as an employee. For the time being, we have put her in a cell, and her weapons in the vaults."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_REVOLUTIONARY_GIRL", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_REVOLUTIONARY_GIRL_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be an aspiring revolutionary, looking to join our cause. For the time being, we have put her in a cell, and her weapons in the vaults."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_SNIPER_GIRL", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_SNIPER_GIRL_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be some sort of a sharpshooter for hire. For the time being, we have put her in a cell, and her weapons in the vaults."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ROGUE_CLONE", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ROGUE_CLONE_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a weird-eyed, silent and a dangerous-looking girl with a big sniper rifle. For the time being, we have put her in a cell, and her weapons in the vaults."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_DAMSEL_OF_WAR", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_DAMSEL_OF_WAR_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a woman in a high tech armor, carrying herself in a princely manner. After some negotiations, she agreed to wait in a cell till you wish to talk to her."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WILD_GNOME", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WILD_GNOME_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout and made quite a ruckus. It is a mystery how this diminutive person survived in the wild naked and carrying only some basic weapons. We have put her in a cell for now."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_OGRE_WORKER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_OGRE_WORKER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a really big guy, looking for employment as a worker.{NEWLINE}[Ogre Worker gained]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_STORYTELLER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_STORYTELLER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a wandering storyteller. In exchange for some food, he shared a captivating story with your crew. Morale improves.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_GIFTMASTERS", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_GIFTMASTERS_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be... Or it was a she? Actually, nobody seems to remember who that really was. Only that the weird person had a hooded robe, was very nice, and said that she/he came here to give us a 'gift'. It could have been just a hallucination, if not for the fact that the 'gift' is real...{NEWLINE}[+1 Mystery Box]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ARTIFICIER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ARTIFICIER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be an artificier, and had an awesome robotic parrot with him! The parrot performed all sorts of tricks! The Gals were absolutely amazed, and finally managed to convince him to sell us the toy for $75,000 plus some 'favours'.{NEWLINE}[-$75k, -25 Infamy, +1 Robo Parrot]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WILLING_SLAVE", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WILLING_SLAVE_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a wealthy guy who offered to become our willing slave. First thing we ordered him was to hand over his money, which he did with enthusiasm.{NEWLINE}[Slave x1, $50,000 acquired]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ARTISANS", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ARTISANS_DESCRIPTION", "Some visitors showed up at our hideout. They turned out to be a wandering band of artisans. They were quite persuasive about their usefulness and agreed to work without insurance.{NEWLINE}[Worker x5 acquired]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_SUICIDER_BOMBER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_SUICIDER_BOMBER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. Before we figured out who he was, he started screaming something in a foreign language and then blew himself up. The sum total of sustained damage is $250."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_YOUNG_UBER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_YOUNG_UBER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a Young Uber looking for group. We put her in the prison for the time being."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_GNOME_MAD", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_GNOME_MAD_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. It was a disheveled young lady who kept pounding the main gate, murmuring 'Hellerium... Hellerium...' When we approached her, she attacked us viciously and it took a lot of effort to restrain her. The follow up investigation I leave to you, Cap'n."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WANDERER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_WANDERER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a handsome wanderer who got lost in the wilderness and ran out of supplies. I put him in a cell to stop the ladies from harassing him."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_CASTAWAYS", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_CASTAWAYS_DESCRIPTION", "Some visitors showed up at our hideout. It was a pair of our old comrades who escaped the Academy on their own, met on the road and finally managed to find our hideout. But who knows if they weren't infected by some weird ideas? So I put them in the jail for now, Cap'n."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_BRAD_AND_JANET", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_BRAD_AND_JANET_DESCRIPTION", "Some visitors showed up at our hideout. It was a lost couple whose aircar had broken nearby. They went looking for help, but they found us instead!{NEWLINE}[Sharp Guy x1, Sharp Girl x1, Small Ship Engine x1 acquired]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_JESTERS", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_JESTERS_DESCRIPTION", "Some visitors showed up at our hideout. It was a group of travelling jesters. They organized a splendid spectacle for your Gals, raising their morale. They also billed you $250, and stole $250 more.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_FREAK", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_FREAK_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a half-starved to death, freaky-looking Uber gal, who was cast out of her community. I ordered to feed her and put her in a cell for the time being. The Hellerium radiation seems to have soothed her."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_STUDENT", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_STUDENT_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a stranded Academy student in a disheveled state. Seeing our installations and female crew, she thought she found an Academy outpost. She might be starting to realize her mistake, sitting in a cell, but she is still intact, pristine and oblivious to the fate you have prepared for her, Cap'n!"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_HUNTER", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_HUNTER_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a hunter, seeking to sell some rare furs. We have bought them for the low, low price of $50k."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ALCHEMIST", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_ALCHEMIST_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a wandering alchemist, looking to sell some weird elixirs. Sounded like some sort of merchant to me, and what do pirates do to merchants? Rob them!{NEWLINE}[+5 Healing Gel, +$15k]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_PENITENT", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_PENITENT_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. He turned out to be a grizzled veteran, a penitent, who wants to join our fight to atone for his past sins."},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_PROTESTERS", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_PROTESTERS_DESCRIPTION", "Some visitors showed up at our hideout. They were very upset and screaming how we live in immoral ways, hold hostages, kill people. Like we were doing anything dishonorable or something. We challenged them to a brawl, and the poor bastards got thoroughly thrashed. They shouldn't return anytime soon.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_CATGIRL", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_CATGIRL_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a very hungry and pretty unwashed Catgirl in prison robe, which is what the arrested people are forced to wear by Megapol. Well, yes, now WE have put her in OUR prison, but this is different! It's like a hotel from which she can leave at any time!{NEWLINE}[Fugitive Catgirl Captive adopted]"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_CATGIRL_TOURIST", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_CATGIRL_TOURIST_DESCRIPTION", "A visitor showed up at our hideout. She turned out to be a catgirl! She says she belongs to something called 'Peregrine Cult' and that she wants to join our crew to experience the best of Earth's culture!{NEWLINE}[Obtained a Catgirl Tourist and her stuff]"},
		{"STR_MAD_SCRIBBLINGS", "Mad Scribblings"},
		{"STR_MAD_SCRIBBLINGS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}One of our brainers underwent a major episode of madness. She worked for several days without sleep, food, or social interaction. When she finally collapsed, there was a weird blueprint left on her desk. However, the design depends on some sort of 'space-time quantum instabilities' which means it will work only once. How useless."},
		{"STR_USE_MAD_SCRIBBLINGS", "Use Mad Scribblings"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_PHOTOS", "A Party to Remember"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_PHOTOS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Yesterday's party went a bit wild, and someone took lots of photos. I have secured them, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[+3 Zines]"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_BRAWL", "A Party to Remember"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_BRAWL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Yesterday's party went a bit wild, causing some damage to the hideout's insra... infrastructure. I strongly condemn these acts of mindless vandalism and sluttery, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[-1000 $]"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_LEGENDARY", "A Party to Remember"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_LEGENDARY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Yesterday's party went a bit wild, even by our standards. People in the area are already circulating the wildest rumors.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_AGENT", "A Party to Remember"},
		{"STR_A_PARTY_TO_REMEMBER_AGENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Yesterday's party went a bit wild after we unmasked a Govt Agent who had infiltrated it. We caught him and put him under lock and key, Cap'n!"},
		{"STR_DEATHS_DOOR", "Death's Door"},
		{"STR_DEATHS_DOOR_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy last month reached such a low that it threatens you with outright crew mutiny. However, your will is indomitable and you manage a heroic effort to turn the tide.{NEWLINE}[+250 Infamy, +$200k]"},
		{"STR_RED_REIGN_AND_RULE", "Reign And Rule"},
		{"STR_RED_REIGN_AND_RULE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you saved some escaped fugitives from bounty hunters. They turned out to be so freakishly honorable that they immediately offered their lives to your cause."},
		{"STR_RED_OLD_MINES_RATS", "Old Mines"},
		{"STR_RED_OLD_MINES_RATS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you come across an abandoned mine and decide to explore it. It turned out to be filled with giant rats! Luckily you know no fear, especially of rodents, and make short work of them.{NEWLINE}[+10 scrap metal, +25 Mutant Meat]"},
		{"STR_RED_DOCTOR_AWAY", "Keep The Doctor Away"},
		{"STR_RED_DOCTOR_AWAY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you come across a small Academy patrol, conducting 'medical examinations' on some frightened villagers. You step in and swiftly rescue the victims from the grubby Academician fingers, chasing the molesters away.{NEWLINE}[+75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_RED_NIGHTMARES", "Nightmares"},
		{"STR_RED_NIGHTMARES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You're plagued by recurring nightmares. Your enemies surround you, but your limbs are heavy, you cannot fight, you cannot escape. This time the crew has heard you screaming, which won't help with their morale...{NEWLINE}[-40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_RED_THIEF", "A Thief!"},
		{"STR_RED_THIEF_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Being a mighty warrior is not just about killing, it is also about keeping order, both inside and out. Doing your daily patrol you've managed to catch a Savvy Girl who was trying to steal stuff from your Hideout!"},
		{"STR_RED_WAY_OF_THE_SWORD", "The Way Of The Sword"},
		{"STR_RED_WAY_OF_THE_SWORD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}While your enemies were doing... whatever degenerate stuff these lazy asses are doing... you were studying the sword! You've gained some enlightenment about how to kill people better.{NEWLINE}[+1 Cultural Wealth, Gained Info]"},
		{"STR_RED_WANDERING_MONSTERS", "Wandering Monsters"},
		{"STR_RED_WANDERING_MONSTERS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you come across a small settlement besieged by dangerous beasts. Longing for a good fight, you confront the predators and slay them one by one in an exhilarating battle!{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy, +5 Heroes' Blessings, +3 Capitatory Tax]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_EVIL_BOTTLE", "Evil Bottle"},
		{"STR_GREEN_EVIL_BOTTLE_DESCRIPTION", "As you get up from bed, you trip over an empty bottle and suffer a mild concussion. You spend the rest of the day puking in the infirmary, looking so miserable that nobody even makes any jokes and you get lots of concerned visitors. You are so proud of your dazzling crew!{NEWLINE}[-$100, +30 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_SLUDGE_BATH", "Sludge Bath"},
		{"STR_GREEN_SLUDGE_BATH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You take a long, rejuvenating bath in the submerged caverns below the Hideout. Your problems seem to melt away...{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_DOUBTS", "Doubts"},
		{"STR_GREEN_DOUBTS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Are you an evil person? Or are you doing the right thing? You're beset by doubts, and your crew can sense your weakness...{NEWLINE}[-30 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_TRADITION", "Tradition"},
		{"STR_GREEN_TRADITION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}...Is your bulwark! Despite the repeated calls to innovate, you stick with what you know. It is not very efficient, but you consider it a fair price to pay for salvation.{NEWLINE}[-$50k, +10 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_HOPE", "Hope"},
		{"STR_GREEN_HOPE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your optimism regarding the final victory is unshakeable, in spite of all reason. You believe yourself to be indestructible, and your vitality proves it. This impresses the crew, even if a few of them think you're a cuckoo. Or, because of it.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_PRAYERS", "Prayers"},
		{"STR_GREEN_PRAYERS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}On a whim, you visited a Bloom Lady temple in Jackstown to partake in prayers. Not only the baths and buffet are nice, but you find it reasonable to keep on the good side of a higher power. Especially if she was the one who arranged your escape. In any case, the faithful have noticed and cheered your presence.{NEWLINE}[+3 Heroes' Blessings]"},
		{"STR_GREEN_MAN_OF_THE_CLOTH", "Man Of The Cloth"},
		{"STR_GREEN_MAN_OF_THE_CLOTH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you encounter a wandering priest of Eris. You share some food with him, and he shares a story with you.{NEWLINE}[-$10, +10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GRAY_EIGHT_LEGGED_APPARITION", "Eight-Legged Apparition"},
		{"STR_GRAY_EIGHT_LEGGED_APPARITION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a morning stroll, you spot with the corner of your eye something that looks like a robotic spider. Or maybe demonic. Or spectral. As you turn to look, it's already gone. Whatever it was, you are seriously spooked.{NEWLINE}[-33 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GRAY_BIG_QUESTION", "The Big Question"},
		{"STR_GRAY_BIG_QUESTION_DESCRIPTION", "You spend the whole day pondering the meaning of Life, the Universe and Everything. Your crew is weirded out, but who cares about the ignorant masses?{NEWLINE}[-20 Infamy, +5 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_GRAY_BEST_BARGAIN", "Best Bargain"},
		{"STR_GRAY_BEST_BARGAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Visiting Jackstown, you decide to try and haggle with the shopkeeper a little harder than usual. Eventually he gives you $100 to fuck off."},
		{"STR_GRAY_GOTTA_GO_FAST", "Gotta Go Fast"},
		{"STR_GRAY_GOTTA_GO_FAST_DESCRIPTION", "In your spare time, you've been messing around with an old passenger vehicle you found in the wastelands. Eager to find out how fast it can go, you make countless modifications, sparing no expenses on parts and special fuel. The machine disintegrates during the test, but despite this - or thanks to it? - the attempt is both successful and widely recognized, netting you a solid Infamy boost in the surrounding area. And a week in the infirmary, but who cares? Progress before safety!{NEWLINE}[-$50,000, +125 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GRAY_PARANOIA", "Paranoia"},
		{"STR_GRAY_PARANOIA_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Are your enemies aware of your secret ambitions? Do they have spies right next to you? Are they able to predict and ruin your plans? Can you survive? Crew's reaction to your increasingly erratic behaviour only confirms your suspicions...{NEWLINE}[-70 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GRAY_WANDERING_MONSTERS", "Wandering Monsters"},
		{"STR_GRAY_WANDERING_MONSTERS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you come across a small settlement besieged by dangerous beasts. You give the locals some pointers on how to better protect their village with weapons and traps. They are thankful for your advice and hand you a small gift.{NEWLINE}[1x Treasure Bag, 1x Fried Reaper Innards, 1x Heroes' Blessings acquired]{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GOLD_MYSTERIOUS_CAVE_STORAGE", "Mysterious Cave"},
		{"STR_GOLD_MYSTERIOUS_CAVE_STORAGE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you come across a mysterious cave and decide to explore it. Apparently some bandits use it for storage, so naturally you help yourself to their supplies."},
		{"STR_GOLD_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_BRIBE", "Know When to Hold 'Em"},
		{"STR_GOLD_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_BRIBE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a friendly card game, you accidentally dropped your fifth ace. The crew was not impressed, but you managed to successfully distract them from rioting with sweet talk and luxurious presents you prepared beforehand for such emergency purposes.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy, -$10,000]"},
		{"STR_GOLD_AT_SEANS_NEW_FACES", "At Sean's"},
		{"STR_GOLD_AT_SEANS_NEW_FACES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your usual trips to your favorite pub, you make some unusual acquitances over the glass!"},
		{"STR_GOLD_DEPRESSION", "Depression"},
		{"STR_GOLD_DEPRESSION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You're feeling very blue today. You don't have the heart for this job anymore... Someone, please save you... But no help is coming...{NEWLINE}[-20 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_GOLD_CHARM", "Charm"},
		{"STR_GOLD_CHARM_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your force of personality is so strong it generates a gravity field! Not even money can escape its irresistible pull, and people's adulation practically creates an accretion disk around your person by this point... And yes, you never know when to stop a metaphor before it becomes tired.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +$25k, +3 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_GOLD_LUCKY_FIND", "Lucky Find"},
		{"STR_GOLD_LUCKY_FIND_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your are a sensual person, and your powers of perception are second to none. While enjoying your morning stroll, you have noticed something shiny in the dirt. A good omen!{NEWLINE}[+35 Infamy, Gained Item]"},
		{"STR_GOLD_NOBLE_SAVAGE", "Noble Savage"},
		{"STR_GOLD_NOBLE_SAVAGE_DESCRIPTION", "During one of your escapades, you see a tribal running away from some Academician 'examination', and you help him chase away the pursuers. He insists on following you home to see if he can be of any help to you. Now he's waiting in the cells."},
		{"STR_GOLD_SCORED", "It's Business Time"},
		{"STR_GOLD_SCORED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your last date went better than expected, and it was business time all the night, baby! You are in a great mood today!{NEWLINE}[+30 Infamy, +3 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_NORED_LAZINESS", "Weak Captain"},
		{"STR_NORED_LAZINESS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You're feeling WEAK... Everything is taking so much effort... You're not leaving the bed today, no way...{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORED_TIME_IS_MONEY", "Time Is Money"},
		{"STR_NORED_TIME_IS_MONEY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Time is money, and you were late. Again. Your tardiness in running the enterprise costed you $50,000 and 25 Infamy hit. Whatever, you can surely afford it!"},
		{"STR_NORED_THIEF", "A Thief!"},
		{"STR_NORED_THIEF_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Despite your best efforts, your Hideout is quite disorderly. A random Savvy Girl managed to steal some valuables! The financial loss is minor, but the humiliation stings.{NEWLINE}[-$10k, -40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORED_WANDERING_MONSTERS", "Wandering Monsters"},
		{"STR_NORED_WANDERING_MONSTERS_DESCRIPTION", "During one of your escapades, you come across a small settlement besieged by dangerous beasts. Things get dire, but you manage to get away without any incident. Whew, that was a lot of running!{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NORED_WINO_DINO", "Your Favorite Show"},
		{"STR_NORED_WINO_DINO_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Not feeling particularly productive, you call off everything in today's schedule and spend the whole day eating snacks, playing games and watching new 'Wino Dino' episodes. The crew doesn't seem to mind this unexpected break, but the work accumulates...{NEWLINE}[+15 Infamy, -$20k]"},
		{"STR_NOGRAY_DANK", "Naive Captain"},
		{"STR_NOGRAY_DANK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You constantly find yourself in embarassing situations. Some people say it's because of your lack of FORESIGHT, but who cares, as long as you're having fun!{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NOGRAY_MUST_HAVE_BEEN_THE_WIND", "It Must Have Been The Wind"},
		{"STR_NOGRAY_MUST_HAVE_BEEN_THE_WIND_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bullet holes appearing overnight, knives and mysterious devices found in random places, strange individuals wandering around the Hideout... You don't understand why your crew gets so paranoid about these coincidences. There is no solid proof of anything untowards happening!{NEWLINE}[+15 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NOGREEN_NIHILISM", "Nihilist Captain"},
		{"STR_NOGREEN_NIHILISM_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}FAITH in people is a joke... You don't give a damn about their feel-good fantasies, all that counts is who's the top dog. And it's gonna be you!{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NOGREEN_YESGOLD_MAN_OF_THE_CLOTH", "Man Of The Cloth"},
		{"STR_NOGREEN_YESGOLD_MAN_OF_THE_CLOTH_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you encounter a wandering priest of Eris. You decide that he should find a real job instead of living off the common folk, so when he's not looking, you grab his possessions and scram.{NEWLINE}[1x Lokk'Naar Scriptures, 1x Ankh]"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_ULTIMATE_EVENT", "Master Of The Universe"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_ULTIMATE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You are basically a Goddess! And the world recognizes you as such with tribute and prayer!{NEWLINE}[+666 Infamy, +$666k]"},
		{"STR_SAINTS_REINFORCEMENTS", "The Saints"},
		{"STR_SAINTS_REINFORCEMENTS_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Saint's aura has drawn a recruit, willing to accept your lead."},
		{"STR_PICKING_UP_STUFF_ROCK", "Picking Up Stuff"},
		{"STR_PICKING_UP_STUFF_ROCK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You found an interestingly coloured piece of rock. It's a really nice rock, so you keep it."},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_FAILED_PRIVILEGE", "Know When to Hold 'Em"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_FAILED_PRIVILEGE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a friendly card game, you accidentally dropped your fifth ace. You tried to justify it as your 'Cap'n's privilege', but the crew seems to be skeptical. One way or another, now they refuse to play with you.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_RABID_FANS_GLAMOUR", "Rabid Fans"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_RABID_FANS_GLAMOUR_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a stroll through Jackstown, you bumped into some avid fans of yours. They made such a fuss about this fortuitious event that even you feel almost intimidated by your own presence!{NEWLINE}[+20 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_WARDROBE", "Mysteriously Shrinking Wardrobe"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_WARDROBE_DESCRIPTION", "All your bras and belts are too short! What on Earth has happened to them?{NEWLINE}Your FBB prescribed you a diet and some exercise in order to 'meet the standards for the position'. You are devastated and not hiding it.{NEWLINE}[-30 Infamy, -$1000]"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_REALITY_CHECK", "Reality Check"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_REALITY_CHECK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Ideas are important, but their execution is importanter... As you and your crew learned the hard way. Maybe next time you come up with some revolutionary improvements, you should run them through the Runts first.{NEWLINE}Our facilities sustained $75,000 in damages, leaving you with some rubble and scrap metal."},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_CAPTAIN_ON_THE_BRIDGE", "Captain on The Bridge"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_CAPTAIN_ON_THE_BRIDGE_DESCRIPTION", "As you triumphantly entered the bridge to impress and awe the crew with your bombastic presence, just like you do every day, you hit your head against a railing rather painfully. The crew had a laugh, and now you're severely depressed over your ruined reputation. This would never happen to a proper Cap'n! What the hell is wrong with you?!{NEWLINE}[-75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_BIRD_IN_HAND", "Bird in Hand"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_BIRD_IN_HAND_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a morning stroll, you spot a small bird caught in some netting just outside your base. After you release it, soon it comes back, carrying a small, shiny object. It drops the item at your feet and disappears into the wild. You pick it up to examine it later."},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_BIRD_IN_HAND", "Bird in Hand"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_BIRD_IN_HAND_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During a morning stroll, you spot a small bird caught in some netting just outside your base. What a tiny snack!{NEWLINE}[+2 Infamy, +1 Mutant Egg]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_SECRETS_OF_THE_SUN", "Secrets of The Sun"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_SECRETS_OF_THE_SUN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}They say that it's dangerous to look at the sun directly, but what if it's a lie to cover some mystery? Risky or not, you must find out yourself! Well, if there is a secret, you still missed it, and now your eyes need some advanced medical attention to work properly. Your FBB still looks- er, seems impressed; she's the only one who actually gets you.{NEWLINE}[-$20,000, +5 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_LEWD_MOOD_MASSAGE", "Lewd Mood"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_LEWD_MOOD_MASSAGE_DESCRIPTION", "Overcome with erotic fantasies, you cannot focus today, so you decide to ask your FBB for help. She offered you a special massage, which got you very intrigued and you agreed eagerly. From what came afterwards, you don't remember much besides the feeling of your every bone slushing around your body, but now your mind is crystal clear. You don't exactly feel like yourself now, but you decide to take this opportunity and finally go over these boring reports you normally don't have the patience for.{NEWLINE}[+$99,000]"},
		{"STR_EXPERIMENTAL_NUDITY", "Experimental Nudity"},
		{"STR_EXPERIMENTAL_NUDITY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In order to test your grip over the crew, you decide to spend this entire day naked, as you go about your usual business. Throughout the day, the Hideout is plagued with minor accidents and meltdowns, happening wherever you go. Looking at all the damage reports, you feel absolutely great about yourself!{NEWLINE}[-$15,000, +66 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NOGOLD_LONELY", "Lonely Captain"},
		{"STR_NOGOLD_LONELY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You don't understand people, and they don't understand you. Whatever. If you amass enough gold, it will surely cure your lack of SELF-ESTEEM, and make them love you.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_NOGOLD_BODY_MODDING", "Body Modding"},
		{"STR_NOGOLD_BODY_MODDING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You get a new piercing. You feel more beautiful, even though it hurts. So pain makes you beautiful... But does it mean that pain itself is beautiful? Hmm... You feel inspired to inspire!{NEWLINE}[+3 Cultural Wealth, +1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_MAXIMUM_EXPLOITATION", "Maximum Exploitation"},
		{"STR_MAXIMUM_EXPLOITATION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You need money to grow, and you need it NOW. You order your gals to put the locals to work on expanding your economic empire. You manage to secure $500k and 20 Workers, but your actions create widespread resentment: -150 Infamy and +600 Capitatory Tax."},
		{"STR_TIME_IS_MONEY", "Time is Money"},
		{"STR_TIME_IS_MONEY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy last month was high. You've convinced the Govts to make advance payments for the next month.{NEWLINE}[+$250k, -500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_0", "Broken Spiral"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_0_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Against your expectations, last month your Infamy was below the minimum for your Captain's Rank! Your plans suffered an irksome setback!{NEWLINE}[-200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_1", "Broken Spiral"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_1_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Against your expectations, last month your Infamy was below the minimum for your Captain's Rank! Your plans need to be readjusted!{NEWLINE}[-300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_2", "Broken Spiral"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_2_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Against your expectations, last month your Infamy was below the minimum for your Captain's Rank! Your plans are ruined!{NEWLINE}[-500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_3", "Broken Spiral"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_3_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Against your expectations, last month your Infamy was below the minimum for your Captain's Rank! Your masterplan has fell to pieces!{NEWLINE}[-800 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_4", "Broken Spiral"},
		{"STR_BROKEN_SPIRAL_4_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Against your expectations, last month your Infamy was below the minimum for your Captain's Rank! Your bid for world domination has failed again!{NEWLINE}[-1250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_0", "Burning Spiral"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_0_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy has surpassed your Captain's Rank last month by a wide margin! You're on ascent!{NEWLINE}[+125 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_1", "Burning Spiral"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_1_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy has surpassed your Captain's Rank last month by a wide margin! You're rising fast!{NEWLINE}[+250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_2", "Burning Spiral"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_2_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy has surpassed your Captain's Rank last month by a wide margin! Your star is shining bright!{NEWLINE}[+375 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_3", "Burning Spiral"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_3_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy has surpassed your Captain's Rank last month by a wide margin! You're on fire!{NEWLINE}[+625 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_4", "Burning Spiral"},
		{"STR_BURNING_SPIRAL_4_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Infamy has surpassed your Captain's Rank last month by a wide margin! You're unstoppable!{NEWLINE}[+1000 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_DIGGING_A_HOLE", "Digging a Hole"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_DIGGING_A_HOLE_DESCRIPTION", "You have dedicated some of your free time to dig a hole beneath your Hideout. Finally, you struck some good find! Now it's time to wash up and count the spoils..."},
		{"STR_SOREASS_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN", "Hardworking Captain"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Anxious for some productive activity, you head down to the workshops to give your Runts a hand. You spend the entire day fiddling with machinery and bonding with your coworkers. This was fun!{NEWLINE}[+$300, +40 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_CHESS", "Chess"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_CHESS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You wanted to play a game of chess, but all the crew refused to play with you. You ended up playing against yourself. And you've lost.{NEWLINE}[-10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_EVIL_BOTTLE", "Evil Bottle"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_EVIL_BOTTLE_DESCRIPTION", "As you get up from bed, you trip over an empty bottle and suffer a mild concussion. You spend the rest of the day puking in the infirmary, causing some sarcastic comments and snickering. Once you're out of here, these good-for-nothings will learn some respect!{NEWLINE}[-$100, -30 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_UNION_MEETING", "Union Meeting"},
		{"STR_SOREASS_UNION_MEETING_DESCRIPTION", "A delegation of Runts barges into your office, demanding a raise. You earnestly dedicate yourself to negotiations, where each side takes great care to understand the other's position and needs and never rushes to conclusion. Fifteen hours later, the delegation decides to not only drop their demands and pretend this never happened, but even pay you a negotiation fee just to finalize the meeting ASAP! All thanks to your peerless diplomatic skills!{NEWLINE}[+$1,000]"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_SUDDEN_INVENTION", "Sudden Invention"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_SUDDEN_INVENTION_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}While reading a whole pile of technical books at once, you become so engrossed with them that you lose track of time. In fact, you lose track of everything, included what you are doing. You emerge from your quarters two days later, groggy and exhausted, but oddly satisfied. Also, your quarters need some renovation now.{NEWLINE}[-$5,000, Mad Scribblings +1]"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_EFFORT", "Maximum Effort"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_EFFORT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Today, you've tried the hardest you could. You've used no less than 30% of your capacity! Now you can have some well-earned rest...{NEWLINE}[+30 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_BOTTLES", "Resolution"},
		{"STR_LAZYASS_BOTTLES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today you woke up and immediately crashed into a mountain of empty bottles next to your matress! Enough is enough! You gathered all the bottles, sold them and resolved to never let that happen again!{NEWLINE}[+$3000]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_THIEF_CHASING", "Thief Chasing"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_THIEF_CHASING_DESCRIPTION", "During a stroll around the Hideout you notice a suspicious person, trying to get away sneakily and holding what definitely looks like a looting sack. Whatever she may have stolen from the Hideout's vicinity was probably not worth much, but it's still yours, so you immediately chase after the culprit. The thief is very fast, but not very enduring, so only like 8 hours later you catch up to her, take her down and retrieve your possessions (well, apparently not only yours). And the thief too, of course.{NEWLINE}[+5 Money Purses, +1 Scrap Metal, +1 Savvy Girl]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_BLIND_LUCK", "Dumb Luck"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_BLIND_LUCK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You can't believe your luck! You've found a money purse!"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_MINOTAUR", "Beastly Challenge"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_MINOTAUR_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You were challenged to a single fight by a huge Beastman! But he gravely underestimated your smooth moves! Who's 'weak and dumb' now?{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_MINOTAUR_DEFEATED", "Beastman Conqueror"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_MINOTAUR_DEFEATED_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}Your victorious fight with the huge Beastman gave you a great idea! To organize a big Clothless Beat'em'up Tournament (CBT) where you could face and defeat even greater foes, while showing off your awesome moves and perfect physique! You just need lots of free time for that...{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]{ALT}"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT", "Clothless Beat'em'up Tournament"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_UFOPEDIA", "Finally having enough free time, you've managed to convince Jack to hold the tournament at Jackstown, with you as the celebrity fighter. He was unsure at first, but flaunting your perfect body won him over! The tournament will be held roughly four times a year, and regardless of your perfomance, Jack will give you a cut of the profits, not to mention you'll get a lot of publicity! However, your true goal is winning. Possessing a Dojo and Onsen would increase your chances (Spa obsoletes both in that role)."},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_LOSE_BAD", "CBT"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_LOSE", "CBT"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_WIN", "CBT Won!"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_LOSE_BAD_DESC", "{NEWLINE}The tournament was long and brutal, with fists and clothes flying everywhere. Some of the finest Uber Gals from all over the world participated. You were ill-prepared and you've received thorough thrashing. But the fight alone was worth it, and, some months from now, there will be another tournament. You can hardly wait!{NEWLINE}[+$50k, +1000 Infamy, Loss Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_LOSE_DESC", "{NEWLINE}The tournament was long and brutal, with fists and clothes flying everywhere. Some of the finest Uber Gals from all over the world participated, you've bested many of them, but eventually you've found your match. You were defeated... this time! But the fight alone was worth it, and, some months from now, there will be another tournament. You can hardly wait!{NEWLINE}[+$50k, +300 Infamy, Loss Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_WIN_DESC", "{NEWLINE}The tournament was long and brutal, with fists and clothes flying everywhere. Some of the finest Uber Gals from all over the world participated, but you were unstoppable! You are the CBT champion! But the fight doesn't end here, and your opponents have sworn to challenge your title the next tournament! You can hardly wait!{NEWLINE}[+$250k, +700 Infamy, Win Prizes]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_CBT_CHAMPION", "CBT Champion"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_CBT_CHAMPION_UFOPEDIA", "You've managed to climb to the very top! You've defeated all the strongest, sexiest and fastest gals at Jackstown's Clothless Beat'em'up Tournament! This establishes your position as a world-renowned prizefighter, and some of the former rivals joined you as willing sla... disciples. Time to enjoy the accolades, defend the title, and look for greater challenges!{NEWLINE}(Relevant facilities: Spa)"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHAMP_LOSE", "CBT Title Lost!"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHAMP_WIN", "CBT Title Defended!"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHAMP_LOSE_DESC", "Well, you cannot really lose the title, but the thrashing you've received in the tournament has tarnished your reputation. At least you've got some decent money...{NEWLINE}[+$100k, -250 Infamy, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHAMP_WIN_DESC", "You are invincible!{NEWLINE}[+$150k, +200 Infamy, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA", "CBT Challenge: Ninja"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DESC", "You were busy sparring with hapless fools in your dojo, when suddenly a Sky Ninja bursted in and challenged you to a duel, you, the champion of your own tournament! And she wasn't even respecting the rule of it being a clothless dojo! Nevertheless, confident in your abilities, you accepted.{NEWLINE}The fight was short... Her charging attack was impossibly fast and she knocked you out with a single strike. You only heard her muttering about 'having cut your ego down to size' before she left...{NEWLINE}[-2000 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_UFOPEDIA", "The Ninja defeated you by using an inhumanly fast flying charge, ended with an even faster strike. Every smart person is at a loss on how could you possibly counter that move, but to the dumb you it's simple: you must sidestep it! You already have a name for the technique of doing so: the Super Sexy Martial Dance! You must learn enough about your body to become even more perceptive, agile and hypnotic, and to be able to keep that state for any amount of time - perhaps even some Ninja techniques could be of help...?{NEWLINE}(Relevant facilities: Spa, VIP Club)"},
		{"STR_SUPER_SEXY_MARTIAL_DANCE", "Super Sexy Martial Dance"},
		{"STR_SUPER_SEXY_MARTIAL_DANCE_UFOPEDIA", "After long training, you've finally managed to develop your own martial art! It combines your natural ability to enter hyper-perceptive state with Mutant biofield manipulation and distracting dance moves to play with the enemy until they overextend themselves. In the final test, you have fought countless sparring partners for the whole day and the following night. When the sun came up and you greeted it with your dance, you knew that you're ready to defeat any opponent."},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT", "CBT Challenge: Ninja"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_DESC", "{NEWLINE}To the cheers of the crowds and whirring of cameras, you've faced the Ninja swordsmaster naked and unarmed. She came at you with her lightning attack, but still too slow to your Super Sexy Martial Dance. You've sidestepped it, saying, 'I have boobs of steel.' Pissed off, she attacked you again and again, but each time you did the exact same thing. She was growing weaker. You've played with her some more before ending the show with a kick to her ear.{NEWLINE}[+2500 Infamy, prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_BANISH_PREQ", "?Ninja Champion: Banish?"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_ENSLAVE_PREQ", "?Ninja Champion: Enslave?"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_BEFRIEND_PREQ", "?Ninja Champion: Befriend?"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_BANISH", "Ninja Champion Banished"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_ENSLAVE", "Ninja Champion Enslaved"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_BEFRIEND", "Ninja Champion Befriended"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_BANISH_UFOPEDIA", "You've performed a ritual of demonic sacrifice and thrusted the Ninja Champion naked through the portal to the Shadow Realm. Before it closed you could see the hands of countless dead grasping at her. The Demon Gods have kept their end of the bargain, too.{NEWLINE}[Mystery Box Obtained]{NEWLINE}[+250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_ENSLAVE_UFOPEDIA", "You've turned the honorable nature of the Ninja Champion against her. You've declared that it would be dishonorable of her to disobey you after you have spared her life. In return, she has to fight in the CBT arena for the entertainment of the crowds. In an act of 'leniency', you've even allowed her to keep her sword, her adornments and her panties. How fair of a deal to a vanquished foe!{NEWLINE}[Enslaved Ninja Champion will generate $50k profit monthly and trigger special CBT Events]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_NINJA_DEFEAT_BEFRIEND_UFOPEDIA", "You've used your innate charm to compel the defeated Ninja Champion to your side. Sort of. You've said that you own her now, since you've defeated her but spared her life. After that, it was just a question of Stockholm Syndrome to kick in before she joined your defacto harem.{NEWLINE}[Ninja Scroll Obtained]{NEWLINE}[+1500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SLAVE_NINJA_CHAMPION", "SLAVE NINJA CHAMPION"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_ENSLAVED_NINJA", "CBT Event!"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_ENSLAVED_NINJA_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your pet Ninja Champion fights on your VIP Club's arena, bringing you money and fame!{NEWLINE}[+$100k, +100 Infamy, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CHARMY_DANCE_TRAINING", "Charmy Dance Training"},
		{"STR_CHARMY_DANCER", "Charmy Dancer"},
		{"STR_CHARMY_DANCER_UFOPEDIA", "You can teach your Gals the basics of the Super Sexy Martial Dance to awaken their inner Hellerium energy to dazzle and distract enemies. They will learn how to gain Boobs (and Ass) of Steel.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}However, this requires 50 Bravery as well as some Glamour and Zines. Needs any Dojo facility. Recovery time is 28 days.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+5 HP and REA;{NEWLINE}+3 Armor (Front & Bottom)"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS", "CBT Challenge: Oni"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_DESC", "A huge, barbaric looking woman arrives at your VIP club. She says: 'The news travel. You have defeated the Ninja Champion. You might be an interesting opponent to fight. I grew tired of defeating weaklings.' You laugh at her, but she just shrugs. 'Spare me this. Today is not a fighting day. Let's drink.'"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_UFOPEDIA", "This new challenger is a mystery. She appears to be a female Ogre, a thing unique in itself, and possesses absurd strength. She's also a pretty good drinking companion, as it turned out. You parted on good terms. You feel excited about fighting her, however you doubt she will be much of a challenge... What is strength alone worth, after all? And those Lokk'Naar whispers about her being a demon from the Underworld and that only the Light Force can defeat her are most certainly just superstition. Hopefully the match will at least draw some audience!"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_LOSE", "CBT Challenge: Oni"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_LOSE_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You enter the arena and fight the Ogress! The crowds cheer as you dance around her, but she doesn't appear to be getting tired or unfocused. You finally start attacking, and she manages to grab you by the ankle and throw you to the ground with such force that you're out for a longer while. At least the crowds liked it...{NEWLINE}[-1000 Infamy, +$200k, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_LOSE2", "CBT Challenge: Oni"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_LOSE2_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Before the fight, you meditate for hours, until Light Force starts to shine through your skin. Shimmering and nude, you enter the arena and confront the Ogress. You trade blow for blow for a long time. But in the end, she is still able to take one more hit, and you don't...{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}[-1000 Infamy, +$200k, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_WIN", "CBT Challenge: Oni"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_WIN_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Before the fight, you meditate for hours, until Light Force starts to shine through your skin. Shimmering and nude, you enter the arena and confront the Ogress. You trade blow for blow for a long time. Finally, you focus all your power into a Super Holy Punch and she is knocked down!{NEWLINE}[+3000 Infamy, +$500k, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_DEFEAT", "Ogress Defeated"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_OGRESS_DEFEAT_UFOPEDIA", "Now you truly are the strongest fighter! The Ogress slowly stands up and gives you a word of advice. 'There is always someone stronger than you.' Seeing her leave, you can only reflect on these words... After all, she's been undefeated for over 200 years... Hah! You will worry about it in 200 years!"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_NO_CHALLENGER", "No Challenges Left"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_NO_CHALLENGER_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You have a sinking realization that the whole CB Tournament was for naught. You will probably never find a worthy opponent... You succumb to seeking oblivion in expensive pleasures.{NEWLINE}[-$100k]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON", "CBT Challenge: Dragon"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You yearn for another opponent to fight, but, being a Saint, you've managed to overcome that desire. It is then when a miracle happens. 'Your wish is granted, Saint, or you are granted to it' a monotone voice speaks in your head. 'I, the Black Guardian, shall test your mettle in personal combat. Soon I will come to your world. Prepare yourself.' "},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_UFOPEDIA", "The Black Guardian, one of the Demon Gods, has officially issued you a challenge for a duel and seems to be excited about it. If that emotionless, alien being can be excited about anything at all. Finally, you'll get to fight someone important! However... while you have the power of a Saint, can you defeat a Dragon? Nevermind! It's going to be a blast, and you can always try to befriend her! You can hardly wait!{NEWLINE}[+250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_LOSE", "CBT Challenge: Dragon"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_LOSE_DESC", "{NEWLINE}On the chosen day, you see a Tannhauser Gate opening in the middle of the arena. The Black Dragon comes out and you confront her in your glowing Saint form. Devastation spreads across the area as you two fight. She seems somewhat clumsy, but after hours have passed, you grow tired, while her attacks only grow stronger. Finally she sends you crashing into the wall and you don't get up. She leaves with a bored look on her face.{NEWLINE}[+250 Infamy, +$300k, Prizes]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_WIN", "CBT Challenge: Dragon"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_WIN_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}On the chosen day, you see a Tannhauser Gate opening in the middle of the arena. The Black Dragon comes out and you confront her in your glowing Saint form. You look at each other for a long time. Finally you say, 'You're kinda cute.' She nods. 'You too.' You tilt your head. 'Soo, will you let me win?' Her eyes flash. 'No. But I can make you scream louder than usual.' She drops her sword."},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_DEFEAT", "Charmed Dragon"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_CHALLENGER_BLACK_DRAGON_DEFEAT_UFOPEDIA", "In the end, she never fully undressed, but she did keep her promise of making you scream like you never did before. These dragon claws can be really dextrous, as it turns out... She still leaves you exhausted and unable to move. 'I won again, you hopeless idiot,' she says, smirking, and you don't feel like disagreeing... 'We're not that different,' she adds unexpectedly and you feel that she had lowered her shield a little... You also feel like ending the CBT adventure. Maybe you will establish a new tournament, someday!{NEWLINE}[+10k Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_UNSATISFIED", "CBT Tournament"},
		{"STR_CBT_TOURNAMENT_UNSATISFIED_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You yearn for another opponent to fight, but there is nobody strong enough left to be a challenge! You feel dissatisfaction which nothing can really slake... That damned Ogress has cursed you!{NEWLINE}[-200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_SPONSORS", "Charm Offensive"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_SPONSORS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You have organized a meeting to gain favors from your sponsors and find new contacts.{NEWLINE}[-$100k, +50 Cleaning Bills, Bounty Tokens (Jack, Zaxx and MA each) and Pers. Data]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_SUPERSTAR", "Superstar"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_SUPERSTAR_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You're immensely popular on the Ethyrnet! Your fans are sending you love letters!{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy, +20 Databases, +10 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_IMPRISONED", "Inmate"},
		{"STR_DUMBASS_IMPRISONED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your compulsive behaviour landed you in a jail. You had to pay a $25k fine to get out of there, but not before you've made a couple of friends!"},
		{"STR_JACKASS_ADHD", "Micromanagement"},
		{"STR_JACKASS_ADHD_DESCRIPTION", "Having woken up with a firm resolve to improve the overall efectiveness in the Hideout, you spent your day running from one place to another to correct mistakes, promote sound procedures, lecture some slackers and encourage some burn-outs. You also solved a number of complex issues in place of the Gals who normally should be doing this, but clearly are not up for this challenge. Now the Hideout really runs a little more smoothly, but also the crew seems grumblier than usual. Those ingrates!{NEWLINE}[+$50k, -50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKASS_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN", "Hardworking Captain"},
		{"STR_JACKASS_HARDWORKING_CAPTAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Anxious for some productive activity, you head down to the workshops to give your Runts a hand. They seem to appreciate the gesture, but also seem eager to keep you away from the machines and out of there as soon as possible, so you excuse yourself rather quickly and return to your quarters. Bummer...{NEWLINE}[-10 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKASS_FRAIL", "Health Issues"},
		{"STR_JACKASS_FRAIL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your spirit is strong, but your body is frail. This is a weakness your crew should never find out about. You're always on a lookout for miracle cures and rare foods, which is expensive, but also increases your medical knowledge.{NEWLINE}[-$100,000]"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You've found trouble.{NEWLINE}[-$10k, -300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_LOOTBOX", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_LOOTBOX_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You've found and appropriated some interesting loot!"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_FRIENDS", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_FRIENDS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You've made some friends and found useful contacts during your journey.{NEWLINE}[+10 Glamour, +10 Databases, +1 Journey Notes]"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_ENEMY", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_ENEMY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You've found an opponent, whom you've managed to subdue and capture."},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_ALLY", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_ALLY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You've found a potentially useful ally."},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_RAMPAGE", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_RAMPAGE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You desacrated a village temple and broke every possible taboo in at least 5 separate mutant communities. The locals are already sending complaints to the govt, to Jack, and even to the Mutant Alliance."},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_FINE", "Troubleseeking"},
		{"STR_TROUBLESEEKING_FINE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In your free time, you've engaged in seeking trouble. You beat up a govt officer on duty. You were fined by the court."},
		{"STR_TREASURE_HUNTING", "Treasure Hunting"},
		{"STR_TREASURE_HUNTING_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}As you ordered, Cap'n, we'll be on constant lookout for opportunities for a big treasure haul. The more Regions have a Hideout of ours in them, the more opportunities!"},
		{"STR_LOOTBOX_SCAVENGING", "Scavenged Supplies Extraction"},
		{"STR_LOOTBOX_SCAVENGING_UFOPEDIA", "The world is full of forgotten places, some of them as old as Old Earth, some abandoned due to various plagues and disasters, some swept away by Deep One invasions. There is still stuff to be looted in these places. Especially Lokk'Naars are famous for exploring them, due to their superhuman endurance, small statures and insatiable greed."},
		{"STR_LOOTBOX_SCAVENGING_ARCTIC", "Scavenge: Arctic"},
		{"STR_LOOTBOX_SCAVENGING_ANTARCTICA", "Scavenge: Antarctica"},
