		{"STR_JACKASS_EXPANSION_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "You have founded a $50,000 expedition to hunt for treasure in the area of your Hideout in {0}. They will soon return with their findings..."},
		{"STR_JACKASS_EXPANSION_EVENT_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "You have founded a $50,000 expedition to hunt for treasure in the area of your Hideout in {0}. However, they failed to find anything of value. This wild goose hunt has undermined their trust in your greatness (-75 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_DUNGEON_MASTER_EVENT", "Dungeon Master"},
		{"STR_DUNGEON_MASTER_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}The bold exploits happening in your Dungeon are whispered about far and wide, and many rich perverts want to pay good dolaro to visit it.{NEWLINE}[+75 Infamy, +$50k, +10 Zines]"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_RUTHLESS_STEAMROLL", "Know When to Hold 'Em"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_KNOW_WHEN_TO_HOLD_EM_RUTHLESS_STEAMROLL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your crew invited you over for a game of cards. You eagerly agreed, and thoroughly trashed them with your superior intellect, bravery and luck. Some of your opponents have the nerve to complain, but what can you do?{NEWLINE}[+$10,000, -5 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_INTERNAL_AUDIT", "Internal Audit"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_INTERNAL_AUDIT_DESCRIPTION", "Having wondered about how to make things better, you decide to randomly grill various crew members about their jobs, duties and results. It turns into a very busy day, but once it's over, you know that literally everyone in the Hideout knows their role perfectly well and is aware of all their transgressions! Including yourself!{NEWLINE}[+$15,000]"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_REIGN_AND_RULE", "Reign And Rule"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_REIGN_AND_RULE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}During one of your escapades, you saved some escaped fugitives from bounty hunters. Naturally, this sort of thing does not come for free...{NEWLINE}[+5 slaves]"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_INVINCIBLE_SUN", "The Invincible Sun"},
		{"STR_JACKSORE_INVINCIBLE_SUN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You dream of red skies looming above, while this world bathes in nuclear fire, burning away the extraterrestrial taint along most other things. You wake up scared, but also elated.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, +5 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_VIOLENT_SPREE", "Rampage"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_VIOLENT_SPREE_DESCRIPTION", "You're surrounded by idiots, and most people in general are stupid. This pisses you off often enough, but today your temper was especially foul. You flung into a violent rage and went outside to vent off some steam.{NEWLINE}[+10 Infamy, +Random Result]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_BAR_BRAWL", "Bar Brawl"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_BAR_BRAWL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You're surrounded by idiots, and most people in general are stupid. This pisses you off often enough, but today your temper was especially foul. You decided to visit a bar in Jackstown to get drunk. Predictably, it ended in a huge brawl.{NEWLINE}[+50 Infamy, +10 Capitatory Tax]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_PISSED", "Foul Mood"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_PISSED_DESCRIPTION", "You're surrounded by idiots, and most people in general are stupid. This pisses you off often enough, but today your temper was especially foul and your crew was unimpressed with your brooding.{NEWLINE}[-15 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_LUST", "Lust"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_LUST_DESCRIPTION", "Today you really needed to blow off some steam. You grabbed someone from Jackstown's tavern for your personal entertainment. The captive didn't complain too much, but you had to buy the silence of the witnesses for $1000.{NEWLINE}[Gained Random Companion]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_SLUDGEDIVE", "Sludge Study"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_SLUDGEDIVE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You've had enough with the sluggishness of your Brainers! You grabbed one of them and tossed her into the sludge below. You kept her there without food until she came up with something useful. You paid her $20,000 bonus.{NEWLINE}[Gained Mad Scribblings]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_CAPTIVES", "Aggravated Assault"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_CAPTIVES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Your crew has spotted a couple of pretty and young travellers, and your further behavior was dictated by your sadistic urges.{NEWLINE}[Robbed $3000 and other stuff]"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_SHOOTING", "Self-Therapy"},
		{"STR_AXCRAZY_SHOOTING_DESCRIPTION", "To calm yourself down, you've grabbed a gun and started shooting indiscriminately all around your Hideout! The crew is in awe.{NEWLINE}[+40 Infamy, -$5000]"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_OLD_MINES_TREASURE", "Old Mines"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_OLD_MINES_TREASURE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}While studying an ancient map, you locate an abandoned mine and decide to explore it. This was a great decision! You found something shiny!"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_OLD_MINES_MINEFIELD", "Old Mines"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_OLD_MINES_MINEFIELD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}While studying an ancient map, you locate an abandoned mine and decide to explore it. Unfortunately, you misread the label and ended up in the middle of an old minefield. How embarrassing.{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy, +5 Landmines]"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_OLD_MINES_OLD_BATTLEFIELD", "Old Mines"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_OLD_MINES_OLD_BATTLEFIELD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}While studying an ancient map, you locate an abandoned mine and decide to explore it. All you find is some rusted equipment, a few squatter skulls and very old marks of violence on the walls. Whatever happened here long ago, it was brutal.{NEWLINE}[+50 Scrap Metal, +25 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_FENG_CHOOY", "Feng Chooy"},
		{"STR_LAZYSORE_FENG_CHOOY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}An irresistible force compelled you to spend the whole day picking up all the empty bottles laying around your room and placing them upright, in regular patterns.{NEWLINE}[-15 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_BUY_BOOKS", "Book Nerd"},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_BUY_BOOKS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You have squandered $75,000 without regret to order a delivery of something you think to be a rare book. Now you're excited to open the package and see if you were right..."},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_TREASURE", "Ancient Treasure"},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_TREASURE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}When reading one of your books, you've found an ancient map with a treasure location. It has cost you $50,000 to fund an expedition to check it out. You reckon there is about 50% chance of success. Now, they have returned, and you're very excited to see if you were right..."},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_WISDOM", "Studies"},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_WISDOM_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}When reading one of your books, you've found a piece of ancient wisdom...{NEWLINE}[+10 Infamy, +1 Cultural Wealth]"},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_CAUGHT_UP", "Avid Reader"},
		{"STR_BOOKWORM_CAUGHT_UP_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You got so caught up in reading your books that the crew thought you got spirited out to another world! In a way it was true, but your duties as Captain got seriously neglected and the crew got loose. At least you've learned something...{NEWLINE}[-90 Infamy, +1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_DISAPPOINTED", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_DISAPPOINTED_DESCRIPTION", "While wandering the tunnels of your Hideout, you were looking for mysterious doors. Sadly, you didn't find any which lead to anywhere interesting. You're feeling deeply disappointed. You'd prefer the world to be more Gothic!{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_APHRODISIAC", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_APHRODISIAC_DESCRIPTION", "While wandering the tunnels of your Hideout, you've found a mysterious door. When you opened it, a cloud of mysterious gas has erupted from it. It is nice to recall, but not to relay, what was everyone doing before it dispersed. Now you have a lot of cleaning to do.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_FORBIDDEN_KNOWLEDGE", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_FORBIDDEN_KNOWLEDGE_DESCRIPTION", "While wandering the tunnels of your Hideout, you've found a mysterious door. Behind it, a room with an even more mysterious book which you of course took. Now everyone in the Hideout is having nightmares.{NEWLINE}[-75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_SPACESUITS", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_SPACESUITS_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found a long-sealed airlock, containing three unusual-looking space suits in good condition!"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_JUNK", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_JUNK_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found even more of the same junk as everywhere else.{NEWLINE}[Pile of Junk x10 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_MEDICAL_SUPPLIES", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_MEDICAL_SUPPLIES_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found an intact medical cabinet.{NEWLINE}[Medical Supplies x10 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_AIR_MISSILES", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_AIR_MISSILES_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found some old air-to-air missiles.{NEWLINE}[Seagull Missile x10 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_AIR_CANNON", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_AIR_CANNON_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found a broken aircraft cannon and some ammo.{NEWLINE}[50mm Cannon Parts x2, 50mm Shell x30, Scrap Metal x30 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_OLD_EARTH_WEAPON", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_OLD_EARTH_WEAPON_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found an old armory.{NEWLINE}[Old Earth Weapon Box x4 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_MEGASCORPION_NEST", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_MEGASCORPION_NEST_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found a cave where a Megascorpion nest used to be. We salvaged a good haul of chitin from their decrepit corpses.{NEWLINE}[Chitin x50 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_OLD_ARCHIVE", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_OLD_ARCHIVE_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found an old archive.{NEWLINE}[Old Earth Books, Old Money Briefcase x5 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_BOOBY_TRAP", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_BOOBY_TRAP_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. The door was booby trapped! Nobody was injured, but the hideout sustained $10,000 in damage."},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_EMPTY", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_EMPTY_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. The passage turned out to be empty and useless, so we at least salvaged the door, Cap'n.{NEWLINE}[Plastasteel x4 acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_CYBERKNIGHT", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_CYBERKNIGHT_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found a skeleton wearing remains of a power armor.{NEWLINE}[Power Armor Parts x1, Vibro Sword x1, and a Raygun with 4 Cells acquired]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_OLD_BOOTS", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_OLD_BOOTS_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found 100 Old Boots, but none of them fit."},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_BOTTOMLESS_PIT", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_BOTTOMLESS_PIT_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we only found a pit of an undeterminable depth. The Gals are seriously spooked.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_14MM_ROUNDS", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_14MM_ROUNDS_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Behind the door we found a bunch of 14mm ammo boxes."},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_SOREASS", "Secret Door"},
		{"STR_SECRET_DOOR_SOREASS_DESCRIPTION", "We found a hitherto unknown passage in our hideout. Being a Headstrong Captain, you're not tempted by it and order the door welded shut.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, -$250]"},
		{"STR_UNDERGROUND_ANOMALY_UAC", "Underground Anomaly"},
		{"STR_UNDERGROUND_ANOMALY_UAC_DESCRIPTION", "The Lokk'Naars informed us about a strange stone circle, located in the depths beneath our Hideout. When we sent our Runts there, they found something resembling a scene of a ritual: three desiccated corpses in UAC Space Suits, arranged around a glowing rock formation. The Runts salvaged everything and even managed to repair the suits.{NEWLINE}[+75 Infamy, -$7,500]"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_PERSONALITY_AUTOCHOICE_DUMBASS", "Crew Vote: Dumbass Captain"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_PERSONALITY_AUTOCHOICE_JACKASS", "Crew Vote: Jackass Captain"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_PERSONALITY_AUTOCHOICE_LAZYASS", "Crew Vote: Lazy-Ass Captain"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_PERSONALITY_AUTOCHOICE_SOREASS", "Crew Vote: Sore-Ass Captain"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_PERSONALITY_AUTOCHOICE_PUSSY", "Crew Vote: Captain Who?"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_PERSONALITY_AUTOCHOICE_DESC", "{NEWLINE}You haven't made a choice by yourself, so this is the choice your crew made for you...{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_VOODOO_SCARE", "Voodoo Scare"},
		{"STR_VOODOO_SCARE_DESCRIPTION", "Wild and slanderous rumors about our voodoo rituals are sweeping the countryside. I wish we did half the things they claim we do!{NEWLINE}[-75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_VOODOO_SCARE_AVERTED", "Voodoo Scare"},
		{"STR_VOODOO_SCARE_AVERTED_DESCRIPTION", "Wild and slanderous rumors about our voodoo rituals are sweeping the countryside. Thankfully, due to our Dark Dominion presence, we know how to turn this scare into awe...{NEWLINE}[+75 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SONIC_BOOM", "Sonic Boom"},
		{"STR_SONIC_BOOM_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Some local villagers claim to be 'repeatedly disturbed' by supersonic craft coming and going from our hideout. They threatened us with a lawsuit. I gave them $10000 to fuck off. What an outrage!"},
		{"STR_SACRIFICES", "Sacrifices"},
		{"STR_SACRIFICES_DESCRIPTION", "The local villagers brought us sacrifices to honor our divine mandate to be awesome.{NEWLINE}[Fruits, Vegetables and Meat acquired]"},
		{"STR_DESPERATE_SMUGGLER_LOOTBOX_STOLEN", "Desperate Smuggler"},
		{"STR_DESPERATE_SMUGGLER_LOOTBOX_STOLEN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The guy sought us out for us to take a Smuggler Strongbox off his hands as quick as possible. We mugged him to give it up, but we did not find it. So we took all his cash instead.{NEWLINE}[+$2000, -20 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_DESPERATE_SMUGGLER_LOOTBOX_BOUGHT", "Desperate Smuggler"},
		{"STR_DESPERATE_SMUGGLER_LOOTBOX_BOUGHT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The guy sought us out for us to take a Smuggler Strongbox off his hands as quick as possible. We bought it for a reasonable price of $65,000. Key was not included."},
		{"STR_DESPERATE_SMUGGLER_MYSTERYBOX_BOUGHT", "Desperate Smuggler"},
		{"STR_DESPERATE_SMUGGLER_MYSTERYBOX_BOUGHT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The guy sought us out for us to take a Smuggler Strongbox off his hands as quick as possible. We bought it for a reasonable price of $65,000. On the second look, though, this Strongbox seems kinda strange..."},
		{"STR_OMNIVENDER", "Omnivender"},
		{"STR_OMNIVENDER_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You've spotted a vending machine in one of Hideout's corridors. A slick, magnificient, elegant vending machine which definitely wasn't there before. Feeling a sudden urge to buy something, you shrugged and dropped $1 into its slot."},
		{"STR_MAD_GNOME_EVENT", "A Social Experiment"},
		{"STR_MAD_GNOME_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}The Gnome we keep in our dungeon has been saying weird things to our crew. This confused them enough to engage in bizarre behaviour. Morale suffered, but we learned a few interesting things.{NEWLINE}[-75 Infamy, +3 Zines]"},
		{"STR_MAD_GNOME_EVENT2", "Ungovernable Inmate"},
		{"STR_MAD_GNOME_EVENT2_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Gnome we keep in our dungeon has somehow escaped her bindings and went to scavenge various items to make her cell more comfortable. Then she shackled herself back. We'll better leave it at that...{NEWLINE}[-$5,000]"},
		{"STR_MAD_GNOME_EVENT3", "Gnome Xenology"},
		{"STR_MAD_GNOME_EVENT3_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A Gnome we're holding captive was assaulted by the Slime! An unspeakable spectacle followed...! However, she eventually managed to calm the creature down.{NEWLINE}[+7 Zines]"},
		{"STR_DRUNKEN_GNOME_EVENT", "Drunken Gnome"},
		{"STR_DRUNKEN_GNOME_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}A Gnome had somehow managed to sneak out of her containment and made a drunken rampage across our Hideout. I have pictures proving the crew wasn't exactly trying to stop her.{NEWLINE}[+3 Zines, -$20k damages]"},
		{"STR_GNOME_TECH_EVENT", "Gnome      Tech"},
		{"STR_GNOME_TECH_EVENT_FINISHED", "Gnome Tech Off"},
		{"STR_GNOME_TECH_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our contact with the Gnome Tech allows us to learn some knowledge from these mysterious beings..."},
		{"STR_REDUNDANCY", "Redundancy"},
		{"STR_REDUNDANCY_DESCRIPTION", "Our brainer locked herself up in the lab, with a microwave oven. Despite her best efforts, no scientific breakthroughs happened, but after she put the device back together, she ended up with enough leftover parts to build another one. So now we have two microwave ovens.{NEWLINE}[Consumer Goods acquired]"},
		{"STR_DRINKING_BINGE", "Drinking  Binge!!!"},
		{"STR_DRINKING_BINGE_DESCRIPTION", "Someone opens a bottle of moonshine, and before you can blink, the whole crew is having a wild party. They destroyed some equipment in drunken rage, but morale had improved.{NEWLINE}[+125 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_OPERATION_BROKEN_WAGON", "Operation Broken Wagon"},
		{"STR_OPERATION_BROKEN_WAGON_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A local peasant's wagon broke down and fell into a ditch. We had nothing better to do, so we went to help; we pulled the wagon out, fixed the wheel, and caught the frenzied Reaper which pulled it. Operation costs: $10, for beers. Operation result: +10 Infamy."},
		{"STR_ELECTION_MEDDLING_SHADOWY", "Election Meddling"},
		{"STR_ELECTION_MEDDLING_SHADOWY_DESCRIPTION", "A wealthy peasant came to us asking for help with him getting elected as the village soltis. He gave us $50,000 in exchange for our blessings. He seemed to be very interested in the topic of 'shadows'."},
		{"STR_ELECTION_MEDDLING_UNSUCCESSFUL", "Election Meddling"},
		{"STR_ELECTION_MEDDLING_UNSUCCESSFUL_DESCRIPTION", "A wealthy peasant came to us asking for help with him getting elected as the village soltis. He asked for a donation of $50,000 to his campaign and was... very persuasive. He promised to make us loved by the common man, in... many ways. Anyway, I'm sorry to inform that the candidate didn’t win anyway, so he's in no position to make good on his promise. Oh well, politics!"},
		{"STR_ELECTION_MEDDLING_SUCCESSFUL", "Election Meddling"},
		{"STR_ELECTION_MEDDLING_SUCCESSFUL_DESCRIPTION", "A wealthy peasant came to us asking for help with him getting elected as the village soltis. He asked for a donation of $50,000 to his campaign and was... very persuasive. He promised to make us loved by the common man, in... many ways. I have a good feeling about this, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CATGIRL_FROM_LAPUTA_EVENT", "Catgirl from Laputa"},
		{"STR_CATGIRL_FROM_LAPUTA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Catgirl, with whom we talked earlier, finally came to us. More precisely, she fell from the sky in a landing pod, in which one more passenger was found: the lifeless body of one of those Big Factions' purebloods. [+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_PUMA_SISTERS_PREQ_EVENT", "Puma Sisters"},
		{"STR_PUMA_SISTERS_PREQ", "Puma Sisters (Preq)"},
		{"STR_PUMA_SISTERS_PREQ_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We have drawn attention of a notorious couple of Catgirl bounty hunters... but they want to work for us - if we're famous enough!"},
		{"STR_ANNA_PUMA_EVENT", "Twins from Laputa"},
		{"STR_ANNA_PUMA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The infamous twin catgirl bounty hunters think we're tough enough to do great things together. Whether you like it or not, Anna Puma is on her way! [+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_UNI_PUMA_EVENT", "Twins from Laputa"},
		{"STR_UNI_PUMA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The infamous twin catgirl bounty hunters think we're tough enough to do great things together. Whether you like it or not, Uni Puma is on her way! [+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_MRSHAN_ADVENTURER_EVENT", "Catgirl from space"},
		{"STR_MRSHAN_ADVENTURER_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A Smuggler Ship asked us for landing near the Hideout: there is a brave Catgirl who heard about our struggle and wanted to join the ranks. You are glad to have such an ally, and the fact that the pirates' infamy thunders even outside the Solar system has encouraged the crew. [+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_MRSHAN_WARRIOR_EVENT", "Catgirl from space"},
		{"STR_MRSHAN_WARRIOR_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}An unidentified spaceship asked us for a permission to land a drop capsule near the Hideout: there is a Catgirl warrior who heard about our struggle and had petitioned an assignment to Earth. You are glad to have a new ally, moreover - she is a skilled soldier. [+250 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_MRSHAN_FIGHTER_EVENT", "Ace Catgirl"},
		{"STR_MRSHAN_FIGHTER_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A military interceptor starship asked us for landing near the Hideout: there is a Catgirl from elite Nekomimi forces who heard about our struggle and wanted to join the ranks. You are very happy to have such an ally. [+300 Infamy, Nekomimi Starship has docked]"},
		{"STR_JASMIRA_INTRODUCING_EVENT", "Catwoman in touch"},
		{"STR_JASMIRA_INTRODUCING_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "We didn't call the Nekomimi;{NEWLINE}they called us instead.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You see a Catwoman{NEWLINE}on the screen.{NEWLINE}Her smooth furless{NEWLINE}skin is a sign of an{NEWLINE}avid space traveler."},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_REQUEST_1_EVENT", "Nekomimi: trade request #1"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_REQUEST_1_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}From: Jasmira{NEWLINE}The House has become interested in the 'Forcefields' technology available to you and would like to study all the knowledge you have accumulated in this area. In exchange, you will get access to the power armors of Nekomimi elite warriors."},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_CAT_PATH_SECRET_DEAL", "Incoming Transmission"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_CAT_PATH_SECRET_DEAL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We are receiving a message from some honcho of the Nekomimi Network... they seem to be pleased."},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_CAT_PATH_SLANDER_EVENT", "Catophobia"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_CAT_PATH_SLANDER_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "Our sponsors are not happy about our close cooperation with the Nekomimi, claiming that we owe allegiance to them and not some alien freaks. Some even compare us to how Osiron started ages ago: as criminals turned alien collaborators.{NEWLINE}-100 Infamy"},
		{"STR_ASTROROCK_EVENT", "Astrorock!"},
		{"STR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Citizens of {0} have enjoyed your music! The first time in history Purebloods allowed mutants to give a concert on big scene. Perhaps this is the beginning of a thaw in a difficult interspecies relationship. It's a resounding success, Cap'n!{NEWLINE}[+$12,000,000; +3000 Infamy; +500 Glamour; +100 Culture. Also, one of the fans followed us]"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_EPIC", "Interstellar Astrorock!"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_EPIC_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}We recorded an awesome electronic track and sent it towards one of the inhabited planets. As soon as they heard our music, the aliens on the screen yelled merrily, many of them began to dance. This party went on for several hours!{NEWLINE}[+600 Infamy, + 200 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_GOOD", "Interstellar Astrorock!"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_GOOD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}We recorded an awesome electronic track and sent it towards one of the inhabited planets. The aliens were very happy to see us and even sang along!{NEWLINE}[+300 Infamy, +130 Glamour]"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_OK", "Interstellar Astrorock!"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_OK_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}We recorded an awesome electronic track and sent it towards one of the inhabited planets. The alien on the screen was nodding in time with our music, and then he offered us something to listen to. Cultural exchange had a success!{NEWLINE}[+200 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_BAD", "Interstellar Astrorock!"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_BAD_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}We recorded an awesome electronic track and sent it towards one of the inhabited planets. It seems that our music was not liked by the listener. Angrily staring at us with his eyes, he interrupted the connection.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_ABYSMAL", "Interstellar Astrorock!"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_ABYSMAL_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}We recorded an awesome electronic track and sent it towards one of the inhabited planets. The Star God appeared on the screen! He was very angry and threatened us with his withered fist. Several gals became unwell.{NEWLINE}[-500 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_SILENCE", "Silence"},
		{"STR_INTERSTELLAR_ASTROROCK_EVENT_SILENCE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our broadcasts were heard by those who were not supposed to hear them. A terrible creature with dead eyes appeared on the screen. It looked straight into the soul, and it was very scary. A few seconds later, our devices broke down. We will fix everything, but from now on it is better to use only secure hyperwave channels.{NEWLINE}[-$100k, -1000 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_00", "X-Piratez{NEWLINE}An OpenXCom Mod by Dioxine{NEWLINE}I claim no rights to any of the resources used, only to the way I wrote and put it together. Support free data!{NEWLINE}Last chance to turn this off. Continue only if you dare.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Remember: Read or Die."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_01", "An alarm rang all across the Academy's secret lab. The test subjects were escaping."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_02_A", "Guards scrambled to restrain them, but the mutants, naive as they were, possessed far superior strength, speed, and motivation. And most importantly, they already laid their hands on some weapons. Explosions, fire, and chaos were spreading."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_02_B", "Unsure of everything but their desire to break free, the mutants made it to the landing pads. Hellerium burning in their veins and thoughts racing in their heads, they took a small transport craft. To their relief, Academy ships had very simple controls. Disabling the autopilot was as simple as hitting it with a hammer. Soon they were speeding into the night. They had escaped."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_03", "The night sky was vast and mysterious. They knew nothing about the world; neither their childhood in the secluded villages deep within Uber Zones, nor the bedtime stories and dreams they shared in captivity, nor the sanitized knowledge fed to them by their teachers, could have prepared them for such freedom."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_03_B", "For over a decade, the life of these young mutants was contained within the sterile corridors of the underground base; it was a regulated life of study, exercises and tests under the watchful, cold gaze of the all-female staff and its weird head scientist, Dr. X. Her obsession with their performance, her mix of pride, lust and... genuine sympathy was the closest thing to human affection they experienced in that place."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_04", "There was only a single clue as where to go now. Their leader had a dream about a woman with unnaturally violet eyes who provided a set of coordinates. Maybe it was insane to pin their hopes on a dream, but they'd already done it once before - a dream was what spurred them to break free. They had no other option now; they knew nothing else."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_05", "They made peace with their gods and followed through until the break of dawn. The vast mystery of darkness was replaced an endless expanse of strange vistas bathing in the morning sun; an abundance of possibilities and a sea of information that they couldn't make much sense of."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_06", "Nearing their destination, they saw sparse villages separated by swathes of wilderness. A quite standard landscape in these times, but it was all so new to them."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_07", "They landed in a desolate valley, a small band of ragged castaways with nothing but a dream quest. The only proof of it being real was a small, drill-shaped amulet they had. The amulet that turned out to be a key, fitting a keyhole they found half-buried in the ground. And when the key was turned, they could only watch in amazement as part of a hillside slowly began to open, exposing a cavernous entrance."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_08", "Inside they found an underground complex, seemingly abandoned for centuries. But to them it was a hidden fortress, a roof above their heads; and below it, they found a huge pool of Hellerium sludge. Their Uber mutant metabolism needed the energy of Hellerium to function, meaning the sludge made the complex habitable to them. It was a good place to set up a new village, and that is what they decided to do."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_09", "Life was simple in the first weeks; they met with local villagers, they hunted and traded, they made their new hideout a real home."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_10", "But the idyll couldn't last forever. A heavily armed convoy arrived in the valley. The arrivals said they spoke on behalf of local tribes, the Mutant Alliance, as well as governments of the planet. They said they represented an alliance of peoples tyrannized by the Academy and their ilk: Earthlings who sold out their souls to the Star Gods. The Star Gods, masters of a Stellar Empire the Earth was occupied by for many centuries now."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_11", "Negotiations were held. Why should the castaways be content with what they are, if they could become so much more? The hideout they'd found - especially the old laboratory inside of it - contained the power to change the world, even if only by a little. The visitors offered an alliance on one condition: if the mutants dared to act like real masters of the castle they found, and not just use it selfishly like common bandits. Alternatively, the mutants could vacate the facility and seek their fortunes elsewhere. Earth already had bandits aplenty, and was in a dire need of brave warriors instead."},
		{"STR_CUTSCENE_INTRO_12", "They decided to stay, to agree to this attachment, gaining in exchange the means to make this hideout their safe harbor, from which they would set out to engage in adventure; and thus begins our story..."},
		{"AURA_ACID_RAIN", "Acid Rain"},
		{"AURA_MAGMA_BURN", "Burning Air"},
		{"AURA_POISON_GAS", "Poisonous Fumes"},
		{"AURA_DUST_STORM", "Dust Storm"},
		{"AURA_COLD", "Freezing Cold"},
		{"AURA_COLD_INTENSE", "Freezing Cold"},
		{"AURA_COLD_DEADLY", "Freezing Cold"},
		{"AURA_COLD_GHASTLY", "Freezing Cold"},
		{"STR_AURA_HEAT_TXT", "It's scorching hot! Taking Stun damage!"},
		{"STR_AURA_COLD_TXT", "It's freezing! Energy is drained!"},
		{"STR_AURA_COLD_INTENSE_TXT", "Warning! Extreme cold!"},
		{"STR_AURA_COLD_DEADLY_TXT", "You feel the cold of the void."},
		{"STR_AURA_COLD_GHASTLY_TXT", "The ghastly cold saps your resolve."},
		{"STR_AURA_FRESHNESS_TXT", "Too excited to lose Freshness!"},
		{"STR_ACID_RAIN_TXT", "It's raining acid! It hurts!!!"},
		{"STR_DUST_STORM_TXT", "Dust Storm! It gets everywhere!"},
		{"STR_MAGMA_BURN_TXT", "It burns! It burns!"},
		{"STR_POISON_GAS_TXT", "The air is full of poisonous fumes!"},
		{"STR_RADIATION_TXT", "Radiation damages Freshness and Shields."},
		{"STR_RADIATION_STRONG_TXT", "High Radiation! Fresh and Shield damage!"},
		{"STR_AURA_PSYCHEDELIC_TXT", "The air is ripe with psychedelics..."},
		{"STR_AURA_FEAR_TXT", "Governor's oppressive aura is lowering our Morale!"},
		{"STR_AURA_BRAVERY_TXT", "Not a Step Back! Gals gain extra Morale!"},
		{"STR_AURA_ENEMY_MORALE_TXT", "Defenders receive Morale buff!"},
		{"STR_LOC_SIBERIA", "Siberia Base Investigation"},
		{"STR_MARKER_XCOM_FILES", "Mysterious Siberia Base"},
		{"STR_ALERT_XCOM_FILES", "Siberia Base Found!"},
		{"STR_LOC_SIBERIA_BRIEFING", "We've finally found the location of the ancient base our interrogations hinted at. We need to secure any tech data we find. We detect a large enemy presence on the ground and high energy signatures.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Furious."},
		{"STR_VESSEL_FOOT_PATROL_NECRO_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A pack of sickly-looking, black-clad bandits is besieging a lone farmhouse here. We could land and try breaking the siege. The air smells of tasty Hellerium, but these guys don't look normal..."},
		{"STR_LOC_TAVERN", "A Party!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_TAVERN", "Party Location"},
		{"STR_ALERT_TAVERN", "{NEWLINE}Awesome Party Detected In"},
		{"STR_MISSION_TAVERN", "A Party!"},
		{"STR_LOC_TAVERN_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Hands want to go to a party to blow off some steam; and not just any party, either. They're sayin' that there is no party like the party currently being held at a certain tavern on the outskirts of this city. If you can't get at least some of them there, they will be disappointed. Only craft with 13 or less max crew allowed, except interceptors. PS. the 'what to wear text' lies, don't believe anyone - FBB."},
		{"STR_FLOATER_MANSION", "Guild (Mansion)"},
		{"STR_LOC_EMANSION", "Mansion Invasion"},
		{"STR_MARKER_EMANSION", "Exquisite Mansion"},
		{"STR_ALERT_EMANSION", "Mansion Robbery Opportunity!"},
		{"STR_LOC_EMANSION_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}This place be holdin' many a treasure! We will launch a sneaky attack. Any non-Infiltration equipment we're carrying will be sent to the Hideout now. We have 36 Turns before the enemy cavalry arrives, after which time, anything and anyone not on the green escape zones on the roof will be LOST. We can also try to defeat them all and take everything!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_PIR_EMANSION", "!Mansion Invasions!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_PIR_EMANSION_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}There are rich mansions around the world, waiting to be robbed! Yet them defenses are too strong for a frontal assault. We need to go sneaky by dressing up as servants, and then escape from the roof. Therefore only maid, nurse, dress, thieving, and highly magical outfits are allowed. Lacking these, we'll scrounge up some maid outfits inside. Also only Infiltration-type items can be sneaked in. For getaway, we need a fast or inconspicuous ship.{NEWLINE}WARNING: the time to finish the mission will be limited, and who knows where our gear is gonna end up, so it's better not to take anything that isn't held in inventories.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_LOC_EMANSION_GUILD_REP", "Executive Retreat"},
		{"STR_ALERT_EMANSION_GUILD_REP", "Mansion Assault Opportunity!"},
		{"STR_LOC_EMANSION_GUILD_REP_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}We have located one of Guild mansions. If we strike fast and hard, we can deal a serious blow to Guild's reputation, and possibly capture some Reps, too. Not to even mention the loot! The mansion will be swarming with security, including a contingent of Bodyguards, but at least they shouldn't be packing any explosives. We will land on the roof, normal Mansion craft restrictions thus apply, we can't take heavy tanks either, but we don't need to play stealth this time."},
		{"STR_MISSION_PIR_EMANSION_GUILD_REP", "!Executive Retreats!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_PIR_EMANSION_GUILD_REP_UFOPEDIA", "The Guild maintains a bunch of expensive mansions on Earth, not to really live there, but to use them as social meeting places to influence Govt politicians and other important figures. Having made some serious inroads into Guild security patterns, and having friends in high places, we can now create opportunities to strike these mansions, making the Guild think they are about to receive a visit from a Govt General. This way we will bypass air defenses and ensure that Guild Reps are present."},
		{"STR_MISSION_NINJA_APC_RAID", "Ninja Raid"},
		{"STR_NINJA_APC_RAID_SITE", "Help the Lokk'Naars"},
		{"STR_NINJA_ESCALATION_1", "Interfered with Narlocks"},
		{"STR_NINJA_ESCALATION_2", "Narlocks Spied on Hideout"},
		{"STR_NINJA_ESCALATION_3", "Ninja Weak Squad Defeated"},
		{"STR_NINJA_ESCALATION_4", "Ninja APC Squad Defeated"},
		{"STR_NINJA_ESCALATION_5", "Ninjas Go After Govts"},
		{"STR_NINJA_ESCALATION_6", "Officers Defended from Ninjas"},
		{"STR_NINJA_WAR_READY", "Ready for Ninja War"},
		{"STR_NINJA_WAR_READY_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You have amassed enough knowledge to start a full scale war with the Ninjas, Cap'n. If you do that, you'll be able to attack them directly, and most of their current pesky activities will stop. However, they'll be also forced to show the true extent of their power..."},
		{"STR_GODS_WILL_BE_WATCHING", "Demon Gods Will Be Watching"},
		{"STR_GODS_WILL_BE_WATCHING_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You sense that the Shadowmasters are bending this hellish reality to their will, creating an unlikely destiny. The Sky Ninjas are out to get you, unprovoked. But this is what you have asked for. This is what you have been condemned to."},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE", "Help the Lokk'Naars"},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE_2", "Help the Lokk'Naars"},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE_NARLOCK", "Help the Lokk'Naars"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOKNAR_VILLAGE", "Lokk'Naar Village"},
		{"STR_ALERT_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE", "Help the Lokk'Naars"},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE_NARLOCK_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We have received a word from Jack that the evil Narlocks are making a rodeo in one of the rival Lokk'Naar villages. Jack promises to reward us in apples for repelling the Narlock assault squad - when Jack has enough to spare. However, who can tell what will happen, if we take part in this ancestral feud... Maybe it'd be better to ignore it?{NEWLINE}Weather: Warm. Sea: Worrying."},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE_BRIEFING", "We have received a word from Jack that the Sky Ninjas are occupying one of the Lokk'Naar villages in retaliation for our strike against their evil Narlock masters. The Ninjas let most of the locals to escape, but they also challenged us to show up, so it will cost us reputation if we refuse, or even worse, appear and flee.{NEWLINE}Weather: Warm. Sea: Worrying."},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_VILLAGE_DEFENSE_2_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We have received a word from Jack that one of the Lokk'Naar villages is being attacked by Ratmen raiders. We'll be rewarded in apples for repelling this attack - when Jack has enough to spare.{NEWLINE}Weather: Warm. Sea: Normal."},
		{"STR_NINJA_APC_RAID_SITE_BRIEFING", "We have received a word from Jack that one of the Lokk'Naar villages is being attacked by a well-armed Ninja party in an armored vehicle. His militia was mobilized and is putting up an uneven fight against the invaders. He won't hold it against us if we don't show up, but our help will be rewarded. We only have 5-10 hours to arrive there.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Rough."},
		{"STR_MISSION_CHURCH_CAMP", "*Neophyte Boot Camp*"},
		{"STR_MISSION_CHURCH_CAMP_UFOPEDIA", "Oi, Cap'n! Raiding these temples is fun, but it gets repetitive, no? We figured out, that as we train our recruits, so the Church has to run their own courses to whip all these Neophytes into some shape as well. And what does it mean for us? Heaps of guns and free target practice! We'll be on the lookout for these Camps from now on, and get back to you when we find one!"},
		{"STR_LOC_ATRIUM_CHURCH", "Church Boot Camp"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CHURCH_CAMP", "Church Boot Camp"},
		{"STR_CHURCH_CAMP_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}The Church of Sirius is training a new batch of fanatics in this jungle camp. Let's show them the error of their ways and loot their weapons!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Uneven."},
		{"STR_LOC_BEASTMEN_ALTAR", "Blood Rituals"},
		{"STR_MARKER_BEASTMEN_ALTAR", "Beastman Altar"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BEASTMEN_ALTAR", "Blood Rituals"},
		{"STR_LOC_BEASTMEN_ALTAR_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}A group of deplorable beings has caught an adventurer and prepares to perform a macabre sacrifice to their gods!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Uneven."},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_SACRIFICE", "Demonic Sacrifices"},
		{"STR_MARKER_DEMON_SACRIFICE", "Sacrificial Altar"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DEMON_SACRIFICE", "Demonic Sacrifices"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_SACRIFICE_BRIEFING", "Tracking for Shadow Lamp emissions allowed us to pinpoint this location as the likely place of the rumored demonic sacrifices. If we move out fast, we might be able to rescue them!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Rough."},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOM_OUTPOST", "Outpost of Hell"},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOM_OUTPOST_TITLE", "Outpost of Hell"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DOOM_OUTPOST", "Outpost of Hell"},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOM_OUTPOST_BRIEFING", "From: Mystery Patron{NEWLINE}My champion! It is time for your Trial of Brawn. A major demonic incursion has taken place. Evil energy emanates from there in unprecedented amounts. You must eradicate this foothold of the demonic forces, before some worse calamity happens. I believe their remains can hold a clue on how to stop them, but this kind of research is contrary to my nature... Thankfully, I have you!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEMON_BAIT_PREQ", "Demon Bait (Preq)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEMON_BAIT", "!Demon Bait!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEMON_BAIT_2", "!More Demon Baits!"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT", "Demon Bait"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_1", "Demon Bait"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_2", "Demon Bait"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_TRAP", "Demon Bait"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_MEAT_MAZE", "Demon Bait"},
		{"STR_DEMON_BAIT_TRAP_DONE", "Demon Bait Conquered"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DEMON_BAIT", "Demon Bait"},
		{"STR_INCOMING_MESSAGE", "Incoming Message..."},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A Gnome says she can find a Demon Gate in this location, and salvage it for Demonic Essence... Assuming that everything goes as planned!{NEWLINE}Use any craft, but only 1 unit will be spawned. No tanks."},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_TRAP_1_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Erm, Capt'n, so you're probably wondering what happened. Well, I was kind of captured, and I kind of lost all my things. Thankfully I was able to ...convince them to not kill me yet, but now... It seems I'm not in Kansas anymore. That is, I'm on the other side of the portal.'"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_TRAP_2_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'I'm still alive, Cap'n... in fact, the Shadowrealms feel great! If not for having to run in the nude while under constant threat of getting iced! But now a question arises... Should try to escape ASAP - the exit should be located somewhere on the ground level - or should I... clear this place for maximum gain?'"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_TRAP_3_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'I can sense another demon entering the area. It feels... large, and shadowy. Looks like the longer I stay here, the more of them will be coming... Scary, huh?'"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_MEAT_MAZE_1_BRIEFING", "'Well, so I fell into the portal, all right? But there were no Dark Ones here. Instead, a bunch of tentacles grabbed me, stripped off my belongings and... Well, I admit, it was kind of fun until they just dumped me, naked and alone, in this weird flesh maze! How ungentlemanly!'"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_MEAT_MAZE_2_BRIEFING", "'Hey, what's with that nice box? Did the tentacle monster leave it here for me? Oh my, it shouldn't have! Maybe it's not so ungentlemanly after all... Yet, I don't want to stay here forever. I believe the way back to the portal should be somewhere due West...'"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_MEAT_MAZE_3_BRIEFING", "'I hear a lot of slithering sounds from the East! It seems they've finally noticed my presence, and are coming after my... life fluids! I gotta hurry up. But where was that portal? I THINK it's more due NW than SW...'"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEMON_BAIT_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A Gnome tells you that her research on Dark Ones gave her an idea for further explorations, if she is given funds and allowed to work alone on field trips. If you're on board with this, investigate the !Demon Bait! project. Naturally, Gnome soldiers will be required to participate in these missions."},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEMON_BAIT_UFOPEDIA", "Gnomes think that our world is subjected to a rising number of assaults by Dark Ones, and they propose a novel way to profit from it. They excitedly say they can 'stalk the demons' to pinpoint their elusive portals, and investigate them. This however supposedly requires Gnomes to work alone, because any outside interference would just 'get in the way of the exploration'. But even if it's all true, can a little Gnome defeat a gaggle of demons?"},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEMON_BAIT_2_UFOPEDIA", "The Gnomes are yearning for more adventures with the demons, and, having analyzed their reports, now we can provide them with this unusual form of entertainment from which sane people would run away really fast. We can help the Gnomes to find more portals, and lure the demons to pull them into the Shadowrealms more often. Gnomes get their experiences and scientific observations, we get loot, they can do jobs which would be death to others, why should we question their strange tastes?"},
		{"STR_DEMON_BAIT_TRAP_DONE_UFOPEDIA", "During one of her excursions against Demons, our Gnome made a slip and ended up trapped in the Shadowrealms beyond the portal. Yet, against the odds, she managed to survive and return home with new knowledge. We can exploit these and go for !More Demon Baits!, which will double their number and increase the chance of random portal trips."},
		{"STR_LOC_TENTACLE_CAVE", "Tentacle Pit"},
		{"STR_LOC_TENTACLE_CAVE_PREQ", "Tentacle Pit (Preq)"},
		{"STR_ALERT_TENTACLE_CAVE", "Tentacle Pit Located!"},
		{"STR_TENTACLE_CAVE_DONE", "Tentacle Pit Cleared"},
		{"STR_LOC_TENTACLE_CAVE_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You have to calm down an excited Gnome who tells you that the tentacle monsters do exist, and they, in fact, have a nest right under your Hideout! She insists that an expedition should be sent to investigate these 'marvelous creatures'. And by expedition, she means a single person, that is her, others would only interrupt the delicate research!{NEWLINE}Depth: Average. Small People Only. Use any craft, but only 1 unit will be spawned.{NEWLINE}Mission will keep respawning until cleared."},
		{"STR_LOC_APOC_TUNNEL", "Tunnels of Apocalypse"},
		{"STR_LOC_APOC_TUNNEL_TITLE", "Tunnels of Apocalypse"},
		{"STR_ALERT_APOC_TUNNEL", "Tunnels of Apocalypse"},
		{"STR_LOC_APOC_TUNNEL_BRIEFING", "From: Mystery Patron{NEWLINE}My champion! It is time for your Trial of Savvy. The Cult of Apocalypse is using this site to summon demons. I believe a certain artifact, called 'Grimoire of Transfiguration', is responsible. You must capture this item if we are to stand any chance at stopping them! Their stronghold is heavily guarded, but I trust your resourcefulness will allow you to penetrate deep into the complex and retrieve the artifact from their vaults! Be careful of the upper level overhead.{NEWLINE}Nonflying heavy armor and tanks disallowed due to difficult terrain. Look for yellow exit tiles."},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID", "Zombie Panic"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID_TITLE", "Zombie Panic"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID", "Zombie Panic"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID", "Zombie Panic"},
		{"STR_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID_DONE", "Zombie Panic (Done)"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID_BRIEFING", "From: Mystery Patron{NEWLINE}My champion! It is time for your Trial of Brains. Zombies started appearing in this peaceful hamlet, and they do it in huge numbers, seemingly out of nowhere. Please, figure out the source of this evil plague, as I suspect some malicious intelligence behind it."},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_PYRAMID_WON_TXT", "It's done. You have prevailed. When you take a look at the landscape from above, you notice that the black pyramids which still had working portals inside, start disappearing in flashes of red light. The horror is finally over... or is it?"},
		{"STR_LOC_TABERNA_DEL_DIABLO", "Taberna Del Diablo"},
		{"STR_MARKER_TABERNA_DEL_DIABLO", "Taberna Del Diablo"},
		{"STR_ALERT_TABERNA_DEL_DIABLO", "Taberna Del Diablo"},
		{"STR_LOC_TABERNA_DEL_DIABLO_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}That is what the place is called; it likely means 'welcome, weary travellers' or something like that. Exploring Tabernas sounds like our kind of thing, so why won't we pack all the necessary party supplies and give the place a closer look? Might turn out to be a good forward operations base in the future.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Stormy."},
		{"STR_LOC_RATLING_VILLAGE", "Ratmen Rodeo"},
		{"STR_MARKER_RATLING_VILLAGE", "Ratmen Village"},
		{"STR_ALERT_RATLING_VILLAGE", "Ratmen Rodeo"},
		{"STR_LOC_RATLING_VILLAGE_BRIEFING", "We have found a ramshackle 'village' of them Ratmen. They're known as scurvy thieves and bandits, even their leaders go by a shady title of 'swaggins'. Hopefully they hid their stash of stolen goods here. And even if they didn't, no one is going to miss these good-for-nothings!{NEWLINE}Weather: Warm. Sea: Normal."},
		{"STR_LOC_HT_HOUSE", "Bring Down the Watchtower"},
		{"STR_MARKER_HT_HOUSE", "Watchtower"},
		{"STR_ALERT_HT_HOUSE", "Bring Down The Watchtower"},
		{"STR_LOC_HT_HOUSE_BRIEFING", "Dis building be used by them Big Factions to spy on the local people so they can come up with some new taxes or other villainy. The Factions might be big, but the tower be small, so let's get to work, nay, Cap'n? We just need to find a way to defeat or fool the robotic guard - beware of the Curse of the Machine!{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Gentle."},
		{"STR_LOC_ISOLATED_VALLEY", "Isolated Valley"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ISOLATED_VALLEY", "Isolated Valley"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ISOLATED_VALLEY", "Isolated Valley"},
		{"STR_LOC_ISOLATED_VALLEY_BRIEFING", "The Pureblood inhabitants of this place grew peaceful and harmless, trusting their safety in their remoteness and the power of a strange shrine they worship. But time waits for no one, and the fools would be destroyed sooner or later. If we will interfere, it will hasten this change, since the forces of evil will follow our wake - but at least some of the inhabitants stand a chance of surviving, and the mysteries of the shrine will end up in worthy (our) hands. However, the local elders won't trust mutants nor foreign males enough to let them in peacefully.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: No Escape!"},
		{"STR_LOC_GOVT_CAR", "Stranded Govt Agent"},
		{"STR_MARKER_GOVT_CAR", "Stranded Govt Agent"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GOVT_CAR", "Stranded Govt Agent"},
		{"STR_LOC_GOVT_CAR_BRIEFING", "One of the Provincial Govts has lost a squad in this area during a false flag operation and now cannot rescue their own men from the local bandits due to something called 'plausible deniability'. If we manage to clear the place out, they will pay us a good ransom for any Agents we manage to recover.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_BAD_COMPANY", "Bad Company"},
		{"STR_MARKER_BAD_COMPANY", "Bad Company Warehouse"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BAD_COMPANY", "Bad Company"},
		{"STR_LOC_BAD_COMPANY_BRIEFING", "The local police forces have a hunch about this warehouse, belonging to some shifty fruit company. However they seem to be hesitant to go in, because the bandits are well armed (possibly even including an armored car). We are to clear the place so they can obtain evidence, but they set us several rules: 1. We must be able to pass for locals, which means no Ubers, Lokk'naars or other obvious foreigners. 2. No tanks. 3. No craft; we will arrive as a 'fruit delivery convoy'.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Rough."},
		{"STR_LOC_DEATH_AND_TAXES", "Death and Taxes"},
		{"STR_MARKER_DEATH_AND_TAXES", "Death and Taxes"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DEATH_AND_TAXES", "Death and Taxes"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEATH_AND_TAXES_BRIEFING", "The local Govt has a job for us. They say that they cannot handle their own corrupt officials, who keep 'taxing' the locals of this remote area for their private profit. If we bring death to them, we can keep the taxes. We also got a 'fair warning' that the evildoers are likely to take hostages, and if these hostages die, the Govt won't be pleased. They won't hold it against us if we refuse, but can we miss out on the loot?{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_FOOD_PIRATES", "Food Piracy"},
		{"STR_MARKER_FOOD_PIRATES", "Food Piracy"},
		{"STR_ALERT_FOOD_PIRATES", "Food Piracy"},
		{"STR_LOC_FOOD_PIRATES_BRIEFING", "In this location, there is an Uber Wheat farm run by bandits. They're using slave labour from the surrounding villages and selling the harvest to the Guild. Due to such practices, food is always expensive in mutant communities. Crashing this whole business down can surely bring us a lot of fame.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_PRECINT13", "Precinct Under Siege"},
		{"STR_ALERT_PRECINT13", "Precinct Under Siege"},
		{"STR_MARKER_PRECINT13", "Govt Precinct"},
		{"STR_PRECINT13_BRIEFING", "Bandits are besieging Govt cops in this place. These cops must think highly of us (for whatever reason), or are desperate enough to call our help. If we ignore this situation, we'll lose some potential friends. Mission rules:{NEWLINE}>No escape, our stuff will be randomly stashed at the Precinct.{NEWLINE}>Only Mostly Harmless equipment. The locals don't want us to blow up their town.{NEWLINE}>The jail in the west was breached, letting loose a few very angry Ogre Convicts.{NEWLINE}>The cops expect multiple waves of attacks. If we rout the bandits quickly, we can prevent this."},
		{"STR_DETECITIVE_PAPERS", "Govt Detective Papers"},
		{"STR_PRECINT_ATTACK_ORDERS", "Precinct Attack Orders"},
		{"STR_PRECINT_ATTACK_ORDERS_UFOPEDIA", "We have recovered evidence indicating that Megapol organizes gang attacks on Govt precincts, to drive the Govt forces out and establish Highwaymen stations in their place. This evidence, obtained through helping the beleaguered cops, can win us some points with the Govts.{NEWLINE}+500 Infamy."},
		{"STR_LOC_DRIFTER_CAMP", "Bandits!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_DRIFTER_CAMP", "Drifter Camp"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DRIFTER_CAMP", "Bandits!"},
		{"STR_DRIFTER_CAMP_BRIEFING", "There is no honor amongst Drifters. Our contacts amongst Drifters and other bandits sold us the location of this camp, where a small band is resting after scoring some good haul. Appropriation of stolen goods is techically not a theft, so we can effect an ownership change with a clear conscience.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Mostly Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAMP_SMALL", "Bandits!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_BANDIT_CAMP_SMALL", "Small Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BANDIT_CAMP_SMALL", "Bandits!"},
		{"STR_BANDIT_CAMP_SMALL_BRIEFING", "We got a word about a small band of good-for-nothings operating in this area and harassing the Black Market supply lines. Why do we want to murder them? Well, first off, it won't be too hard, second, the Black Market will notice us, third, the bandits might be a source of guns and other goods nobody will miss. Except for the bandits, naturally, but it's not like we plan to cozy up to them anyway. I advise to equip some long-range guns instead. Cry havoc!{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_PREPPERS", "The Truth is Out There"},
		{"STR_MARKER_PREPPERS", "Prepper Camp"},
		{"STR_ALERT_PREPPERS", "The Truth is Out There"},
		{"STR_LOC_PREPPERS_BRIEFING", "We've got a hit mission from one of the Govts. An armed and dangerous group of 'preppers' has holed up in some remote village and is broadcasting messages on how the Govt is collaborating with evil aliens. Unclear what these guys are prepping for, since it's hundreds of years after the aliens have conquered us, but the preppers have protection of the Church of Sirius and the Govt can't go against them openly.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_SURVHOUSE_WASTE", "The Sniper"},
		{"STR_LOC_SURVHOUSE_VILAGE", "The Sniper"},
		{"STR_LOC_SURVHOUSE_JUNGLE", "The Sniper"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SURVHOUSE", "Sniper's Last Stand"},
		{"STR_LOC_SURVHOUSE_BRIEFING", "A guy on the Ethyrnet, claiming to be a dangerous fugitive, was known for unmasking corruption and crime within law enforcement agencies. Looks like he was finally found out, and an assault section of Stormrats, backed by a squad of Highwaymen, is preparing to storm his house. If he's really that dangerous, he could be a fine recruit. If he's just a poser, at least he might have some rare data. On the other hand, we can refrain from sticking our noses into this issue for an easy +50 Infamy.{NEWLINE}Warning: entrances to his house are likely to be booby-trapped, pay close attention to your Minimap!"},
		{"STR_ALERT_HUMANIST_TANK_TEST", "Humanist Tank Tests"},
		{"STR_LOC_HUMANIST_TANK_TEST", "Humanist Tank Tests"},
		{"STR_MARKER_HUMANIST_TANK_TEST", "Humanist Tank Tests"},
		{"STR_HUMANIST_TANK_TEST_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Humanists are testing their new model of a small, automated tank in this location. The tank is heavily armored but has only a small squad to support it. We could play heroes and try to save the locals, but gathering information on this machine can be even more valuable.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Dangerous."},
		{"STR_ALERT_WITCH_QUEST", "Witch Quest!"},
		{"STR_LOC_WITCH_QUEST_ACADEMY", "Witch Quest: Love and Beauty"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_ACADEMY_DONE", "Love and Beauty Quest Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WITCH_QUEST_ACADEMY", "Love and Beauty"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_ACADEMY_BRIEFING", "FROM: 'Golden Rose', the blonde Witch{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Hello, my sweet, burly pirate! We need to keep spreading beauty across the world, and the biggest problem is the Academy; their girls are ugly and frigid. Time to heat them up! And if you still hesitate, know that there are many cute Students there to seize! Good Hunting!'{NEWLINE}Rules: Little Girls Only, No Tanks, No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_WITCH_QUEST_MONASTERY", "Witch Quest: Monastery of Death"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_MONASTERY_DONE", "Monastery of Death Quest Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WITCH_QUEST_MONASTERY", "Monastery of Death"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_MONASTERY_BRIEFING", "FROM: 'Dark Temptress', the pink-haired Witch{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'The Church of Sirius trains their warrior girls here. But is their faith truly stronger than Death? Can YOU look into Her face? Game - start!'{NEWLINE}Rules: Little Girls Only, No Tanks, No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_WITCH_QUEST_RAGNAROCK", "Witch Quest: The Ragnarock"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_RAGNAROCK_DONE", "The Ragnarock Quest Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WITCH_QUEST_RAGNAROCK", "Ragnarock"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_RAGNAROCK_BRIEFING", "FROM: 'Flame Dancer', the redhead Witch{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Howdy, Pardner! Did ya know how cool my Ragnarock is? It can telly-porty to any city, so I can travel out of Doom Harbour without leaving my home! But, y'know, it cannot take me to the place I need to be to do some stuff I have to do. Meantimes, vermin have multiplied 'round the Ragnarock. I dun like doin' household chores, be a darlin' and help me out there, will ya?'{NEWLINE}Rules: No Vehicles/Pwr Armor, No Strong Races, No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_WITCH_QUEST_BROTHERHOOD", "Witch Quest: The Brotherhood"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_BROTHERHOOD_DONE", "The Brotherhood Quest Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WITCH_QUEST_BROTHERHOOD", "Brotherhood Meeting"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_BROTHERHOOD_BRIEFING", "FROM: 'She-Devil', the black-haired Witch{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Hey, chooser. Do you know about the Assassin Brotherhood? They go way back, to the fall of Mummu, and they used to be big and mighty at times, for example as Men in Black. My job for you is to check if they haven't become rusty. Some of their mid-level brothers have a meeting in this town, with blackjack, hookers and some customary human sacrifices. Assassinate the Assassins? Haha.'{NEWLINE}Rules: No Vehicles/Power Armor, No Ubers, No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_WITCH_QUEST_VAMPIRE_NEST", "Witch Quest: Nocturne in Red"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_VAMPIRE_NEST_DONE", "Nocturne in Red Quest Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WITCH_QUEST_VAMPIRE_NEST", "Nocturne in Red"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_VAMPIRE_NEST_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}FROM: 'Ice Blade', the blue-haired Witch{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'My Hero! I have a truly joyous challenge for you! Deep under this city, a Vampire Lord made himself a lair, teeming with his slaves. Beware, my Hero, for he is vicious and augmented, but I have no doubts that you will manage to slay him!'{NEWLINE}Rules: No Vehicles/Power Armor, No Ubers, No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_WITCH_QUEST_NAZI_VOID_CATACOMBS", "Witch Quest: Shadow Catacombs"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_NAZI_VOID_CATACOMBS_DONE", "Shadow Catacombs Quest Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WITCH_QUEST_NAZI_VOID_CATACOMBS", "Shadow Catacombs"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUEST_NAZI_VOID_CATACOMBS_BRIEFING", "FROM: 'Sky Tearer', the white-haired Witch{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Shhh... did you hear it, SisteR? It was a quiet hiss of the VOID, escaping through a tiny-tiny cut... In these cat-a-combs, HUmAns have found SSsomeThING they should NOT have... Go through the tiny-tiny, secret tunnel, I'll show you, and surprise them from behind... Send them alL to the VOID, and receive a ShAdOW gIFt... Just for you, SiSTEr :3'{NEWLINE}Rules: Small People, No Hvy Armor, No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_DISTRESS_BUNKER", "Shipwrecked Gal"},
		{"STR_LOC_DISTRESS_BUNKER_TEMPERATE", "Shipwrecked Gal"},
		{"STR_LOC_DISTRESS_BUNKER_JUNGLE", "Shipwrecked Gal (Jungle)"},
		{"STR_LOC_DISTRESS_BUNKER_COLD", "Shipwrecked Gal (Cold)"},
		{"STR_LOC_DISTRESS_BUNKER_DESERT", "Shipwrecked Gal (Desert)"},
		{"STR_MARKER_DISTRESS_BUNKER", "Shipwrecked Gal"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_BUNKER_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "One of our fellow escaped Gals has broadcasted a call from this location. In her last transmission, she was delirious from the lack of water and radiation. We must rescue her before she dies or gets captured - if she's still there.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Gentle"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_BUNKER_JUNGLE_BRIEFING", "One of our fellow escaped Gals has broadcasted a call from this location. In her last transmission, she was delirious from the lack of water and radiation. We must rescue her before she dies or gets captured - if she's still there.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Gentle"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_BUNKER_COLD_BRIEFING", "One of our fellow escaped Gals has broadcasted a call from this location. In her last transmission, she was delirious from the lack of water and radiation. We must rescue her before she dies or gets captured - if she's still there.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Gentle"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_BUNKER_DESERT_BRIEFING", "One of our fellow escaped Gals has broadcasted a call from this location. In her last transmission, she was delirious from the lack of water and radiation. We must rescue her before she dies or gets captured - if she's still there.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Gentle"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL", "Distress Call"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_TEMPERATE", "Distress Call"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_JUNGLE", "Distress Call (Jungle)"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_COLD", "Distress Call (Cold)"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_DESERT", "Distress Call (Desert)"},
		{"STR_MARKER_DISTRESS_CALL", "Distress Beacon"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DISTRESS_CALL", "Distress Call Intercepted"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "A shipwrecked party, lost somewhere in this area, has broadcast its position on an open frequency. Let's find them and teach them a practical lesson what can happen if you do something like that!{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_JUNGLE_BRIEFING", "A shipwrecked party, lost somewhere in this area, has broadcast its position on an open frequency. Let's find them and teach them a practical lesson what can happen if you do something like that!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_COLD_BRIEFING", "A shipwrecked party, lost somewhere in this area, has broadcast its position on an open frequency. Let's find them and teach them a practical lesson what can happen if you do something like that!{NEWLINE}Weather: Cold. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_DISTRESS_CALL_DESERT_BRIEFING", "A shipwrecked party, lost somewhere in this area, has broadcast its position on an open frequency. Let's find them and teach them a practical lesson about what can happen if you do something like that!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST", "Scientific Experiments"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST_TEMPERATE", "Scientific Experiments"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST_JUNGLE", "Scientific Experiments (Jungle)"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST_COLD", "Scientific Experiments (Cold)"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST_DESERT", "Scientific Experiments (Desert)"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ACADEMY_OUTPOST", "Academy Outpost"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ACADEMY_OUTPOST", "Scientific Experiments"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "Here the Academy wenches have erected a fancy house. A house of pain it is, where captured people and animals go to an unknown fate. Honor demands putting an end to this and liberating everything that isn't bolted down to the ground! We can garner some savvy there too, especially from these blonde Medics. They're armored against buckshot but are worth much more alive anyway!{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Normal"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_OUTPOST_JUNGLE_BRIEFING", "Here the Academy wenches have erected a fancy house. A house of pain it is, where captured people and animals go to an unknown fate. Honor demands putting an end to this and liberating everything that isn't bolted down to the ground! We can garner some savvy there too, especially from these blonde Medics. They're armored against buckshot but are worth much more alive anyway!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Normal"},
