		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN", "Academy Campus"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN_TEMPERATE", "Campus Carnage"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN_HOT", "Campus Carnage (Hot)"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN_COLD", "Campus Carnage (Cold)"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ACADEMY_TOWN", "Academy Campus"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ACADEMY_TOWN", "Campus Carnage"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "We have located a poorly secured Academy town, ripe for conquest. Our knowledge of the Academy and its protocols allows us to land inside of their compound and start wreaking havoc in their midst. It is a great opportunity to deal a powerful blow to these wenches, and fill our coffers with their stuff.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Rough"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN_HOT_BRIEFING", "We have located a poorly secured Academy town, ripe for conquest. Our knowledge of the Academy and its protocols allows us to land inside of their compound and start wreaking havoc in their midst. It is a great opportunity to deal a powerful blow to these wenches, and fill our coffers with their stuff.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Rough"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_TOWN_COLD_BRIEFING", "We have located a poorly secured Academy town, ripe for conquest. Our knowledge of the Academy and its protocols allows us to land inside of their compound and start wreaking havoc in their midst. It is a great opportunity to deal a powerful blow to these wenches, and fill our coffers with their stuff.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Rough"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_TOWN_PREQ", "Campus Carnage (Preq.1)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_TOWN_PREQ2", "Campus Carnage (Preq.2)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_TOWN", "!Campus Carnage!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_TOWN_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Our knowledge of Academy's hubris and wickedness has grown quite broad - as did our knowledge of their codes, procedures and ties. Therefore, we can start targetting some of their permanent settlements to inflict as much damage as possible."},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_CRUISE", "Cruising Counsellors"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ACADEMY_CRUISE", "Cruising Counsellors"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ACADEMY_CRUISE", "Cruising Counsellors"},
		{"STR_LOC_ACADEMY_CRUISE_BRIEFING", "This ship is a floating den of Academy's kinkiest. These beneficiaries of Ghoul organ trade are using the vessel to enjoy their privilege, away from the prying eyes of the public. ONLY A SINGLE PERSON CAN PARTICIPATE. NO RETREAT. No equipment restrictions. Expect to be subjected to heavy Charm attacks.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Normal"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_CRUISE_PREQ", "Cruising Counsellors (Preq.)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_CRUISE", "!Cruising Counsellors!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ACADEMY_CRUISE_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}Our lead about Ghoul organ trade leads us to those most interested in keeping forever young, the master diplomats and negotiators, Academy Counsellors. We learned that they sometimes convene in the seclusion of sea vessels. By posing as Ghouls we can get info on where and when that happens. The security will be light, but we better not let our guard down...{ALT}"},
		{"STR_SPACE_FREIGHTER", "Space Freighter Raid"},
		{"STR_SPACE_FREIGHTER_DONE", "Space Freighter Raid Done"},
		{"STR_MARKER_SPACE_FREIGHTER", "Space Entry Point"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SPACE_FREIGHTER", "Space Freighter Spotted"},
		{"STR_SPACE_FREIGHTER_BRIEFING", "We have intercepted messages sent by a Guild freighter travelling in near-Earth space. With the right ship, we can chase it down, approach unseen and land in one of its hangars. It is risky but we decoded that the freighter is carrying some mysterious 'object' of great value... wonder what it could be?"},
		{"STR_SPACE_FREIGHTER_BRIEFING_2", "We have landed in the middle hangar. Our information says that the 'object' is in possession of a Team Leader. Hopefully it's not a wild goose chase...{NEWLINE}We should be also wary of Marsec ships coming to their rescue and blasting our craft. However, we probably have over 150 turns before that happens."},
		{"STR_MISSION_GUILD_FREIGHTER", "!Raid Space Freighters!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_GUILD_FREIGHTER_UFOPEDIA", "Large freighters, controlled by the Guild, criss-cross the space between Earth and Mars quite frequently. Attacking them is a risky business, but if we'll sniff out a good opportunity, the effort might be worth it. We can expect Marsec guards and robots, high Guild officers, as well as mysterious Belters on board. There is one issue... we need a ship with enough speed and endurance to give it a chase (any craft marked IPL). Space Junkers can help us salvage the craft."},
		{"STR_MISSION_VAMPIRE_RAMPAGE", "!Vampire Rampages!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_VAMPIRE_RAMPAGE_UFOPEDIA", "Your Vampire Princess tends to go out hunting and she has a uncanny ability to find good hunting spots. You consider sending your people along with her on these escapades.{NEWLINE}(To Be Continued)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_WITCH_QUESTS", "!Witch Quests!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_WITCH_QUESTS_DESC", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Hello again, my aspiring Saint, hahaha. I and my sisters decided to test your might by giving you quests befitting your aspiration. And shall you prove to be a fake, it will hasten your demise! I'm inclined to believe you're genuine, but you may easily prove me wrong..."},
		{"STR_MISSION_WITCH_QUESTS_UFOPEDIA", "The She-devil of the so-called Arch-Witches says that they decided you're an interesting individual, for good or worse. Expect to start receiving quests from them; do not expect any rhyme or reason to these quests. These quests will usually have racial constrictions regarding your crew, will disallow use of craft or combat vehicles and will expire in 48 hours. If you skip or abort such a Quest, the Witches will laugh at your weakness. But despite that, it might be better to approach the Witches and try to learn more before rushing in."},
		{"STR_MISSION_ZOMBIE_BAIT", "!Zombie Bait!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ZOMBIE_BAIT_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}We can try to use the Z-Comms to try and bait Zombies. However, it has to look inconspicuous, so we cannot deploy any Gals (too much Hellerium) or vehicles to such missions. We'll let you know when we achieve some success, Cap'n.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_BAIT", "Baiting Zombies"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ZOMBIE_BAIT", "Zombies Baited!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ZOMBIE_BAIT", "Zombie Bait"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_BAIT_BRIEFING", "This secluded area has proven to be conductive to our zombie baiting. However, using our craft, tanks or Hellerium-rich Uber Gals is impossible, as it would tip the zombie masters and ruin our trap. We need to set up camp here and wait. Zombies won't come at day, that's logical, but why it always has to be a small cabin in the woods?{NEWLINE}Warning: No Escape."},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST", "Warehouse Wars"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_TEMPERATE", "Warehouse Wars"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_JUNGLE", "Warehouse Wars (Jungle)"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_COLD", "Warehouse Wars (Cold)"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_DESERT", "Warehouse Wars (Desert)"},
		{"STR_MARKER_GUILD_OUTPOST", "Traders' Guild Warehouse"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GUILD_OUTPOST", "Warehouse Wars"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "The omnipotent Traders run a warehouse in this area. If we 'ware' to strike it, we could turn their wares into warez. Dem dogs in guild colors are free targets to show off our prowess, but we can take some wh... wenches alive as warez too. Be-ware of them Guild Security, they mighta be just oxen in armor, but that armor makes them very resistant to shotguns and lo-end pistols. Better to catch them un-a-wares and backstab 'em. Pun!{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Normal"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_JUNGLE_BRIEFING", "The omnipotent Traders run a warehouse in this area. If we 'ware' to strike it, we could turn their wares into warez. Dem dogs in guild colors are free targets to show off our prowess, but we can take some wh... wenches alive as warez too. Be-ware of them Guild Security, they mighta be just oxen in armor, but that armor makes them very resistant to shotguns and lo-end pistols. Better to catch them un-a-wares and backstab 'em. Pun!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Normal"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_COLD_BRIEFING", "The omnipotent Traders run a warehouse in this area. If we 'ware' to strike it, we could turn their wares into warez. Dem dogs in guild colors are free targets to show off our prowess, but we can take some wh... wenches alive as warez too. Be-ware of them Guild Security, they mighta be just oxen in armor, but that armor makes them very resistant to shotguns and lo-end pistols. Better to catch them un-a-wares and backstab 'em. Pun!{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Normal"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUILD_OUTPOST_DESERT_BRIEFING", "The omnipotent Traders run a warehouse in this area. If we 'ware' to strike it, we could turn their wares into warez. Dem dogs in guild colors are free targets to show off our prowess, but we can take some wh... wenches alive as warez too. Be-ware of them Guild Security, they mighta be just oxen in armor, but that armor makes them very resistant to shotguns and lo-end pistols. Better to catch them un-a-wares and backstab 'em. Pun!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Normal"},
		{"STR_MISSION_GUILD_OUTPOST", "!Warehouse Wars!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_GUILD_OUTPOST_UFOPEDIA", "It's time to step up our game. The Traders' Guild runs a vast network of warehouses all over the globe. We'll be going for the small ones but still we can expect some armored guards. Our informants will be on a lookout and we can expect the first target to show up within one or two months."},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST", "Temple Raid"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_TEMPERATE", "Temple Raid"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_JUNGLE", "Temple Raid (Jungle)"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_COLD", "Temple Raid (Cold)"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_DESERT", "Temple Raid (Desert)"},
		{"STR_MARKER_CHURCH_OUTPOST", "Temple of Sirius"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CHURCH_OUTPOST", "Temple Raid"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "This isolated temple be rumored to be easy pickings. Let us pilfer their coffers and get rich! We can either sneak in and seize the gold, or subdue everyone and get more loot and glory! We may need to be careful with civilians, better to catch them alive lest we want to appear like we have little style.{NEWLINE}WARNING: We must approach our target on foot to not cause suspicion, and thus we're unable to bring our craft. Green tiles are escape tiles.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_JUNGLE_BRIEFING", "This isolated temple be rumored to be easy pickings. Let us pilfer their coffers and get rich! We can either sneak in and seize the gold, or subdue everyone and get more loot and glory! We may need to be careful with civilians, better to catch them alive lest we want to appear like we have little style.{NEWLINE}WARNING: We must approach our target on foot to not cause suspicion, and thus we're unable to bring our craft. Green tiles are escape tiles.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_COLD_BRIEFING", "This isolated temple be rumored to be easy pickings. Let us pilfer their coffers and get rich! We can either sneak in and seize the gold, or subdue everyone and get more loot and glory! We may need to be careful with civilians, better to catch them alive lest we want to appear like we have little style.{NEWLINE}WARNING: We must approach our target on foot to not cause suspicion, and thus we're unable to bring our craft. Green tiles are escape tiles.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_LOC_CHURCH_OUTPOST_DESERT_BRIEFING", "This isolated temple be rumored to be easy pickings. Let us pilfer their coffers and get rich! We can either sneak in and seize the gold, or subdue everyone and get more loot and glory! We may need to be careful with civilians, better to catch them alive lest we want to appear like we have little style.{NEWLINE}WARNING: We must approach our target on foot to not cause suspicion, and thus we're unable to bring our craft. Green tiles are escape tiles.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Calm"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONGORN_ATTACK", "Mongorn Migration"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONGORN_ATTACK_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This remote village is being attacked by giant apes. And these apes are known for their luxurious and expensive furs! We can earn a bunch of Dolaros while helping out some locals in distress. Double profit!{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT", "Monster Hunt"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_BRIEFING", "Oi Cap'n! Let us slaughter some poor,{NEWLINE}defenceless animals, skin them and collect{NEWLINE}a fat prize for their useless body parts!{NEWLINE}We just need to be careful not to bump into{NEWLINE}another crew of hunters!"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_MEGASCORPION", "Stingy Megascorpions"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_MEGASCORPION", "Megascorpion Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_MEGASCORPION", "Megascorpion Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_MEGASCORPION_DESC", "Find Megascorpions for their Stings and Poison. Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Normal."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_GIANTSPIDER", "Spider Scare"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_GIANTSPIDER", "Giant Spider Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_GIANTSPIDER", "Giant Spider Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_GIANTSPIDER_DESC", "Find Giant Spiders for their Silk and Poison. Weather: Warm. Sea: Uneven."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_CHUPACABRA", "Chupacabra Carnage"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_CHUPACABRA", "Chupacabra Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_CHUPACABRA", "Chupacabra Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_CHUPACABRA_DESC", "Find Chupacabras for Fun and Profit. Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneven."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_BLOOD_DOG", "Them Bloody Hounds"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_BLOOD_DOG", "Blood Hound Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_BLOOD_DOG", "Blood Hound Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_BLOOD_DOG_DESC", "Find Blood Hounds for Fun and Profit. Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneven."},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT", "!Monster Hunt!"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_UFOPEDIA", "We been askin' the local hunters for hints and tips regarding their trade (what a hangover, Cap'n!). Turns out that them landlubbers be paying good coin for various animal parts - fer example, remember them Megascorpions we used to eat? Their stings fetch an astounding price, and if we manage to catch one alive, we could maybe examine their poison. We be keeping our ears open for any profitable hunt opportunities, and as soon as we hear somethin', we'll give you the word immediately, Cap'n!"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_SHAMBLER_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Wampa Wovi' is a traditional Blackmarch name of the hunt for the legendary White Shambler. I'm telling you this, Cap'n, because this fabled animal has been spotted somewhere near this location! Lets bag it, and get rich!{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_SHAMBLER", "Wampa Wovi"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_SHAMBLER", "Shambler Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MONSTER_HUNT_SHAMBLER", "Shambler Hunt"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNTS_PRIMAL", "!Primal Hunts!"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_UFOPEDIA", "Shooting beasts with machineguns is easy. But the challenge of hunting them Stone Age style can give us the wisdom of our ancestors. We'll need a Hunt Party to attend."},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL", "Primal Hunt"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_SHAMBLER", "Primal Hunt: High Mountains"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_SHAMBLER_DONE", "Primal Hunt: Shambler: Done"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_SHAMBLER_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This challenge involves hunting a pack of White Shamblers atop their snowy peaks. Requires sending a Hunting Party, and only Stone Age equipment can be used.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Savage."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_WEREWOLF", "Primal Hunt: Dark Forests"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_WEREWOLF_DONE", "Primal Hunt: Werewolf: Done"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_WEREWOLF_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This challenge involves clearing the forest from a pack of Werewolves. Requires sending a Hunting Party, and only Stone Age equipment can be used.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Savage."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_BULLFROG", "Primal Hunt: Steamy Marshes"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_BULLFROG_DONE", "Primal Hunt: Bullfrog: Done"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_BULLFROG_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This challenge involves fighting a plague of Mega Bullfrogs in these marshes. Requires sending a Hunting Party, and only Stone Age equipment can be used.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Savage."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_COCKROACH", "Primal Hunt: Scorched Deserts"},
		{"STR_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_COCKROACH_DONE", "Primal Hunt: Cockroach: Done"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_COCKROACH_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This challenge involves removing an infestation of Giant Cockroaches from this desert. Requires sending a Hunting Party, and only Stone Age equipment can be used.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Savage."},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_FINALE", "Primal Hunt: Finale"},
		{"STR_LOC_MONSTER_HUNT_PRIMAL_FINALE_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This island is occupied by a tribe of Canny Gals, guarding ruins of an ancient civilization, and thus having access to arms more advanced than you can use. Defeating them will be the final challenge, proving your mastery of the primal ways. {NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Savage."},
		{"STR_CANNY_QUEEN_1_TXT", "The battle ends, and there's a sudden moment of tranquility. You marvel at the beauty of the green jungle, the azure sea, the mossy old stones. Suddenly, a Canny Gal in ornate clothing appears, followed by a group of warriors.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'I'm not here to fight,' she says. 'I'm the queen of this tribe, and you have rightfully defeated the guardians of this ancient place, by the use of even more ancient ways. Thus, you have earned the right to call yourselves civilized, if you wish so.'"},
		{"STR_CANNY_QUEEN_2_TXT", "The Canny Queen leads you to the shore and hangs a Sivalinga Stone on your neck.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'When the night falls, bathe in these sacred waters and pay respects to our Mother Earth. Then we shall celebrate and feast on the fallen, they don't deserve to be eaten by lowly worms.'"},
		{"STR_CANNY_QUEEN_3_TXT", "The feast ends with your crowning ceremony. The Queen passes you her crown. 'This is not a mere symbol,' she says. 'The ancient Mummu existed before Egypt and didn't die with it. We, of the first human civilization, still have some sway over the world. Your claim will be accepted by those who are in the know.'"},
		{"STR_UNDERCOVER_OPERATIONS", "Undercover Operations"},
		{"STR_UNDERCOVER_OPERATIONS_UFOPEDIA", "Cities are a difficult area to infiltrate. Having a Pass is one thing, but it doesn't allow us to just barge in with our craft and weapons. We need to blend in, as fighting security on a large scale is not only hopeless, it also would compromise our mission goals.{NEWLINE}There are 2 general varieties of city infiltration:{NEWLINE}>Safehouse. We will appear like rough elements of the city, which means no obvious combat armor, and only Humans and Gnomes (other races only in stealth armor which allows for longer operation). No weapon restrictions.{NEWLINE}>Stealthy. Heavy weapon restrictions, plainclothes only, but more stealth outfit options for non-humans."},
		{"STR_UNDERSEA_OPERATIONS", "Undersea Operations"},
		{"STR_MISSION_SEA_ADVENTURE", "!Undersea Treasures!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_SEA_ADVENTURE_UFOPEDIA", "So many ships have crashed into the sea, making it impossible to loot them! This has to be a true treasure cove, and we could simply dive right in - provided we have a proper craft, marked as SUBmersible. In the underwater world, unprotected divers take constant Stun damage and most armors cannot be worn. Only armors which have a 'sea' version (see Pedia) will be used."},
		{"STR_UNDERSEA_OPERATIONS_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Fighting in an underwater environment will be a serious challenge. Until proper diving suits are developed, we'll have to rely on oxygen tanks or Stimms to stay conscious. But that is only one of the problems; we'll also be facing painful penalties to all combat skills.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>Melee Combat. With hampered movement rates and energy regeneration, only the very best warriors will be able to go toe-to-toe with aquatic enemies, who operate on their own turf, and thus will outspeed and outdodge us.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>Throwing Weapons. Throwing is penalized as well, but these can work surprisingly well as middle-ground backup, as there will be time to replenish our Energy. Especially interesting will be weapons that use half throwing and half melee skill, due to their good attack ratings.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>Ranged Combat. This will be the most advantageous, but hampered by the sparsity of good underwater guns. Looks like Crossbows and Harpoon Guns are going to be the mainstay weaponry."},
		{"STR_SEA_ADVENTURE", "Sea Wreck"},
		{"STR_SEA_ADVENTURE_BRIEFING", "Long searches have pinpointed this location as promising for an undersea treasure hunt. So let's get out of these overland duds and start exploring!{NEWLINE}Two things we need to be watchful for. First, even if our Hellerium-powered physiques can withstand the conditions, no oxygen supply means our whole team may simply drown if we're not careful. Second, any native creatures will have better vision range than ourselves in this environment.{NEWLINE}Sea: Restless."},
		{"STR_SEA_ODDITY", "Sea Oddity"},
		{"STR_SEA_CORAL_EXIT", "Undersea Passage"},
		{"STR_CORAL_ISLAND", "Mysterious Island"},
		{"STR_SEA_CORAL_EXIT_BRIEFING", "There are stories about an undersea tunnel present in this location. It supposedly leads to a mysterious island, impossible to find otherwise due to weird weather conditions. After finding the tunnel, gather all crew on orange exit tiles and 'Abort' mission. Alternatively, if we kill everything that moves, we can explore the tunnel at leisure.{NEWLINE}Sea: Restless."},
		{"STR_CORAL_ISLAND_BRIEFING", "We have climbed to the surface of the island, and we can smell treasure! But something is not right... Something scary, yet strangely titillating clouds our senses... We should be on guard against whatever weird stuff dwells here...{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot."},
		{"STR_BEACH_SWEEP", "Beach Sweep"},
		{"LOC_BEACH_SWEEP", "Beach Sweep"},
		{"ALERT_BEACH_SWEEP", "Beach Sweep"},
		{"MARKER_BEACH_SWEEP", "Beach Sweep"},
		{"STR_LOC_BEACH_SWEEP_BRIEFING", "Our Dreams of the Deep allow us to use our premonitions to pinpoint concentrations of confused Deep Ones, who have just landed onshore. We can go there and hunt them down, if you so desire, Cap'n.{NEWLINE}Weather: Warm."},
		{"STR_DEVILS_REEF", "Devil's Reef"},
		{"STR_SEA_DEVILS_REEF", "Devil's Reef"},
		{"LOC_DEVILS_REEF", "Devil's Reef"},
		{"ALERT_DEVILS_REEF", "Devil's Reef"},
		{"MARKER_DEVILS_REEF", "Devil's Reef"},
		{"LOC_DEVILS_REEF_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}From: Inter-Govt Council{NEWLINE}Another Deep One migration is imminent. We contact you as we do every other available mercenary. There is little profit or glory in this job, but someone has to do it. The Depth Dwellers outnumber us all greatly. So ultimately we're all in the same boat.{NEWLINE}The mission is to land close to their staging area, then proceed underwater and destroy the Aquatoid beacons, before too many Deep Ones gather. Killing them is of lower priority; you can retreat after destroying the three beacons."},
		{"STR_BEACONS_DESTROYED", "ALL BEACONS DESTROYED"},
		{"STR_SEA_HIGHSTAR", "Fallen Stars"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SEA_HIGHSTAR", "Fallen Stars"},
		{"STR_SEA_HIGHSTAR_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}According to the gnomes, the plane carrying Highway Star motorcycles crashed around this area. However, they refuse to allow anyone near their 'precious artifacts' nor betray the exact location, so we can either send in a gnome crew or forget about this whole wild goose chase. If we choose to send them in, they'll need to clear the area of hostiles to start the search."},
		{"STR_SEA_PIRATE_TREASURE", "Sunken Treasure"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SEA_PIRATE_TREASURE", "Pirate Treasure"},
		{"STR_PIRATE_TREASURE_BRIEFING", "Having studied old Pirate legends, we have learned about this location. It supposedly holds great treasure, hidden there in the ages past. Hidden where? That's the tricky part, it's an underwater cave complex. What an opportunity to face your claustrophobia head on! Even if the treasure is just a hoax!"},
		{"STR_SEA_SUNKEN_USO", "Sunken USO"},
		{"STR_SEA_SUNKEN_UFO", "Sunken UFO"},
		{"STR_SEA_SUNKEN_GALLEON", "Sunken Galleon"},
		{"STR_SEA_SUNKEN_CARGO_SHIP", "Sunken Cargo Ship"},
		{"STR_SEA_SUNKEN_PLANE", "Sunken Airplane"},
		{"STR_MARKER_SEA_ADVENTURE", "Sea Wreck"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SEA_ADVENTURE", "Sea Adventure"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SEA_ADVENTURE_DESC", "Recover Undersea Wreck. SEA/Underwater items only. Sea forecast: Restless."},
		{"STR_LOC_WHOREHOUSE", "Red Lantern Villa"},
		{"STR_ALERT_WHOREHOUSE", "Save a Sister"},
		{"STR_LOC_WHOREHOUSE_TITLE", "Save a Sister"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_WHOREHOUSE", "Red Lantern Villa"},
		{"STR_LOC_WHOREHOUSE_BRIEFING", "A Zone Stalker gave a word that local banditos have caught a strange-eyed, travelling Uber and are keeping her in their private dungeon. If she's still alive, we can offer her a much better house to stay, plus, blowing up a Bandit-ran bordello is a sure-fire way to promote healthier lifestyle and win some publicity (people will rejoice at a brothel gone, right?).{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm. No Wide Craft."},
		{"STR_MISSION_HIGHWAY_STATION", "!Highway House!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_HIGHWAY_STATION_UFOPEDIA", "We can now start the search for Highwaymen stations, minor strongholds which they use to control the roads. Looting their big guns will give us something to arm our craft with. It is more likely than not we'll eventually find something. However, once we secure trusted suppliers of air ordnance, Highwaymen will be scared and our searches less fruitful."},
		{"STR_MISSION_BANDIT_CAMP", "!Bandit Camps!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_BANDIT_CAMP_UFOPEDIA", "Our growing knowledge about the world, its riches, problems, its heartbeat, has diverged our attention towards the issue of wilderness bandits. Many Black Market routes are plagued by this menace. While numerous, the Bandits are weak, and, well, they probably still keep hold on stolen riches that could be OURS instead!"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAMP", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAMP_TEMPERATE", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAMP_DESERT", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAMP_JUNGLE", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAMP_COLD", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BANDIT_CAMP", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_MARKER_BANDIT_CAMP", "Bandit Camp"},
		{"STR_BANDIT_CAMP_TEMPERATE_BRIEFING", "We sniffed out a large bandit camp here. If we're to re-appropriate their assets, we're in for a big shootout. The camp covers a large area, and most of the bandits are likely to be concentrated in a handful of places, which can be used to our advantage.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_BANDIT_CAMP_COLD_BRIEFING", "We sniffed out a large bandit camp here. If we're to re-appropriate their assets, we're in for a big shootout. The camp covers a large area, and most of the bandits are likely to be concentrated in a handful of places, which can be used to our advantage.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_BANDIT_CAMP_HOT_BRIEFING", "We sniffed out a large bandit camp here. If we're to re-appropriate their assets, we're in for a big shootout. The camp covers a large area, and most of the bandits are likely to be concentrated in a handful of places, which can be used to our advantage.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_MISSION_BANDIT_TOWN", "!Bandit Business!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_BANDIT_TOWN_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}It seems there is no honor amongst thieves. Bandits attack anyone who is easy prey, and we can appropriate their gains in turn. Putting their seedy towns out of business will not only bring us profit, but also some infamy. How hard it can be for us Ubers to defeat these dregs? Even if their Outzone world isn't our home turf?{ALT}"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_TOWN", "Bandit Town"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BANDIT_TOWN", "Bandit Town"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_TOWN_TITLE", "Bandit Town"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_BANDIT_TOWN", "Bandit Town"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_TOWN_BRIEFING", "We have located a Bandit Town in this area. They're surely possessing some riches and captives we can take - Viking style! There will likely be many of them, and they know their turf, but they're weak. We should have no trouble if we prepare for a big fight.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Restless."},
		{"STR_LOC_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST_", "Rimrider Outpost-{0}"},
		{"STR_LOC_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST", "Rimrider Outpost"},
		{"STR_ALERT_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST", "Rimrider Outpost"},
		{"STR_LOC_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST_TITLE", "Rimrider Outpost"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST", "Rimrider Outpost"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST_", "Rimrider Outpost-{0}"},
		{"STR_LOC_RIMRIDER_OUTPOST_BRIEFING", "Looking for crime opportunities, Rimrider scum established a bandit camp in this area. Let's repossess their ill-gotten Hellerium before it leaves our planet! We will be storming a 'hole nest of 'em. Do or die!{NEWLINE}Depth: Shallow."},
		{"STR_MISSION_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY_PREQ", "Raider Arms Factory (Preq)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY_DONE", "Raider Arms Factory (Done)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY", "!Raider Arms Factory!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}Our interrogations of higher echelons of banditry revealed their source of supply in armored vehicles and the notorious Rattlesnake rockets. Turns out the production is carried out in secretive factories, located deep in Uber Zones, utilizing remnants of old industry. We can try to perform a hostile takeover. Administrating such a site directly would be impossible, but owning it would still open an extra source of revenue plus an ability to purchase its wares at a discount.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_LOC_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY", "Raider Arms Factory"},
		{"STR_ALERT_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY", "Raider Arms Factory"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY", "Raider Arms Factory"},
		{"STR_LOC_RAIDER_ARMS_FACTORY_BRIEFING", "These Raiders are running an old arms factory deep inside their Zone. They produce a wide array of weapons, including the infamous Rattlesnake SAM armored cars, which they sell to various bandits. They are well armed (including, naturally, Armored Cars), but if we manage to break their resistance, the place is for a change in management!{NEWLINE}Warning: discretion is required and this site can only be approached in a ground or undetectable vehicle.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Rough."},
		{"STR_LOC_POLIS", "Beautiful People"},
		{"STR_POLIS_DONE", "City Mission Done"},
		{"STR_ALERT_POLIS", "City Raid"},
		{"STR_LOC_POLIS_TITLE", "Beautiful People"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_POLIS", "City Raid"},
		{"STR_LOC_POLIS_BRIEFING", "Ha-ha-harr! Them Purebloods think they can hide from us behind the walls of their cities, but that's an illusion! With Alliance's help, we can infiltrate a rich neighbourhood, where surely much ransom can be had! Which is important, as we won't have the time to properly loot their houses! We can smuggle any weapons in, but battle armor would be too suspicious, also, 'No Mutants Allowed'.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_SMUGGLER_BASE", "Smuggler Hideout"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SMUGGLER_BASE", "Smuggler Hideout"},
		{"STR_LOC_SMUGGLER_BASE_TITLE", "Smuggler Hideout"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_SMUGGLER_BASE", "Smuggler Hideout"},
		{"STR_LOC_SMUGGLER_BASE_BRIEFING", "This is it, our chance to get some answers on Shadowtech trading! The Smuggler facility is well stacked with stationary defenses, so we need to pretend we're customers. They won't care too much about our weapons, but too warlike-looking armor is sure to raise their suspicions - so we won't be using these. Once we get inside, we can start shooting away. Our goal is to capture a Smuggler Negotiator. If the mission goes south, we can seek escape through a lift."},
		{"STR_LOC_SMUGGLER_LAIR", "Smuggler Lair"},
		{"STR_ALERT_SMUGGLER_LAIR", "Smuggler Lair"},
		{"STR_LOC_SMUGGLER_LAIR_TITLE", "Smuggler Lair"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_SMUGGLER_LAIR", "Smuggler Lair"},
		{"STR_LOC_SMUGGLER_LAIR_BRIEFING", "We have the approximate location of one of Smuggler safehouses in city's sewers, but finding it will require us to explore a large area. This might prove difficult, as while we can smuggle any weapons in, we're still being restricted by city rules - meaning mutants can only infiltrate in special outfits, and humans cannot use too obviously military armor. No point talking any longer, our job will be lengthy enough. {NEWLINE}Depth: Very Shallow."},
		{"STR_LOC_POLIS_TERMINAL", "Terminal Terror"},
		{"STR_ALERT_POLIS_TERMINAL", "Terminal Terror"},
		{"STR_LOC_POLIS_TERMINAL_TITLE", "Terminal Terror"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_POLIS_TERMINAL", "Terminal Terror"},
		{"STR_LOC_POLIS_TERMINAL_BRIEFING", "In this mission we need to capture a Corrupt Clerk and escape with the Transstellar Shuttle to the West, before security arrives from the East in 10-15 turns. Using mutant troops in this mission is tricky, and better read 'What to Wear' closely to avoid ending up in a Box. Only Stealthy equipment can be carried in, and better not to take more than needed as it can easily get misplaced.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Rough."},
		{"STR_LOC_DETECTIVE_HUNT", "Scum & Villainy"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DETECTIVE_HUNT", "Scum & Villainy"},
		{"STR_LOC_DETECTIVE_HUNT_TITLE", "Scum & Villainy"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_DETECTIVE_HUNT", "Scum & Villainy"},
		{"STR_LOC_DETECTIVE_HUNT_BRIEFING", "Our spy network has located a corrupt Megapol Detective who is involved in the cover-up of the optronic smuggling operation. We need to secure the list of names of other conspirators he is carrying. To make sure he's beyond any suspicion, he made himself quite a celebrity amongst the Big Faction people, trading favors left and right. We need to stake him out in the Faction entertainment district inside this city. We have around 10 turns before Megapol reinforcements arrive.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Rough. No Mutants Allowed. No Retreat."},
		{"STR_ALERT_BOUNTY_HUNT_D", "Bounty Hunt! (Lvl: D)"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BOUNTY_HUNT_C", "Bounty Hunt! (Lvl: C)"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BOUNTY_HUNT_B", "Bounty Hunt! (Lvl: B)"},
		{"STR_ALERT_BOUNTY_HUNT_A", "Bounty Hunt! (Lvl: A)"},
		{"STR_LOC_PIRATE_CRUISE", "Hell Cruise"},
		{"STR_LOC_PIRATE_CRUISE_TITLE", "Hell Cruise"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_PIRATE_CRUISE", "Hell Cruise"},
		{"STR_PIRATE_CRUISE_DONE", "Hell Cruise Won"},
		{"STR_LOC_PIRATE_CRUISE_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Pirate Straits{NEWLINE}Help! One of our totally innocent cruise ships is being attacked by Deep Ones! These things happen when you get to the sea... but we need the profits! Save the ship, and you can have all the wares it carries, as well as our gratitude.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Stormy."},
		{"STR_LOC_FUNKY_ZOMBIES", "Sunday Town"},
		{"STR_LOC_FUNKY_ZOMBIES_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Wiz Biz{NEWLINE}The wizards require a small task of you. One of our Associates has a... sensitive piece of property near this town. The place is absolutely quiet and safe, full of happy mutants and there is no way anything could go wrong. In an unlikely case something does, limit the damage. Note that since you have to move in to keep watch over the town, aborting the mission is impossible. Only Mostly Harmless weapons allowed.{NEWLINE}Weather: Wizards Rule!"},
		{"STR_LOC_CANNIBAL_CAMP", "Cannibal Camp"},
		{"STR_MARKER_CANNIBAL_CAMP", "Cannibal Camp"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CANNIBAL_CAMP", "Cannibal Camp"},
		{"STR_LOC_CANNIBAL_CAMP_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Wiz Biz{NEWLINE}Taking a trip to the wildside is a dangerous endeavour. One of our client's friends tried his luck and was eaten by a tribe of cannibals. More importantly though, he had a Liber Occultus on him. Find the valuable tome and bring it back to me!{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Stormy."},
		{"STR_LOC_HIGHWAY_STATION", "Highway House"},
		{"STR_ALERT_HIGHWAY_STATION", "Highway House"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_HIGHWAY_STATION", "Highway House"},
		{"STR_LOC_HIGHWAY_STATION_BRIEFING", "This is it! Our chance to get a craft weapon! We just need to pry it out of cold dead hands of Highwaymen who use it for home defence. Oh and the area is swarming with the locals, but that was to be expected, right?{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_HAUNTED_FOREST", "Haunted Forest"},
		{"STR_ALERT_HAUNTED_FOREST", "Haunted Forest"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_HAUNTED_FOREST", "Haunted Forest"},
		{"STR_LOC_HAUNTED_FOREST_BRIEFING", "We got a tip from a Zone Stalker about strong Hellerium glow in this area. The Stalker was also babbling something about the place being haunted. The fool! Now all the Hellerium can be ours!{NEWLINE}Weather: Ghastly. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_OUTBREAK", "Zombie Hunt"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_OUTBREAK2", "Zombie Hunt"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ZOMBIE_OUTBREAK", "Zombie Hunt"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ZOMBIE_OUTBREAK", "Zombie Hunt"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_OUTBREAK_BRIEFING", "We were informed that a group of 'Zombies' has been spotted in this area. Whatever they are, we can exterminate them for fun and profit.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE_ROMANICA", "Bewitched Village"},
		{"STR_ALERT_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE", "Bewitched Village"},
		{"STR_MARKER_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE", "Bewitched Village"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE_ROMANICA_BRIEFING", "Our Romanican hosts ask for help! One of their villages has been overrun by something they call... Undead! Can you believe that, Cap'n? Anyway, apparently we're the only ones who can make it on time, and if we don't, we're going to be seen as weak. If we help, we're going to be paid a 'traditional fee'. I have a feeling it's not worth much.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE_ROMANICA_REINFORCEMENTS", "A wild Errant Knight appears!"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE_GHOSTGATES", "Bewitched Village"},
		{"STR_LOC_ZOMBIE_VILLAGE_GHOSTGATES_BRIEFING", "An aristocratic family from Ghostgates proposed us a deal. They have what they call 'rotten pests' in one of their villages, which have caused the peasants to flee, thus disrupting their work. Aristocrats offer to give us one of their daughters (peasants', not their own) into slavery if we clear the place.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot. Sea: Calm."},
		{"STR_LOC_KKK_HOUSE", "Humanist Safehouse"},
		{"STR_LOC_KKK_HOUSE_TITLE", "Lynchers"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_KKK_HOUSE", "Humanist Safehouse"},
		{"STR_LOC_KKK_HOUSE_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level D{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}I have received information about a group of Humanists who lynched an innocent mutant family. This cannot go unpunished. These so-called Purebloods are currently celebrating their deed in a house located in this area. Strike from the shadows and leave no-one alive.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_TRAITORS", "Traitors at large"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRAITORS_TITLE", "No Mercy For Traitors"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_TRAITORS", "Traitors at large"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRAITORS_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level D{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}A small group of people was selling out Alliance secrets to enemies of all Mutants. They must be killed and their corpses must be found to send a message. If you don't hurry, their Highwayman escorts will take them to a safehouse and tracking them down again might be difficult.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_BARN_GROX", "Lokk'Naar Farm"},
		{"STR_LOC_BARN_GROX_TITLE", "Farmer's Debts"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_BARN_GROX", "Lokk'Naar Farm"},
		{"STR_LOC_BARN_GROX_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level D{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx Banking Cartel{NEWLINE}Good day, our most valued customer. We're happy that you're paying your dues within agreed schedules. This fellow here, however, wasn't as smart; borrowed too much and now can't pay. Do us a favor and turn the collateral (his red barn) into collateral damage. Avoid hurting the fellow: his clansmen won't like it and the mission will end instantly. Don't get into a fight with them and don't get caught; do what you can within 5 turns (running out of time will do you no harm).{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_MUSEUM", "Archeological Adventure"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_MUSEUM_TITLE", "Archeological Adventure"},
		{"STR_MARKER_CATACOMBS_MUSEUM", "Deep Archeo Site"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_MUSEUM_REINFORCEMENTS", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You can feel a slight change in the air from the direction of the long underground passage that led you to this place. It can mean only one thing: someone has followed you!"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_MUSEUM_BRIEFING", "From: Gnome Museum{NEWLINE}Howdy there! See, see I have a job for you! I mean less like a job, more like an opportunity for scientific adventure! Okay, maybe I'm overstating this a bit, this complex is rather robust and not very old, so you shouldn't be able to break anything. What complex? Oh! I learned that there is a site, very deep one. There might be something in there that I really, really want. Or there might be not. The rest you can keep. Why don't you check it out? Pretty please? {NEWLINE}Depth: Deep (Hot). Small Races only. Pickaxes not included.{NEWLINE}Watch out for enemies following you after 5+ turns."},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_COIN_HUNT", "Practical Archeology"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_COIN_HUNT_TITLE", "Practical Archeology"},
		{"STR_MARKER_CATACOMBS_COIN_HUNT", "Archeological Dig"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_COIN_HUNT_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx Banking Cartel{NEWLINE}What a day, what a day. A group of archeologists we have hired has vanished, and all our security subcontractors are currently busy, which created this problem in the first place. Would you investigate the dig site they were exploring? Relax, no complex problems to solve, we simply want any genuine old coins you can find there, whether they've got legs or not.{NEWLINE}Depth: Average."},
		{"STR_LOC_TAVERN_CELLAR", "Infested Cellar"},
		{"STR_LOC_TAVERN_CELLAR_TITLE", "Infested Cellar"},
		{"STR_ALERT_TAVERN_CELLAR", "Infested Cellar"},
		{"STR_MARKER_TAVERN_CELLAR", "Infested Cellar"},
		{"STR_LOC_TAVERN_CELLAR_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}So you're this band of warriors for hire? Pirates, you say? Whatever. I run a tavern at one of Black Market's trade routes and I need some brave fools... I mean, help. My tavern is built atop old ruins, which recently got infested by a plague of dirty rats. Get rid of these freeloaders before they eat all my pillows, and you can keep whatever you find (namely, the stuff I was silly enough to store in the cellar). I will also whisper around a good word about you. Deal?"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRIBALS_IN_CATACOMBS", "Tribals in Catacombs"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRIBALS_IN_CATACOMBS_TITLE", "Tribals in Catacombs"},
		{"STR_ALERT_TRIBALS_IN_CATACOMBS", "Tribals in Catacombs!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_TRIBALS_IN_CATACOMBS", "Tribals in Catacombs"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRIBALS_IN_CATACOMBS_BRIEFING", "Acting on advice from the Wasteland Priestess, a tribal shaman contacts you through his old Ethyrnet terminal to ask for help. A group of experienced hunters were chasing some big game and broke taboo by following it underground, and were subsequently cut off by horrifying subterranean monsters. As a great warrior and the Chosen One, will you help protect these foolhardy men from a certain demise? The shaman also insinuates that he knows what kind of reward would satisfy your needs, if you succeed.{NEWLINE}Depth: Average."},
		{"STR_LOC_TRAWELL_THAT_ENDS_WELL", "Trawell That Ends Well"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRAWELL_THAT_ENDS_WELL_TITLE", "Trawell That Ends Well"},
		{"STR_ALERT_TRAWELL_THAT_ENDS_WELL", "Catgirl Tourists in Peril!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_TRAWELL_THAT_ENDS_WELL", "Trawell That Ends Well"},
		{"STR_LOC_TRAWELL_THAT_ENDS_WELL_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}We have detected a distress call, but instead of the usual suspects, this time these are actual catgirls from space! They are on a pilgrimage to Earth, but they clearly didn't study its dangers and now are running for their lives from a horde of Earth creatures. They seem rather desperate and are requesting immediate assistance. If there are any actual Peregrines among them, some might be interested in joining us!{NEWLINE}Weather: Varied."},
		{"STR_SEA_SUNKEN_TOWN", "Underwater Assets"},
		{"STR_SUNKEN_TOWN_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx Banking Cartel{NEWLINE}Oh hello there, Madame. We have another job for you. Perusing through old records of a late company, called 'Amazmo', we have found a location of one of their business parks. The location in question wasn't... ideal, and the whole operation went... underwater, so to speak, during the 22nd century. We sniff money, though. Don your sea gear, prospect the place, and be on guard for any low-income squatters that tend to infest such properties."},
		{"STR_LOC_SINS_OF_THE_FATHER", "Sins of the Father"},
		{"STR_LOC_SINS_OF_THE_FATHER_TITLE", "Sins of the Father"},
		{"STR_MARKER_SINS_OF_THE_FATHER", "Temple of Sirius"},
		{"STR_LOC_SINS_OF_THE_FATHER_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level D{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx Banking Cartel{NEWLINE}It is a sad fact that no human is sinless, not even the priesthood, and greed is an awful temptation indeed... We have entered a deal with the resident priest of this temple. He was supposed to gather any Old Coins from his flock and sell them to us. Alas, our tenacious competitors, the Elfman Bro$ offered a better price. Relieve the priest from the burden of his sin. Be careful, though: he will flee at any sign of danger, so you may only use plain clothes and infiltration gear."},
		{"STR_LOC_CRACKHOUSE", "Crackhouse"},
		{"STR_LOC_CRACKHOUSE_TITLE", "Crackhouse Raid"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_CRACKHOUSE", "Crackhouse"},
		{"STR_LOC_CRACKHOUSE_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level D{NEWLINE}From: Jack{NEWLINE}Listen up, mercenaries. I have located the current hiding place of one of these Sharp Guys, who try to cheat people on the Black Market all the time. He could use some old-fashioned justice before he has a chance to change his location again. You can keep whatever else you find there as extra booty.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_HITMAN", "Reservoir Dog"},
		{"STR_LOC_HITMAN_TITLE", "Reservoir Dog"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_HITMAN", "Dog's Hideout"},
		{"STR_LOC_HITMAN_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx{NEWLINE}One of our contractors has become a liability. We've tracked him down to this little hole in the ground. Take care of him before he can damage our company, and it will be most appreciated indeed. Just be careful - he is rather... well trained.{NEWLINE}Weather: Unknown."},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAVES", "Bandit Caves"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAVES_TITLE", "Bandit Caves"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_BANDIT_CAVES", "Bandit Caves"},
		{"STR_LOC_BANDIT_CAVES_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Jack{NEWLINE}I have a problem with some bandits. They're harassing travellers, raiding farms and refusing to pay up. Rumor is, they even have fallen into some weird worship. There is no place in my country for unreasonable guys like them. They have holed up in some caves that are difficult to reach for my militias. Purge the place clean.{NEWLINE}Depth: Very Shallow."},
		{"STR_LOC_MAGAZYNMAFII", "Double-Crossing Dudes"},
		{"STR_LOC_MAGAZYNMAFII_TITLE", "Double-Crossing Dudes"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_MAGAZYNMAFII", "Bandit Warehouse"},
		{"STR_LOC_MAGAZYNMAFII_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Jack{NEWLINE}Mercenaries, this work is of a somewhat delicate nature. One gang of bandits is trying to double-cross me. Yet if you simply barge in, waving your guns, they will flee - and I want to know whom they're working for. Visit their warehouse in a small group (max. 6), posing as fellow traitors. They will check you on entry, so take only Infiltration weapons and armor which doesn't look like a weapon in its own right. Once you've had a chat with them and learned enough, start the bloodbath.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_ESCAPE_TOWER", "Escape Tower"},
		{"STR_LOC_ESCAPE_TOWER_TITLE", "Escape Tower"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_ESCAPE_TOWER", "Escape Tower"},
		{"STR_LOC_ESCAPE_TOWER_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}They say a Mage always arrives on time. Make sure he and his consorts aren't late for their funeral. They're fleeing a mutant uprising, caused by their evil deeds. By the time you arrive, you will find most of them holed up in their escape craft. If you're unable to stop them in time, return to your craft or wait in the green exit area for our evac vessel, lest you want to face the blind rage of the people yourself.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_ARSENAL", "Humanist Arsenal"},
		{"STR_LOC_ARSENAL_TITLE", "Humanist Arsenal"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_ARSENAL", "Humanist Arsenal"},
		{"STR_LOC_ARSENAL_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}Any revolution starts with seizing an armory. The mutants of this town have already risen up against the ongoing genocide, in which the murderous Humanists have allied themselves with a few corrupt local MPs. Your task will be to strike at the Humanist arsenal, while their mobile forces are occupied by mutant skirmishers. You have 24 turns to succeed. Make the Humanist pigs bleed.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_USA", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_BLACKMARCH", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_NORDFED", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_RUSSIA", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_CHINA", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_UK", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_EGYPT", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_EXPANSE", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_CANADA", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_NCR", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_LATIN", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_REDREV", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_DARKDOM", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_STEEL_PACT", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_EUROSYNDICATE", "Guns of the Patriots"},
		{"STR_LOC_GUNS_OF_THE_PATRIOTS_BRIEFING", "The local mutants have informed us about the existence of a large weapon warehouse in this area, which belongs to the Humanists. However, the area is under the protection of the local govt and if we take too long in clearing the place, their patrols will investigate the disturbance. Killing them will hurt our relations.{NEWLINE}Sea: Stormy. Weather: Varied."},
		{"STR_LOC_HUMANIST_VILLA", "Humanist Villa"},
		{"STR_LOC_HUMANIST_VILLA_TITLE", "Humanist Villa"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_HUMANIST_VILLA", "Humanist Villa"},
		{"STR_LOC_HUMANIST_VILLA_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}Our spies have located a countryside villa where Humanist supporters are having a meeting with one of their leaders. I don't need to explain how important this opportunity to strike is. On the other hand, the enemy is numerous and has at least one armored car. I won't be too surprised if you chicken out of this.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_RAYNOR", "Raynerd Must Survive"},
		{"STR_LOC_RAYNOR_TITLE", "Raynerd Must Survive"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_RAYNOR", "Imprisoned Raynerd"},
		{"STR_LOC_RAYNOR_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}We're going to bust up one of the hell-prisons where the Beastmen keep our mutant kin in captivity. Most importantly, this prison holds one of our special operatives, a Raynerd. You will recognize him by his white suit. It would be good to rescue any other captives as well, but don't jeopardize the primary objective. And don't forget to take your break-in tools.{NEWLINE}Weather: Freezing Cold; Minefields; No Wide Craft"},
		{"STR_LOC_RET_DUNGEON", "Reticulan Vats"},
		{"STR_LOC_RET_DUNGEON_TITLE", "Reticulan Vats"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_RET_DUNGEON", "Reticulan Vats"},
		{"STR_LOC_RET_DUNGEON_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}Today's mission requires a squad of trained and willing Peasants. Why? Because the objective is to infiltrate Reticulan Vats, where female captives are kept for breeding purposes. They will be resisting. You will act as willing slaves, break out from inside. Squad size limited to 12 to not rouse suspicion. No equipment or pets. You will have 64 turns to get out. If you don't manage to secure the whole facility in time, carry any captures to the exit located on level 3, in the central area."},
		{"STR_LOC_ELFMAN_BROS", "Bank Robbery"},
		{"STR_LOC_ELFMAN_BROS_TITLE", "Bank Robbery"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_ELFMAN_BROS", "Bank Robbery"},
		{"STR_LOC_ELFMAN_BROS_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx{NEWLINE}Today we need your help in cultivating the noble spirit of competition. Our greatest rival, the Elfman Bro$, keeps a large amount of Old Money in a local branch here. We would really appreciate if you deposited that money in our account instead.{NEWLINE}Be careful - you only have 20 turns before the police arrives.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_EXTERMINATOR", "The Professional"},
		{"STR_LOC_EXTERMINATOR_TITLE", "The Professional"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_EXTERMINATOR", "Professional Pest Control Site"},
		{"STR_LOC_EXTERMINATOR_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level C{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx{NEWLINE}The Exterminators are highly paid professionals, working for Govts to take care of various pest infestations, like Deep Ones, Zombies or Chryssalids. Least hassle for the Govts that way. So what makes this case special? The Exterminator in question is a pesky bastard who bought a Platinum Life Insurance Plan from us. Hence, his death would make us very sad, and we would be very grateful if you went there and made sure it won't happen.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot."},
		{"STR_LOC_GNOME_LAIR", "Gnome's Lair"},
		{"STR_LOC_GNOME_LAIR_TITLE", "Gnome's Lair"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_GNOME_LAIR", "Gnome's Lair"},
		{"STR_LOC_GNOME_LAIR_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx{NEWLINE}Dear Lady, today you might have 1,250 Tokens coming your way. We'd like to hire you to retrieve a valuable individual. As you might have heard, Gnomes are highly elusive Hellerium mutants, gifted with exceptional tech savvy and longevity. We happen to have learned a location of an underground arms workshop one Gnome runs for the Raiders. Do I need to say more?{NEWLINE}Depth: Very Shallow."},
		{"STR_LOC_DARK_TOWER", "Mysterious Tower"},
		{"STR_LOC_DARK_TOWER2", "Mysterious Tower"},
		{"STR_LOC_DARK_TOWER_TITLE", "Mysterious Tower"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_DARK_TOWER", "Mysterious Tower"},
		{"STR_LOC_DARK_TOWER_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Wiz Biz{NEWLINE}An experiment in planar travel went a bit too well, resulting in the creation of an anomaly. It is presumed the experimenter is gone for good, so the Society tasks you with salvaging the place, especially recovering any leftover Void Salts you can find. Expect to face demons and other nuisances that tend to accompany a rift in reality.{NEWLINE}Weather: Unpredictable."},
		{"STR_MISSION_UAC_VAULTS", "!UAC Vaults!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_UAC_VAULTS_PREQ", "UAC Vaults (Preq)"},
		{"STR_MISSION_UAC_VAULTS_UFOPEDIA", "Gathering info on this long-defunct organization, we came to conclusion they got closed down by Star Gods quite possibly as a response to tampering with Shadowtech; clues are given both by history and by the UAC legacy surviving to this day, for good or worse. If this connection with Shadowtech is indeed true, we might be able to find a few yet-undiscovered UAC bases, most likely located deep underground, thanks to our Hyperwave Mystycism."},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS", "UAC Vaults"},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_TIGHT", "UAC Vaults"},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_TOXIC", "UAC Vaults"},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_TITLE", "UAC Vaults"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_UAC_VAULTS", "UAC Vaults"},
		{"STR_ALERT_UAC_VAULTS", "UAC Vaults"},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_BRIEFING", "Cap'n, we have succeeded in divining the location of an old UAC base.{NEWLINE}This one is relatively easy to access, and we can bring a normal attack squad of up to 25 people there. It'd be a wise precaution to take some good digging equipment with us.{NEWLINE}We get just one shot at this: if we don't explore the base, someone else will.{NEWLINE}Depth: Deep. Conditions: Hot."},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_TIGHT_BRIEFING", "Cap'n, we have succeeded in divining the location of an old UAC base.{NEWLINE}It won't be easy to reach, and only small soldiers like Lokk'Naars can navigate underground passages leading there. It'd be a wise precaution to take some good digging equipment with us.{NEWLINE}We get just one shot at this: if we don't explore the base, someone else will.{NEWLINE}Depth: Deep. Conditions: Hot."},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_TOXIC_BRIEFING", "Cap'n, we have succeeded in divining the location of an old UAC base.{NEWLINE}Its exploration poses a bit of a problem, though, because it's likely filled with a poisonous gas, judging by its geological location. It'd be a wise precaution to also take some good digging equipment with us.{NEWLINE}We get just one shot at this: if we don't explore the base, someone else will.{NEWLINE}Depth: Deep. Conditions: Toxic."},
		{"STR_THE_UNDERGROUND_FACILITY_QUEST", "The Underbase Facility Quest"},
		{"STR_THE_UNDERGROUND_FACILITY_QUEST_UFOPEDIA", "The documents found by a Gnome in the tunnels below our Hideout call for an Adventure! There is supposedly a whole ancient facility hidden somewhere down there! However, to be able to mount an expedition into the depths, we will need the knowledge of Underground Missions, Gnomes, and the caves themselves... We will also need a crew of sufficienty compact and hardy folk to venture there."},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_UFQ", "Underbase Facility"},
		{"STR_ALERT_UAC_VAULTS_UFQ", "Underbase Facility Found!"},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_VAULTS_UFQ_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}We expected all sorts of tentacle monsters, but apparently there isn't any. What a letdown. Is this a teaser, or what? Also, if we blow this adventure, it means it's not worth our effort, so we got one shot at this.{NEWLINE}Only small races can go there."},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_SHELTER", "UAC Shelter"},
		{"STR_ALERT_UAC_SHELTER", "UAC Shelter Located!"},
		{"STR_LOC_UAC_SHELTER_BRIEFING", "Our investigation borne fruit, we have located one of the secret UAC shelters. Salvaging it might prove difficult, but scrounging up rare UAC tech might be worth it. We will have to force our way in, so we'd better take some heavy duty mining equipment. UAC did not build from Plastasteel, so a Fusion Torch might be overkill, but better safe than sorry!{NEWLINE}Only small races can go there. Conditions: deep and hot."},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOMED_FARM", "Doomed Farm"},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOMED_FARM2", "Doomed Farm"},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOMED_FARM_TITLE", "Doomed Farm"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_DOOMED_FARM", "Doomed Farm"},
		{"STR_ALERT_DOOMED_FARM", "Doomed Farm"},
		{"STR_LOC_DOOMED_FARM_BRIEFING", "This land suffers from frequent incursions of Dark Ones, raiding villages and scaring off travellers. People want someone to solve this problem, and let that someone be us, Cap'n! There is no hefty price for taking care of these Dark Ones, but we can count on the locals' gratitude and earn some infamy. After all, everybody hates Dark Ones!{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate. Sea: Uneasy."},
		{"STR_LOC_TIGER_TANK", "Sitzkrieg"},
		{"STR_LOC_TIGER_TANK_TITLE", "Sitzkrieg"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_TIGER_TANK", "Sitzkrieg"},
		{"STR_LOC_TIGER_TANK_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Jack{NEWLINE}At ease, Mercenaries. The Humanists are making a landgrab on one of my outlying towns. The local militia is overwhelmed, as Humanists brought a tank. No, not one of these small robotic platforms, but the real deal. The militia is currently sitting in wait. They will spring into action once you arrive. If you don't destroy the tank, I will have to cede the town.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_DEEP_ONE_02", "They Came From The Sea"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEEP_ONE_02_TITLE", "They Came From The Sea"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_DEEP_ONE_02", "They Came From The Sea"},
		{"STR_LOC_DEEP_ONE_02_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level B{NEWLINE}From: Jack{NEWLINE}One of my tribes reports unusual Deep One activity. Something is driving them nuts. I need you to crew one of our coastal forts and scatter their main assault. Local militia will take care of the rest. Go there quickly - if they pass the presidium, we will have no choice but to evacuate. (24 turn limit). One more thing: beware of stepping too close to the sea.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_EXECUTIVE_OUTCOMES", "Executive Outcomes"},
		{"STR_LOC_EXECUTIVE_OUTCOMES_TITLE", "Executive Outcomes"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_EXECUTIVE_OUTCOMES", "Executive Outcomes"},
		{"STR_LOC_EXECUTIVE_OUTCOMES_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level A{NEWLINE}From: Goblin Zaxx{NEWLINE}Hello, our important Partner. We have a sensitive job for you. A Paramilitary Company has stolen a number of our freshly-printed IOUs. It would be an... unwanted complication when we put these papers into circulation. Retrieve the IOUs stored in the PMC's vault. Time is of the essence since the PMC has the support of the local militia.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_LOC_HIGH_CASTLE", "Man From The High Castle"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_HIGH_CASTLE", "Humanist Castle"},
		{"STR_LOC_HIGH_CASTLE_BRIEFING", "Bounty Hunt Level A{NEWLINE}From: Mutant Alliance's Saya{NEWLINE}This worthless piece of old ruins is the residence of a very high ranked Humanist. By surrounding himself with walls and henchmen, he lives in an ilusion of safety. Prove him wrong, and take this opportunity to kill a whole lot of Humanists in one go. By the way, the place has radars and AA defenses, so you need to approach on foot.{NEWLINE}Weather: Temperate."},
		{"STR_AIRCAR_RACE_FINISH", "Aircar Race"},
		{"STR_AIRCAR_RACE_WON", "Race Won!"},
		{"STR_ALERT_AIRCAR_RACE", "Aircar Race!"},
		{"STR_ALERT_AIRCAR_RACE_DESC", "Bounty Hunt Level D{NEWLINE}From: Jack{NEWLINE}I heard you're quite the hot stuff when it comes to flying, so I got you an invitation to an aircar race. Jump into your ride, and get to the target town before the others. It should take them 2 to 4 hours, depending on luck of my Lokk'Naar saboteurs. Besides the fame and cash, there are 150 Tokens in it for you - if you win. I'm betting some big money on your fresh faces, so you'd better do. One more thing - Hellerium-fired ships aren't allowed."},
		{"STR_MARKER_AIRCAR_RACE", "Aircar Race Finish"},
		{"STR_AIRCAR_RACE_FINISH_BRIEFING", "Congratulations! You're the winner of this month's Yello's Aircar Rally! Yet again, beauty, skill and raw engine power have triumphed over the lack of the aforementioned! You have won $100k in golden chips, and this super-hot bikini as a bonus! A freshly-caught, young and pristine Academy Student will deliver the goods. You can have her too - if you manage to calm the spectators down before they tear her to pieces! (Press End Turn to claim the prize and fame)."},
		{"STR_GROUND_VEHICLE_RACE", "Ground Vehicle Race!"},
		{"STR_GROUND_VEHICLE_RACE_FINISH", "Ground Vehicle Race!"},
		{"STR_GROUND_VEHICLE_RACE_WON", "Race Won!"},
		{"STR_GROUND_VEHICLE_RACE_DESC", "There is news about another run of the Burning Wheels race taking place in this town! Contestants from all over the world are, well, burning the wheels to get there ASAP. We can win too, if we manage to get there first (under 30 hours... and ideally within half that time). Of course, we also need a WHEELED vehicle."},
		{"STR_MARKER_GROUND_VEHICLE_RACE", "Ground Race Finish"},
		{"STR_GROUND_VEHICLE_RACE_FINISH_BRIEFING", "Congratulations! You have won a set of Burning Wheels this month! The prize, as usual, is an intact Academy Drone, a purse of Credits, some barrels of fuel, plus adoration of the masses and maybe even some followers! The Drone will be ritually released to celebrate the victory. It might cause some injuries and even fatalities, but, as we say here, all is wheel that ends wheel! (Press End Turn to claim the prize and fame)."},
		{"STR_ALERT_ORBIT", "Orbital Mission"},
		{"STR_ORBITAL_ENTRY_POINT", "Orbit Entry Point"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_1", "Orbital Lab"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_1_BRIEFING", "This space laboratory seems to be quite silent and secluded. Let's raid it and plunder its riches!{NEWLINE}Only 0-G allowed. Sea: Uneven.{NEWLINE}BLAST OFF?"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_2", "Refuelling Station"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_2_BRIEFING", "Many ships land on this platform to refuel. We shall take all fuel and pay nothing!{NEWLINE}Only 0-G allowed. Sea: Uneven.{NEWLINE}BLAST OFF?"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_3", "Sleeping Satellite"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_3_BRIEFING", "The guys manning this station have surely grown sleepy due to the lack of dangers - let's wake them up!{NEWLINE}Only 0-G allowed. Sea: Normal.{NEWLINE}BLAST OFF?"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_4", "Cold Storage"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_4_BRIEFING", "We have found a small, orbital prison built for the likes of us. Down with oppression!{NEWLINE}Only 0-G allowed. Sea: Uneven.{NEWLINE}BLAST OFF?"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_5", "Lost Spaceship"},
		{"STR_LOC_SPACE_STATION_5_BRIEFING", "A small, mysterious, seemingly abandoned spaceship was spotted in orbit.{NEWLINE}Only 0-G allowed. Sea: Unknown.{NEWLINE}BLAST OFF?"},
		{"STR_ALERT_COMMS_DISRUPTION", "Disruptive Transmissions"},
		{"STR_LOC_COMMS_DISRUPTION", "Disruptive Transmissions"},
		{"STR_LOC_COMMS_DISRUPTION_BRIEFING", "This strange satellite is emitting some trace radiation which causes disruptions to our Shadowtech, and somehow, also to our Laboratory. This makes all our operations more difficult, which hurts our morale, efficiency and reputations. If we just bounce it off the sky with our ship (by aborting), we will reduce the score hit to 100 Infamy."},
		{"STR_EVENT_COMMS_DISRUPTION_DESCRIPTION", "Our Shadowtech experienced a series of weird malfunctions over the duration of the few last hours. The Gals report experiencing strange, scary visions appearing in their heads and their bodies acting compulsively on their own. They are seriously spooked (-500 Infamy). The Brainers speculate we were hit by a beam coming from the space, and that we should improve our space capacity to confront this new threat."},
		{"STR_LOC_HOT_PURSUITS", "Hot Pursuits"},
		{"STR_LOC_HOT_PURSUITS_BRIEFING", "Did you hear the news? There was a huge explosion at this town and now everything is on fire! If we brave the firestorm (and whatever caused it), we can turn a profit on this. If we want to own the place, we need to survive the flames somehow (36 turns is maximum in any case). Alternatively, we can enter the buildings, minimap in hand, break the crates if applicable, and flee with whatever we can grab.{NEWLINE}Weather: IT BURNS. Sea: Stormy."},
		{"STR_MARKER_HOT_PURSUITS", "Burning Town"},
		{"STR_ALERT_HOT_PURSUITS", "Hot Pursuits"},
		{"STR_MISSION_GHOUL_REFINERY", "!Organ Traffickers!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_GHOUL_REFINERY_UFOPEDIA", "Having interrogated Academy staff, and gotten some insights into the darkness of The True Reality, we think we have uncovered the secret behind the long-lasting smoothness of Academy boss gals. Simple enough - as they're catching mutants for 'humanitarian reasons', they 'disappear' some of them to the Ghouls in exchange for choice organ transplants. We can brave these chem-contaminated Ghoul hellholes to rescue some victims and grab Ghoul tech, but it won't be easy."},
		{"STR_MARKER_GHOUL_REFINERY", "Ghoul Town"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GHOUL_REFINERY", "Organ Grinder"},
		{"STR_LOC_GHOUL_REFINERY", "Organ Grinder"},
		{"STR_LOC_GHOUL_REFINERY_BRIEFING", "The locals shudder when they mention this contaminated area, where the Ghouls are conducting their gruesome trade. We need to prepare for acid rains and noxious fumes if we endeavour to loot the place and rescue the victims of the ghouls!{NEWLINE}Weather: heavy smog and acid rain. Sea: Stormy. No Wide Craft."},
		{"STR_ALERT_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY", "Scout Gate"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY", "Scout Gate"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY_TITLE", "Scout Gate"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY", "Scout Gate"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY_BRIEFING", "From: The Red Mage{NEWLINE}Hel... Uh, Avast, Cap'n. I have managed to open a Tannhauser Gate at this location. I have no idea what to expect on the other side, but that's why I'm hiring you. Hurry up, it won't stay open for too long, and opening it wasn't for free, you know."},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY_2", "Dungeon Of Death"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY_3", "Dungeon Of Death"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY_2_BRIEFING", "The decrepit staircase leads you to a maze of ancient halls. The smell of death surrounds you... The place is disorienting, and someone apparently took all your Shadowrealms equipment away when you were unconscious after passing the portal..."},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_ENTRY_3_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}As you descend deeper into the labyrinth, your minds start hear a cold, irresistible command to submit to your final fate, and your members start to move on their own ... Your senses become numb, and before you know it, you end up locked up in a cage."},
		{"STR_ALERT_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER", "Dungeon Of Death"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER", "Dungeon Of Death"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_TITLE", "Dungeon Of Death"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER", "Gate (Dungeon Of Death)"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}There's an unknown force permeating this eldritch location, a force that compels any visitor to surrender to the ghoulish inhabitants. They take away all the possessions and prepare the guests for some horrible fate...{NEWLINE}But some of you manage to shake the stupor off!"},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_BRIEFING2", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Yet again we gain access to the same area of Hell. And yet again, if we go there, we will fall victim to its prison magic and temporarily lose our Shadowrealms equipment."},
		{"STR_LOC_CATACOMBS_BUTCHER_WON", "Against all odds, you've managed to clear this hellish dungeon. Working for the Red Mage is surely a chore..."},
		{"STR_MISSION_HALLS_OF_FEAR", "*Halls of Fear*"},
		{"STR_MISSION_HALLS_OF_FEAR_UFOPEDIA", "Our analysis of the Realm of Fear allows us to adjust the portals to avoid being trapped in the Death Dungeon. We have identified long hallways (measured probably in thousands of kilometres), connecting various parts of this underground hellscape. Travelling them seems like the next logical step in exploring and exploiting this dimension."},
		{"STR_LOC_HALLS_OF_FEAR", "Halls of Fear"},
		{"STR_ALERT_HALLS_OF_FEAR", "Halls of Fear"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_HALLS_OF_FEAR", "Gate (Halls of Fear)"},
		{"STR_LOC_HALLS_OF_FEAR_BRIEFING", "As predicted, this Tannhauser Gate connects to the long hallways of the Fear Realm. We expect numerous locals, better armed than in the Death Dungeon, but at least this time they won't take our Shadowrealms equipment. There is no retreat from this mission."},
		{"STR_GATE_OF_FEAR_DONE", "Past the Gate of Fear"},
		{"STR_GATE_OF_FEAR_DONE_UFOPEDIA", "We have managed to unlock the Gate of Fear, which allows us to open Tannhauser Gates to the parts of the realm that were previously inaccessible, like the Necropolis."},
		{"STR_LOC_GATE_OF_FEAR", "Gate of Fear"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GATE_OF_FEAR", "Gate of Fear"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_GATE_OF_FEAR", "Gate (Gate of Fear)"},
		{"STR_LOC_GATE_OF_FEAR_BRIEFING", "To finally break out of the hellish, unending dungeons and travel across the Realm of Fear in its entirety, we need to open this gate, and for that, we need to bring the corresponding Padlock with us. Of course, we can expect heavy resistance in such a strategic location. We CAN retreat from this mission."},
		{"STR_LOC_NECROPOLIS", "Endless Necropolis"},
		{"STR_ALERT_NECROPOLIS", "Endless Necropolis"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_NECROPOLIS", "Gate (Necropolis)"},
		{"STR_LOC_NECROPOLIS_BRIEFING", "We've found just that when trying to open a Gate to the surface of the Realm of Fear. But some of its areas seem to be rich in treasure. We will just have to deal with the swarms of local residents. And who knows what can be found beyond the Necropolis?"},
		{"STR_LOC_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_SCOUTING", "Plunge Into Deadspace"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_SCOUTING", "Scout Gate"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD", "Gate (Deadspace)"},
		{"STR_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_SCOUTING_BRIEFING", "From: The Red Mage{NEWLINE}'Aha! I'm finally ready with the Gate! The quest for the Fountain of Youth can begin! On the other side is the Shadowrealm of Death. I don't imagine the place is very hospitable, but your task is simple, my retainer: obtain the evidence of the fabled Water of Life. With this, I will be able to prepare the next step. Now, go! Plunge into the unknown once again!'"},
		{"STR_LOC_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD", "Deadspace Delving"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD", "Deadspace Delving"},
		{"STR_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_BRIEFING", "We have delivered to the Red Mage the Water of Life she wanted so much, but what's stopping us from exploring this Shadowrealm some more? We might find some interesting things. Besides, we have improved our targeting of the Gate to make sure the area is more isolated (no Dead Cops reinforcements expected this time)."},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEAD_SEWERS", "!Sewers of Death!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_DEAD_SEWERS_UFOPEDIA", "The Water of Life must be coming from somewhere, and sure enough, it's coming from the Dead City's sprawling sewers. The sewers seem to be chock full of those Skeletons who don't like the current regime, and they won't like our presence either. At least we won't meet any Dead Cops, but we suspect the Sewers, or whatever lies below, is the origin of the Ghost Gals... The vibes we feel are way too similar to those we get from Shade Summoning..."},
		{"STR_LOC_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_SEWERS", "Sewers of Death"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_SEWERS", "Sewers of Death"},
		{"STR_CITY_OF_THE_DEAD_SEWERS_BRIEFING", "We've managed to open a Gate into a section of sewers deep below the urban surface of Paradiso. The place is swarming with Awakened Dead. After we pacify it, we can use it as a place to meditate on Dream Echoes to learn more about this realm."},
		{"STR_LOC_FOUNTAIN_OF_YOUTH", "Fountain of Youth"},
		{"STR_LOC_FOUNTAIN_OF_YOUTH_G", "Fountain of Youth"},
		{"STR_ALERT_FOUNTAIN_OF_YOUTH", "Fountain of Youth"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_FOUNTAIN_OF_YOUTH", "Gate (Fountain of Youth)"},
		{"STR_FOUNTAIN_OF_YOUTH_BRIEFING", "This is it. Time to help the Red Mage with her ritual of Descent Into Shadow. We need to take her Ritual Coffin with us, and once she rises from it, to protect her until the ritual is complete.{NEWLINE}There is no escape from this mission; if the ritual fails and the Red Mage dies, we need to defeat all the enemies in the area to return to our world."},
		{"STR_FOUNTAIN_OF_YOUTH_G_BRIEFING", "This is it. Time to help the Red Mage with her ritual of Descent Into Shadow. We need to take her Ritual Coffin with us, and once she rises from it, to protect her until the ritual is complete.{NEWLINE}Gudrun, as her assistant, took the task of distracting the locals, so we should be facing less of them.{NEWLINE}There is no escape from this mission; if the ritual fails and the Red Mage dies, we need to defeat all the enemies in the area to return to our world."},
		{"STR_MISSION_INTO_THE_VOID", "!Into the Void!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_INTO_THE_VOID_UFOPEDIA", "We know the Gate and the Key. Now we only need the right Time and Space. The Void awaits. We shall reach out and seize its secrets."},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_NIGHTOSHPHERE", "Gate (Void)"},
		{"STR_LOC_NIGHTOSHPHERE_DELOREAN", "Into the Void"},
		{"STR_LOC_NIGHTOSHPHERE_DELOREAN_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}It's time to enter the Void. Our objective here is to find Red Queen's car, which should be somewhere south of our entry point. We don't have to eliminate all the locals; when we find the car, we can use it to return home (put crew and loot on green exit tiles and Abort mission.)"},
		{"STR_LOC_NIGHTOSHPHERE_HARVEST", "Void Harvest"},
		{"STR_LOC_NIGHTOSHPHERE_HARVEST_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Since we have access to the Nightosphere, what's stopping us from plundering its riches? This mission will only end if we eliminate all the enemies; there's no retreat."},
		{"STR_MARKER_GDX_PRISON", "X-Prison"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GDX_PRISON", "X-Prison"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_PRISON", "X-Prison"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_PRISON_BRIEFING", "We're ready to infiltrate a prison where ones like us are being experimented upon. We need to pretend we're surrendering, so no armor or weapons, nor any equipment can be taken on this mission (except Shivs). Only Uber gals should participate. We need to find data on Dr. X (her office is likely to have a 'chair of confessions' nearby), and either escape through the top, or clear the whole place."},
		{"STR_MARKER_GDX_DUEL", "Duel Arena"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GDX_DUEL", "Dr. X Challenges You!"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_DUEL", "Duel with Dr. X"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_DUEL_BRIEFING", "Dr. X called us and set the location of the duel{NEWLINE}she envisioned. The whole place is likely a trap{NEWLINE}with no way of escaping. Go, if you want,{NEWLINE}but I would advise against placing yourself at her mercy.{NEWLINE}Anyway she will be expecting a single person craft coming,{NEWLINE}and you wearing a Gravball outfit. No weapons.{NEWLINE}(+200 score for ignoring the mission)"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_DUEL_BRIEFING_2", "I've been waiting for you.{NEWLINE}Proceed downstairs to the arena and{NEWLINE}pick up the Disc.{NEWLINE}Don't be afraid."},
		{"STR_GDX_DUEL_LOST_01", "As you come back to your senses, you notice Dr. X standing above you. She slowly removes the final parts of her Gravball outfit, then lights up a cigarette, regarding you with a weird, inscrutable look. You're not sure if that's triumph, or curiosity, or greed, or lust, or love, or all of these things together, or maybe a joke, whose meaning is known only to her. One way or another, she looks like she's having the time of her life."},
		{"STR_GDX_DUEL_LOST_02", "She exhales smoke and starts to speak: 'They say you shouldn't create things you cannot control. I did not know if I had the strength of will to handle you. Yet I won... again. Now the struggle is over, and we're all alone here, you and me, with no Academy interfering. Nothing left to hide between us... as you can see.'"},
		{"STR_GDX_DUEL_LOST_03", "'You know, I was never even considering having children. Maybe I should have, being the head of my household. But in a weird way, you are my child. I raised you, I nurtured you. You, and others like you. And you will take your rightful place as my heirs. It makes my black heart tingle with such a strange excitement. It is you who did that to me, you little cute thing.'"},
		{"STR_GDX_DUEL_LOST_04", "'Are you worried about your band? I am sure they will find themselves a new leader. All the struggle, all the fighting, all the worry, it is all over for you. A better time starts. You will see the nice family I have created for you and your sisters. There is so much for us to achieve together. Things the world has never seen before.'"},
		{"STR_GDX_DUEL_LOST_05", "'Now come. Come to your mother. I have such sights to show you.'"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_CANYON_OF_DEATH", "Dr. X's Residence"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_CANYON_OF_DEATH_TITLE", "Canyon of Death"},
		{"STR_ALERT_GDX_CANYON_OF_DEATH", "Dr. X's Residence"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_GDX_CANYON_OF_DEATH", "Dr. X's Residence"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_CANYON_OF_DEATH_BRIEFING", "Our sources report massive Humanist activity in the area of Dr. X's old residence, which indicates its value might be higher than we anticipated. We can expect heavy AA defenses, so we need to take indirect approach route through a canyon, then hitch a lift that leads up the mountain, into the residence proper. Difficult terrain rules out the use of non-flying tanks, and we can expect heavy weapon emplacements inside the canyon.{NEWLINE}Weather: Scorching Hot"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_HOUSE", "Mountaintop Station"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_HOUSE_TITLE", "Dr. X's Residence"},
		{"STR_LOC_GDX_HOUSE_BRIEFING", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}After the long elevator ride, we have arrived on the mountaintop. The structure here is swarming with Humanist troops. Time to storm it and make its secrets ours!"},
		{"STR_GDX_HOUSE_ENDING_TXT", "After clearing out all Humanist presence in Dr. X's castle, we scoured it for promised treasure. Two items caught your attention: a grimoire of sorcerous magic, and an ancient sword, called 'The Black Falcon'."},
		{"STR_LOC_MOON_NAZIS_1", "Black Sun Outpost"},
		{"STR_LOC_MOON_NAZIS_1_TITLE", "Black Sun Outpost"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MOON_NAZIS_1", "Black Sun Outpost"},
		{"STR_LOC_MOON_NAZIS_1_BRIEFING", "Careful combing of Moon's surface has shown a spike of Shadow activity. This must be one of Glitterdust collection sites. We need to land on the Moon, find out what's going on and blast this place to pieces.{NEWLINE}Weather: Moon"},
		{"STR_LOC_MOON_NAZIS_2", "Black Sun HQ"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MOON_NAZIS_2", "Black Sun HQ"},
		{"STR_LOC_MOON_NAZIS_2_BRIEFING", "We have finally pinpointed the location of the most secret Humanist base. All that remains is to storm it, but it's not going to be easy. We need to approach the location on foot (no craft) and storm through the fortifications to find entrance to the base proper, which is deep underground.{NEWLINE}Weather: Moon"},
		{"STR_LOC_THULEBASE", "Heart of Darkness"},
		{"STR_LOC_THULEBASE_BRIEFING", "The sprawling complex under the surface of the Moon is swarming with Humanists and all sorts of horrors they created. Killing them all might prove difficult, since they will be rushing all their reserves to this location. However, all we need to do is to locate their main laboratory and grab the master copy of their database, then we can retreat."},
		{"STR_LOC_THULE_BOSSBATTLE", "Blacksun High Temple"},
		{"STR_MARKER_THULE_BOSSBATTLE", "Gate to Blacksun High Temple"},
		{"STR_THULE_BOSSBATTLE_BRIEFING", "With her own means, Gudrun managed to open the gate to the 'Leader'... the legendary hero, now your enemy, Otto Zander. The other side doesn't feel encouraging. The portal opens into the heart of a jumbled mess of fused ice and machinery, the Humanist structures changed by the Shadowrealm. The portal radiates cold and despair. Only a squad of 6 can go through, and you're wondering if Gudrun should lead it..."},
		{"STR_ZBOSS_DEFEATED_1_TXT", "When the Super Aryan falls, his psionic death scream blinds and deafens you. After a while, in the darkness, you begin to see a face, an apparition forming. It seems to be speaking something, almost inaudibly, so you strain your hearing and nearly go deaf when his voice, cold and powerful{NEWLINE}'SOLDIER, CAN YOU HEAR ME?'{NEWLINE}hits you like an avalanche."},
		{"STR_ZBOSS_DEFEATED_2_TXT", "Before your reeling mind fully forms a confirmation, he continues{NEWLINE}'DO YOU REALIZE WHAT YOU HAVE JUST DONE?'{NEWLINE}You regain your wits just enough to throw back a raw, emotional,{NEWLINE}'I killed... I killed Otto Zander.' In response you hear strange rasping sounds, which you not immediately recognize as laughter. Which is then cut with an icy blade.{NEWLINE}'ZANDER LIVES.'"},
		{"STR_ZBOSS_DEFEATED_3_TXT", "'THE IMPOSTOR SHARED MY MENTAL PATTERN. IT WAS IMPRINTED ON YOUR MIND. THAT IS WHY WE CAN TALK.'{NEWLINE}'But... how... why?' Your half formed question is cut off again.{NEWLINE}'I KNOW WHO YOU ARE. DO YOU WANT TO KILL THE ALIEN BRAIN?'{NEWLINE}You regain enough resolve to say, 'I do!'{NEWLINE}'IT IS NOT ENOUGH. WE DID THAT BEFORE.'"},
		{"STR_ZBOSS_DEFEATED_4_TXT", "'Not enough... but... And you?'{NEWLINE}The apparition doesn't wait for you to finish.{NEWLINE}'I HAVE A BETTER PLAN. BUT I NEED YOUR HELP, SOLDIER. MEET ME AT LABYRINTHUS NOCTIS.'{NEWLINE}And with that... the vision is gone."},
		{"STR_LOC_CRYPTEK_CAVES", "Crypt of the Technomancer"},
		{"STR_LOC_CRYPTEK_CAVES_TITLE", "Crypt of the Technomancer"},
		{"STR_ALERT_CRYPTEK_CAVES", "Black Mask Trail Found!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_CRYPTEK_CAVES", "Crypt of the Technomancer"},
		{"STR_LOC_CRYPTEK_CAVES_BRIEFING", "In an area infamous for disappearing people, we have located a secret cave, guarded by Zombie Troopers. If our lead is true, a Technomancer, wearing a mask resembling the one we've got, dwells there, apparently feeling confident that no one will dare to challenge her. This is a chance to advance our investigations. The place is a maze and employing SENSE can prove highly useful.{NEWLINE}Depth: Shallow"},
		{"STR_LOC_MAGE_VILLA", "Mage's Villa"},
		{"STR_LOC_MAGE_VILLA_TITLE", "Padlocks of Chaos!"},
		{"STR_ALERT_MAGE_VILLA", "Padlocks of Chaos!"},
		{"STR_MARKER_MAGE_VILLA", "Mage's Villa"},
		{"STR_LOC_MAGE_VILLA_BRIEFING", "From: The Red Mage{NEWLINE}I summon thee, my Pirate retainer. The opportunity to strike has just presented itself. This villa belongs to a Mage of ill reputation, who is in possession of a Padlock of Chaos. You will approach the villa on foot and surround it to prevent the mage from escaping or calling any reinforcements. My intelligence tells of Zombie Trooper bodyguards and a Vampire butler, of the kind that can turn invisible. I lack the full picture, though, so be prepared for anything. Better don't take more stuff than you can carry."},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE_ENTRY", "Winter Palace"},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE_MAIN", "Winter Palace 2"},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE_DUNGEON", "Winter Palace 3"},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE", "Attack on Winter Palace"},
		{"STR_ALERT_WINTER_PALACE", "Attack on Winter Palace"},
		{"STR_MARKER_WINTER_PALACE", "Winter Palace"},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE_BRIEFING", "We have sniffed an opportunity to kidnap Aurora. We've located her at the Canadian Winter Palace, and she'll stay there for the next several days. It'll be a bit difficult. We cannot simply fly there, because they would shoot us down. We need to do it the hard way: approach the outer wall by land, and break through the fortifications."},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE_2_BRIEFING", "We have breached through the outer gates and into the palace proper. Now we need to locate Queen Aurora within its maze of corridors."},
		{"STR_LOC_WINTER_PALACE_3_BRIEFING", "We have been tricked. We didn't find Aurora, just a cybernetic doll in her likeness. But we've also found a mysterious underground complex under the palace. Maybe the answers lie somewhere there... if we dare to enter."},
		{"STR_MARKER_EUROSYNDICATE_ELIMINATION", "Elimination Target"},
		{"STR_ALERT_EUROSYNDICATE_ELIMINATION", "Elimination Request From EuroSyndicate"},
		{"STR_LOC_EUROSYNDICATE_ELIMINATION", "ELIMINATION MISSION"},
		{"STR_LOC_EUROSYNDICATE_ELIMINATION_BRIEFING", "EUROSYNDICATE MINITEL NETWORK INITIALIZING{NEWLINE}TRANSMISSION START{NEWLINE}MISSION: INFILTRATE DESIGNATED AREA ON FOOT. ELIMINATE ALL TARGETS. PAYMENT: $1,250,000. ORBITAL STRIKE IS PREPARED AS AN ALTERNATE OPTION IF YOUR PROGRESS IS INSUFFICIENT. FAILURE TO COMPLY WILL RESULT IN CONSEQUENCES."},
		{"STR_LOC_EUROSYNDICATE_ELIMINATION_LOST", "The locals witnessed only a lance of searing light, piercing the heaven and vaporising the town. Your crew had no time to witness anything at all."},
		{"STR_LOC_RITUAL_CAVE", "Ratmen Cache"},
		{"STR_LOC_RITUAL_CAVE_TITLE", "Ratmen Cache"},
		{"STR_ALERT_RITUAL_CAVE", "Ratmen Cache"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_RITUAL_CAVE", "Ratmen Cave"},
		{"STR_LOC_RITUAL_CAVE_BRIEFING", "There are rumours about an underground cache of Ratmen treasure in this area. However, the tunnels leading there are very tight, and only Lokk'Naars and similarly small units will be able to infiltrate them (and only when wearing standard-sized armor).{NEWLINE}Depth: Average"},
		{"STR_MISSION_LOKNAR_ALTAR", "!Demon God Shrines!"},
		{"STR_MISSION_LOKNAR_ALTAR_UFOPEDIA", "Lokk'Naars speak of underground shrines, dedicated to their Demon Gods. Lokk'Naars have built these shrines in centuries past, when they were still dwelling beneath the earth. If these Demon Gods have a connection to Shadowmasters - or ARE Shadowmasters themselves, this might be a lead worth investigating... We will study old maps and inform you, Cap'n, once such a shrine is located."},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_ALTAR", "Demon God Shrine"},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_ALTAR_TITLE", "Demon God Shrine"},
		{"STR_ALERT_LOKNAR_ALTAR", "Demon God Shrine"},
		{"STR_MARKER_LOC_LOKNAR_ALTAR", "Demon God Shrine"},
		{"STR_LOC_LOKNAR_ALTAR_BRIEFING", "We have pinpointed the location of one of the fabled underground shrines. Who knows what horrors lurk there? What forgotten treasures await for the brave? Only Lokk'Naars and similarly small units will be able to infiltrate them (and only when wearing standard-sized armor).{NEWLINE}Depth: Deep"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO", "Old Earth Metro"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_TOXIC", "Old Earth Metro"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_IRRADIATED", "Old Earth Metro"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_PSYCHEDELIC", "Old Earth Metro"},
		{"STR_ALERT_OLD_EARTH_METRO", "Old Earth Metro"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_BRIEFING", "Despite the passage of centuries, there are still some unexplored (ie. not looted) underground subways left from the times of Old Earth. And with the help of Lokk'Naar experts, we have found another one. Better to send ours there before other Lokk'Naar scavengers learn about this location...{NEWLINE}Depth: Average"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_TOXIC_BRIEFING", "Despite the passage of centuries, there are still some unexplored (ie. not looted) underground subways left from the times of Old Earth. And with the help of Lokk'Naar experts, we have found another one. Better to send ours there before other Lokk'Naar scavengers learn about this location...{NEWLINE}Warning: the place is filled with toxic gas.{NEWLINE}Depth: Average"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_IRRADIATED_BRIEFING", "Despite the passage of centuries, there are still some unexplored (ie. not looted) underground subways left from the times of Old Earth. And with the help of Lokk'Naar experts, we have found another one. Better to send ours there before other Lokk'Naar scavengers learn about this location...{NEWLINE}Warning: the place is highly radioactive, ensure that you have decent Plasma resistance!{NEWLINE}Depth: Average"},
		{"STR_LOC_OLD_EARTH_METRO_PSYCHEDELIC_BRIEFING", "Despite the passage of centuries, there are still some unexplored (ie. not looted) underground subways left from the times of Old Earth. And with the help of Lokk'Naar experts, we have found another one. Better to send ours there before other Lokk'Naar scavengers learn about this location...{NEWLINE}Warning: there is a strange, hypnotic aura about this place...{NEWLINE}Depth: Average"},
		{"STR_MISSION_SET_THE_WORLD_ON_FIRE", "*Set The World On Fire*"},
		{"STR_MISSION_SET_THE_WORLD_ON_FIRE_UFOPEDIA", "The echoes of your deeds are reaching me, disciple of Destruction. The drums of Shadowfall are beating louder. I will use that power to set cities ablaze. Baptise yourself in that fire to become stronger.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}(Listening to this voice wasn't good for your sanity, but you feel so good! Your crew is murmuring: -1000 Infamy)"},
		{"STR_SDD", "SINISTER DEVICE OF DOOM"},
		{"STR_GONE", "Gone"},
		{"STR_PIRATE_TANK_TURRET", "Battle Tank"},
		{"AUX_PIR_TANK_TURRET_WEAPON", "Battle Tank Gauss Cannon"},
		{"STR_TIGER_TANK_TURRET", "Battle Tank"},
		{"TIGER_TURRET_ARMOR", "Humanist Battle Tank Examination"},
		{"STR_TIGER_CORPSE", "Battle Tank Parts"},
		{"AUX_BIG_TANK_TURRET_WEAPON", "Battle Tank Cannon"},
		{"STR_TRUCK_TURRET", "Armored Truck Turret"},
		{"TRUCK_TURRET_ARMOR", "Armored Truck Turret"},
		{"STR_BUNKER_TURRET", "14mm Bunker Turret"},
		{"BUNKER_TURRET_ARMOR", "14mm Bunker Turret"},
		{"STR_14MM_LIGHT_TURRET", "14mm Light Turret"},
		{"TRUCK_TURRET_14MM_ARMOR", "14mm Light Turret"},
		{"STR_TRUCK_TURRET_CORPSE", "Damaged Turret Bill"},
		{"STR_BLACK_PYRAMID_TURRET", "Black Pyramid"},
		{"PYRAMID_ARMOR", "Black Pyramid Examination"},
		{"AUX_PYRAMID_EYE", "Eye of the Pyramid"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_PROBE", "Imperial Probe"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_PROBE_DISTRESS", "Comm Wave"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_BANDIT_WARTRUCK", "Bandit Wartruck"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_BANDIT_CAR", "Bandit Car"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_RUFF_RAIDERS", "Armored Patrol"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_MILCONVOY", "Highway Convoy"},
		{"STR_MISSION_MILCONVOY", "Highway Convoy"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_ROGUE_COURIER", "Rogue Courier"},
		{"STR_MISSION_ROGUE_COURIER", "Rogue Courier Run"},
