		{"AUX_PURR_PURR_UFOPEDIA", "Cats can soothe the Gals, raising their Morale."},
		{"AUX_DOGE_BARK_UFOPEDIA", "Dogs can bark at enemies, distracting them and reducing their Time Units, as well, to a smaller extent, Morale. Max Range of this attack is 3."},
		{"AUX_KILLBOT_LASER_UFOPEDIA", "A very powerful laser beam, which shoots through Destroid's eye. Each shot consumes 325 Energy."},
		{"AUX_SLIME_TENTACLES_UFOPEDIA", "A Slimegal can reshape her body to form tentacles. They're a very effective stun weapon with several secondary effects: armor penatration, damage to armor, TUs, Freshness and Morale. The Lash attack has a range of 3, while the Envelop attack is stronger and deals more severe secondary effects."},
		{"AUX_ELECTRIC_GLOVE_UFOPEDIA", "Great for a truly memorable handshake. But be careful with friendly pranks, because despite being primarly a stun weapon, this glove deals quite a lot of lethal damage. Used by the Theban Aqua Suit, due to its limited capacity to carry anything that isn't built-in."},
		{"AUX_WARP_CLAWS_UFOPEDIA", "Warp Claws are used by Chorts to rip apart and dissolve enemy armor at a frightening rate. Using these claws, however, is quite exhausting."},
		{"AUX_IRON_WIND_UFOPEDIA", "Iron Wind is a special power of a Chort. She uses parts of her dispersed metal body as a cloud of highly accelerated projectiles that grind everything in their path. This power also incorporates Warp Claws."},
		{"AUX_ENTROPY_BLAST_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The VooDoo attack employed by Golden Saints. It tries to overwhelm the target's mind, and, if successful, channels raw chaos energy through it, resulting in a reality-tearing explosion. I believe we might be able to use this magic ourselves, if we understand the nature of Golden Saints' powers. Using this power costs 50 Energy and 3 Freshness."},
		{"AUX_GOLDEN_SAINT_WEAPON_UFOPEDIA", "Another of Golden Saints' powers, this one is a direct energy attack with a moderate area of effect. Damage and accuracy drop above range of 12. It ignores 90% of armor. Using it costs 2 Freshness."},
		{"DOGE_ARMOR_UFOPEDIA", "A dog is more of a hunter than a beast of burden; Reserved Wt: 25. Energy Recovery 200%. NV: 12. DV: 30. SPOT: 4. CAMO: 8/0."},
		{"BLOODOGE_ARMOR_UFOPEDIA", "A Blood Hound is an extremely sturdy animal, able to carry cargo if needed (but not as much as a human); Reserved Wt: 30. Energy Recovery 120%. NV: 16. ThV: 50%. SPOT: 4."},
