		{"STR_VIP_022", "Admiral Helmut 'Fisheye' Adamos"},
		{"STR_VIP_030", "The Golden Lady"},
		{"STR_VIP_041", "The Red Queen"},
		{"STR_VIP_001_UFOPEDIA", "The mysterious hero and champion of the Narlocks. She supposedly established Jillsville to gather all the remaining free people in the world. It happened decades ago, yet the legend has it that she's not a normal person, but a revenant, unjustly murdered and risen from her grave to be the defender of all who are treaded upon. Others say she doesn't exist at all, and her persona is assumed by various champions of justice in the form of a symbol. This could explain how she survived all her battles, many of which were lost. She is the arch-enemy of Jack, leader of the Lokk'Naars."},
		{"STR_VIP_002_UFOPEDIA", "The teenage Crown Princess of the Kingdom of Canada, aka 'Prinzesin'. Her ethereal beauty made her quite a celebrity in the media, but in reality, not that much is known of her, as she remains secluded in her castle, possibly due to mental ilness. Some blame the inbreeding within the Blackmarch-originating Canadian dynasty, others speak of dark magics involved and attribute her with demonic powers, such as multilocation."},
		{"STR_VIP_003_UFOPEDIA", "A celebrity Inquisitor for the Church of Sirius, famous for his radical methods and rose-tinted sunglasses. A good-natured man with a great sense of humour. His skill and passion for hunting heretics are the stuff of legend. His utter disregard for their social status made him many enemies, foremost the Academy, but, in his own words, 'I killed a good man once, and I will regret this mistake forever. They're a very rare breed.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_004_UFOPEDIA", "Not much is known about this mysterious 'Knight of Love' aka 'Kokoro', other than she's a lesbian fighter of impressive skill who rescues maidens in peril and often misplaces her armor (but never her sword). Does she have an unlimited supply of it? Her powers must be considerable since she's still alive. Yet somehow you were too overwhelmed with her... personality to ask her."},
		{"STR_VIP_005_UFOPEDIA", "A world-famous author of detective stories, globetrotter and investigator. Known for unparalelled analytical intelligence, which make her books fascinating logical mazes to navigate (or supremely boring, depending on whom you ask). She never actually smokes her trademark pipe. Conspiracy lovers say that she only parades as a detective, while secretly being a criminal mastermind, a plagiarist, or even a gnome. That she is so old, that the meridians are named after her. But everyone knows that gnomes don't exist!"},
		{"STR_VIP_006_UFOPEDIA", "A living legend of the Death Games, a champion for decades before she was welcomed into the Council of Violence, the highest committee of the Games. Vicious and augmented, not even dismemberment can stop her. Infamous for her violent rage, which she can only keep in check by smoking tons of Sectoweed. Blacksmith by trade, lives in the mountains. Capricious and stubborn. Prone to brutalize anyone who'd suggest to innovate the Games. Nobody knows her real age."},
		{"STR_VIP_007_UFOPEDIA", "Your friendly neighbourhood Uber heroine from Doom Harbor underground. Her main passions in life include helping out neighbours and burning things with her high-powered, nuclear flamethrower. She tried to combine these two passions by shooting a series of video tutorials about handling a flamethrower in a safe manner, or, as they're better known, the 'crazy gal burning everything down and setting herself on fire' Net classics."},
		{"STR_VIP_008_UFOPEDIA", "A mythical ancient Ghoul Scientist, also known as the Tallyman of the Apocalypse. To cite her own words:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'No death is in vain,{NEWLINE}if it makes the formula more plain.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_009_UFOPEDIA", "A former Blackmarch military officer, who got discharged due to her overt obsession with strict rules and pedantic order (which is like being expelled from Hell for sinning too much). Now she commands a mercenary band, operating in the Lybian region and fighting Theban Hive 'communists'. Her obnoxious demeanour provokes some of her underlings to challenge her, which is exactly what she wants. These Schweinhunds need to be disciplined HAAART, every day, until zey like it!"},
		{"STR_VIP_010_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}A renegade virtual idol, made in the Technocracy during the crazy 2300s. When her popularity waned, she reinvented herself as a construction worker, building towns, airfields, and even hellerium craft. She had been in this business for so long, we're very likely to see her unique handiwork on many ships we plunder. She disappeared over a century ago, but is rumored to have been recently seen on one of the Central Province's rice farms. After her experiences with the Technocracy, she now helps any oppressed peoples to fight tyranny (by destroying and creating in equal measure).{ALT}"},
		{"STR_VIP_013_UFOPEDIA", "Dark Temptress, a member of the Coven of the Arch-Witches. Wielder of the strongest sorcerous element, Death.{NEWLINE}She is rumored to live deep in the forests of Blackmarch.{NEWLINE}As the first amongst equals, she leads the unruly Coven in the secret fight to protect human magic-users from being used and suppressed by alien creatures. A passionate being, she loves to play with the mortals, and is infamous for her irresistible, dark allure."},
		{"STR_VIP_014_UFOPEDIA", "Golden Rose, a member of the Coven of the Arch-Witches. Everything on Earth draws its power from the Invincible Sun, and thus her sorcerous element has the power over Nature, from rocks, through weather, to living things.{NEWLINE}She is rumored to live in the Theban desert.{NEWLINE}Her chosen role in the Coven is to support the unity between the disparate Witches, but she rarely bothers being soft-spoken and supportive to mortals as well. In rare cases though, she trains prospective witches (like you), if only to satiate her deep longing for domination and intimacy."},
		{"STR_VIP_015_UFOPEDIA", "She-Devil, a member of the Coven of the Arch-Witches. Wielder of Eternal Ethyr, the most elusive sorcerous element, which is also called wizardry: the power of mind, trickery, illusion, clairvoyance and change.{NEWLINE}She is rumored to live in the forbidden jungles of Dark Dominion.{NEWLINE}Being a sort of an oddball in the Coven, this fickle and mysterious Witch enjoys manipulating the other Witches for the fun of it. Despite being generally unconcerned with mortals, she seems to have taken a special interest in your adventures. But with her, you never know."},
		{"STR_VIP_016_UFOPEDIA", "Flame Dancer, a member of the Coven of the Arch-Witches. Wielder of the Power of Chaotic Chaos, the most destructive and least controllable sorcerous element.{NEWLINE}She is rumored to live somewhere in Doom Harbor.{NEWLINE}Being usually passive, she doesn't think much of her fellow Witches, but values the Coven for the cool quests it tasks her with. This satiates her need for adventure and novelty. She accepts quests from mortals as well, but woe to the fools who manage to get on her bad side."},
		{"STR_VIP_017_UFOPEDIA", "Ice Blade, a member of the Coven of the Arch-Witches. Wielder of the sorcerous element of Life, she can control the lifeforce itself, to heal, strengthen and improve soul, mind and body.{NEWLINE}She is rumored to live in a secret monastery upon a holy mountain in the Himalayas. She believes firmly in Coven's mission to protect humanity, but her passion and arrogance often put her at odds with the other Witches, and her patronizing ways tend to antagonize mortals.{NEWLINE}Knowing this weakness, she usually acts indirectly through her 'Templar Order', seeking out and empowering mortal 'champions', or exceptional individuals, to help her with her mission."},
		{"STR_VIP_018_UFOPEDIA", "Sky Tearer, the Emissary of the Coven of the Arch-Witches. While the Five draws power from basic aspects of reality, this one is The End of Things, Herald of The White Void, The Great Devourer. Her role is to maintain balance in the name of the Coven.{NEWLINE}She is rumored to live in the outer space, perhaps on the Moon."},
		{"STR_VIP_020_UFOPEDIA", "The immortal dictator of the Theban Hive, the Queen-Bee, the Living Goddess. Everyone knows what she's like, so what's there to add? Her charming exterior hides a cold mind which is as ruthless as it is devious, much like that of a snake, a pair of those being one of her symbols. She rules her domain with an army of bioengineered clones and she throws mean people to her crocodiles. Curiously enough, the local peasantry finds her rule a benevolent one..."},
		{"STR_VIP_021_UFOPEDIA", "Twin outlaws who damaged and stole so much of the Guild's property that not only Megapol but also the formidable Marsec are looking for them. Catgirls squeak with delight when they talk about their adventures. We cannot know for sure, but most likely Pumas are specially trained saboteurs carrying out a secret mission on the territory of the Empire."},
		{"STR_VIP_022_UFOPEDIA", "A high ranking officer of Marsec, infamous for The Denebola Massacre, where he ordered his ships to fire upon a mining colony taken hostage by Rimriders, killing all the aliens and miners alike. Recently has been moved to Earth sector, to stem the tide of rising attacks on Guild personnel. Supposedly he considers this assignment as a punishment, which however makes him only more tenacious about fulfilling it. He might take interest in our operation before long."},
		{"STR_VIP_030_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}You can find references to this 'patron of knowledge' in every Academy book, but there is more to it than just a mere symbol. The Golden Lady is a Star Goddess who struck a deal with Osiron in the early days after the conquest of Earth. In exchange for her protection and aid, they agreed to help create the Academy in the image of Star Goddesses. The first Academicians were female mages from an obscure Asian cult of the Golden Lady, taken under Osiron's wing. The Academy ensures the spiritual and political presence of Star Goddesses on Earth. The Star Gods are less than happy about it, but they begrudgingly accept this arrangement.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_VIP_041_UFOPEDIA", "Digging deeper into the UAC Data Reels, we have uncovered a diary of a researcher, signed only as 'Red Queen'. She made many forays through Tannhauser Gates into a realm called 'Void', 'Abyss', 'Nightosphere' or 'Nine Moons'. There, the Red Queen became changed and gained knowledge that baffles our minds. Her notes reveal bits and pieces about her pet project of changing some sort of Old Earth automobile into a Gate-creating device. If we understood even half of this, we might perhaps be able to punch a Gate into this 'Void'. However, to comprehend a Pureblood mad scientist, you need another Pureblood mad scientist, and thus we're stuck."},
		{"STR_EVENT_001", "Beauty and the Beast"},
		{"STR_EVENT_001_UFOPEDIA", "Apparently the Brainer who was 'interrogating' the Beastman, turned him into her personal pet instead. We learned nothing. Drats! But what can we do? Girls will be girls. At least I confiscated some photos. (+100 score, +1 Zine)"},
		{"STR_GRAVBALL_LEAGUE", "Gravball League"},
		{"STR_GRAVBALL_LEAGUE_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Confederation: Red Bulls            Eurasian Autonomy: Gray Wolves{NEWLINE}Iron Tribe: Meteor Kings                  EuroSyndicate: Neon Gladiators{NEWLINE}Blackmarch: White Hawks                      Romanica: Golden Griffons{NEWLINE}Nordfederation: Blue Knights            Central Province: Purple Dragons{NEWLINE}Fuso: Flaming Kitsunes                          Ghostgates: Night Flyers{NEWLINE}Dark Dominion: The Jaguars               Death Realms: The Masticators{NEWLINE}Hidden Expanse: Stout Spears                Rogue Fields: Lucky Lemurs{NEWLINE}Theban Hive: Vengeful Vipers         Kingdom o'Canada: Kanuck Kodiaks{NEWLINE}Cali Republic: Ghost Riders                   Latin Empire: The Centurions{NEWLINE}Technocracy: The Battlecats                       Turan: Gravball Khans{NEWLINE}Pirate Straits: Black Pearls                   Steel Pact: The Charioteers{NEWLINE}Red Revolution: Bakunin's Brothers"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUESTS_ADVICE", "Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUESTS_ADVICE_DESC", "We were contacted by one of the Witches..."},
		{"STR_WITCH_QUESTS_ALL_ADVICE_GIVEN", "All Witch Quest Advice Collected"},
		{"STR_VIP_013_QUEST_ADVICE", "Death Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_VIP_014_QUEST_ADVICE", "Day Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_VIP_015_QUEST_ADVICE", "Night Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_VIP_016_QUEST_ADVICE", "Fire Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_VIP_017_QUEST_ADVICE", "Angel Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_VIP_018_QUEST_ADVICE", "Void Witch Quest Advice"},
		{"STR_VIP_013_QUEST_ADVICE_UFOPEDIA", "'My my, you're coming here to make me to spill secrets I share with my lovely little She-Devil? So bold of you. But do not worry, I think I might share something... She's too cute to not be shared around a bit with my friends!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Brotherhood: She thinks herself to be a true honorable assassin, so she will pit you against a bunch of those, backed by a swarm of half-competent gangsters. Their weapons are weak, but you will be limited to non-powered armor, so avoid being overwhelmed or sniped. They will surely have some explosives as well. Also, be wary for their Attack Quads. In short, find good cover and start the bloody harvest. Be like Death, steady but inevitable.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_014_QUEST_ADVICE_UFOPEDIA", "'Oh there you are, hello! Let me make you some tea while you get rid of this clothing? It's warm in here, and it's a shame to cover such a powerful body... I mean, too much! So, yes, I know, you came here for tactical advice. I know the ways of the Sky-Tearer since she's especially close to me... She's rash and a little bit brutal, and I don't want to see you hurt, so please listen carefully.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Shadow Catacombs: Your major advantage there will be superior night vision and stealth. However, do not get cocky. The enemy weapons will be basic, but strong enough. Also not all enemies will be blind. I'm sure you will meet a few Stormtroopers, and at least one Supersoldier, prepare for him.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_015_QUEST_ADVICE_UFOPEDIA", "'Argh you're bothering me again? Can't find someone else to bother? Ah, it's about the Quests? Fine. Fine. You deserve some help, maybe of the professional kind, but none the less, I have to put up with you. So I will tell you a bit about what my friend, the Dark Temptress, might expect you to do. She doesn't like to mess around, so..{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Monastery of Death: It's pretty straightforward. The enemy will be packing a lot of lasers. Be laserproof. And fireproof. And watch your head, you know the kind of beasties the Church uses to melt your face. You will be allowed to use top-tier armor, so use it, but you need to prepare armor for Peasants, Gnomes or Lokk'Naars.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_016_QUEST_ADVICE_UFOPEDIA", "'Ya want my help with quests? Won't tell ya about mine! It's a sikret! But... Yea, I hafta tell ya about what that idiot Ice Blade has in store for ya, because she's devious and is gonna lead you up that ol' garden path. So lis'n up, I won't be tellin' ya twice!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Nocturne in Red's a trap, obviously, heck. Ya'll end up bare arsed... figurativ'ly, at the edge of a ginormous cavern full of them zombies and goddamned bats. Ya gonna get battered by fire and acid from the getgo. Ya gonna hafta think on yer feet, girl, to survive, and bigger prize is if you win fast. Then there is the boss, and he ain't some pansy, so dun poke him just break out yer big stuff rigt away.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_017_QUEST_ADVICE_UFOPEDIA", "'You need advice on the quests, Hero? Well.. Telling you is against the rules, but I won't let that... base, brutish, dishonorable redhead bandit to have her way with you!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Ragnarock: Her place is disgusting and a total mess. You will find heaps of junk in there, but keep your eyes sharp, you might stumble upon some good weapons hidden around. No, she won't mind you taking her filthy stuff, she has more of it where it came from... wherever it is... Anyway! Her house itself is like a castle, so use it like one! The bandits outside will be weak, but numerous and carrying dishonorable weapons. Don't dignify them with open combat.'"},
		{"STR_VIP_018_QUEST_ADVICE_UFOPEDIA", "'AHHH... a wild seeker of WisDom appears. I WiLL tell you about the Quest of the Day Witch becauSe she's my... my... nevermind, al-right?! Don't look at my face!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Love and Beauty: FIRE AND LIGHTNING! THE FURY OF THE SUN WILL BE LEVELLED UPON YOU! BuT... There IS a SseCrET. MATCH and ExCEEd their sCorNed FeMALe fury. FEAR might be your greatest wEaPon. Bring DOWN all their CyBerDisCS, and they WILL be ready to BREAK.'"},
		{"STR_ADVICE_ON_ANG_004", "Advice On The Trial Of Brains"},
		{"STR_ADVICE_ON_ANG_004_UFOPEDIA", "Seeking to figure out how to solve this puzzle, we tried to contact the Fire Witch whom we have helped in the past. She revealed that she, too, was investigating the case, and mocked our customer for withholding vital information from us. It turns out that half of the solution is waiting for a 'Zombie Guardian' to come out of the portal and capturing such an individual, who is sentient enough to be interrogated. The other half is blowing up a portal before it disappears and analyzing its remains. The Fire Witch had already done both, many times, but she couldn't figure out the portal by herself, so {ALT}she passed the remains to us.{ALT} She was however unwilling to share any Zombie Guardians, claiming that she is still researching them."},
