		{"STR_ARMOR_DOCTOR_X_SORCERESS_UFOPEDIA", "????Comes with a mysterious umbrella. Inv: 6. Eva: REA*40% + MEL*10%. NV:20. ThV: 30%. SPOT: 7. SENSE: 7. 1 HP and FRS regen/turn."},
		{"STR_DOCTOR_X_A70_UFOPEDIA", "This unassuming accessory is what Lady Gudrun is using instead of a pretentious wizard's staff. It has the advantage of being stealthy, while it can launch three types of spells: Hologal, Dazzler and Brainmelt Missile. The umbrella itself isn't harmless either. Through her influence over probabilities, Lady Gudrun can stab with it, causing nontrivial damage (including to TUs) that ignores half of enemy's armor. This melee attack costs 1 Freshness."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_MENTAL_RAY_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The most deadly spell in Lady Gudrun's umbrella, it launches a bolt of mental energy which can literally melt brains. Even if the victim survives, they will take a lot of TU, Freshness and Stun damage. And now the best part: the bolt can follow up to 7 waypoints on its way to the target, making it extremely difficult to hide from it.{NEWLINE}Ignores 90% armor. Cost: 5 Freshness."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_HOLOGAL_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This spell summons a half-naked chick as a bait. It is, sadly, just an illusion, but one so detailed (thanks to Lady Gudrun's vivid imagination) that enemies will be distracted by it. Range is unlimited, but the accuracy is poor over long distances, and there are limits as to where the illusion can be summoned.{NEWLINE}Cost: 3 Freshness."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_DAZZLER_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The most basic spell which Lady Gudrun can conjure from her umbrella. It is a mental projectile which stuns and disorients the target (Major TU and Stun damage, minor Freshness damage). This spell can be used for opportunity fire during the enemy turn.{NEWLINE}Ignores 90% armor. Cost: 1 Freshness."},
