		{"STR_TEC_041", "Shadowtech Haters Alarmed"},
		{"STR_TEC_042", "Red Eyed Menace"},
		{"STR_TEC_043_PREQ", "Storm Is Coming"},
		{"STR_TEC_043", "Storm Is Close"},
		{"STR_TEC_044", "Technocracy Datapad #1"},
		{"STR_TEC_045", "Operation Snowstorm"},
		{"STR_TEC_046", "Recalibrate Shadowtech"},
		{"STR_TEC_047", "Fun Was Had"},
		{"STR_TEC_051", "Disruptive Transmissions Triggered"},
		{"STR_TEC_052", "!Technocracy Contact!"},
		{"STR_TEC_053", "Doctored Customs Ledger"},
		{"STR_TEC_100", "Aurora's Plot"},
		{"STR_TEC_101", "!Kidnap Aurora!"},
		{"STR_TEC_102", "Aurora Fiasco"},
		{"STR_TEC_103", "Aurora's Trump Card"},
		{"STR_TEC_001_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This arcane device emits waves that disrupt the workings of Shadowtech. These waves can be amplified by any strong antenna, and seem to work even if they're very weak. I theorize that it creates some sort of resonance within the Shadowtech, that slowly builds up and leads to disruption when the damage control kicks in and excess energy is released. It would be possible to adjust our devices to avoid this problem, but to that end, we'd need to know more about how exactly the Disruptor works, and this will require information which is only possessed by those who have employed it."},
		{"STR_TEC_002_UFOPEDIA", "It is unknown who is disrupting the Shadowtech, but, given our reliance on it, these mysterious haters are a problem, if not an outright enemy. Our only lead is to assume they have the same source of Shadowtech as ourselves. We need to investigate the criminal underground, and find as much about the origins of Shadowtech as possible. It will be hard due to how the Factions hunt down the Shadowtech as heretical, but someone has to know something."},
		{"STR_TEC_003_UFOPEDIA", "We were already aware that the Technocracy sells Optronics to the Smugglers, in direct defiance of the Star Gods. We have vigorously prodded our Smuggler contacts for answers (-100 score). Rumors have it, they're indeed trading in Shadowtech. Shadowtech itself, it is said, originates from space. If they trade it to Technocracy, they would be doing it in one of the Technocracy's starports. There they can hide amongst the heavy traffic, and there the Technocracy can obscure the dealings - its special status of Optronics producers ties up the hands of Guild-associated watchmen. To investigate it further, we need to somehow get access to Pureblood cities, as well as find names of those involved, to capture and interrogate them."},
		{"STR_TEC_004_UFOPEDIA", "With the ledger secured from the Megapol detective, we were able to identify corrupt Technocracy officials who deal with the Smugglers. So a bold plan codenamed 'Terminal Terror' was devised. We shall capture one of these officials, right off said starport and escape in a Transstellar shuttle. Infiltrating a terminal won't be easy; we will be only able to use Stealth items. Finding the right opportunity to snatch the guy might take some time, so we need to conjure our patience, Cap'n."},
		{"STR_TEC_005_UFOPEDIA", "The corrupted Technocracy official revealed that Smugglers conduct their operations in vast undercity sewers. Armed with hints and passwords, our agents can start hitting shady bars to find out proverbial (or literal) trapdoors into city's underground. Even if raiding Smuggler Lairs won't yield us information, it will surely be materially rewarding. (+2000 Score)"},
		{"STR_TEC_006_UFOPEDIA", "This manifesto details the wares moved by the Smugglers out of Technocracy. Not only Optronics, but also UAC technology, restricted guns and explosives, medicines and drugs, the list is quite impressive. Disappointingly, there is no mention of Shadowtech, but the list doesn't add up - it is unclear how the Smugglers were meant to pay for all these goods. However, the log does mention secret frequencies used by major Smuggler hideouts. If there is a definitive answer somewhere, it must be in one of these forts!"},
		{"STR_TEC_007_UFOPEDIA", "With the unwilling help of a certain Smuggler Negotiator, we have uncovered the secret pipeline that supplies Shadowtech to Technocracy via Smugglers. Our further investigations can take two directions. On one hand, we learned about Technocracy installations which conduct experiments on the Shadowtech. On the other hand, the Shadowtech gets into the hands of the Smugglers mostly from the mysterious Belters, who seem to have more connections to Shadowmasters. But pursuing Belters necessitates moving out far into the depths of cold space, where they live.{NEWLINE}(To Be Continued)"},
		{"STR_TEC_036_UFOPEDIA", "You've been getting weird videocalls from some seriously troubled girl, who somehow can get access to Govt networks and is able to cover up her tracks really well. You're not sure which is more disturbing, that, or the image of her cosplaying as a pirate which she sent you. What is even her angle? Have you just acquired a stalker?"},
		{"STR_TEC_042_UFOPEDIA", "It seems that the red-eyed brat hijacked our bases' electronic grid, just like that, only to deliver a message warning us about some sort of bad consequences for tampering with 'her' Shadowtech Disruptors. I ordered all internal systems to be physically disconnected from any signal receivers. But I feel that the damage was done already, and I sense trouble ahead... There's no telling what can happen if she can somehow detect our Shadowtech."},
		{"STR_TEC_044_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This datapad is protected by some advanced data encryption. We can't access its contents without the proper technology. We might need to research this item several times to get all the information it contains."},
		{"STR_TEC_045_UFOPEDIA", "We have decrypted this Technocracy datapad. It contains targeting data against our Shadowtech. We can start a project to recalibrate our Shadowtech to stop their missile attacks, but they still will be able to use old targeting data for up to a month after that. The codename for the operation is 'Snowstorm' and the signature reads 'PRISS-000', whatever that means."},
		{"STR_TEC_046_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}With the use of our mystical knowledge, we were able to recalibrate our Shadowtech, which will hopefully compromise the 'Snowstorm' operation soon."},
		{"STR_TEC_052_UFOPEDIA", "Now once we know some ins and outs of operating in Pureblood cities, as well as faction politics, we were able to find a good lead into the mysterious Optronic smuggling scheme. Naturally, any Megapol investigation is imminent danger to such operation, so certain big-wig Megapol officers are involved as well. And these will be much easier to track down for our spies than anonymous Technocracy clerks. Step by step, we will untangle that web, since it seems too important and profitable to ignore."},
		{"STR_TEC_053_UFOPEDIA", "This document gives us the names of Technocracy clerks involved in Optronics smuggling. Now we need to devise plan on how to use that information, but it will be impossible without broadening our knowledge about undercover operations."},
		{"STR_TEC_100_UFOPEDIA", "There can be little doubt - the red-eyed brat who claims to be behind Shadowtech disruptions is none other than Aurora, the elusive Canadian Crown Princess. But, how?! And why?!"},
		{"STR_TEC_101_UFOPEDIA", "These 'games' Aurora is playing with us have to end! Now, that we know her identity, we could simply snip the problem at its bud. Sure there is the issue of her living in the Canadian royal palace, but Canada doesn't seem like an overtly dangerous foe, as far as nation-states go, right?"},
		{"STR_TEC_102_UFOPEDIA", "We have been tricked by Aurora, but in every loss there is lesson to be learned (as long as you're still alive, that is). The Canadian Monarchy, it appears, is run by a robotic impostor - and the only possible culprit, as we have learned from our other endavours, can only be the Technocracy. They apparently also have wide access to Shadowtech. But where is the real Aurora? Whatever is her secret, we can profit greatly from uncovering it... Probably?{NEWLINE}(To Be Continued)"},
		{"STR_TEC_103_UFOPEDIA", "Apparently, Aurora is alive and well. She warned you that she haven't used her trump card yet... whatever that can possibly be. How to end this infernal game?{NEWLINE}(-300 Infamy)"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_FIRST_CONTACT", "Red-Eyed Brat"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_FIRST_CONTACT_DESCRIPTION", "You get a videocall on a govt frequency. When you pick up, you see a hyped girl. 'Big Sis!', she exclaims. 'So good to finally see you! I am your greatest fan! I admire your work, especially all that Shadowtech stuff!' You answer, 'I have no idea what you're talking about.' 'Oh, don't be like that! I love you, so why don't you share your secrets with me?' 'Sorry, kiddo, Mom told me to not trust strangers.'. The brat becomes angry. 'You must feel safe in that bunker of yours, Big Sis, to be so mean to people. But it's not deep enough to make you untouchable.'"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_SECOND_CONTACT", "Red-Eyed Brat, Again"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_SECOND_CONTACT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}'Big Sis, why are you being sooo difficult? I really just want to be your friend! You could tell me sooo much about the Shadow!' You answer, 'You still didn't tell me your name.' She rolls her eyes. 'I would, but I simply can't, Big Sis, you wouldn't understand.' Then she brightens up: 'But I have something better, I took a picture of myself, specially for you! Will you love me now?' You look at it, and hang up."},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_WARNING", "RED EYES TAKE WARNING"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_WARNING_DESCRIPTION", "A sudden burst of static blinds all monitors in your base. Someone speaks through them:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Poor idiot. Did you really think you could tamper with my Shadowtech Disruptors and go unnoticed? That is cute, but I see everything. I think you're a meanie. And meanies must be exterminated~!{NEWLINE}[-350 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_STRANGER", "Mysterious Stranger"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_STRANGER_DESCRIPTION", "Local villagers report several sightings of a stranger, who was asking questions about the whereabouts of our Hideout. He was a big guy, dressed in black leathers, donning shades and speaking in a monotonous voice. Most likely it's just a hoax, but I have a weird feeling... just like when a storm is coming...{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_STRANGE_LIGHTS", "Deadly Lights"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_STRANGE_LIGHTS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}There have been more reports about the mysterious stranger from the last month who had been looking for us. This time, they were often accompanied by sightings of unusual, twin-engine crafts, flying low, appearing and disappearing without a trace. To top it off, after one of such flybys, an old iron mine had been hit by a high-yield hypersonic missile, resulting in a complete cave-in.{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_THAT_WAS_FUN", "I had fun!"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_THAT_WAS_FUN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}But now, you're hiding from me, Big Sister? Silly, you're too big to stay hidden for long! And when I find you, we shall play together again~!{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_FUN_CONTINUES", "Do you love me yet?!"},
		{"STR_AURORAS_GAMES", "Let's play a game!"},
		{"STR_AURORAS_GAMES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Wow, Big Sister, you really are big! I heard that you are claiming yourself to be a Superhuman, like the legendary Jack Sparrow, but I had my doubts~! Now I clearly see you might be a threat to my plans. So let's see how much fun you can take before you break~! My Robots -- assemble!!!"},
		{"STR_AURORAS_GAMES_2", "Do you love me yet?!"},
		{"STR_AURORAS_GAMES_2_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Hahahaha! You do, or you don't, I still want to play with you! I'll bring my toys again, Big Sister, but I might be not so gentle next time. And we're going to have so much ~fun~ together. So. Much. Fun. Together."},
		{"STR_NEWS_FROM_CANADA", "Solar Courier"},
		{"STR_NEWS_FROM_CANADA_DESCRIPTION", "We received news about social upheaval in Canada."},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_WHO_IS_YOUR_MASTER", "'Who Is Your Master?'"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_WHO_IS_YOUR_MASTER_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}When Red-Eyes calls you again, she only asks this question in a strangely hesitant tone. 'I have none,' you answer. She narrows her eyes. 'You LIE! Everyone has a master! We're all dancing, like puppets! Just look at me! I dance, and dance, and dance!' She gives it a couple of hypnotic twirls. She is not wearing any panties. 'But you're trying to deceive me, Big Sis, like everyone is. This call... was a mistake.' She becomes genuinely sad. 'I cannot trust you. Not before I have you.' She disconnects."},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_PRINCESS_IS_IN_ANOTHER_CASTLE", "The Princess Is In Another Castle"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_PRINCESS_IS_IN_ANOTHER_CASTLE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Looks like my trap has failed, Big Sis. I hoped to wreck your favorite dolls, but you wrecked many of mine instead. No big deal, I can always get more. But you might think this means you've won. You haven't. I still haven't played my strongest cards. You WILL love me, eventually, whether you like it or not."},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_I_HAVE_DR_X", "Aurora's New Toy"},
		{"STR_TEC_EVENT_I_HAVE_DR_X_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Hey, Big Sis! Guess what my minions have found! It's gorgeous, cuddly, and green-eyed! A beautiful specimen! She's sort of your mommy, right? This makes playing with her almost as good as playing with you! Almost. It will let me pass the time more happily while waiting for you to start loving me. I will have a special surprise for you!"},
