		{"STR_WIZ_001_UFOPEDIA", "Hello there, Miss. It didn't escape my attention that you're bringing pain and misery to the people who deserve it the most. Like my, shall we say, pitiful rivals. I so approve of that. Our Society needs more straight people like you; I'm willing to get you into the Wiz Biz if you do some relatively simple magical research for me. After that, learn more about the wizard world - demons, zombies, portals - and I might have further business with you. Good, uhm, winds, skipper!"},
		{"STR_WIZ_003_UFOPEDIA", "Well, well, just look at you, Miss. It appears you've grown in fame enough to be trusted with a difficult mission. You're also knowledgeable enough to not need explanation for basic terms. You see, there is a secret war going on in the Wizard world, a war to get control over Tannhauser Gates, colloquially known as portals to other dimensions. Beside the known Gates, there are others, which can be opened with the help of PADLOCKS OF CHAOS. Yes, we open such doors with padlocks, not keys. I want to hire you to help the good side, that is me, to win this war. Have a little advance payment and wait for my orders.{NEWLINE}(Million Dollar Safe obtained)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_004_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This is the mysterious artifact that is supposed to help the Red Mage to open portals to other worlds and presumably win her 'war'. If that is not foreboding enough, it also emanates weird eerie light. Better store these in some thick containers. At least this one was taken away by the Red Mage."},
		{"STR_WIZ_005_UFOPEDIA", "'You have succeeded in retrieving the Padlock of Chaos. Well done. We can start phase two, which is opening an experimental Gate. I have to research the matter first, but I'll need the help of your Brainers with a necessary, yet quite time-consuming series of measurements. I cannot trust anyone else with this. But meanwhile, my enemies have started to make a move. Take your reward and use it well; there is a hard struggle ahead.'{NEWLINE}(Treasure Chest obtained)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_006_UFOPEDIA", "'What? No, it's not my underwear! I'm just showing you my magical outfit for traveling the Gates. It's so small because special materials required to make it are so hard to come by, that's all! They can only be found in the realms beyond Gates. So take a good look, because these materials are what you'll be searching for. With the calculations you helped me with, I found places on Earth where the Gates appear spontaneously. I'll start monitoring these, so be ready to go on my signal. No, I don't know where they lead, it's up to you to find out. And no, you can't have this outfit, I'll be using it and I did not gather enough resources for more. Gosh, why do you always need so many explanations!'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_007_UFOPEDIA", "'Good job on clearing that portal, despite some, eheheh... issues. Well, considering you could have materialized inside, say, a sea of flames, it ended very well! Some challenge and adversity just makes the life of a genius less boring, doesn't it? And you've found some exciting stuff there! I won't be able to sleep at night now, thinking of all the possibilities! The Zortrium Crystal is one of four elemental resources, required to create the fabled Orichalc. And coincidentally, I am very well versed in the transmutation magic. When I... we have the Orichalc, nothing will stop us!{NEWLINE}You're a very powerful servant, Captain. Have some more gems as a reward. So, how about more forays like this one?'{NEWLINE}(Treasure Chest obtained; +200 Score)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_008_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage has started to appear at the Luxury Spa. Sure, her choice of dress is shocking, but not in direct violation of your rules! And she became more available for further interaction. Your plan is working!"},
		{"STR_WIZ_009_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage emerged from her tower, wearing a completely new outfit and with a strange sparkle in her eyes. Is she turning into a Succubus?{NEWLINE}'Oh, this? It's a Shadowrealms dress I made. Now, with Succubus wings and so on, we can return to the topic of designing some for your crew as well...{NEWLINE}More importantly, my new powers allow me to open new vistas for your bold conquests, Cap'n. By that, I mean Shadowrealms, of course', she adds with a smug expression. 'Just a couple more steps, and Orichalc will be mine...! I mean, ours!'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_010_UFOPEDIA", "'Good job finding Brimstone, my retainer! The quest for Orichalc reached an important milestone. What is Orichalc, you're perhaps curious? Some call it the Fifth Element, a fusion of the four, fire, air, earth and water. The truth is more complex. The Zortrium gives it the material component; Brimstone, energy; the patterns of Chrono Prism - mastery of time and space. The final component, Liquid Glitter, the capacity to process information. What is created from the fusion of it all? I'll leave that as a mystery for now.' The Red Mage winks at you and gives you another Treasure Chest as a reward."},
		{"STR_WIZ_011_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage is very interested in your latest find, the Glitterdust. 'Curious. The fourth and rarest component of Orichalc is the Liquid Glitter. What you've found is merely some residue of that true Glitter, but it has its uses! It easily bonds with souls, which can allow for creation of Shadowrealms equipment...'{NEWLINE}The Red Mage shares her knowledge on the matter (+200 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_020_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Mage asks you to meet her. 'Captain, there is something I was not telling you... And it's important. I guess it's time to reveal it to you...'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_020_UFOPEDIA", "'So I've decided to trust you a litte, my cute Captain. And I couldn't keep my desire to master the Shadow hidden for too long, anyway. You see, it's not just about Orichalc, but also... myself. Your discovery of Phlegeton gave me the final clue how to... descend into the Shadow. But the success is a question of how and where. The place I'm looking for is the Fountain of Youth, located in the Shadowrealm of Death, as it is called. Will you help me out again? We will have to start with a scout portal first, of course...'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_021_UFOPEDIA", "'Care to join me, Captain?... Ah, the Water of Life. Truly exquisite when mixed with plum vodka. Excellent. I knew that jumping headlong into a new dimension full of mortal threats won't be a big deal for you. Now while you were having fun exploring, I did additional research. For my ritual, I'll need to improve myself, and some Living Brimstone from the Shadowrealm of Destruction will be neccesary too. Keep searching for the Fountain of Youth, we're on the right track. Here, your usual fee.'{NEWLINE}(Treasure Chest obtained; +500 Score)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_022_UFOPEDIA", "You have finally discovered the location of the Fountain of Youth, the source of power and life everlasting... at the price of Descending into Shadow. This is what the Red Mage wanted; but if you share this information with her, there will be no going back. Do you trust her enough? Or will it be better to keep this secret to avoid her gaining too much power?{NEWLINE}(+1000 Infamy)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_023_UFOPEDIA", "'Amazing work! Another step of my... I mean our, plan was completed flawlessly! Now on to the next step. Once we're ready, you will have to make a ritual coffin for me. Don't look at me like that, it's wizard stuff, okay? Then, take me to the Fountain of Youth. I will need you to keep my back protected, as the ritual will undoubtedly draw all sorts of local troublemakers like a moth to the flame. Now take this; I kept it just for you with such a special occasion in mind.'{NEWLINE}(Mystery Box obtained)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_024_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Mage told us to not ask any questions, but we somehow cannot shake the feeling she might have something to do with Necromancy. Anyway, once we put her in this casket, she will be... Sleeping, right? Until the time is right to open the Tannhauser Gate towards the Fountain of Youth and perform her ritual of Descent Into Shadow... It will be surely worth the effort, right?"},
		{"STR_WIZ_025_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}'New adventures await us, Captain! With the mastery of Chronomancy added to our arsenal, the world is almost within our grasp! Speaking of which, I've scrounged up some more gems for ammunition.'{NEWLINE}(+250 Infamy, Treasure Chest obtained){ALT}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}(To Be Continued)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_041_UFOPEDIA", "'Still nothing? Damn it, I was sure the Fountain of Life must be there somewhere. Keep looking. In the meantime, I need to come up with some alternative plans... Just in case.'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_042_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage is restless about the lack of your progress. A Succubus Servant gave you an idea: shower the Mage with gifts and distractions to such a degree that she forgets about the whole thing. Red Mage is not easy to please, but, say, if you made her a Zortrium & Gold plated Spa filled with the Water of Life and attended by Succubi? And added some diamonds on top?"},
		{"STR_WIZ_080_UFOPEDIA", "It is obvious that the Red Mage is not telling us everything, and the Black Mask we've found is a clue that her 'war' could be a much bigger thing than it might look at first. And it is dangerous to immerse yourself into a dark plot blindly. Finding out the story behind the Mask might at least allow us to understand the whole game better, and be able to turn back before any major disaster strikes. Hmm, didn't we already hear about masked mages somewhere...?"},
		{"STR_WIZ_081_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The data storage device we've found at the Technomancer's hideout took some time to decrypt. It details the designs for cyborgization of zombies, apparently to create a grand army. How to feed them with Zombie Juice and Vampire Blood to make them strong, fit and smart (but apparently, not too smart); how to ensure their obedience and make them understand orders; how to adapt cybernetics to their physiology to achieve synergy. The most puzzling parts refer to Shadowtech and Chernobog; the latter being some sort of a command and control network. The details on Shadowtech are scarce, but by the study of Necronomicon, they plan to be able to make the Army of Chernobog travel between dimensions and communicate in a manner completely inscrutable to the Star Gods."},
		{"STR_WIZ_101_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Mage has suddenly arrived at our Hideout! She brought an absurd amount of luggage with her, and some dangerous-looking guy."},
		{"STR_WIZ_101_UFOPEDIA", "'What, my dress? I might have worn that Theban-styled topless outfit when we first met, as I heard you consider such stuff elegant. However, a Mage needs to put on her traditional dress for such a major event as changing her residence. Ah, yes, I am moving in. Just me, my servant and my luggage. I've been getting trouble from these Chernobog types as well, and it will be more efficient to join forces. I will provide you with plans and materials to make me a proper dwelling where I could research things like this... Necronomicon, for example. What's with that look? I'll wait in your quarters until it is done, I am very patient.'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_102_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage is still not willing to share her true plan with you. She had barricaded herself in her tower, constantly busy and unavailable. You might have an opening, but to influence her, you must draw her out. However, showering her with more gifts will only show your weakness, undermining your current position. Same goes for trying to pressure her. No; it is her who has to make the next move. You must only find a way to make her want to...{NEWLINE}Suddenly, you are struck by an idea. A Luxury Spa! Surely, if there was one next to her tower, she wouldn't be able to resist its allure, especially with how overworked she is! And you would have, uhm, a plausible deniability! You let out a diabolic laughter. Soon, the Red Mage will reveal all her secrets to you!"},
		{"STR_WIZ_103_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}You discover a new side to the Red Mage. A playful, energetic, expressionate one. One which is wise, gentle, and capable of laughing at her own vices. Could the image of cold ferocity she projects to be just a mask? Or are both sides equally true?{ALT}"},
		{"STR_WIZ_104_UFOPEDIA", "As you keep providing the Red Mage with various stuff she desires, you can feel she's opening up to you. She is a fiercely independent creature, yet, almost imperceptibly, she had come to depend on your help more and more... You can't help but wonder how you can increase that dependence... And what to do with such power. There are many options, some of them benign, some of them dark..."},
		{"STR_WIZ_105_UFOPEDIA", "The Succubus plot worked! The Red Mage loves her new spa so much she's spending several hours per the day there, forgetting about the whole world. Her behavior became more careless and indecent. Her nagging ceased and she's working less, too. (t.b.c.)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_110_UFOPEDIA", "The sight was impressive enough back at the ritual site. But as you walk in on the Red Mage as she is looking her new self up in the mirror, with no clothes on (except for a little heart-shaped patch on her... most private place), the sensation of being in the presence of something out of this earth, beautiful and dangerous, is overwhelming. She turns her glowing eyes to you, apparently not minding the intrusion. You stay like that for a while, before deciding it's better to leave."},
		{"STR_WIZ_111_UFOPEDIA", "Since the Red Mage is a Shadow now, she is sort of immortal, or at least her Shadow is. As long as her corpse is relatively intact, we can revive her by the use of Summoning Circle and Water of Life. We just need to ask the Lady of Bloom nicely to let her go (the question of 'why does that Demon Goddess interfere' is a mystery for another time)."},
		{"STR_WIZ_112_UFOPEDIA", "Red Mage's trust in you might have been misplaced. Despite her power, every time she dies, she's at your mercy to do with her as you please. That very power makes the idea all the more appealing. With the use of Chrono Prisms, you can entrap her during the resurrection process in a pocket dimension, and use her power towards your own ends."},
		{"STR_WIZ_113_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}The Red Mage is in your power and she can never escape her prison! Probably. The new pocket dimension provides lots of space (effectively obtained 5 T-D Lockers), while Mage's fiery powers are yours to command (effectively obtained a Shadow Orb of Blood).{NEWLINE}(+666 Infamy){ALT}"},
		{"STR_WIZ_126_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage wants to buy X-Slave from us. She's offering $1M Safe in exchange. To complete the transaction, research X after transferring her (via Workshop project, requires Red Tower)."},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_126_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Mage summons you to her Tower.{NEWLINE}'I have noticed you have a very interesting person in your... bondage. I want her. She will be useful to me, and you'll get the money. What say you?'"},
		{"STR_WIZ_127_UFOPEDIA", "The next time you see the Red Mage, she has Gudrun all dressed up in a maid-like outfit... While not wearing much in the way of clothing herself. They seem to be enjoying each other's company, but there's a dimension to it, or several hidden dimensions, which you can't hope to understand. 'She wants to thank you for this useful assistant,' Gudrun says. 'Now, please leave us.'{NEWLINE}(+100 Infamy)"},
		{"STR_WIZ_128_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Suspiciously nicely packed for 'some useless stuff'..."},
		{"STR_WIZ_128_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You get a visit from Gudrun. You can hardly recognize her. 'Listen up, worm. The Red Mage decided to give you some useless stuff she no longer needs. Better be thankful.' With these words, she hands you a package and gracefully leaves. You can almost see a faint smile and blush on her face, but you might be imagining things."},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_CONTACT", "The Red Oni"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_CONTACT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}You are getting a videocall from a demon,{NEWLINE}or so it seems."},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_IMPATIENT", "Red Mage Is Getting Impatient"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_IMPATIENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}She does not appreciate living in substandard conditions.{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_DISAPPROVES_KNIGHT", "Red Mage Disapproves"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_DISAPPROVES_KNIGHT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Nothing good will ever come out of those Gudrun's fantasies of reviving the golden age of chivalry. You'd better get rid of her before this make-believe goes too far.'{NEWLINE}[-25 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_APPROVES_VAMPIRE", "Red Mage Approves"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_APPROVES_VAMPIRE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Mage finds our Vampiress cute. And the latter becomes surprisingly passive and nice in her presence... You feel inspired to write something about the strange vagaries of human personality.{NEWLINE}[+25 Infamy, +1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_009_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Thanks to the Void resources you have provided her with, the Red Mage has improved her control over Time and Space."},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_WHERE_FOUNTAIN", "Where's My Fountain?!"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_WHERE_FOUNTAIN_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Red Mage is really pissed about your lack of progress in the search for the Fountain of Youth. You've managed to lie your way out of this, but she might be starting to suspect something... Your crew feels like stormclouds have gathered over the Hideout.{NEWLINE}[-350 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_ENSLAVED", "Mutual Humiliation"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_ENSLAVED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You have visited the Red Mage in her prison dimension to have some proverbial 'fun'. The results were mixed. You returned with your ego hurting, but also with some good pictures.{NEWLINE}[-30 Infamy, +1 Zine]"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_FLOWERS", "Flowers"},
		{"STR_WIZ_EVENT_FLOWERS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Red Mage brought you some pretty flowers today. She seemed very tense and told you to be grateful. Overall, it was kind of hot.{NEWLINE}[+30 Infamy, +1 Glamour]"},
