		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_THANATOS_SHORT", "Rest Eternal"},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_ARES_SHORT", "Explosion"},
		{"STR_ARMOR_RED_MAGE_GORGON_UFOPEDIA", "Red Mage's hereditary combat outfit, currently enhanced with Brimstone and Zortrium. It benefits from 2 layers of Shields, internal (Red, 80/20) and external (Purple, 90/30). Flying. NV 16, ThV 100% (Fire Mage ability), SENSE: 3 (Passion Mage ability). Comes with Gorgo Shield."},
		{"STR_ARMOR_RED_MAGE_EXO_UFOPEDIA", "To enter dangerous environments, Red Mage wears a skintight suit under her Gorgo armor, providing immunity to Choking and increased resistances to Chem and Cold. Thin as it is, it still interferes with her mobility and Evasion."},
		{"STR_ARMOR_RED_MAGE_SPACE_UFOPEDIA", "Not the perfect space suit due to Cold Resistance being not total, yet the Red Mage can use it quite well in 0-g environment. NV improves to 20 and encumbrance is reduced by 15."},
		{"STR_ARMOR_RED_MAGE_DRESS_UFOPEDIA", "Need an undercover assassin? The Red Mage can do that too. CAMO: 1/12. No Gorgo Shield, nor shielding of any kind whatsoever, but she still can use her innate powers and Mage's Dagger. Glamorous."},
		{"STR_ARMOR_RED_MAGE_BIKINI_SEA_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage is taking the undersea environment at a leisure, wearing her bikini and a Golden Mask. If her Gorgo Shield is insufficient protection, she regards a mission as being too risky anyway. Visibility: 20. ThV 100%, SENSE 3. SHIELDS: 90/30 (Purple). Glamorous."},
		{"STR_ARMOR_RED_MAGE_DREAMWORLD_UFOPEDIA", "The fabric of the Shadowrealms is more susceptible to one's will, and after the Red Mage descended into the Shadow, it allows her to manifest her true charming nature. NV 16, ThV 100%, SENSE: 5, +1 HP regen/turn. The Gorgo Shield cannot, however, be taken there."},
		{"AUX_GORGON_SHIELD_UFOPEDIA", "The Red Mage never goes to combat without it, if she can help it. The Shield has belonged to her family for generations, and, if powered, it can unleash sorcerous abilities of the Wind (allowing her to fly and her increasing movement), Death (see Hand of Thanatos) and Explosion (see Fist of Ares). It also adds an extra layer of energy shields (Purple, 90/30)."},
		{"STR_RED_MAGE_ASC_30_UFOPEDIA", "This nicely crafted gauntlet is not actually the source of Red Mage's abilities, it is a fitting for energy crystals that power them. When asked about the origins of the gauntlet, the Red Mage just said, 'It's a gift, a friend found it on a corpse', while smiling mysteriously. Further inquiry seemed too dangerous to pursue."},
		{"AUX_REDMAGE_DAGGER_UFOPEDIA", "A handy dagger, any self-respecting mage has one of those to backstab people when least expected, and to perform some or other forbidden rites. This one is adequately elegant and sharp for a valued personal weapon of the Red Mage."},
		{"AUX_REDMAGE_HEART_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Red Mage's most personal possession. Due to the intimate status of the item, we do not know much about its origins or true nature, but we know its effects in combat: it regenerates 3 Energy, 3 Morale, 2 Stun and 1 HP per turn. However, this is only true if the Red Mage herself is wearing it. For the other people, it seems, it's just a stunningly lavish gem that could probably fetch many millions on the Black Market..."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_HADES_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Allows the Red Mage to use one of her innate powers, The Discipline Of Fire. A long range burst of flames, which can cover a large area with its 6 shots. Causes a bit more damage than normal fire and can even instantly vaporize weak obstacles."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_EREBUS_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Allows the Red Mage to use one of her innate powers, The Discipline Of Steam. For all intents and purposes it creates a dense cloud of smoke (through which the Red Mage can see perfectly), but causes Fire type damage, very destructive to armor and morale. It also causes Stun and instant loss of Time Units."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_ATHENA_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Allows the Red Mage to use one of her innate powers, The Discipline Of Passion. This ability can be deployed both to stop enemies (it instantly drains a huge amount of TUs and causes some Stun) as well as to buff allies (it restores Morale, Energy and can even close Fatal Wounds, if you're lucky). The Charm damage type makes it tricky to use, though.{NEWLINE}The Red Mage can React with this ability."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_THANATOS_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Allows the Red Mage to use her Gorgo Shield to unleash one of its powers, The Discipline Of Death. These beams, designed to deal with supernatural creatures, are extremely effective against living targets. They drain their victims' bodies energy (Stun damage, Energy damage, Freshness damage, TU damage, the whole deal), allowing to put them to deep sleep (potentially lethal) or at least to stop them in their tracks. They also ignore 85% of armor.{NEWLINE}The Red Mage can React with this ability."},
		{"STR_WIZ_SPELL_ARES_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Allows the Red Mage to use her Gorgo Shield to unleash one of its powers, The Discipline Of Explosion. As the name implies, the ability is brutally simple in its application. It has a quite long effective range, and causes more armor damage and Stun than your average explosion."},
		{"STR_ANG_001", "Shadow Lamp"},
		{"STR_ANG_002", "!Demonic Sacrifices!"},
		{"STR_ANG_003_PREQ", "Mystery Patron (Preq)"},
		{"STR_ANG_003", "Mystery Patron"},
		{"STR_ANG_004", "*Bountyhunts for Mystery Patron*"},
		{"STR_ANG_007", "Pyramid Portal Remains"},
		{"STR_ANG_010", "Dream of Black Towers"},
		{"STR_ANG_011", "Demonic Transfiguration"},
		{"STR_ANG_012", "Infernal Connections"},
		{"STR_ANG_101", "Martyrdom"},
		{"STR_ANG_102", "Repentance"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REPENTIA", "Masochist"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_WEIRDGAL", "Weirdseeker"},
		{"STR_BIOFIELD_COLLAPSE", "Bio-Forcefield Collapse"},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BIOFIELD_COLLAPSE", "Blitzgal"},
		{"STR_ANG_103", "Sivalinga Rewards"},
		{"STR_ANG_104", "Sivalinga Creation"},
		{"STR_ANG_EVENT_CONTACT", "Weird Dream"},
		{"STR_ANG_EVENT_SIVALINGAS", "Sivalinga Rewards"},
		{"STR_ANG_001_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This strange device was seen to cause weird darkness, when operated by the Bogeymen. Despite studying it for some time, however, we were unable to find out how to activate it. As for its inner workings... Its shell withstood all our tools without as much as a scratch."},
		{"STR_ANG_002_UFOPEDIA", "It can be now said as a fact: demons are running rampant across our lands. There are rumors about dark masses and mass sacrifices. After some rounds of thinking, we figured out that the Shadow Lamps seem the easiest to follow, and if we listen in to global communications, we can figure out where they were likely used. This will give us a shot at exploring the issue."},
		{"STR_ANG_EVENT_CONTACT_DESCRIPTION", "You see a strange, blurred apparition... You feel her staring at you, and you realize you're completely naked- Bloody Hell?!{NEWLINE}'Kind Sister...' She speaks otherworldly. 'I've seen you saving my trusted Templar devotee, and other people, from deathly peril. I commend you for these good deeds. The world is full of unnatural evil: the vile Demons, the insane Cultists of Apocalypse, the abhorrent Zombies. People need a champion... I need a champion, and I beg of you to become one. I have nothing to offer but my teachings. Will you accept?'"},
		{"STR_ANG_EVENT_SIVALINGAS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Mystery Patron contacts you with her thanks for cracking the issue of Zombie Portals. She sends you 3 Sivalinga Stones as a reward.{NEWLINE}+250 Infamy"},
		{"STR_ANG_003_UFOPEDIA", "Your dreams have been brutally invaded by a strange woman, the 'Mystery Patron'. She said some things about fighting evil for her in exchange for some 'teachings'. Now, should you write it off as a mere dream, or give in to madness and ask about her at the Bounty Hunters' Guild?"},
		{"STR_ANG_004_UFOPEDIA", "You've decided to take up the cooperation with this 'Mystery Patron'. It seems to be the only way to figure out who she is and what her real motives are, anyway. And maybe her 'teachings' might be worth a dime.{NEWLINE}Sure enough there was an application waiting at Bounty Hunt network, so she's recognized as an official Bounty Hunt customer. She does not offer any Tokens, but writes that you need to pass 'three difficult tests' of 'brains, brawl and savvy' before most of her teachings 'even start to make sense'. Figures, work comes first, and the pay... well you will make sure it is extracted, one way or another."},
		{"STR_ANG_007_UFOPEDIA", "The explosion was so powerful that there is not much to be divined out of the charred debris, mostly chucks of very dense slate, of which the whole pyramid was built. Of note, we've only found pieces of metal, covered with some mysterious runes. What is the meaning of these runes, however, and can they hold the secret to how the pyramid and the portal were created - and where?"},
		{"STR_ANG_010_UFOPEDIA", "Dreaming with Zombies, you dreamed of the runes we've found on a destroyed portal, and this let you find a dream about an ominous place in a strange world. You've seen enough to divine that Zombie invasions originate from there. The 'Mystery Patron' was pleased; she said this specific knowledge will allow her to block these assaults, somehow, at least temporarily. She was apologetic for what you have gone through; when pressed, she solemnly promised more answers 'in due time'.{NEWLINE}(+500 score)"},
		{"STR_ANG_011_UFOPEDIA", "We were finally able to understand and accept the mad passages of the Grimoire of Transfiguration and thus we have learned the horrible origin of demons and dark ones. It seems the Cult of Apocalypse is taking its victims to Hell (quite literally) and there it uses the 'Anvil of Souls' to turn them into demons. The Mystery Patron alludes that she might want us to go to Hell ourselves to stop the Cult.{NEWLINE}(+500 score)"},
		{"STR_ANG_012_UFOPEDIA", "With the knowledge of the otherdimensional, we were finally able to piece together how the demons work. Spiderdemon's huge brain must be an antenna, through which it draws energy (and, possibly, orders) from some other dimension. Namely, from Hell itself. This must be the same process the other demons are using, and the Demonic Essence must be a catalyst. This implies the demons and their works can appear anywhere, at any time.{NEWLINE}(+500 score)"},
		{"STR_ANG_101_UFOPEDIA", "Our Hellerium metabolism is both a source of power and a weakness that can be exploited. When overcharged, it makes us burn up like dry grass. Yet the flame which burns the shortest, also burns the brightest. If we can control this process, it can give us almost supernatural abilities - at the price of agony. Thus, at the edge of death, we'll be able to inflict even greater pain on those with similar weakness, as well as on the denizens of the Shadowrealms. Only Repentia Gals, however, can withstand such self-denial."},
		{"STR_ANG_102_UFOPEDIA", "Ambition is dangerous, and flying too close to the sun has burnt many. The spiritual authority to deal due punishment to those who have sinned now rests on your shoulders, Cap'n. The quest of Repentance does end only in death, but it might heal a flawed soul.{NEWLINE}Repentance removes any Rank the Gal had and reduces her pay to $500. Removes all Augmentations.{NEWLINE}Repentance will destroy worn armor;{NEWLINE}>Disallows use of sneaky outfits.{NEWLINE}>Set V.PWR at 44, if was lower;{NEWLINE}>Set V.SKL cap at 20;{NEWLINE}>Raise Bravery by 20, but not past 100;{NEWLINE}Raise HP by 10 and HP cap to 110;{NEWLINE}>Reduce ACC, THR and REA caps to 100, 80, 90."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_REPENTIA_UFOPEDIA", "Only in death can Repentance end. Before that, masochism is all the fun you need.{NEWLINE}All Repentias receive this bonus on top of any normal stats; as their VooDoo powers are diminished, their biofield grows in power. However, paradoxically, they can wear some Weirdgal-only armors.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+2 Armor{NEWLINE}+33 Freshness;{NEWLINE}+10 HP and BRA;{NEWLINE}+1 Stun regen per turn;{NEWLINE}Decreased TU drain on low Freshness (9);{NEWLINE}Extra Morale Recovery at low HP (up to +8)."},
		{"STR_MEDAL_BIOFIELD_COLLAPSE_UFOPEDIA", "One thing that makes Weirdgals more powerful in VooDoo is the partial collapse of their mutant bio-forcefields. But we asked ourselves a question, could we collapse the field any further to get even greater gains at the price of increased vulnerability? Turns out, we can. This augmentation is Weirdgal-only. The cost includes $80k life insurance.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}+10 VPWR, +15 VSKL{NEWLINE}+25 Stamina{NEWLINE}+5 TU & REA{NEWLINE}-10 HP, -15 FRS{NEWLINE}-9 Armor"},
		{"STR_ANG_103_UFOPEDIA", "The Mystery Patron conceded that you deserve some reward, for 'furthering the cause of Life' (that is fighting Zombies). She handed you three Sivalinga Stones that you can use to ressurect the fallen warriors. She also revealed that while the stones are exceedingly rare, she, being the master of Life Magic, can teach you how to make them - if you can procure the fabled Water Of Life, apparently a thing that can only be found in the Shadowrealms."},
		{"STR_ANG_104_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}The Mystery Patron is greatly impressed by our retrieval of the Water of Life.{NEWLINE}'My champion! You have truly become a seasoned Shadowrealms traveler! This means my plans for you were not misconceived... But enough about that for now! The Water of Life is the true mystery behind the power of Sivalinga Stones, and it allows their creation. But it is not the only liquid required, ha, ha... Your craftsmen are female, right? Good. I hope their bodies... and artistic crafting skills are both up to the task!'{NEWLINE}(Basic manufacturing + VooDoo required){ALT}"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CHALLENGE", "Cleopatra's Challenge"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CHALLENGE_DESCRIPTION", "Don't be alarmed. I mean you no harm. In fact, I call you with an offer, of a rather... frivolous nature. You've become quite famous and recognized. Some even say you're a legendary hero. But... legendary heroes perform timeless deeds. Would you consider indulging me by being my champion? Prove that you can defeat monsters without modern weapons. If you manage to do it, we will both profit. If not... Well! It is only my reputation at risk here. What will you say?'"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CHALLENGE_UFOPEDIA", "Cleopatra, the Queen Bee of the Theban Hive herself, has challenged us to a game. We would have to fight various monsters, using only stone age equipment. She wired us a 'small donation' of $250k for expenses. If we accept, we need to research the '!Primal Hunts!' topic. If not... well, probably nothing will happen?"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CHALLENGE_COMPLETED", "Cleopatra's Challenge Completed"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CHALLENGE_COMPLETED_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'My bet on you wasn't misplaced. You have performed some amusing feats. I will remember you in the future, friend of Thebes... As for now: knowledge is power, and knowledge I will share. Let me tell you about my old friends, the Mummu...{NEWLINE}[+300 score, +$1M, +50 Databases]"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CATGIRLS", "Cleo's Catgirls"},
		{"STR_CLEO_CATGIRLS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Greetings again, friend of Thebes, Terror of the Skies and delver into the Shadow. Your venture into broadening our contacts with the Nekomimi have alarmed me a little, but also provided me with new, unique opportunities. Allow me to present to you my newest creation: Theban Assault Catgirls. If you have been good to cats, I'm willing to share a few of them with you, for your enjoyment...'"},
		{"STR_JACKS_DUNGEON_EVENT", "Invitation to the Dungeon"},
		{"STR_JACKS_DUNGEON_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}So I heard you're a PLAYER? You amuse me, girl! Now you can count yourself into the circle of my personal friends. Come and drop by to my Dungeon, and let's revel in the festivities of the Demon Gods!"},
		{"STR_JACKS_DUNGEON", "Jack's Dungeon"},
		{"STR_JACKS_DUNGEON_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}You are amongst those privileged to visit The Dungeon, Jack's secret den of gambling and debauchery. This allows you to gain more favors and expands your Socializing options."},
		{"STR_GOLDEN_CREDIT_BOUNTY", "Golden Creds at Jack's Dungeon"},
		{"STR_BLK_001", "Adventuring Knights"},
		{"STR_BLK_001_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'You've been making progress in my realm. Very Good. It will harden your mettle and bring you to the challenge I want you to face. Yet. Every action causes reaction. You have swung the Gates between the two worlds wide open. My Dreadknights will want to see what's on your side. They won't refuse a good fight.'"},
		{"STR_DES_001", "Bloodied Message"},
		{"STR_DES_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A strange letter was aired to us from an unknown source. It brings the smell of something burning to mind."},
		{"STR_DES_001_UFOPEDIA", "The flow of spilled blood propels the Wheel of Pain, to hasten the coming of the Shadowfall."},
		{"STR_GOP_001", "A Curious Gift"},
		{"STR_GOP_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This impossibly well-packaged parcel was just found at Hideout's entrance. Looks like some sort of a love letter... What shall we do with it, Cap'n?"},
		{"STR_NEC_001", "Crumbling Message"},
		{"STR_NEC_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A strange letter was aired to us from an unknown source. It brings the smell of freshly overturned earth to mind."},
		{"STR_NEC_001_UFOPEDIA", "So you seek contact with the dead. My dear... Aren't all your lives slowly ebbing away, even if not abruptly ended? Tick-tock. Soon enough you will stand naked before the Grim Reaper, without even your body to protect you. Do you think She can be bargained with? Hahaha, I knew you would say so. But you're not completely wrong. Heroes like yourselves can get special treatment. I can bring their shades back to you. You guessed right, there's always a price to pay... But there's no hurry. We will SURELY meet again, after all."},
		{"STR_LFS_001", "Scented Message"},
		{"STR_LFS_002", "Scented Message 2"},
		{"STR_LFS_003", "Scented Message 3"},
		{"STR_LFS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A strange letter was aired to us from an unknown source. It brings the fragrance of ripe cherries to mind."},
		{"STR_LFS_001_UFOPEDIA", "Is it a mere coincidence that a band of fleeing, determined outcasts found an underground military base that was hidden for centuries?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Is it a mere coincidence that the base contained a functional laboratory, of a kind that would be envied even by the Guild?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Did it simply happen that a tribe of so well-supplied nomads was living nearby?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Is it a mere coincidence that it was not much after these mysterious Cloaking Devices appeared first? Why does nobody know where these devices are coming from? Is Clemborg even an Earth name...? Teeheehee. Is there a spring of change coming? Who flies on its wings?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Love is in the air.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}                     - Lady of Bloom"},
		{"STR_LFS_002_UFOPEDIA", "The shadows are growing deeper in the streets of Babylon. A change is coming. People leave their enshrined responsibilities and celebrate for no apparent reason, even though the penalty is death. The Golden Ziggurat cannot comprehend it. Can you? What is that change that makes so many tingle with excitement or fear? And who is bringing that change, my dear? Who might that be? (Yes, it's you). Love requires nothing but reaching out. Love forgives everything. But love is all-consuming, too... are you afraid? {NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}                     - Lady of Bloom"},
		{"STR_LFS_003_UFOPEDIA", "Hello there, my beloved Seeker.{NEWLINE}Are you dying to find out my secret?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Or are you simply irritated and aggressive?{NEWLINE}Love makes no distinction.{NEWLINE}All you need to be is interesting.{NEWLINE}Oh how beautiful it is to be drunk...{NEWLINE}How ugly it is to be boring and bland and useless.{NEWLINE}Watch out for the Pink Ships, bearing gifts of Love.{NEWLINE}Do not thank me; be nice and tasty instead.{NEWLINE}Consume this world like you were Love itself.{NEWLINE}   - Lady of Bloom"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GOLD_AWAKENS", "Golden Codex Awakens!"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GOLD_AWAKENS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Having experimented with VooDoo for a while, you finally tried to reach out to your Codex. The result was spectacular. You had a vision of a huge mirror, inside of which there was the most beautiful person you've ever seen. 'You are the most beautiful person I've ever seen', said your mirror image. 'You are me, and I'm you. Let's shine like the brightest star!'"},
		{"STR_CODEX_RED_AWAKENS", "Red Codex Awakens!"},
		{"STR_CODEX_RED_AWAKENS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Having experimented with VooDoo for a while, you finally tried to reach out to your Codex. The result was spectacular. You had a vision of it exploding in flames. You saw the world burning, and blood flowing like rivers while you were chopping heads off, each strike calming your mind. The drums of war are calling you..."},
		{"STR_CODEX_GRAY_AWAKENS", "Gray Codex Awakens!"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GRAY_AWAKENS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Having experimented with VooDoo for a while, you finally tried to reach out to your Codex. The result was spectacular. You had a vision of endless possibilities, spaces and times far away, but now seemingly within hand's reach. Your vision blurred from the information overload, but now, once you've seen it, your journey towards mastery of the unknown has already started."},
		{"STR_CODEX_GREEN_AWAKENS", "Green Codex Awakens!"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GREEN_AWAKENS_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Having experimented with VooDoo for a while, you finally tried to reach out to your Codex. The result was spectacular. You had a vision of a serene cemetery, where everyone who has ever died was buried. You were buried there as well, naked and purified from all evil. You felt no fear or regret, as in the cycle of life, death always precedes rebirth, and nothing important ever dies."},
		{"STR_CODEX_GOLD_AWAKENED", "Gold Ascended"},
		{"STR_CODEX_RED_AWAKENED", "Red Ascended"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GRAY_AWAKENED", "Gray Ascended"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GREEN_AWAKENED", "Green Ascended"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GOLD_AWAKENED_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}The Codex is no longer just a fancy data slate. Now it has taken an appearance of an expensive-looking, golden-covered book. However on the inside there is only a mirror which you can operate with touch or mind to bring up any image, while the rest of the pages is filled with porn.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_CODEX_RED_AWAKENED_UFOPEDIA", "The Codex is no longer just a fancy data slate. Now it's a heavy book, reinforced with brass and bound by chains. It smells of brimstone and heated metal. Sometimes it causes fires. You need to find a safe way to store it... or to weaponize it."},
		{"STR_CODEX_GRAY_AWAKENED_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}The Codex is no longer just a fancy data slate. Now it's a blue leather bound tome, adorned by a triangle with a reptillian eye inside which seems to trace your movements. At your mental command it can levitate and turn to a desired page by itself. However it also tends to whisper strange things, things that make you choose different pages, pages that weren't there before...{ALT}"},
		{"STR_CODEX_GREEN_AWAKENED_UFOPEDIA", "The Codex is no longer just a fancy data slate. Now it's a thick, beaten-up tome of yellow pages with a brown leather cover, which sometimes splits to show a big, toothy maw. Despite this it's rather cute and very nice to the touch. It might be the best pillow you've ever slept on...{NEWLINE}[Acquired 3 Transdimensional Lockers]"},
		{"STR_CODEX_AWAKENED", "Codex is Awakened"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G1", "Gifts of Adulation"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G1_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}After you opened your Codex, you saw a wrapped gift on the other side of its mirror. Without thinking much, you reached for it..."},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G2A", "Gifts of Adulation"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G2A_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}After you opened your Codex, you saw a familiar face on the other side of its mirror. Overwhelmed by her feminine presence and sweet fragrance of half-rotten flowers, you barely noticed when she handed you a cake through the mirror. 'Eat up, whore', she said, smiling. So you did, and the cake made you feel rejuvenated (+50 Infamy). There's even some of it left..."},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G2B", "Gifts of Spirits"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G2B_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Your Codex opened its toothy maw and spat something out. It turned out to be a cake, covered in slime. You'd never have eaten it, if your senses hadn't been overwhelmed by a vague, charming presence and a sweet fragrance of half-rotten flowers. 'Eat up, whore', said the Codex in a feminine voice. So you did, and the cake made you feel rejuvenated (+50 Infamy). There's even some of it left..."},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G3", "Gifts of Spirits"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G3_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Your Codex opened its toothy maw and spat something out. It turned out to be a strange gem, covered in slime. 'Nobody lives forever,' the mouth said, 'But some get to die more than once!', it added with a sardonic chuckle. As the chuckle faded out, all that remained was the smell of freshly overturned earth..."},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G4A", "Gifts of Blood"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G4A_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Codex spoke to you today in a monotone, emotionless female voice: 'You're a blade of justice. I give you the gift of Dragon Eye, it will strike fear into the hearts of the wicked. Show them no mercy but remember: only the weak find joy in revenge.'{NEWLINE}[+300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G4B", "Gifts of Spirits"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G4B_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Codex opened its toothy maw today and spoke to you in a monotone, emotionless female voice: 'You're a blade of justice. I give you the gift of Dragon Eye, it will strike fear into the hearts of the wicked. Show them no mercy but remember: only the weak find joy in revenge.'{NEWLINE}[+300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G5", "Gifts of Blood"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G5_DESCRIPTION", "Your Codex spoke to you today in a metallic voice: 'Dogs are good.' You heard something barking. 'Have one.'"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G6A", "Gifts of Blood"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G6A_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Codex spoke to you in an sharp female voice: 'You're in the presence of the Queen of Snakes, mortal. But I'm in a generous mood today. Do not show cowardice nor foolishness, and you will be rewarded.'"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G6B", "Gifts of Sorcery"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G6B_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Codex whispered to you in an mesmerizing female voice: 'You're in the presence of the Queen of Snakes, mortal. But I'm in a generous mood today. Do not show cowardice nor foolishness, and you will be rewarded.'"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G7A", "Gifts of Sorcery"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G7B", "Gifts of Sorcery"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G7C", "Gifts of Sorcery"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G7_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Today your Codex rose into the air, its whispers reached a crescendo, then something like a portal formed next to it. You wonder what's going to come out... Or should you go in?"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G8A", "Gifts of Adulation"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G8A_DESCRIPTION", "Looking at your image in your Codexes mirror, like you often do, you suddenly noticed some vague presence on the other side. It spoke in a seductive, female voice: 'You know that you're SPECIAL to me, dear... I'll bless you with a bit of my CHARM so you can become even prettier...'"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G8B", "Gifts of Sorcery"},
		{"STR_CODEX_BONUS_G8B_DESCRIPTION", "Your Codex whispered to you in a soft, female voice: 'You know that you're SPECIAL to me, dear... I'll bless you with a bit of my CHARM so you can become even prettier...'"},
		{"STR_CRYPT_MEMORIAL", "Crypt of Remembrance"},
		{"STR_CRYPT_MEMORIAL_2", "Crypt of Remembrance (Continued)"},
		{"STR_CRYPT_MEMORIAL_UFOPEDIA", "Forever be remembered those,{NEWLINE}Whose skulls have been taken by the Black Dragon;{NEWLINE}May their souls take solace in the Dark Utopia.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Alex D, Andreas Tybussek, Angelic Joker, AlianarOne, Amuys, Anonynamja, Arctic Air, Arthanor, Ashert, Finn Bacall, Baldoran, Berriebun, Богдан Брожко, Bouchacha, Casey's Handmade, EricDaMidget, Florian Bucher, Leonardo Chingcuanco, Chinolee, Marek Chmiel, Comrade East, Filip Cakl, Elseleth, Eoghan Cregan, Dr. Entropi, Drago888, Ethanw80, Ethereal Medic, Evan Hillis, eXalted, Flyte, Fonzo, François Glanard, Fulgulator, Stefan Glüsing, Gunner-chan, Hardcastle, Heiper, Tim Heise, Yavgeni Hotimsky, HumanTraitor, Ilan Nikritin, JamTheDane, Jan Nilsson, Jason Fable, Jiří Jevický, John Cheng, Juffos the Silicoid, Kajamablar, Karadoc, Kammerer, Kato, Ketonur, Kitsune106, Viacheslav Kobylinskyi, Kribu, Krieg, LusciousPear, Machli, Maciej Cieloszyk, Maelstrom Zephyr, Machinehater, Magic Skeleton, Mammothus, Mathias Edman, Mattdo, Mieko, Meridian, Anthony Mohr, Morrandir, Mr. Casper, Msx, Robert Mulholland{NEWLINE}Donate per Paypal to: GSDioxine@gmail.com"},
		{"STR_CRYPT_MEMORIAL_2_UFOPEDIA", "NepNep the Cabin Pet, Nikodemos, Ola Osttveit, PaladinF1, Patrick Patzelt, Petar Petrov, Remigijus Pigaga, Quickmind, raziel_malakai, renecane, remiz, RelicLord Rex Fujishima, Richard Bohn, Ring Dang Doo, Rolan7, Ruludos, SabreCat, Sahti Waari, Saladofstones, Sarissofoi, Peter Savranskiy, Searmay, Seilacara112, Shai Gelbaum, Shirke and Rhea, David Siegrist, Michael Sterr, SymbolBlue, Michael Thomas, Taylor Lopez, Thyl, TomRon, Torchwood, Troubleshooter, TÜ Spire, Tyralocus, Vengarr, Vesparco, VDBomber, WarStalker, Piotr Wasilewski, Weirdfoe, Adrian Wójcik, Xaphias, XCOMJunkie, Yassine Meskhout, HF Zaffari, Zastaver, Zedd B.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Donate per Paypal to: GSDioxine@gmail.com"},
		{"STR_NEKO_THANKS", "Salute to Cats"},
		{"STR_NEKO_THANKS_UFOPEDIA", "The best friends{NEWLINE}of Catgirls:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Alexey Sapunkov{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Anton Bordanov{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Arthur N.{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Dmitry Zelten{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Dukoni Ber{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} just_dont{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Konstantin Polyakov{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} kot_nastoyatel{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Mikhail I.{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Nikolai Radchuk{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Roman Chromov{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Vitaly Staneiko{NEWLINE}{ALT}♥{ALT} Vitaly Starodubtsev{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Purring Thanks!"},
		{"STR_CRAFTS_ARMAMENTS_TITLE", "Yer Trusty Vessels"},
		{"STR_WEAPONS_AND_EQUIPMENT_TITLE", "YER ARMORY"},
		{"STR_UFOS_TITLE", "ON YER RADAR"},
		{"STR_TREASURE_TITLE", "YER PRECIOUS BOOTY"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_TITLE", "YER COZY HIDEOUT"},
		{"STR_FACTIONS_TITLE", "YER HOSTAGES"},
		{"STR_MYSTERIES_TITLE", "ARCANE MYSTERIES"},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_LOGS_TITLE", "YER LOG"},
		{"STR_PRIZES_TITLE", "BOUNTIES, TROPHIES, PRIZES"},
		{"STR_LORE_TITLE", "LORE"},
		{"STR_TIPS_TITLE", "TIPS & TRICKS"},
		{"STR_CONDEMNATIONS_TITLE", "YER POWER-UPS"},
		{"STR_CRAFTS_ARMAMENTS_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "In front of you, Cap'n, lies the Bootypedia, a mighty tome of many thousands pages. From the humble beginnings, we're going to fill them during the course of our grand journey.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Let us start from chapter one, which covers the most important thing: the crafts we're going to use to transport warriors and, in time, assert our dominance in the skies. For the latter, we're going to need airborne weapons, which are also described here."},
		{"STR_WEAPONS_AND_EQUIPMENT_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "In the chapter three we turn our focus to the equipment yer crew can use in personal combat. From bare hands, it will proceed to melee weapons, firearms, explosives, traps, and finally all sorts of utilities, like medicine to patch up yer wounds or light sources to control the night, not to mention things secretive and exotic..."},
		{"STR_UFOS_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "Chapter tenth is about things that we can send to the bottom and plunder, if we have means and desire. Shootdowns alone can be a major source of Infamy, while ignoring crash sites costs us nothing. Beware of shippings with their own radar circles; they will actively seek to attack us."},
		{"STR_TREASURE_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}Bootypedia lives the most to its title in chapter four, because it collects information on all kinds of booty we can loot from our generous donors, with the exception of weapons and armor described above. It can be of monetary, knowledge, practical, or questionable value. It can be materials, it can be rights or obligations, it can be livestock, all of it is lumped here.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_HIDEOUT_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "Our Hideouts are the heart of our power, the safe harbors we use to prepare for our raids and rest after them. Chapter five of the Bootypedia describes various Hideout facilities. We will eventually have to expand and build more Hideouts, but their size and number is limited; there is enemy spies, there is logistics, and there is only so much a single Cap'n can manage, even such a magnificient one as yourself!"},
		{"STR_FACTIONS_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}The sixth chapter of the Bootypedia is fully dedicated to the characters and factions we'll find ourselves fighting against, and sometimes alongside. Its first part contains descriptions, the second one technical reports on their strengths and weaknesses. The best way to fill the pages in this chapter is to interrogate our hostages.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_MYSTERIES_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "The seventh chapter, as it befits the number, contains scientific and technological secrets, as well as cultural advances, unlocked by our tireless Brainers. This is the font of knowledge from which all our other achievements blossom."},
		{"STR_CAPTAIN_LOGS_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "This chapter, the eighth, focuses on yourself, Cap'n, your crew's origins, as well as key story events. It also contains all contacts and missions which we manage to unlock."},
		{"STR_PRIZES_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "There is a plethora of prizes you can unlock via gathering enough reputation with various organizations, communities and VIPs. These prizes usually allow to buy unique merchandise. Some prizes unlock higher-tier prizes. All of it is gathered here, in the ninth chapter of the Bootypedia."},
		{"STR_LORE_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "The eleventh chapter of the Bootypedia is dedicated to the knowledge which doesn't have direct applications. It describes places, events and tales of past and present, it contains legends, myths and reports."},
		{"STR_TIPS_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "Running your own pirate empire of a global reach is not a piece of cake. The purpose of chapter 12 is to put together assorted advice, mechanics explanations, as well as a lot of tits... ehm, tips & tricks. Not all info is available right away; most of it has to be found."},
		{"STR_CONDEMNATIONS_TITLE_UFOPEDIA", "Our crew can be improved in a variety of ways which go beyond normal skill limits (and never counts towards these limits either), called Augmentations. The most basic way of gaining these is earning CONDEMNATIONS through performing various feats in combat. However, these will be described here only after our Gals discover them by performing such feats. There is over a hundred Condemnations, and there are many other ways of receiving Augmentations, some of which may also train normal skills. This is the theme of the 13th and final chapter."},
