		{"STR_PINUP_001_UFOPEDIA", "While dusting off old data, rummaging through junk piles and kicking the rats (yummy) out of storage cabinets, we've found a decryption program that broke the code on a Data Disc we've also found; here you can see an image and a number. There are many of such libraries of knowledge, and grabbing each will be a solid boost to our fame.{NEWLINE}Data Discs can sometimes be seized from our enemies. Some can contain the data we've mentioned; most others will describe some piece of technology or equipment.{NEWLINE}Much has been lost in this wild world we inhabit. While the Stellar Empire has brought technology, it also took away our means of understanding it. We can tinker, match and mix, but not really improve. We need to find some well-informed allies, as well as gain the knowledge of Old Earth books - either through Discs (that can only be decrypted here) or random interrogation of anyone who seems smart, and then start the 'Back To School' project."},
		{"STR_PINUP_002_UFOPEDIA", "Be wary of your encumbrance, as it could really slow you down. If the carried weight surpasses a soldier's Strength, you will have less TUs available, and unlike TU penalties incurred by armor, it can even make it impossible to fire weapons. However a soldier can pick up any weight and suffer no ill-effects if the weight is dropped before the end of turn. There is no extra bonus for carrying less than your maximum allowed encumbrance."},
		{"STR_PINUP_003_UFOPEDIA", "Come at them from the back.{NEWLINE}It will reduce any Evasion they might have by half (attacks from the flank reduce it by 1/4th)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_004_UFOPEDIA", "What constitutes beauty is often a complicated matter, but here we simply sum it up as 'beefness'. Beefness, or physical ability is broken into stats: Strength, Health, TUs (speed) and Energy (Stamina). To increase beefness (and thus beauty), you need to train; the lower a stat, the faster it's likely to increase. Working out surely gets you there, but it requires effort. And there is a more fun way: combat. Hitting enemies with ranged and melee weapons or casting magic will not only influence related skills, but also gradually increase your beefness (and thus beauty)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_005_UFOPEDIA", "The placement of your spare ammo does matter. The TU cost of reloading is increased by the cost of moving ammunition to your hand (as much as 20 if it's in your backpack). You will avoid paying extra TUs only if the spare ammo is in your free hand."},
		{"STR_PINUP_006_UFOPEDIA", "Most Piercing weapons of 60+ Power will always cause some armor damage. Even more armor damage is caused by Plasma weapons, regardless of their Power."},
		{"STR_PINUP_007_UFOPEDIA", "Even if you can't get enough plundering, still take a break every few hours. Savor the anticipation, protect your sanity and let your body regenerate. Or you will die."},
		{"STR_PINUP_008_UFOPEDIA", "Discretion is the better part of valour."},
		{"STR_PINUP_009_UFOPEDIA", "No matter how good you think your armor is, if you're presenting your backside to the enemy, you're asking for it. Even the best armor is usually much more vulnerable from the back, and your Evasion is the worst there as well."},
		{"STR_PINUP_010_UFOPEDIA", "Diversify your weapons."},
		{"STR_PINUP_011_UFOPEDIA", "Strong and skilled melee fighters can destroy anything."},
		{"STR_PINUP_012_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The normal approach speed in dogfight equals 1 km per 4 seconds; when equipped with short-range weapons, you might take as many as 10 enemy blasts before getting into engagement range. Some enemies may flee instead of fighting, as long as the Max Speed of their craft exceeds that of your interceptor. High Bravery is essential to close-in faster."},
		{"STR_PINUP_013_UFOPEDIA", "Do not underestimate skilled, but weak melee fighters. Many of the lighter melee weapons inflict damage based rather on Melee, Reactions or Throwing than Strength, and they're much less tiring to use (melee weapon's swing Energy cost equals 2/3rds of its Weight, rounded down). High Reactions will allow for a frontal charge without being shot at. Thus speed sometimes wins over sheer strength (but having both is the best)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_014_UFOPEDIA", "Armor is only useful to those who get hit."},
		{"STR_PINUP_015_UFOPEDIA", "Maximum level of stun damage is four times the max health, so it might be worth it to inflict extra stun on a fallen enemy. However, if you see a ghost leaving their body, it means they're losing Health from excess Stun. Stun also causes Energy drain (20% of its value), so don't be surprised that a freshly woken Gal has little Energy..."},
		{"STR_PINUP_016_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Normal autofire range is 11 tiles.{NEWLINE}The chance to hit drops by 2% per every tile after that."},
		{"STR_PINUP_017_UFOPEDIA", "Dragons might eat you, but they might not.{NEWLINE}Sometimes you ride a dragon, but sometimes a dragon rides you..."},
		{"STR_PINUP_018_UFOPEDIA", "Greed kills. Don't stuff your mouth with more than you can swallow."},
		{"STR_PINUP_019_UFOPEDIA", "Cover saves lives. Ending your move in the open is the surest ticket to the other world. Hide at least 1 tile away from a corner for maximum safety. When going under a low ceiling, kneel to see elevated enemies and be able to throw bombs further away. Standing on corpses brings bad luck."},
		{"STR_PINUP_020_UFOPEDIA", "Don't panic: any explosive can be unprimed. This operation usually costs 15% of your TUs."},
		{"STR_PINUP_021_UFOPEDIA", "Cut and Stab damage, inflicted by weapons like knives and bows, causes very little extra Stun damage (half as much as bullets).{NEWLINE}However, such weapons sometimes can cause Reactions Disrupt or Extra Pain, which inflict, respectively, TU and Morale damage proportional to HP damage caused."},
		{"STR_PINUP_022_UFOPEDIA", "Certain underhanded monsters (usually the tentacled ones and witches, or, worst case, tentacled witches) will use attacks based on Charm damage, that sometimes also destroy armor. Pink-hazed landscapes are a sure sign of environmental hazards similar in nature. Resistance to Charm damage will be the key in dealing with them, which usually means the less clothing, the better. Bringing along stims is also recommended."},
		{"STR_PINUP_023_UFOPEDIA", "Chem can melt your opponent right out of their armor. All chem weapons cause armor damage equal to 0-20% of their Power, before armor's defense is even considered, unless otherwise stated in the Pedia. This makes subsequent shots more effective. The effect stacks with armor damage caused by any penetrating hits, if applicable. Chem also causes moderate Morale damage. However, the tradeoff is less armor penetration (usually 33%)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_024_UFOPEDIA", "Running is faster than walking, but you won't automatically stop upon seeing an enemy, allowing them an unopposed Reactions check."},
		{"STR_PINUP_025_UFOPEDIA", "Clothing and armor made for humans and normal-sized mutants is too small for Uber gals to wear, at least in battle! Most outfits can be worn by only a single race of warriors, but exceptions exist. When in doubt, try until it fits someone!"},
		{"STR_PINUP_026_UFOPEDIA", "The gals will be hurting when wounded, whether you like it or not! And it's not a good kind of hurt!{NEWLINE}Health damage not only reduces combat skills, but also affects Stun and Energy recovery. When you're seriously wounded, you will be suffering constant Stun damage, and your Combat skills will be reduced by up to 25%, proportionally to health loss. This affects all human-like creatures."},
		{"STR_PINUP_027_UFOPEDIA", "You can switch a craft's weapons off and on by clicking their icons. Disabled weapon won't be reloaded, possibly saving rounds."},
		{"STR_PINUP_028_UFOPEDIA", "Lethal weapons cause so-called System Shock damage, which is extra stun damage, normally equal to 0-50% of HP damage inflicted. If a weapon description says, eg. 'Shock x3' it means 0-150% Stun in addition to Health damage.{NEWLINE}Some enemies to which normal biology doesn't apply, mainly robotic ones, are immune to System Shock damage.{NEWLINE}However, stun weapons, based on electricity or radiation, often ignore that immunity."},
		{"STR_PINUP_029_UFOPEDIA", "The basic method of training Bravery is to use medikits (alcohol and drugs don't count). It can also be gained from piloting. However, some gals insist that swagging about without much, or any, apparel on is the best way of building up their confidence."},
		{"STR_PINUP_030_UFOPEDIA", "The main combat Skills are Firing, Throwing, and Melee. Some unusual weapons use unusual combinations of skills and even flat numbers.{NEWLINE}To make heads and tails of this, you only need to remember that weapon's accuracies (Aimed, Snap etc.) are displayed for effective Skill = 100."},
		{"STR_PINUP_031_UFOPEDIA", "If you remain unseen, you cannot be targeted. Use terrain, darkness and camouflage to your advantage. However, once spotted, you will be remembered by well-trained enemies (Spotters), allowing Snipers to target you for a few turns even out of their direct Line of Sight."},
		{"STR_PINUP_032_UFOPEDIA", "Only fools rush in.{NEWLINE}Always check your surroundings and avoid disembarking on Turn 1."},
		{"STR_PINUP_033_UFOPEDIA", "Kneeling usually increases your hit chance by 20%."},
		{"STR_PINUP_034_UFOPEDIA", "Where can you find pleasure{NEWLINE}Search the world for treasure{NEWLINE}Learn science technology{NEWLINE}Where can you begin to make your dreams all come true{NEWLINE}On the land or on the sea{NEWLINE}Where can you learn to fly{NEWLINE}Play in sports and skin dive{NEWLINE}Study oceanography{NEWLINE}Sign up for the big band{NEWLINE}Or sit in the grandstand{NEWLINE}When your team and others meet!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}In the Hideout! Yes, you can sail the seven seas{NEWLINE}In the Hideout! Yes, you can put your mind at ease{NEWLINE}In the Hideout! Come on people, fall an' make a stand{NEWLINE}In the Hideout! IN THE HIDEOUT!{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}...Can't you see we need a hand!"},
		{"STR_PINUP_035_UFOPEDIA", "Every paradise has its snake. Always read between the verses."},
		{"STR_PINUP_036_UFOPEDIA", "Bothered by all the useless items cluttering the manufacturing projects list? R-click on a project name to cycle between normal (white), new (blue) and purple (hidden).{NEWLINE}To find a hidden item, select 'Hidden' in the pull-down tab to the left."},
		{"STR_PINUP_037_UFOPEDIA", "Tired of all the hassle with daily dressing up in all that equipment and agonizing in front of the mirror? Can't ever seem to find pieces of the stuff you want to wear?{NEWLINE}In the equip screen, you can use Quicksave hotkey (F5) to save current soldier's equipment as a custom template. You can load any of these by pressing the Quickload key (F9). Alternatively, you can save a PERSONAL loadout by S, load by L and check by P. You can also use [Q]uicksearch button to find things."},
		{"STR_PINUP_038_UFOPEDIA", "Runts will work really hard to get your ships back into shape, but it's not an easy matter to repair such a large hull in the tight, hot confines of an underground hangar.{NEWLINE}The normal repair rate is 1 Hit Point per hour, so it might take even 10 days to repair a heavily damaged craft."},
		{"STR_PINUP_039_UFOPEDIA", "Pain Resistance increases the rate Stun damage passively decays by over 50%, and every next level increases it by a progressively smaller amount.{NEWLINE}This should not be confused with active Stun damage recovery, which depends on the % of Freshness and Health remaining.{NEWLINE}Outfits and races with special Stun recovery rules override these formulas."},
		{"STR_PINUP_040_UFOPEDIA", "Using a two-handed weapon single-handedly usually incurs a 50% accuracy penalty (33% for melee weapons).{NEWLINE}However, some weapons (indicated by the red 2-handedness marker) are either too heavy, too intricate or otherwise impossible to use when your off-hand is full."},
		{"STR_PINUP_041_UFOPEDIA", "Bravery as well as current Morale influence defense against black magics. One who's scared becomes an easier prey to evil spells."},
		{"STR_PINUP_042_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No Pain, No Pleasure.{NEWLINE}No Train, No Treasure!"},
		{"STR_PINUP_043_UFOPEDIA", "With each craft we have, our global influence increases: mission alerts won't timeout as long as there is at least one craft targeting them. This is false only for a few missions with non-negotiable schedules, like races or crash sites."},
		{"STR_PINUP_044_UFOPEDIA", "Throwing requires sufficient physique. To throw most items, bombs and grenades you need to expend twice as much Energy as the object weighs (min. 6 Energy, max. 20). Normal throwing range is equal to 2.5*Strength divided by item's Weight. Dedicated thrown weapons, like Ninja Stars, Javelins and Molotovs often override these rules, though."},
		{"STR_PINUP_045_UFOPEDIA", "Death is your most faithful friend. Anyone whose Stun level is thrice or more their current HP will start to slowly pass into its cold embraces. The rate is 1 HP per turn, but doubles when Stun level is 6x your current health etc. (possible only if you're wounded). People losing HP this way are indicated by a ghost icon. Keep the wounded hydrated and don't leave them to exposure!"},
		{"STR_PINUP_046_UFOPEDIA", "Experiencing comrades' deaths and being subjected to evil magics will instantly decrease Morale. The lower the Bravery, the higher the loss - someone who has Bravery 90 is twice as susceptible as someone with Bravery 100, one with Bravery 80 - thrice etc.{NEWLINE}Losing one's nerves can occur if Morale is below 50 - the closer to zero, the higher the chance."},
		{"STR_PINUP_047_UFOPEDIA", "Daze is a type of damage caused by unarmed attacks, as well as clubs, handles, rubber bullets etc. Its primary effect is Stun, but it often causes extra lethal damage (percentile means how much compared to Stun). Attacks with magical energies often use Daze (or Mind) damage type but are sometimes straight deadly. Enemies like machines or zombies are very resistant or immune to these two damage types."},
		{"STR_PINUP_048_UFOPEDIA", "The 'Ramming Speed' attack setting will increase firing rates of some weapons, most notably guided missiles and, to a lesser extent, big guns."},
		{"STR_PINUP_049_UFOPEDIA", "Craft's Range is calculated differently for crafts that use physical fuel, like Chemicals or Hellerium; they burn fuel faster the faster they go. Fuel is replenished at a rate of 1 fuel item / hour. 1 fuel item gives a much better range for light craft than for heavy ones."},
		{"STR_PINUP_050_UFOPEDIA", "Craft's Acceleration score governs how rapidly it can disengage from dogfight.{NEWLINE}Score up to 2 means half speed, 6-8: x1.5, and 9+ double speed."},
		{"STR_PINUP_051_UFOPEDIA", "Warships should be attacked by multiple craft.{NEWLINE}Up to 4 interceptors can be used in a single combat.{NEWLINE}Minimize the interception window to let them catch up, but beware; you can be spotted and attacked."},
		{"STR_PINUP_052_UFOPEDIA", "An airborne weapon causes 50-100% of its stated damage upon a successful hit."},
		{"STR_PINUP_053_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The chances to hit a target in air combat are influenced by the size of the target. The number provided in the weapon entry is the chance to hit a Medium target (not counting pilot's bonus).{NEWLINE}Very Small have a to-hit modifier of 75%, while Small - 87.5%.{NEWLINE}Large targets have a modifier of 125%. Very Large are trivial to hit with a modifier of 200%."},
		{"STR_PINUP_054_UFOPEDIA", "Never do it alone. A pair is much better. Four makes a party."},
		{"STR_PINUP_055_UFOPEDIA", "To train Reactions, you need either to fire (or at least attempt to fire) opportunity shots, or hit enemies with fast melee weapons (costing 12 or less TUs to use)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_056_UFOPEDIA", "When someone moves, attacks or throws, a reaction check is called. There is no random factor: the Reaction scores of both fighters are multiplied by their remaining TUs percentage, and penalized if the reacting unit is out of LoS. If the defender has a higher score, they're permitted an attack of opportunity, which can be only a primary Melee attack or a Snap Shot."},
		{"STR_PINUP_057_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}If you don't seem to be able to progress, check your manufacturing projects. Some things that are key researches need to be manufactured first, before their properties can be fully tested. Yet others need to be bought."},
		{"STR_PINUP_058_UFOPEDIA", "There is nothing shameful about the human body, yet there's a time and a place for everything. For example, being clothed is required for some infiltration missions, while swimming naked costs less Stun damage per turn than in a swimsuit."},
		{"STR_PINUP_059_UFOPEDIA", "Sometimes it is easier to just haul treasure into your craft and call it a day."},
		{"STR_PINUP_060_UFOPEDIA", "Underwater environments modify resistances to several types of damage. Concussive damage becomes extremely dangerous, being modified x1.5, while Piercing, Fire, Daze and Cutting all deal 20-30% less damage. These values are already accounted for in aquatic armors' descriptions."},
		{"STR_PINUP_061_UFOPEDIA", "Any interrogated prisoners will be lost, along with all their possessions. Same is true for most items. What happens to all that stuff? Better not to ask... We had to lure the Brainers into working for us somehow."},
		{"STR_PINUP_062_UFOPEDIA", "Eyes can deceive you. Sometimes you can't shoot what you see, or can shoot what you don't see. Ctrl+Click to force fire (doesn't work for Arcing weapons).{NEWLINE}Note that enemies with Sniper skill can do that too, but they won't try firing through walls."},
		{"STR_PINUP_063_UFOPEDIA", "Out of Energy?{NEWLINE}Chug down a drink."},
		{"STR_PINUP_064_UFOPEDIA", "No mastery without training.{NEWLINE}No discipline without belief.{NEWLINE}No triumph without loss.{NEWLINE}No real satisfaction without any of them."},
		{"STR_PINUP_065_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Attacking allied or neutral units, as fun as it sounds, yields no combat experience."},
		{"STR_PINUP_066_UFOPEDIA", "Fortune rules the battlefield. Most weapons can and will roll either zero or double damage. Hopeless shots can hit and near-sure ones can miss. Strings of incredibly bad and incredibly good luck will happen. Do not fight the Fortune; accept her rule - did you want to live forever, or what? Seize opportunities as they may not appear again. Always have contingency plans. Some say Fortune favors the bold but she is also merciless towards the unprepared."},
		{"STR_PINUP_067_UFOPEDIA", "Reactions describe the ability to act before others react (or vice versa). Our great physiques give us a clear advantage in that area, but that advantage can be pushed further by equipment: enhancing perception, thwarting detection - but also illusion. Non-threatening appearances can give an edge, however slight; hence, wearing frivolous clothing, or no clothing at all, improves Reactions."},
		{"STR_PINUP_068_UFOPEDIA", "After you win a mission, you recover all items and prisoners from the field. In the post-battle Sell menu, if you sell all recovered items of a certain type, all items of that type will be automatically set to sell next time, if Loot Sell manager is on (such items will be displayed in white)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_069_UFOPEDIA", "Warriors, we are the brave{NEWLINE}Let us feast and love today,{NEWLINE}For tomorrow we might die."},
		{"STR_PINUP_070_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Resistances are sometimes far more important than armor values. Items of Resistance are more powerful than you might think."},
		{"STR_PINUP_071_UFOPEDIA", "Not all weapons are equally effective against armored enemies. Eg. 'armor +25%'. This means that after the damage is rolled, and multiplied by appropriate Resistance value, armor value of the target is multiplied by 1.25, before being subtracted from damage. If it said '-25%', then target's armor would be multiplied by .75. Some damage types fully ignore armor by default (Charm, Burn, Choking, Hot, Cold). A weapon that both damages and reduces armor is dangerous, because the former occurs before the latter. Especially an area weapon against 2x2 units, as it inflicts 4 separate hits on them."},
		{"STR_PINUP_072_UFOPEDIA", "Interrogations increase our knowledge, and the prisoners, released after being interrogated, spread the word about our ferocity, wealth and power. Interrogating any prisoner type for a first time nets us extra Infamy. Interrogations sometimes also yield treasure or potential recruits (potentially repeatedly)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_073_UFOPEDIA", "Where two fight, third one profits. Loot a burning house.{NEWLINE}  - Mun Tzu"},
		{"STR_PINUP_074_UFOPEDIA", "The 'Ship' option lets us ship wares from one Hideout to another, with the help of the Tiger Transport company, at a small fee. To see if any cargo or personnel is incoming at your Hideout, check the 'Transfers' under 'Logs'. The same is true if you're wondering if you bought something lately, or where are the recruits, received from a Workshop project. Also note that all equipment and crew onboard a craft transferred in-flight, will be transferred as well."},
		{"STR_PINUP_075_UFOPEDIA", "How to gauge scientific progress? Here's an explanation of the arcane terms used by the Brainers. Note that their estimations can be wildly inaccurate.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Unknown: less than 33% of the base cost has been researched;{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Poor: over 2 weeks total at the current number of assigned Brainers;{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Average: more than a week total research time; {NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Good: 4-7 days;{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Excellent: 3 days or less."},
		{"STR_PINUP_076_UFOPEDIA", "Cannot manufacture something even if you're sure you have the technology? Make sure you're not missing a required facility. As skilled as we are, we cannot work without proper tools.{NEWLINE}In the manufacturing screen, check the filter tab to the left (it normally shows 'Default'). Set it to 'facility missing'. R-click on the project list to switch to missing facility type info (and back)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_077_UFOPEDIA", "Base defenses fire once and cause 50-150% of their stated damage on hit.{NEWLINE}Their hit chance does not depend on external factors, only on their accuracy rating."},
		{"STR_PINUP_078_UFOPEDIA", "Firing when in enemy melee range (directly adjacent to any enemy) is governed by different rules than ranged shots. A special Close Combat Check is rolled, using 1/2 Melee + 1/2 Reactions, times weapon's CQ Accuracy modifier (average 85%). Evasion (if any) of the enemy closest to gal's front is subtracted from that value. Note that this check is performed always, regardless if you're targeting the enemy in melee range, or anything else."},
		{"STR_PINUP_079_UFOPEDIA", "Holding SHIFT+CTRL when selecting target for autofire enters the Spray Fire mode, where you can select 2 (sometimes 3) waypoints. All the shots subsequently fired will be fanned between these waypoints. As a rule of thumb, all weapons with x4 Auto or faster are capable of Spray fire."},
		{"STR_PINUP_080_UFOPEDIA", "Do not underestimate fire, as it ignores all normal armor, no matter how thick, and causes massive Morale loss.{NEWLINE}A target hit by fire takes 5-10 damage, modified by its Fire Resistance. 2x2 targets take quadruple damage. An additional fire hit is dealt every turn the target is burning (which can last up to 5 turns).{NEWLINE}Fire damage never deals Fatal Wounds.{NEWLINE}Some enemies might be immune to fire, but those who aren't, will eventually succumb to it - especially since Flamers cause multiple hits."},
		{"STR_PINUP_081_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Witchery Guide.{NEWLINE}>The base accuracy of a VooDoo attack is equal to (1% of caster's Mastery (Power*Skill) + 70% of Skill) -30. It drops by 2 per every tile of distance.{NEWLINE}>Difficulty of a VooDoo attack ranges from v. hard (+0 Accuracy) to v. easy (+40 Accuracy); accuracy is displayed when the 'alt' button is pressed.{NEWLINE}>V. Defense decreases effective accuracy. If accuracy is greater than VDEF, the success is guaranteed. If VDEF is 56 higher than acc, the attack can never succeed."},
		{"STR_PINUP_082_UFOPEDIA", "Beware of things that lurk in the darkness. Just because you can't see them, doesn't mean they can't see you... Don't sleepwalk into an unknown place."},
		{"STR_PINUP_083_UFOPEDIA", "The presence of an officer on a mission reduces all morale losses and boosts all morale increases by 10 to 25%, depending on their rank (only the highest one alive counts).{NEWLINE}The highest rank modifies these values by 50%.{NEWLINE}However, the death of an officer also means a more severe morale hit than death of a mere soldier, up to 175% of the normal value.{NEWLINE}Enemies are not affected by these rules, but their leaders are often hardest to panic - so strike right in the heart."},
		{"STR_PINUP_084_UFOPEDIA", "The VooDoo Power rating is also a measure of intellect. Not the kind of intellect which makes you seem and feel smart, but a curious one which leads you towards the paths of madness... But can there be any magic without madness?{NEWLINE}This questionable faculty allows your mind to practice feats which others would name illusions, tricks, or pure luck, which helps operating a host of weapons, from bone clubs to mortars."},
		{"STR_PINUP_085_UFOPEDIA", "Anyone who is illuminated, is visible like in broad daylight. There are 15 levels of lighting; each level below 15 darkens the hues by 1 level as well. Anything affected by light level 6 or more counts as illuminated; everything else is safely hidden in the sacred darkness. The illumination generated by light sources drops by 1 per 1 tile. Lights don't add up; only the strongest one counts. Beware of ambient lighting when you're trying to remain unseen; you might not spot it when using the Night Vision mode."},
		{"STR_PINUP_086_UFOPEDIA", "Only Mun Tzu could a Tank and 4 Gals at the same time."},
		{"STR_PINUP_087_UFOPEDIA", "So many things to find out. R-click on a facility to see what's going on in there. In fact, try r-, l- and m- clicking on everything... who knows what could happen?"},
		{"STR_PINUP_088_UFOPEDIA", "Never trust a door."},
		{"STR_PINUP_089_UFOPEDIA", "The less you wear, the more bonus V. Power you receive. Madness? What can I say, darling. Magic is all about the hidden Truth, which is seldomly found in sanity. Let your clothes go, then your mind."},
		{"STR_PINUP_090_UFOPEDIA", "The govts will judge your progress harshly, and lack of their backing means you're worthless to your allies and crew. Track your Charts and watch out for high enemy activity - their overflights, landings and bases, all hit your Infamy score. Thwart these dangers early or face the consequences."},
		{"STR_PINUP_091_UFOPEDIA", "Vessels made with Star God technology are difficult to destroy. When the damage exceeds half of their vitality, they enter a controlled crash. (With high energies involved, engine explosions can happen). Casualties are minimal. It is possible to override these safety measures and fight to the death (like we do), or be destroyed with a single hit that exceeds total vitality of the ship. Crash sites persist for a few days, until the crew is rescued. Ignoring them causes no Infamy loss."},
		{"STR_PINUP_092_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Sometimes, being nice benefits mostly the benefactor. Each use of any item capable of healing gives the user +5 Morale, whether or not it actually helps."},
		{"STR_PINUP_093_UFOPEDIA", "High Stamina is important in battle, because Energy is used for moving, throwing, melee and magical attacks - eventually you will lose your breath.{NEWLINE}Sprinting (CTRL+move) will allow you to run faster, but will burn through any amount of Energy rather quickly.{NEWLINE}You can alleviate the problem a bit by dressing as lightly as possible, but real endurance can be achieved only through training.{NEWLINE}The Energy recovered per turn is normally equal to one fifth of current Freshness %  + one quarter of the current Health."},
		{"STR_PINUP_094_UFOPEDIA", "Enemies found in environments hazardous to us usually suffer no ill effects themselves. We really cannot feel comfortable anywhere outside the Zones."},
		{"STR_PINUP_095_UFOPEDIA", "When defending our Hideout, we have the home turf advantage (and a morale bonus), but there are perils involved. There is no escape, buildings can get destroyed by explosions (or by losing link to the Lift due to the above), and the Gals might get surprised in their sleeping clothes... well, this last thing has its advantages!"},
		{"STR_PINUP_096_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The turtle must be this hard, because he is so soft.{NEWLINE}        - Mun Tzu"},
		{"STR_PINUP_097_UFOPEDIA", "When all remaining enemies are under your Mind Control, you will capture them."},
		{"STR_PINUP_098_UFOPEDIA", "When charging at your enemy, make sure you won't get yourself flanked; your vision angle is only 90 degrees. Doors and corners, this is where they get you."},
		{"STR_PINUP_099_UFOPEDIA", "Soldiers receive promotions in the order of Promotion Score, which is based on beauty, mettle, skill and reputation. It is a sum of:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}FIRING *6{NEWLINE}BRAVERY *4{NEWLINE}REACTIONS *4{NEWLINE}TUs *3{NEWLINE}HEALTH *2{NEWLINE}STAMINA *2{NEWLINE}STRENGTH *1{NEWLINE}MELEE *1{NEWLINE}THROWING *1{NEWLINE}V. POWER *1 (Trained only){NEWLINE}V. SKILL *2 (Trained only){NEWLINE}Missions Finished *10{NEWLINE}Kills *10"},
		{"STR_PINUP_100_UFOPEDIA", "It pays off to know your hostage! An opponent, when taken alive always yields 10 Infamy if we already know who they are. Otherwise, our ignorance, coupled with vigor, can, uhm, backfire badly if we capture too many 'innocent bystanders', pesky govt personnel, mutant rebels who ended up in a bad place at a bad time etc. In such a case, we might consider cutting our losses by disposing of any witnesses... (In contrast, catching high ranking enemies generates more Infamy if they're unknown to us yet - it increases Gals' morale!)"},
		{"STR_PINUP_101_UFOPEDIA", "Even if your VooDoo is weak, keep using it. The progress made in school is steady but very slow."},
		{"STR_PINUP_102_UFOPEDIA", "Bio damage doesn't need a lot of kinetic force to be delivered, while Electricity goes through the path of least resistance. Thus both these damage types effectively halve target's armor value."},
		{"STR_PINUP_103_UFOPEDIA", "Every automatic weapon can be a drill. Every town can be a quarry.{NEWLINE}Terrain has no hit points; if damage exceeds its armor value, it is destroyed."},
		{"STR_PINUP_104_UFOPEDIA", "Tanks are fast and deadly, but best suited for open terrain. They use large amounts of TUs to turn, even if they turn to move, unlike foot troops. Tank turrets, however, do not pay that extra TU cost."},
		{"STR_PINUP_105_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Certain types of attacks never trigger enemy unit's explosion:{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>Charm{NEWLINE}>Concussive (only melee){NEWLINE}>Laser (only melee and thrown){NEWLINE}>Daze{NEWLINE}>Cutting (only melee, thrown and bows){NEWLINE}>Choking{NEWLINE}>EMP{NEWLINE}>Mind{NEWLINE}>Cold"},
		{"STR_PINUP_106_UFOPEDIA", "Some items, like ammo clips and bandages are consumed when used. After the battle, all charges of all remaining items are tallied up and stacked to fully refill as many items as possible. All excess charges will normally be lost (depending on game options)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_107_UFOPEDIA", "Our mutant bodies are able to quickly regenerate any form of non-lethal injury, so we can be smooth and ready for more adventure again, but it won't happen overnight. The healing might take anywhere from 0.5 to 1.5 times as many days as the amount of HPs an injured warrior was missing. So be a good sis and don't forget to heal as much as you can before ending a mission, since early treatment can greatly reduce the duration of the painful recovery process."},
		{"STR_PINUP_108_UFOPEDIA", "To uncover what is covered; the sacred mission of all scientists! Such a mission is, naturally, best performed at night. Therefore, the research progress is counted every Midnight. Whatever the Brainers were doing at that moment, they will be stuck with it for the rest of the night, whether at their workplace or otherwise. And what do they do during the daytime? I guess sleeping! All the most innovative ideas come when you sleep! During the day, you can switch them from project to project freely, but it doesn't mean they will appear there before the Midnight comes again..."},
		{"STR_PINUP_109_UFOPEDIA", "Building new facilities over obsolete buildings, like Plantations or Burrows, saves valuable time. Precisely, 2/3 of what it took to construct the original establishment. Any refunds for the replaced facilities will be fully paid in any case."},
		{"STR_PINUP_110_UFOPEDIA", "In dogfights, all the pilots of all the craft which participated in a kill get experience. There is no experience if there is no kill."},
		{"STR_PINUP_111_UFOPEDIA", "Wealth. Power. Prestige. Sustainability. Efficiency. Expansion.{NEWLINE}Those leaders who do not aim for constant betterment, are doomed to roast in nuclear fire.{NEWLINE}   - Cleopatra of Thebes"},
		{"STR_PINUP_112_UFOPEDIA", "Some manufacturing projects, like Gambling, yield random results. You will get a full report on what was manufactured (regardless of batch size) when the project ends, but items will be delivered to your stores on-the-go, just like with normal production."},
		{"STR_PINUP_113_UFOPEDIA", "Everything becomes easy once you stop trying so hard."},
		{"STR_PINUP_114_UFOPEDIA", "If you can't sleep, there may be enemies nearby."},
		{"STR_PINUP_115_UFOPEDIA", "There are better goals in life than trying to win every battle."},
		{"STR_PINUP_116_UFOPEDIA", "It's easier to get to the top than to stay there."},
		{"STR_PINUP_117_UFOPEDIA", "VooDoo is also a game for two. When your soldier has fallen under an evil spell, you can mind-control her back to regain her subordination and Time Units. You will only have to defeat her own VooDoo Defense (VDEF), and someone already did that, so it can't be that hard, right?"},
		{"STR_PINUP_118_UFOPEDIA", "Space problems require space solutions."},
		{"STR_PINUP_119_UFOPEDIA", "Feeling too high? To find your bearings in the dark emptiness of space, try activating the multi-layered or 3D display (second-last icon in GUI's top row)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_120_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}If a problem can be solved with money, it is not a real problem."},
		{"STR_PINUP_121_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}One grenade is worth 20 bullets.{NEWLINE}   - Mun Tzu"},
		{"STR_PINUP_122_UFOPEDIA", "The ability to fire at unseen units is not unique to us. Properly trained enemies can do that as well. If such an enemy spots one of our units, she remains spotted for some time and enemy snipers might attack her. Note that hitting a spotter automatically makes you spotted, even if the hit resulted in outright kill. The only exceptions are melee kills."},
		{"STR_PINUP_123_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}If you think the task is too easy to fail, you will fail.{NEWLINE}  - Mun Tzu"},
		{"STR_PINUP_124_UFOPEDIA", "They say that music can soothe even a savage beast. That is the essence of Charm-based attacks: provoking and exploiting the social impulses of others to serve your own ends. The means can range from simple suggestion to advanced hypnosis. Charm can be a powerful stunning or demoralizing weapon that bypasses physical defenses, but also can be used to aid others. Those who are easy to manipulate will be the easiest targets; those who are insane, singleminded or difficult to communicate with, the hardest. Entities completely lacking social behaviour will be immune."},
		{"STR_PINUP_125_UFOPEDIA", "Sometimes the answer is hidden in plain sight. Open your eyes; only the blind need a guiding hand. Exercise your Will; only slaves need to be told what they're supposed to do. Freedom from consequences of your actions is no freedom at all, only self-delusion; there is no way back to Eden. Tasting the Apple brought us death, but also the dignity of choice."},
		{"STR_PINUP_126_UFOPEDIA", "The timer on primed explosives does count down when they're in your inventory. When it reaches zero, they will explode, no two ways about it."},
		{"STR_PINUP_127_UFOPEDIA", "None of our crafts will get refuelled or rearmed until it is fully repaired. We do not want to invite what the Brainers refer to as the 'Gemini Curse', which entails being burnt alive. Not worth it."},
		{"STR_PINUP_128_UFOPEDIA", "Enemies can launch ground-penetrating missiles to obliterate your Hideouts. These behave like base attack craft. Each unintercepted missile swarm inflicts a number of hits indicated by its signature (eg. t.3 = 3 hits). The power rating of the swarm also influences its durability.{NEWLINE}Each hit destroys one building, although large buildings can be hit more than once. Buildings are more or less likely to be hit based on their Missile Attraction attribute (see ANAL). Missile swarms are indicated on radar by a target reticule symbol."},
		{"STR_PINUP_129_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Knowing thy enemy is half the battle. The other half is violence.{NEWLINE}  - Mun Tzu"},
		{"STR_PINUP_130_UFOPEDIA", "Missing a 100%+ shot indicates it was an impossible shot. Missing two proves it. And proving something sure does make you feel smart! Silly, probability cannot be ever equal to 100%! I'm not making fun of you... Or am I? I am the great Unspecified, after all. Hit chances are only estimates, since Chaos cannot be fully controlled in any complex system, you know. Chao is an unit of Chaos, and it is never binary. I'm a Chao of Unspecified Chaos, and my hair is red."},
		{"STR_PINUP_131_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Yet how will ever{NEWLINE}you perceive{NEWLINE}That, as we love,{NEWLINE}as lovingly we yearn,{NEWLINE}Our love is neither comfort{NEWLINE}nor relief{NEWLINE}But like a fire{NEWLINE}it will destroy and burn.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}    - Hymns of Old"},
		{"STR_PINUP_132_UFOPEDIA", "It generally pays off to keep a dozen or so Workers (or Slaves...) on any Hideout we keep any loaded aircraft in. Who knows what can happen if our Vaults are blown up during an attack on that Hideout? Of course, if we have a Land Deed to the surrounding area, this is never a problem."},
		{"STR_PINUP_133_UFOPEDIA", "Gold and valuables are safer means of storing capital than cash."},
		{"STR_PINUP_134_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Heard that warning siren? It means that an enemy craft is hunting you. Despite our stealth, coming too close to an enemy still betrays our position. You can identify such ships by having radar circles. But don't panic! Crafts returning from a mission are extra stealthy and won't be targeted."},
		{"STR_PINUP_135_UFOPEDIA", "Does the music offend your taste? Or perhaps a burning city needs a different tune?{NEWLINE}Hit END key to open the Jukebox."},
		{"STR_PINUP_136_UFOPEDIA", "Wounded warriors will not participate in missions, but they still can defend the Hideout. You can set their minimum allowed HP percentage in the Contracts. Be careful, though, since heavily wounded soldiers may die from system shock if the battle takes too long."},
		{"STR_PINUP_137_UFOPEDIA", "When being intercepted by an enemy craft, the crew will engage some of the safety systems. If the worst comes to pass, this will allow them to survive the controlled crash, but not to save any equipment from the wreckage."},
		{"STR_PINUP_138_UFOPEDIA", "A weapon is a part of your armor, so you don't know how to unload it? Don't despair, there is always a way.{NEWLINE}Shift+Click removes amunition from a weapon and drops it on the ground.{NEWLINE}Another good trick to remember is that Ctrl+Click moves an item from your inventory to the ground, or vice-versa (the latter use is, however, not recommended during battle)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_139_UFOPEDIA", "When one of our crafts gets attacked, friendly crafts will join the fight as long as they're within 50 Nautical Miles range."},
		{"STR_PINUP_140_UFOPEDIA", "Do not regret past mistakes, but learn from them. Guilt arrests progress. Self-pity only makes you weak."},
		{"STR_PINUP_141_UFOPEDIA", "As the old saying goes, mind tricks work best on weak minds. Masters teach that VooDoo defense (VDEF) is influenced by the following parameters:{NEWLINE}>VPWR: Major{NEWLINE}>VSKL: Minor{NEWLINE}>BRA: Minor{NEWLINE}>Morale: Minor{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}But most importantly, sister, mages can't hurt you if you break their necks."},
		{"STR_PINUP_142_UFOPEDIA", "Some aircraft guns use multi-round clips, and these will be fully replaced after combat, even if you fired just 1 round (the ammo clip might disappear, with a chance depending on how many rounds you've fired). To save ammo, you can disable a weapon (in battle or in base) by clicking on its icon. Such a weapon won't be reloaded."},
		{"STR_PINUP_143_UFOPEDIA", "R-Click on a weapon to prioritize it for Reaction Fire. It will be marked by a yellow dot. Note that this will not override default Reaction Fire priority (melee first, ranged weapons second)."},
		{"STR_PINUP_144_UFOPEDIA", "Don't rush into the treadmill of constant battles and resource management. Watch instead as the globe is spinning slowly. It will bring you inner peace."},
		{"STR_PINUP_145_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Reality has a tendency to not conform to your expectations. But you can only change the latter."},
		{"STR_PINUP_146_UFOPEDIA", "When going into underground caves or mazes, don't forget to bring some mining equipment with you. There is always the possibility of blocked passages. Rocks may require many strikes to fully clear, so don't expect it to be easy bread. Do not trust explosives, because they can create impassable craters."},
		{"STR_PINUP_147_UFOPEDIA", "Moving on might cost you losing some of the old opportunities, but usually it doesn't. Time, the slow killer, is much less merciful."},
		{"STR_PINUP_148_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Shower a man with gold and he will forget your generosity before soon.{NEWLINE}Throw him to the crocodiles and he will remember it for the rest of his life.{NEWLINE}- Cleopatra of Thebes"},
		{"STR_PINUP_149_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Who conquers the border, commands the board."},
		{"STR_PINUP_150_UFOPEDIA", "Our science is conducted in accordance with principles of materialist orthodoxy, and each Hideout is an unique environment with its own conditions, infrastructure and heavily personalized workspaces. This gives us big advantages in pursuing the Quest for Knowledge, but it also has a downside: projects researched at different Hideouts run in parallel and their progress doesn't stack."},
		{"STR_PINUP_151_UFOPEDIA", "Running out of storage space is not a question of 'if' but 'when'. But how to avoid being overwhelmed by chaos? The answer is SORTING! When fencing, press keys while selecting something from a combobox on the top left:{NEWLINE}>CTRL+LMB: by total size.{NEWLINE}SHIFT+CTRL+LMB: by unit size.{NEWLINE}ALT+LMB: by total value.{NEWLINE}SHIFT+ALT+LMB: by unit value."},
		{"STR_PINUP_152_UFOPEDIA", "Evasive maneuvers are an action available when you get intercepted by an enemy craft (the top of the 2 attack icons, the other being aggressive stance). It will increase your Dodge, hopefully helping you to survive, but it will also halve the fire rate of all your weapons."},
		{"STR_PINUP_153_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}Walked into enemy reaction fire? DON'T PANIC. Turning away and running is the worst thing you can do, you'll get shot in the back. Don't forget you're not alone on this mission... are you?{ALT}"},
		{"STR_PINUP_154_UFOPEDIA", "Effects of hits are immediately visible as color flashes:{NEWLINE}>Red: primarily HP damage;{NEWLINE}>White: armor damage;{NEWLINE}>Black: stun damage.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Note that this doesn't always work properly for multi-pellet weapons, but there is always CTRL+H/ALT+CTRL+H for hitlogs and m-click for a more... close visual inspection."},
		{"STR_PINUP_155_UFOPEDIA", "Shootdowns of enemy shippings can be a major source of Infamy once we get a powerful airforce. Score depends on exact type of shipping, not its flag; a Faction ship flown by Govt is enemies to our cause and therefore fair game. Note that annihilating a shipping yields double score compared to a crash, and that ignoring crash sites costs us nothing."},
		{"STR_PINUP_156_UFOPEDIA", "When we sell a craft, we retain its fixed weapons. You might ask, Cap'n, why can't we remove them otherwise? Well, while selling, we don't care that much about the craft being actually airworthy..."},
		{"STR_PINUP_157_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}Any researches completed at the turn of a month count as finished during the new month.{ALT}"},
		{"STR_PINUP_158_UFOPEDIA", "A radar contact is not worth your time? Press CTRL and then the 'Ignore' button that will appear to be never notified about it again."},
		{"STR_PINUP_159_UFOPEDIA", "Your Gals are so heroic that when you end the battle, they won't take any extra lingering damage (from bleeding, system shock or being on fire). Which means ending the battle quickly can save your dying Gals. The enemies, however, will take one more round of such damage."},
		{"STR_PINUP_160_UFOPEDIA", "By clicking the middle mouse button on a research topic, you bring out the tech tree viewer. It can be also called forth from the planet view by pressing 'Q', like for any search. It lets you see the whole tech tree, nothing is hidden. This kind of ominiscience, of course, is out of character and will rob you of the sense of discovery.{NEWLINE}To truly experience an approximation how scientific progress looks to most people, never use it.{NEWLINE}To experience it in a way how it feels for a Gnome, use it only sparingly."},
		{"STR_PINUP_161_UFOPEDIA", "They say to work smarter, not harder, but it's a lie: work hard AND smart! Learn to use tools to increase your yield so you can have more leisure. R-click moves stuff ALL the way UP. L-click brings back one position, or to the max available. Ctrl+n lets you take notes. Don't panic!"},
		{"STR_NUNITY_EVENT", "Diplomatic Initiatives"},
		{"STR_NUNITY_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "Rejecting the power of the Drill perhaps bereft us of vast opportunities, but also somehow lifted a weight from our shoulders. We need to be strong, therefore we must act, and one way to do it is to win friends. We have reached out to the Nunity, which appears to be the most friendly wing of the Mutant Alliance. Let's find out where we can go from here..."},
		{"STR_SCHOOLBUS_EVENT", "Flying Dutchman"},
		{"STR_SCHOOLBUS_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "A beaten-up air coach made an emergency landing next to our Hideout. Inside we met seven very old schoolgirls and their rather molested-looking, very tired teacher. We seized the machine and marched the whole merry band to our prison. They're saying they got here by 'serendipity'... Looks like the coach suffered some sort of electric failure. It can be salvaged, but it's so old and weird that we'll better interrogate the passengers to make sure we don't blow it up by accident."},
		{"STR_DEEP_TUNNELS_EVENT", "Tunnels of Adventure"},
		{"STR_DEEP_TUNNELS_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}We have found a disheveled and soaked, but weirdly happy Gnome in the tunnels below our Hideout. No, you know her. Putting aside the question of how she managed to leave her cell, she claims she has found a yet-unknown passage leading deep down, and has a tattered piece of ancient documentation (partial plans of an attack helicopter) to prove it. According to her, there is an ancient facility of some sorts down there, and she insists she can find it..."},
		{"STR_GNOME_TOME_9_EVENT", "Tentacle Enthusiast"},
		{"STR_GNOME_TOME_9_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}The Gnome who has found the underground complex we've explored, insists that the tentacle monsters really exist, despite the fact that we haven't seen any trace of them yet. Oh, she's not scared. Quite the opposite, she's excited about this 'scientific opportunity'. She even wrote a manual for her fellow Gnomes!"},
		{"STR_THE_MAGNIFICIENT_SEVEN_EVENT", "The Seven Heroes"},
		{"STR_THE_MAGNIFICIENT_SEVEN_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "A group of seven dusty and rugged men arrives at your Hideout, riding their quads. They seem to be intent on joining your cause, but they don't explain why. They don't say much at all, they just hand you an ancient laser disc with a mysterious recording.{NEWLINE}[+300 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_HYBRID_OF_TWILIGHT_EVENT", "Disciple of Twilight"},
		{"STR_KNOCK_KNOCK_HYBRID_OF_TWILIGHT", "Knock Knock"},
		{"STR_HYBRID_OF_TWILIGHT_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A very tight-looking Bugeye in a very sharp-looking suit wants to join our band, Cap'n. She (or he? they're all so thin and flat-chested!) claims to be on a religious quest of sorts to better learn 'the ways of human violence from real experts' and claims to be already quite adept at it."},
		{"STR_RACIST_EVENT", "Congratulations, Racist!"},
		{"STR_RACIST_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Dear Customer! We at Tiger Transport have heard that you're a rising racing champion! Not to mention, a real charmer and a knower of war machines! We hereby give you a special offer to buy a curiosity of the ages past, the one-of-their-kind Battle Cabs! All you have to do in exchange is to display our logo!"},
		{"STR_SAKURA_SIVALINGA_EVENT", "Goddess' Favor"},
		{"STR_SAKURA_SIVALINGA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "You have a vision of the purple-eyed woman again. You don't remember what she's saying but she seems to be pleased by the amount of innocents you've saved, thus spreading her cause. She puts a strange stone in your hand. When you wake up, the stone is still there, along with a feeling of relaxation and a fragrance of very ripe flowers..."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_ARCTIC_EVENT", "Location: Arctic"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_ARCTIC_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is extremely cold. There is no solid ground, but our hideout is dug in thick ice. The locals live in ice-houses, warmed by Hellerium power. The region is rich in Hellerium carried by sea currents from all over the planet, which attracts mining activities.{NEWLINE}>The locals can sell us some advanced polar outfits, sadly these only fit normal-sized humans. However, we were able to obtain some furs to replace our completely unsuitable clothing.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Low (+450 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_ANTARCTICA_EVENT", "Location: Antarctica"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_ANTARCTICA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is extremely cold. The ground is covered by hundreds of meters thick ice sheet. The locals live in underground dwellings, warmed by Hellerium power.{NEWLINE}>The locals can sell us some advanced polar outfits, sadly these only fit normal-sized humans. However, we were able to obtain some furs to replace our completely unsuitable clothing.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: None (+700 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SIBERIA_EVENT", "Location: Siberia"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SIBERIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is very forbidding, with its cold, endless forests and marshes. The locals live in fortified villages, separated by huge swathes of wilderness.{NEWLINE}>The people here are welcoming. They gave us some furs so we don't die of cold, and pointers on how to make the local pattern of a warm hat.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Moderate (+200 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_NORTH_ATLANTIC_EVENT", "Location: North Atlantic"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_NORTH_ATLANTIC_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region consists of a few remote shores, blasted by icy wind and hugged by fishing villages.{NEWLINE}>The locals provided us with some cold weather outfits and told us about their trade.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Low (+450 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_EUROPE_EVENT", "Location: Europe"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_EUROPE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is densely populated by many small, agricultural villages. The general climate is temperate.{NEWLINE}>The region is rich in old, radioactive ruins. When scouting the area, we have procured some Rare Earth Elements.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: High (-50 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_NORTH_AMERICA_EVENT", "Location: North America"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_NORTH_AMERICA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>This region contains many large farms and well-fortified towns, separated by large swathes of wasteland.{NEWLINE}>The agricultural character of the region allowed us to learn something about farming, and the locals gifted us a few vodka bottles.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Moderate (+200 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SOUTH_AMERICA_EVENT", "Location: South America"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SOUTH_AMERICA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This vast region stretches from the Latin deserts in the north to the icy tundra in the south, with a lot of hot and steamy jungles in its middle areas.{NEWLINE}>The bountiful nature of this land provided us with a lot of fruits, and inspired us with a certain idea...{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Low (+450 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_NORTH_AFRICA_EVENT", "Location: North Africa"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_NORTH_AFRICA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is dominated by hot climate areas, deserts and jungles. The place has a lot of history to it, and the locals like to talk about it, perhaps too much. We have learned something about ancient treasures.{NEWLINE}>The locals are friendly enough and gifted us some beers to fight the heat, they also advised us to always take some canteens with us when going out.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: High (-50 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SOUTHERN_AFRICA_EVENT", "Location: South Africa"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SOUTHERN_AFRICA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is completely overran by monsters. The locals either hide in towns or live in nomadic tribes.{NEWLINE}>The tribes instructed us in the ways of hunting monsters, and we have procured some local weapons.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Moderate (+200 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_CENTRAL_ASIA_EVENT", "Location: Central Asia"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_CENTRAL_ASIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>This region is infested by bandits, and the locals mostly live in highly isolationist tribes.{NEWLINE}>Some locals immediately filed an avalanche of formal complaints against us for inhabiting their 'holy' or 'forbidden' place, calling us 'zombies' and 'cannibals'. We will have to settle this issue sooner or later.{NEWLINE}We have learned something about dark creatures.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Moderate (+200 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SOUTH_EAST_ASIA_EVENT", "Location: South-East Asia"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_SOUTH_EAST_ASIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is populated by many towns, connected by dizzying, geometric patterns of roads of a highly-organized, machine-like society. Or at least it used to be so, before the polluted wastelands and jungles claimed most of it.{NEWLINE}>The locals seem to be mostly interested in cooking, and, shocked by our ignorance, they provided us with some pointers and ingredients...{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Moderate (+200 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_AUSTRALASIA_EVENT", "Location: Oceania"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_AUSTRALASIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}>This remote region is home to some really crazy folks, constantly fighting some really crazy forms of nature.{NEWLINE}>The locals handed us a score of explosive cannonballs, saying, 'Oy, just start blastin', ya cunts!'{NEWLINE}>In the meantime, we have figured out how to dive.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: Low (+450 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_PACIFIC_EVENT", "Location: Pacific"},
		{"STR_START_LOCATION_PACIFIC_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", ">This region is a huge ocean, with a few islands scattered over it. The few inhabitants live in fortified mountain caves, in constant threat from the Deep Ones. Communication is mostly aerial.{NEWLINE}>To help us survive in this dangerous area, the locals sent us an experienced pilot.{NEWLINE}>Political Pressure: None (+700 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_USA_EVENT", "Country: The Confederation"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_USA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local govt expects of us to act as some sort of representatives, who carry out 'harsh frontier justice.' They gave us a bunch of service guns and some cool badges, but they also have certain expectations (-150 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_RUSSIA_EVENT", "Country: Eurasian Autonomy"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_RUSSIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local govt presented us with a mysterious package, covered in ancient symbols, letters and numbers, 'with a special dedication to the Star Gods.' Now we only need to fill out a ton of paperwork before they will pass it to us..."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_UK_EVENT", "Country: Iron Tribe"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_UK_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: this place is a huge junkyard, and, sure enough, we were able to procure some high-quality junk."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_FRANCE_EVENT", "Country: Eurosyndicate"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_FRANCE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local govt gifted us with some of their weapon tech and bioengineered servants, apparently as a hint to not cooperate too much with their Theban and Blackmarch rivals."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_GERMANY_EVENT", "Country: Blackmarch"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_GERMANY_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: a weird, diminutive person has wandered into our Hideout, and she's trying to convince the Gals that she's one of them."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_ITALY_EVENT", "Country: Romanica"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_ITALY_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local aristocracy have sent us a shipment of 'holy arms' to wage a 'righteous crusade' against their enemies. Whether they mean Star Gods or their neighbours, we do not know. Furthermore, their armor was obviously made for humans only..."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_SPAIN_EVENT", "Country: Nordfederation"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_SPAIN_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local govt sent us a bunch of Uber undesirables, whom they locked up for 'antisocial behaviour' and were about to expel anyway."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_CHINA_EVENT", "Country: Central Province"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_CHINA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the locals, with lots of ceremony, gave us a cartload of a farmable plant. 'One who seeds early, harvests happily', they said."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_JAPAN_EVENT", "Country: Fuso"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_JAPAN_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local aristocracy have passed us a bunch of local weapons to honour our new calling. They also seem to be worshipping us as 'cherry blossoms of war' (+150 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_AUSTRALIA_EVENT", "Country: Death Realms"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_AUSTRALIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: in this place everything is out to kill you! The Runts were fighting off perimeter incursions of local fauna on a daily basis. They finally mounted an expedition to eradicate the local nests and erected an electric fence (-$75k). However, they also hauled back some interesting loot..."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_NIGERIA_EVENT", "Country: Hidden Expanse"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_NIGERIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local govt gifted us some of their surplus military hardware to help us defend our Hideout. However, to make use of it, we need to advance in toolmaking, mining, gunsmithing and electronics first."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_INDIA_EVENT", "Country: Ghostgates"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_INDIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: it is customary here for landlords to keep a harem of slaves. The local govt sent us a bunch to give us some legitimacy as such."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_SOUTH_AFRICA_EVENT", "Country: Rogue Fields"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_SOUTH_AFRICA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local warlords were very vocal about us freeloading on THEIR land, immorally and uncapitalist-like, nevermind we already pay them for services. They want a compensation for the land."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_EGYPT_EVENT", "Country: Theban Hive"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_EGYPT_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the representatives of the Queen licensed us to acquire 12 Assault Clones (with basic weapons) from Hive's military. However, the other govts are deeply concerned by this overt action (-600 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_CANADA_EVENT", "Country: Canada"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_CANADA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: this kingdom is a place where you can easily find all sorts of contacts. The aristocracy is bored and rather easy-going."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_NCR_EVENT", "Country: Cali Republic"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_NCR_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: The local govt dumps 8 'transfer students' on us. What ensues? Sex, drugs & rock and roll! (+100 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_BRAZIL_EVENT", "Country: Dark Dominion"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_BRAZIL_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the place is full of occult knowledge. We were able to procure a few rare books, but it won't be soon before we can decipher most of them."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_LATIN_EMPIRE_EVENT", "Country: Latin Empire"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_LATIN_EMPIRE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: this country's aristocracy is well educated and our simplicity offends them (-50 Infamy). They passed us some old books, so we can become less 'based' (or was it 'more based'?)"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_TECHNOCRACY_EVENT", "Country: The Technocracy"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_TECHNOCRACY_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: there is so much Optronics production in the area that the stuff litters the ground."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_INDONESIA_EVENT", "Country: Pirate Straits"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_INDONESIA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the pleasure industry in this country is really massive, a bunch of hoes made it even to our Hideout, although we're not sure what we should do with them. We know, however, what to do with the things they gave us."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_TURAN_EVENT", "Country: Turan"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_TURAN_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: a trio of the local Uber Warrior Gals arrived riding their feral beasts and wants to join us. Our Gals are a bit intimidated (-100 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_CHILE_EVENT", "Country: Steel Pact"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_CHILE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: due to all the forges around, we've effortlessly procured some Metal Ore. The local govt also gave us some weapon boxes to exercise our sacred right to arm bears (whatever that means)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_VENEZUELA_EVENT", "Country: Red Revolution"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_VENEZUELA_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}Our Hideout lies within the influence, if not within the exact borders of this country. We've managed to collect enough local information to draw a rough outline of the place.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: the local govt sent us some of their political prisoners to do manual labour 'for the glory of the global revolution'. Our workshops are too sensitive to let them anywhere near, but they can be of help with warehousing (we have to pay $5k/month per head)."},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_NONE_EVENT", "Country: None"},
		{"STR_START_COUNTRY_NONE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our Hideout doesn't lie within the influence, if not outside the exact borders of any country. The Lokk'Naar tribes and Mutant Alliance agents are our only allies in the immediate area.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Bonus: we've acquired a bunch of random info. We're also facing less political pressure (+50 Infamy)."},
		{"STR_EGYPT_FRANCE_ENMITY_EVENT", "EuroSyndicate's Concerns"},
		{"STR_EGYPT_FRANCE_ENMITY_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Eurosyndicate has filed a formal protest over the existence of our base in their enemy's territory, the Theban Hive. They demand either scrapping that Hideout or building one on their turf as well.{NEWLINE}[-150 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_EUROPE_POLITICAL_FRICTION_EVENT", "European Politics"},
		{"STR_EUROPE_POLITICAL_FRICTION_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}A Hideout of ours is located in Europe. This area houses several countries who don't really like each other and we cannot avoid to be drawn into their conflicts.{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_SIBERIA_DAMSEL_EVENT", "Snow Tigress"},
		{"STR_SIBERIA_DAMSEL_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}They say Siberia is a land of beautiful women, and indeed, one just appeared at our Hideout located there. She appears bored, but she has that glint of danger in her eye, like a relaxed tiger; an aura of someone who's followed by misfortune and disaster..."},
		{"STR_CENTRAL_ASIA_HASSAN_EVENT", "Hassan's Leaflet"},
		{"STR_CENTRAL_ASIA_HASSAN_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}When you were visiting one of the bustling markets on the outskirts of {0}, someone pushed a mysterious leaflet into your hand. You looked around, but whoever did that had already disappeared..."},
		{"STR_TURAN_MONEYLOSS_EVENT", "Ore-Ore"},
		{"STR_TURAN_MONEYLOSS_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}The Turanian staff we're hiring to run our Hideout located there have their own ideas about private property. We have sustained a loss of $100,000 (but we gained 5 Glamour)."},
		{"STR_RUSSIA_ARMAMENTS_EVENT", "Ancient Weaponry"},
		{"STR_RUSSIA_ARMAMENTS_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "The Eurasian Autonomy has supplied us with an Old Earth weapon, but we will have a lot of paperwork to fill to seal the deal... also while this deal was secret, some people are getting twitchy.{NEWLINE}[-50 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_JAPAN_CULT_EVENT", "Blossoms of War"},
		{"STR_JAPAN_CULT_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Our cult in Fuso is flourishing. We're getting a lot of donations from our fans and even offers to work as idols.{NEWLINE}[+100 Infamy, +$25k]"},
		{"STR_TECHNOCRACY_SCARE_EVENT", "Night Stalkers"},
		{"STR_TECHNOCRACY_SCARE_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Last night, our crew at the Technocracy Hideout noticed humanlike shapes with glowing red eyes, moving just at the edge of sight. Efforts to find these stalkers have failed, but there's no doubt that our Hideout is watched by someone... or something.{NEWLINE}[-100 Infamy]"},
		{"STR_BLACKMARCH_GNOME_EVENT", "Blackwoods Creature"},
		{"STR_BLACKMARCH_GNOME_EVENT_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Something wicked comes this way!"},
		{"STR_GREAT_ADVICE", "Great Advice"},
		{"STR_GREAT_ADVICE_DESCRIPTION", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Your Gals have overheard some secrets and are anxious to tell you all about it!"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_ALL", "Great Advice Collected"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_001", "On Building Hideouts"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_001_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}You have one fine Hideout ready{NEWLINE}What's the point of building more?{NEWLINE}It will cost a LOT of money{NEWLINE}And it's hard to defend all.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}It's much better to sit quietly,{NEWLINE}Radar circle is whole world.{NEWLINE}All enemies within hand's reach,{NEWLINE}Flyin' round, that bunch of fools."},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_002", "Charts - Into The Oven!"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_002_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}When Infamy's underwater,{NEWLINE}And you have no clue just why,{NEWLINE}Never try to understand it,{NEWLINE}Never look into the Charts.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}It is not your job to wonder,{NEWLINE}What goes on in faroff lands.{NEWLINE}God is dumb, can't game design,{NEWLINE}Action should be where YOU are."},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_003", "Less People = More Oxygen"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_003_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}To live like ANTS in a hive?{NEWLINE}No, tis' not a proper way! {NEWLINE}Smaller crew means more liberty{NEWLINE}And is prudent money-wise.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Ten Runts will build us anything,{NEWLINE}Three Brains solve all mysteries.{NEWLINE}Just choose actions very smartly,{NEWLINE}And never, ever get hurt!"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_004", "Apples Are Not For Runts!"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_004_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}What kind of a fruit this is?{NEWLINE}Apples? Let's just eat them all!{NEWLINE}What, about some big profits?{NEWLINE}Something called 'De La Mort'?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}It is bad for you, I tell you,{NEWLINE}While the apples are so good! {NEWLINE}Even if they rot in storage.{NEWLINE}Short on money? To hell with it!"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_005", "Sit At Home, Don't Wander Off"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_005_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}Want to know what is happening{NEWLINE}Out there, beyond radar's reach?{NEWLINE}Do whatever, but remember:{NEWLINE}Expeditions ARE point-less.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Slower than a snail, no cover,{NEWLINE}Hogs a whole Hangar still.{NEWLINE}It reads hundreds of sight range,{NEWLINE}But it's just a stupid bait!"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_006", "Writefaggot the Pompous"},
		{"STR_HARMFUL_006_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}You see a page with a picture,{NEWLINE}And some silly number too.{NEWLINE}Next, a text, that makes no sense.{NEWLINE}Is this some clue, or riddle?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}What it is: a loss of time!{NEWLINE}Just a vomit of poor writing,{NEWLINE}Pointless words and nothing more.{NEWLINE}Where's in that your precious fun?"},
		{"STR_MEGAPOL_MANHACK_TERRORIST", "Manhack"},
		{"STR_MEGAPOL_MANHACK_TERRORIST_UFOPEDIA", "Megapol cops utilize these nimble flying robots in cramped places where afraid to put their fat armored asses themselves: catacombs, caves, sewers, slums etc. Even a single Manhack can cut an armored person to pieces in a matter of seconds; however, a very agile Gal could avoid its rather simple attack patterns. Hack's maneuverability is achieved by rotor usage for lift generation and light Aqua Plastics utilized in its design."},
		{"MANHACK_ARMOR", "Manhack’s examination"},
		{"MANHACK_ARMOR_UFOPEDIA", "Manhacks were designed to fight with criminals in inaccessible, often dark areas, so they’re equipped with fancy optics. They're also quite dodgy. NV: 15; ThV: 75%. Spotter (Basic)."},
		{"AUX_MANHACK_WEAPON", "Manhack's Blades"},
		{"STR_MEGAPOL_MANHACK_TERRORIST_DISASSEMBLY", "D/A: Manhack"},
		{"STR_NEKO_ARMOR_ADAPTATIONS", "Adapting outfits for Catgirls"},
		{"STR_NEKO_ARMOR_ADAPTATIONS_UFOPEDIA", "We have shown our pirate wardrobe to the Catgirl, and found that she is picky enough. Some of our cool clothes were called ridiculous, and some others - even vulgar. However, there was something that she liked. In particular, a warm fur coat, especially valuable for her in our frosty earthly climate. The Catgirl will observe the fashion trends of the Hideout and promptly inform us about the outfits she likes."},
		{"STR_EXOTIC_PLATE_ARMOR", "Exotic Plate Armor"},
		{"STR_EXOTIC_PLATE_ARMOR_UFOPEDIA", "Deceptively fragile in appearance, this Fuso armor is made of Plastasteel processed using a secret method of Toyo Corporation (it supposedly involves molecules being folded 2 million times upon each other, as opposed to usual 0.1-0.5 million). This armor is designed for the quite... peculiar sizes of Fuso inhabitants. By a stroke of luck, Catgirls have very similar dimensions."},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_CULTURAL_EXCHANGE", "Nekomimi Cultural Exchange"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_CULTURAL_EXCHANGE_UFOPEDIA", "'Mrrau. I'm with the Smugglers and I have a trade offer for you, if you have the wares! You have a way with your fellow Ubers no one else has, and you could convince some of them to join us at Laputa. We need them to infilt... to cooperate with them Belters, the space Ubers! In exchange, we can send you some Nekomimi former convi... commandos! Travel costs free of charge, and while we're totally not dumping them on you, they're not so safe here on Laputa! Think of the poor kittens!'"},
		{"STR_CONTACT_NEKOMIMI", "Contacts: Nekomimi"},
		{"STR_CONTACT_NEKOMIMI_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}***SECURE COMMS CHANNEL ONLINE***{ALT}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Ho-bah, humans. Highstar the Speaker here. You want to be a friends of the Nekomimi? You may, as long as you not a friends of Ethereals or Wargots or Silicoids. We shall inform our warriors about you and your warfare and maybe some of them shall even be interested. However, trading relations are not possible yet. You have to prove your worth to the House and Empress.'"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_QUEST_1", "Nekomimi: the proof of friendship"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_QUEST_1_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}***SECURE COMMS CHANNEL ONLINE***{ALT}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Ho-bah, humans. The House is ready to consider establishing a mutually beneficial trade relationship, but first, you must provide irrefutable proof of loyalty to our ideals. Since there is a lot of Ethereal activity in your system, reducing their numbers shall be a fair requirement. Kill as many of them as you can to make them hate you, and send us their remains with one of the free traders' ships.'"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_PREQ", "Trading with Nekomimi (Preq)"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING", "Trading with Nekomimi"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}***SECURE COMMS CHANNEL ONLINE***{ALT}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Ho-bah. Jasmira the Merchant Advisor of System-92 branch here. The House has received the proof of friendship and agrees to grant you access to our warriors' simplest combat suits. Free traders, whom you call 'the Smugglers', have been appointed as intermediaries. We have little interest in your money, so the transaction price includes only the salary of the intermediary. We will take a closer look at your technologies and then inform you what interested us.'{NEWLINE}(+2000 Infamy)"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_REQUEST_1_PREQ", "Nekomimi: trade request #1 (Preq.)"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_REQUEST_1_DONE", "Share Forcefields tech with Nekomimi"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_TRADING_REQUEST_1_DONE_UFOPEDIA", "Merchant Advisor Jasmira looks very pleased. Undoubtedly, Nekomimi successfully pulled off a deal with a huge profit in their favor. Craft-mounted and personal energy shields will make a civilization, that has long mastered interstellar travel, a formidable force, and this will surely change the political map in many systems or even sectors. But we have nothing to worry about, because we are friends.{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Now we may acquire Space Guardian & Space Trooper power suits."},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_SECRET_DEAL", "Nekomimi Secret Deal"},
		{"STR_NEKOMIMI_SECRET_DEAL_UFOPEDIA", "{ALT}***SECURE COMMS CHANNEL ONLINE***{ALT}{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}'Blessings of the Shadowcat be upon you, alien ally. I represent the secret order in the service of our Empress. Our cooperation with you progresses handsomely. You also made an effort to learn the ways of Nekomimi. In exchange, we will signal our network to give you access to Ironcat Armor and other supplies...'"},
		{"STR_CAT_WITCHERY", "Cat Witchery"},
		{"STR_CAT_WITCHERY_UFOPEDIA", "The Nekomimi have their own ways of VooDoo, but with the knowledge and advanced Star God technology we possess, we can unleash the true potential of their fickle powers. Only Herbalist class of Catgirls has the focus to use them. This path of VooDoo is one of subterfuge and calculated lewdness..."},
		{"STR_VESSEL_BRUH", "B'Ruh"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_BRUH_CYD", "B'Ruh"},
		{"STR_VESSEL_BRUH_UFOPEDIA", "The smallest of personal ships of the Solar Governor. Usually used as a shuttle, but its combat performance is at the very peak of Star God tech. It is armed with bunker-busting missiles (power x5).{NEWLINE}ARMOR: 20; SHIELDS: 4900 (Reg x9)"},
