		{"STR_SGR_D-GUY_CORPSE", "Doomed Warrior"},
		{"STR_DOOMED_VEST", "Doomed Vest"},
		{"STR_DOOMED_VEST_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You had a vision: against all the evil that hell can conjure, all the wickedness that mankind can produce, they sent unto them... only one mighty warrior in armor marked with the sigil of the Destroyer. This artifact is capable of making its owner almost invincible, as it prevents half of the Piercing, Fire, Concussive, Plasma, Cutting, Chemical and Stabbing damage taken (RF: 50/0, Protective Gear Type: Shirt).{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}But there is one small problem...{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}No one knows even approximately in which of the worlds to begin the search for the Doomed Vest, if it still exists at all."},
		{"STR_GREAT_EYE", "The Great Eye"},
		{"STR_GREAT_EYE_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}You had a vision of the Eye, which once belonged to one of the Shadow Overlords, who got since overthrown. Overlord's mind is still alive in this artifact, making it as dangerous as it is powerful.{NEWLINE}A Gal who deals damage while wielding the Eye, replenishes her TU, Energy and HP (Mind effect). However, this malevolent entity will drain life force every turn (-2 HP, +3 Stun and some extra Stun when dealing damage) and whisper all sorts of nasty things (-2 Morale). All Mind damage taken is reduced by 2/3.{NEWLINE}Now the Eye is in the possession of an unknown, powerful entity, and we don't even know where to search for it.{NEWLINE}Maybe it's for the best."},
		{"STR_REMOTE_CONTROL", "SGT Remote Control"},
		{"STR_REMOTE_CONTROL_UFOPEDIA", "The Star Gods' technicians use these devices to control some robots or something, but we don't know which button does what."},
		{"STR_PSI_RESONATOR", "VooDoo Resonator"},
		{"STR_PSI_RESONATOR_UFOPEDIA", "{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}This legendary device can be sometimes found on galactic markets. It creates a powerful feedback in the nervous system of the wearer, quickly increasing combat readiness (+20 Freshness per turn), but at a price of wrecking the body (-10 HP and -15 Morale per turn).{NEWLINE}Can be worn on Jewelry slot."},
