		{"STR_PHOTON_BLADE", "Photonic Blade"},
		{"STR_PHOTON_BLADE_UFOPEDIA", "The pinnacle of force blades evolution, miniaturized and exceedingly complex. It looks far too decadent to be made by Star Gods, even if it's undoubtedly based on their technology. But it definitely possesses phenomenal cutting power. Almost like in Cali movies!{NEWLINE}The blade is unusually good at destroying terrain... again, like it was made of cheap movie props!"},
		{"STR_PHOTON_SPEAR", "Photonic Spear"},
		{"STR_PHOTON_SPEAR_UFOPEDIA", "Nubiran melee weapon. It is used as a ceremonial attribute for those serving in the guard of honor, however, if necessary, it can quickly turn a troublemaker into a dead troublemaker. The length of the shaft allows you to lunge at a distance of up to 2."},
		{"STR_NUB_LASER_GATLING", "Nubiran Gatling Laser"},
		{"STR_NUB_LASER_GATLING_UFOPEDIA", "The main weapon of Nubiran shock troops. Fire control is awful, but the weapon allows for quite a lot of movement while firing. It is also unusually good at piercing armor."},
		{"STR_NUB_LASER_GATLING_CLIP", "Nubiran Gatling Laser Clip"},
		{"STR_INCINERATOR", "Incinerator"},
		{"STR_INCINERATOR_UFOPEDIA", "Flamethrower based on matter compression principles. It is able to instantly create a great, raging pit of hell fire (blast radius = 15). The fire is so violent that it utterly destroys target's armor."},
		{"STR_INCINERATOR_CLIP_PLUS", "Incinerator Hellfire Clip"},
		{"STR_BLASTER_MULTI_LAUNCHER", "Blaster Multilauncher"},
		{"STR_BLASTER_MULTI_LAUNCHER_UFOPEDIA", "This modification of man-portable blaster has an 8 round magazine. In aimed mode, it fires a salvo of missiles, and their guidance is still almost as good as that of its older brother. The mind-controlled launch system is temperamental and the number of launched missiles may vary."},
		{"STR_BLASTER_MULTI_BOMB", "Blaster Multi-Bomb"},
		{"STR_DESTRUCTOR_RIFLE", "Destructor-511"},
		{"STR_DESTRUCTOR_RIFLE_UFOPEDIA", "A ray gun used by Star Gods to control their chryssalids, which of course makes it dangerous to us. Its radiation causes an acceleration of all metabolic processes tied to hellerium, and representatives of hellerian life forms burn out, sometimes literally. But it also means that we will be able to get a short-term boost in the form of additional TUs, Energy and a reduction of Stun."},
		{"STR_DESTRUCTOR_RIFLE_CLIP", "Destructor-511 Clip"},
		{"STR_PIR_HEAVY_BOLTER", "Rending Gun"},
		{"STR_PIR_HEAVY_BOLTER_UFOPEDIA", "This weapon fires deadly scatter rounds in a manner similar to Boom Gun, but at much higher rates. The weapon can tear apart any armor in seconds, hence its name. It is rumored to be used by elite Merc squads."},
		{"STR_PIR_HEAVY_BOLTER_AMMO", "Rending Gun Ammo"},
		{"STR_ENERGY_SCYTHE", "Energy Scythe"},
		{"STR_ENERGY_SCYTHE_UFOPEDIA", "A brand weapon of Star God Purifier. This is a plasma blade with very intricate magical circuitries which can be channeled with mental energy to increase the hit power. Due to this way of user interacting with the weapon, an echo of the user's consciousness may exist in Energy Scythe for some time. Therefore, do not be surprised if, taking it in your hands, you hear a voice that says something like 'KILL ALL THE APOSTATES!'{NEWLINE}Merely holding this evil weapon drains 6 Morale per turn."},
		{"STR_DEATH_BLASTER", "Death Blaster"},
		{"STR_DEATH_BLASTER_UFOPEDIA", "Potent and fearsome magical weapon, which seems to be an amplifier of Star God Purifier's innate abilities. It emits an unknown form of short-ranged radiation, which we call the 'Death-rays'. It causes rapid burnout of neural tissues in organic and semi-organic targets, leading to, well, death. However, our VooDoo is incompatible with this kind of device, so it's only useful as a trophy."},
		{"STR_D_RAYS", "Death-rays"},
		{"STR_MEGAVOLT", "Megavolt Discharger"},
		{"STR_MEGAVOLT_UFOPEDIA", "An unusual alien weapon. It fires deadly electric discharges, ignoring half of target's armor. Those who manage to survive are likely to be stunned. The weapon has limited range (10)."},
		{"STR_MEGAVOLT_CLIP", "Megavolt Discharger Clip"},
		{"STR_ELITE_HEAVY_PLASMA", "Elite Plasma Gun"},
		{"STR_ELITE_HEAVY_PLASMA_UFOPEDIA", "Much heavier than Heavy Plasma Gun, and proportionally stronger, this weapon is not issued to usual Star God mooks due to its weight. It is, however, used by elite forces, when maximum firepower is required."},
		{"STR_ELITE_HEAVY_PLASMA_CLIP", "Elite Plasma Gun Clip"},
		{"AUX_DEATH_ORDER", "Death Order"},
		{"AUX_INFERNO", "Inferno Flame"},
		{"AUX_DEMON_SUMMONING", "Summon Demon"},
		{"STR_SUMMON_DOOM_SPIDERDEMON_TERRORIST", "Sum. Spiderdemon"},
		{"STR_SUMMON_DOOM_CACODEMON", "Sum. Cacodemon"},
		{"STR_SUMMON_DOOM_HELL_BARON", "Sum. Baron"},
		{"AUX_GHOST_CLAWS", "Ghost Claws"},
		{"STR_KOSCHEY_LEGENDS", "Grim Legends"},
		{"STR_KOSCHEY_LEGENDS_UFOPEDIA", "Imperial Purifiers had visited Earth in the days of old for reasons unknown. Those who survived the encounter with a Star God in Black composed legends about supernatural deathmaster. He is known in many cultures under the names of Grim Reaper, Thanatos, Koschei the Deathless, Dementor etc. It is equally possible that he impersonated these mythical figures to cause greater fear."},
		{"STR_ULTRAMARINES_LORE", "Mutons Primaris"},
		{"STR_ULTRAMARINES_LORE_UFOPEDIA", "For these hellerium-powered giants, war is the only meaning of life. Their ancestral homeworld is located in the vicinity of the galactic center. In the creation of this unique force, Star Gods have made a drastic departure from their usual philosophy of expendable assets. Each Primaris is clad in a powered armor of a design inherited from ancestors. These warriors use the technology of transferring consciousness into a new body, thus their battle experience is sometimes measured in millennia. Mutons Primaris never answer to System Governors and their deployment can only be authorized by the Purifier Order."},
		{"STR_MARS_THE_FINAL_ASSAULT_BRIEFING", "The tunnels discovered under the pyramid lead to the residence of the Solar Governor. The emergency evacuation system has been disabled and now he is locked up in his bunker like a spider in a jar! You divide your team; Merc reinforcements are in hot pursuit after the main group and you don't want to put all the eggs into a single basket. Or maybe it was someone's suggestion?{NEWLINE}{NEWLINE}Nevermind, Cap'n! Victory or death!"},
		{"STR_UNEXPEXTED_EXPLOSION", "A series of powerful explosions on the technical level shakes the base!"},
		{"STR_MARS_THE_FINAL_ASSAULT_2", "Mars: Living quarters"},
		{"STR_MARS_THE_FINAL_ASSAULT_2_BRIEFING", "Leaving behind the transport terminal, you disable the gravitic lifter. Who would have thought that the Martian base would be so huge? You continue to search for your rival, and the confidence grows in your heart that everything you have seen before was just the tip of the iceberg."},
		{"STR_MARS_THE_FINAL_ASSAULT_3", "Mars: The Anomaly"},
		{"STR_MARS_THE_FINAL_ASSAULT_3_BRIEFING", "These corridors looking like a battlefield: the corpses of aliens and demons everywhere, the walls are splattered with blood or speckled with incomprehensible signs, and fires blaze here and there. Whatever the Star Gods were doing here, it doesn't seem like the situation is under their control. Nowhere to retreat, you must pass through this Hell on Mars."},
		{"STR_ANOMALY_MASTERMIND_DESTROYED", "OREMOR'NHOJ EMLLIK TSUMUOY EMAGEHT NIW OT"},
		{"STR_CHECKMATE", "Mars: The Checkmate"},
		{"STR_CHECKMATE_BRIEFING", "The King must die.{NEWLINE}Long live the Queen!"},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_01", "Exploring the lower levels of the Cydonian base, you find yourself in a place that looks like an Earth subway system. For some reason, you firmly believe that one of the trains can take you to the Solar Governor. You walk into the operator's cab along with the most loyal and reliable of your hands. It is not difficult to understand the controls, since a quiet voice in your head tells you the order of actions."},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_02", "The train starts moving and rushes into the tunnel. You are thrilled to be able to quickly get as far as possible from the demon-held Star Gods' research facility."},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_03", "Suddenly, a voice in your head screams loudly, and an acute attack of headache makes you gasp."},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_04", "Your vision goes dark, but within this darkness you can clearly see an image of the woman with purple eyes - the one who led you to freedom an infinity ago."},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_05", "'He sensed me and is trying to drive me out. So you have to go without me, Avatar. I helped as much as I could, including with the hands of other executors of my will, but now you are alone with our enemy. Here... in a vast cave. There is only one way to get there...'"},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_06", "Following the instructions of the Bloom Lady, you stop the train in the middle of the tunnel and put the engines into super-boost mode, while disabling the safety and cooling systems. Your second in command runs through the entire train, warning everyone to get out of the tail section. The image of the Bloom Lady melts away, she only has time to whisper: 'Well done... Now go deeper... show him what is... Love!'"},
		{"STR_SGR_CUTSCENE_07", "As soon as you could no longer feel her invisible presence, the train shuddered from a huge explosion that thundered in the reactor bay!"},
		{"STR_AURA_FEAR_MANAREGEN_TXT", "Governor's oppressive aura is lowering our Morale!{NEWLINE}Presence of the Shadows is raising our powers!"},
		{"STR_AURA_FEAR_HEAVY_TXT", "Leave this place immediately!"},
